hick. Use your thumb to press an indentation into the center of each patty to prevent a bubble from forming in the center when cooking. Generously season the tops and sides of the patties with salt and pepper.\",\"2\":\"Heat a large cast iron skillet over medium heat. Spread about ½ tablespoon of butter onto each cut side of the hamburger buns. Working in batches, toast the buns, buttered-side down, for about 2  minutes, until golden brown. Set aside.\",\"3\":\"Increase the heat to medium-high. Add a thin layer of canola oil to the pan and cook the burgers for 4 minutes on one side, until nicely browned. Flip and cook for another 2 minutes on the other side. Top each burger with a slice of cheese and cover the pan with a lid. Cook until the cheese is melted and the internal temperature of the burgers reaches 135°F (57°C), another 1–2 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Assemble the burgers: Place a burger patty on each toasted bun, then top with a slice of tomato and red onion, lettuce, ketchup, mayonnaise, and mustard. Serve immediately.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":45,\"calories\":789,\"sugar\":6,\"carbohydrates\":42,\"fiber\":26,\"protein\":48}','\"The secret to these easy burgers is using a blend of different types of ground meat to give the burgers amazing flavor, while keeping them tender. You can ask a butcher to grind them for you, or some grocery stores sell their own unique burger blends.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/f85e0cbe1cc242f693e86fed73d2f7c5.jpeg\"','12 ounces ground 80/20 beef chuck (6 ounces ground beef short rib and 6 ounces ground beef brisket rib)||n/a||n/a||2 teaspoons kosher salt, plus more to taste||1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, plus more to taste||4 large hamburger buns||4 tablespoons (½ stick) unsalted butter, softened||4 slices of sharp cheddar cheese||1–2 tablespoons canola oil||','under_30_minutes||high_protein||dinner||american||fourth_of_july||game_day||comfort_food||bbq||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour'),('18-72ac92cb281d','\"Alix\\u2019s Green Veggie And Chicken Sausage Pasta\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\",\"1\":\"Make the pesto: Add the basil, walnuts, Parmesan, garlic, lemon juice, salt, pepper, and water to a food processor and process until mostly smooth, 1–2 minutes. With the processor running, slowly drizzle in the olive oil and continue blending until emulsified.\",\"2\":\"Make the green veggie and sausage pasta: Add the broccoli, zucchini, and Simple Truth® Italian Chicken Sausage to the prepared baking sheet. Drizzle with the olive oil and season with the salt and pepper, then toss until evenly coated.\",\"3\":\"Roast for 20 minutes, or until the vegetables are softened and everything is starting to brown. Stir in the kale, then return to the oven for another 7 minutes, until the kale is wilted, and the sausage and vegetables have cooked through and browned.\",\"4\":\"Add the cooked pasta to a very large bowl with the roasted vegetables and sausage, pesto, and ¼ to ½ cup of the reserved pasta water, and toss until well coated.\",\"5\":\"Garnish with shaved Parmesan and basil sprigs.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":68,\"fiber\":7,\"protein\":16,\"fat\":18,\"calories\":492,\"sugar\":5}','\"\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/358757.jpg\"','2 cups packed fresh basil leaves||2 Tbsp. walnut pieces||2 Tbsp. grated Parmesan cheese||2 garlic cloves||2 Tbsp. fresh lemon juice||½ tsp. kosher salt||½ tsp. freshly ground black pepper||2 Tbsp. water||¼ cup extra-virgin olive oil||','stove_top||food_processor||spatula||mixing_bowl||baking_pan||oven_mitts||dinner||special_occasion||weeknight||low_sugar||high_fiber'),('18-e77988ea5fb2','\"2-Minute Vegetable Dumplings\"','{\"0\":\"Add the mushrooms, cabbage, chives, cilantro, ⅛ teaspoon sesame oil, soy sauce, hoisin sauce, cornstarch, and salt to a mini food processor. Process until finely chopped.\",\"1\":\"Add a heaping teaspoon of the filling to the center of a wonton wrapper. Dip your finger in water and brush over the edges of the wrapper, then fold the wrapper over itself into a triangle and press the edges together to seal, pressing out any air. Repeat with the remaining filling and wrappers.\",\"2\":\"Add the wonton wrappers to a medium microwave-safe bowl. Pour in the hot water and remaining teaspoon of sesame oil. Cover with a microwave-safe lid or plastic wrap and microwave for 2 minutes, stirring halfway through, until dumplings are floating and the wrappers are translucent.\",\"3\":\"Make the dipping sauce: In a small bowl, stir together the soy sauce, black vinegar, and chile oil.\",\"4\":\"Transfer the dumplings to a plate. Serve with the dipping sauce alongside.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":50,\"fat\":10,\"calories\":1625,\"sugar\":8,\"carbohydrates\":327,\"fiber\":18}','\"Making dumplings in a microwave might sound crazy or even weird but we\\u2019ve figured out a way! The filling is packed with flavor and tons of delicious veggies. Adding a little sesame oil to the cooking water helps the dumplings from sticking together.\"','1','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/b5d003772b0f467fa178b0911c0f0967/BFV81055_2MinVs20MinVs2DayDumplings_AB_071421_ForFinal.jpg\"','1 large shiitake mushroom, stemmed and quartered||½ Napa cabbage leaf, roughly chopped||3 Chinese chives, roughly chopped||½ tablespoon fresh cilantro leaves||1⅛ teaspoons sesame oil, divided||½ teaspoon low-sodium soy sauce||½ teaspoon hoisin sauce (optional)||½ teaspoon cornstarch||Pinch of kosher salt||5 square wonton wrappers||Water, for sealing wrappers||1½ cups hot water||','microwave||food_processor||asian_pacific_american_heritage_month||lunch||dinner||chinese||comfort_food||high_protein||high_fiber||under_30_minutes||under_15_minutes||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian'),('19-3e357fe3486a','\"Chicken Alfredo Lasagna\"','{\"