":\"In a blender, add Frank’s Original Red Hot, orange juice, garlic, chipotle peppers, brown sugar, apple cider vinegar, salt, pepper, paprika, dried oregano, and cinnamon. Blend on high until smooth.\",\"1\":\"Place pork shoulder in Instant Pot. Pour marinade over pork and turn with tongs to coat.\",\"2\":\"Put the cover on the Instant Pot. Be sure the pressure valve is set to “Sealing.” Use the manual setting to set the timer for 40 minutes.\",\"3\":\"When the timer goes off, turn the pressure valve to “Venting” to release pressure quickly. **Be sure to read all Instant Pot instructions carefully for safety.** Be sure Instant Pot is turned off and unplugged before carefully removing the cover.\",\"4\":\"Transfer pork from the pot to a bowl. Use two forks to shred the pork. Pour some of the cooking liquid over the carnitas and toss to coat.\",\"5\":\"Serving options: Build carnitas on top of nachos or tacos.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":34,\"fat\":22,\"calories\":391,\"sugar\":8,\"carbohydrates\":13,\"fiber\":2}','\"\"','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/236085.jpg\"','2 tablespoons Frank’s Original Red Hot||2 oranges, juiced||4 cloves garlic||3 chipotle peppers (from a can)||2 tablespoons brown sugar||¼ cup apple cider vinegar||1 tablespoon salt||1 teaspoon pepper||1 tablespoon paprika||1 teaspoon dried oregano||¼ teaspoon cinnamon||3 pounds boneless pork shoulder, cut into 3-inch cubes||','fall||casual_party||blender||mexican||mccormick_seasoned_pro||comfort_food||chefs_knife||cutting_board||dry_measuring_cups||measuring_spoons||tongs||mixing_bowl||oven_mitts||cast_iron_pan||big_batch||easy||dinner||weeknight||one_pot_or_pan||low_carb||high_protein'),('27-96852152dc35','\"Pesto Asparagus And Sun-Dried Tomato Pasta\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 425˚F/220˚C.\",\"1\":\"In a large pot, bring 4 quarts of water to a rolling boil.\",\"2\":\"Remove the woody ends of the asparagus and discard. Cut the remaining spears into qu