oppy seeds, coconut powder, and a little water in a blender and grind into a fine paste.\",\"1\":\"Heat a pan on medium-high heat and add oil.\",\"2\":\"Add in the whole spices and curry leaves, after a minute add in the chopped onion, green chilies, little salt, turmeric powder, mix and cook until the onions are translucent.\",\"3\":\"Add the ginger garlic paste and mix well. Let cook for 2 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Add chopped tomatoes and a little salt and cook until tomatoes are done.\",\"5\":\"Add in the cubed potatoes, red chili powder, garam masala, salt according to taste, and ground spices mixture and mix well. Then, add water, level until the whole mixture is just immersed and mix well.\",\"6\":\"Cover and cook on medium heat for about 15 - 20 minutes or longer if the potato is not cooked, stirring in between\",\"7\":\"Turn off the heat, garnish with coriander leaves and serve with naan or rice.\"}','{\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":6,\"fat\":13,\"calories\":318,\"sugar\":5,\"carbohydrates\":46}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/bd8d94b0189b4b9aa238a80d8697a9b7.png\"','4 cups potatoes, cubed||2 tbsp olive oil||Whole spices: 4 cloves, 6 black peppercorns, 2 cardamom, 1 star anise, 1 inch cinnamon, 1 teaspoon black cumin seeds||1 sprig curry leaves||1 cup chopped onions||1 tbsp ginger garlic paste||½ cup chopped tomatoes||2 chopped green chillies||12 cashews||2 tbsp poppy seeds||2 tbsp coconut powder (fresh or dried)||1 tbsp garam masala||1 tbsp red chilli powder||Water||Salt||1 tsp turmeric powder||1 handful coriander leaves, chopped||','indian||fusion||stove_top||weeknight||dinner||low_sugar||high_fiber||dairy_free'),('2d-89ae6c89f856','\"Vegetable Gratin 3 Ways\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C).\",\"1\":\"Make the béchamel sauce: Melt the butter in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add the garlic and sauté for 3 minutes, or until fragrant.\",\"2\":\"Add the flour and whisk into the butter. Cook for 3 minutes, or until lightly browned.\",\"3\":\"While whisking, pour in the milk and heavy cream. Season with the salt and pepper. Reduce the heat to low and simmer, whisking frequently, until the sauce coats the back of a spoon, about 10 minutes. Remove from the heat and set aside.\",\"4\":\"Remove the leaves and stem from the head of the cauliflower and chop into roughly ½-inch (1-cm) florets. Set aside.\",\"5\":\"Trim the Brussels sprouts, then thinly slice. Add the sprouts to a 9x13-inch (23x33 cm) baking dish and push to one side, filling about a third of the dish.\",\"6\":\"Add the corn to the center third of the baking dish. Add the cauliflower florets to the remaining third of the baking dish.\",\"7\":\"Pour the béchamel sauce evenly over the vegetables.\",\"8\":\"Top the Brussels sprouts with the Gruyère cheese and bacon bits.\",\"9\":\"Top the corn with the cheddar cheese.\",\"10\":\"Top the cauliflower with the Parmesan cheese.\",\"11\":\"Sprinkle the bread crumbs evenly over the vegetables.\",\"12\":\"Cover the dish with foil and bake for 30 minutes, then uncover and bake for 30 minutes more, until the vegetables are tender and the top is golden brown.\",\"13\":\"Serve warm.\",\"14\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":15,\"calories\":270,\"sugar\":6,\"carbohydrates\":24,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":12}','\"\"','12','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/186873.jpg\"','⅓ cup unsalted butter||4 cloves garlic, minced||⅓ cup all-purpose flour||3 cups whole milk, warmed||¼ cup heavy cream||2 teaspoons salt||2 teaspoons pepper||','comfort_food||big_batch||baking_cups||whisk||measuring_spoons||epoca_walmart||bake||dinner||easy||american||cutting_board||oven||fall||casual_party||liquid_measuring_cup||chefs_knife||oven_mitts||thanksgiving||baking_pan||mixing_bowl||pyrex||spatula||walmart_holiday_bundle||tasty_holiday_christmas||live_shop_all'),('2d-f203a73f7b4f','\"Fancy Garlic Noodles\"','{\"0\":\"Add pasta to salted boiling water and cook until al dente