ive oil over medium-high heat. Season all of the seafood with salt and pepper.\",\"5\":\"Add the scallops to the pan and sear the first side until golden brown, 3 minutes. Flip and sear on the other side for another 3 minutes. Remove from the pan and set aside. Wipe out the pan if needed.\",\"6\":\"Add more olive oil as needed, then add the shrimp to the pan and cook for 3 minutes on one side. Flip  and cook on the other side for 3 minutes more. Set aside.\",\"7\":\"Add more olive oil and the squid to the hot pan and sauté until cooked, 5 minutes.\",\"8\":\"Add more olive oil and the halibut to the hot pan, along with the crushed garlic and remaining 2 tablespoons of butter. Sear the halibut on one side, then flip and cook on the other side for 3 minutes. Baste the fish with the melted garlic butter as the second side cooks. Remove from the pan and set aside.\",\"9\":\"Add the clams and mussels to the pan, pour in the remaining cup of white white, then cover the pot and steam for 5 minutes, until the shellfish pop open. Remove the pan from the heat.\",\"10\":\"Transfer all of the cooked seafood, along with the leftover shellfish steaming liquid and reserved matignon, to the simmering stew; or plate the seafood and reserved matignon artfully in wide bowls and pour the hot stew over the top.\",\"11\":\"Serve with grilled sourdough bread and garnish with parsley.\",\"12\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":46,\"fat\":69,\"calories\":1096,\"sugar\":16,\"carbohydrates\":63,\"fiber\":7}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/160524.jpg\"','4 tablespoons unsalted butter, divided||1 cup extra-virgin olive oil, divided||2 large carrots, peeled, trimmed, and minced||1 leek, white part only, trimmed, cleaned, and minced||1 large yellow onion, minced||1 red bell pepper, cored, seeded, and minced||1 small fennel bulb, trimmed, and minced||1 green bell pepper, cored, seeded, and minced||2 stalks celery, minced||4 cloves garlic, finely chopped, plu