cup||dry_measuring_cups||mccormick_easy_dinner||high_protein||high_fiber'),('3f-028ecf22dc14','\"Raspberry Chipotle Chicken Thighs\"','{\"0\":\"In a small bowl, mix together 2 tablespoons garlic powder, 2 tablespoons onion powder, the paprika, salt, and pepper.\",\"1\":\"Drizzle the chicken thighs with the olive oil, then sprinkle with half of the spice mixture and rub to coat well. Sprinkle with the remaining spice mixture. Set aside while you make the sauce, or refrigerate overnight if you’re grilling the next day.\",\"2\":\"Melt the butter in a small saucepan over medium heat. Add the raspberries and cook until  they start to break down, about 3 minutes. Add the brown sugar, chipotle powder, remaining 2 tablespoons garlic powder, remaining 2 tablespoons onion powder, the ketchup, and liquid smoke and season with salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a simmer and cook until the sauce thickens, 4 minutes. Remove the pot from the heat and set aside.\",\"3\":\"Heat a grill pan over medium-high heat. Grease with grapeseed oil. Add the chicken and grill for about 7 minutes on each side, until the internal temperature of the chicken reaches 165°F (75°C). Once the chicken has cooked through, generously brush with some of the raspberry chipotle sauce. Continue grilling until the sauce caramelizes, 1–2 minutes, then repeat on the other side.\",\"4\":\"Garnish the chicken with the parsley and serve warm with the remaining sauce alongside.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":19,\"calories\":389,\"sugar\":11,\"carbohydrates\":29,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":28}','\"Chicken thighs grilled with a sweet, smoky, and slightly spicy sauce are sure to kick things up a notch at your next indoor or outdoor barbecue.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/8bbcb9fd9a094521aab2a02f11396ab7/BFV67133_Gadgetreviewstovetopgrill_FB_Final.jpg\"','4 tablespoons garlic powder, divided||4 tablespoons onion powder, divided||2 tablespoons smoked paprika||2 tablespoons kosher salt, plus more to taste||2 tablespoons freshly ground black pepper, plus more to taste||6-8 boneless, skinless chicken thighs||2 tablespoons olive oil||1 tablespoon unsalted butter||6 ounces raspberries||2 tablespoons brown sugar||1 tablespoon chipotle chile powder||½ cup ketchup||1 tablespoon mesquite liquid smoke||Grapeseed oil or nonstick cooking spray, for greasing||1 tablespoon minced fresh flat-leaf parsley, for garnish||','american||spring||summer||dinner||bbq||game_day||tongs||mixing_bowl||srsly_sauv_blanc||high_protein||high_fiber||under_30_minutes||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour'),('3f-c9c6753c64d8','\"Honey Mustard Ribs\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat grill for medium-low heat. The thermometer should reach about 300ºF (150°C)\",\"1\":\"Place ribs on a foil-covered sheet tray. Rub both sides of the ribs with olive oil and salt.\",\"2\":\"Brush French’s Honey Mustard on both sides, covering all areas. Fold foil over ribs to form an enclosed packet. Use a knife to poke a few venting slits in each foil pack.\",\"3\":\"Place foil-wrapped rack on grill, close lid, and cook for 1–2 hours, until ribs are tender but not falling apart.\",\"4\":\"Glaze: Melt butter in a small saucepan over low heat. Add in the rest of the ingredients and whisk well. Let glaze simmer for 2–3 minutes. Remove from heat.\",\"5\":\"Unwrap the foil and spread the glaze all over the ribs.\",\"6\":\"Oil the grill and turn the heat up to high. Grill ribs on both sides until ribs become caramelized, 10–15 minutes.\",\"7\":\"Remove from grill, then let cool for 10 minutes before slicing and serving.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":32,\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":19,\"fat\":38,\"calories\":551,\"sugar\":31}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/227480.jpg\"','1 rack baby back ribs, membrane removed||⅓ cup French’s Honey Mustard||','mccormick_seasoned_pro||american||comfort_food||sponsored_recipe||stove_top||chefs_knife||cutting_board||dry_measuring_cups||measuring_spo