joy!\"}','{\"calories\":677,\"sugar\":10,\"carbohydrates\":29,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":43,\"fat\":48}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/9e072404f3f64d3199fdc3fe9c062bb4/fb.jpg\"','600 grams boneless, skinless chicken breasts||100 grams natural yogurt||2 tablespoons garlic and ginger paste||2 tablespoons chili powder||1 teaspoon garam masala||1 teaspoon salt||1 teaspoon turmeric||1 teaspoon cumin||','winter||indian||stove_top||comfort_food||big_batch||dinner||weeknight||pan_fry||fall||fusion||british||casual_party||oven_mitts||baking_pan||measuring_spoons||tongs||chefs_knife||cutting_board||pyrex||dry_measuring_cups||mixing_bowl||plastic_wrap||parchment_paper||sauce_pan||wooden_spoon||liquid_measuring_cup||high_protein||high_fiber'),('4b-cc7bc5d4f104','\"Copycat Campfire Chicken\"','{\"0\":\"Combine paprika, onion powder, salt, garlic powder, rosemary, pepper, and oregano in a small bowl and mix well. Reserve 1 tablespoon of the spice mix and set aside.\",\"1\":\"In a large ziplock bag, place the quartered chicken and spice mix. Marinate for 1 hour or overnight.\",\"2\":\"Preheat the oven to 400˚F (200˚C).\",\"3\":\"Add the carrots, potatoes, and corn to a bowl and drizzle with oil and remaining 1 tablespoon of spice mix and toss until thoroughly coated.\",\"4\":\"Heat a large pan with oil over high heat. Add the chicken pieces and cook until golden brown on both side. Set aside.\",\"5\":\"Place the chicken and veggies on a sheet of aluminium foil. Top with butter and thyme. Fold the foil over the chicken and vegetables and cinch the edge so that no air can escape.\",\"6\":\"Bake for 45 minutes, or chicken is completely cooked.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":69,\"fiber\":10,\"protein\":93,\"fat\":89,\"calories\":1481,\"sugar\":7}','','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/348d0fccad8344fc901927cf559a55df/thumb.jpg\"','1 tablespoons paprika||2 teaspoon onion powder||2 teaspoons salt||1 teaspoon garlic powder||1 teaspoons dried rosemary||1 teaspoon black pepper||1 teaspoons dried oregano||1 whole chicken, quartered||2 carrots, cut into thirds||3 red skin potatoes, halved||1 ear corn, quartered||1 tablespoon olive oil||1 tablespoon butter||5 sprigs thyme||','comfort_food||oven||stove_top||easy||dinner||american||bake||kid_friendly||date_night||weeknight||high_protein||high_fiber'),('4c-fa0c639b95b0','\"Grilled Tofu Tacos\"','{\"0\":\"Set the pressed tofu on a baking sheet and freeze for at least 4 hours, up to overnight. Let thaw completely, then cut into ½-inch-thick slabs. (Freezing is optional, but will give the tofu a meatier texture.)\",\"1\":\"In a wide, shallow dish, whisk together the lime juice and zest, soy sauce, chili powder, cumin, coriander, brown sugar, salt, and canola  oil.\",\"2\":\"Add the tofu to the marinade and turn to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 30–60 minutes, flipping once halfway through.\",\"3\":\"While the tofu is marinating, make the grilled pineapple salsa. Brush a grill pan with canola oil and heat over high heat until just smoking. Working in batches, add the pineapple to the hot pan and cook undisturbed for 5–6 minutes, until distinct grill marks appear and the pineapple is beginning to soften. Flip and cook for another 2–3 minutes, until grill marks appear on the other side. Transfer the pineapple rings to a cutting board and cut into ¼-inch pieces.\",\"4\":\"Transfer the pineapple to a medium bowl, along with the onion, jalapeño, garlic, cilantro, salt, and lime juice and stir to combine. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.\",\"5\":\"Grill the tofu: Brush the same grill pan with more canola oil. Heat over medium-high heat until just beginning to smoke. Working in batches, remove the tofu from the marinade and grill for 3–4 minutes on each side, until distinct grill marks appear. Cut each tofu slab into ½-inch slices crosswise on the diagonal.\",\"6\":\"Just before serving, grill the tortillas over medium-high heat until just warmed through and some brown spots appear, about 1 minute per side.\",\"7\":\"Assemble the tacos: Fill each tortilla with grilled tofu and top with 2–3 tablespoons of pineapple salsa and 1–2 avocado slices. Serve with lime wedges alongside.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\",\"9\":\"RECIPE BY: Karlee Rotoly\"}','{\"protein\":6,\"fat\":7,\"calories\":210,\"sugar\":3,\"carbohydrates\":29,\"fiber\":12}','\"If you love fish tacos, you\\u2019ll also love this vegetarian version that uses grilled tofu in place of fish. Paired with grilled pineapple salsa and topped with avocado, eating these tacos is like taking a bite out of summer. We recommend freezing the pressed tofu before marinating to give it a meatier texture.\"','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/49e1062b00244ac9bd2f48ffd4798246/BFV81950_GrilledVsFriedBajaTofuTacos_JM_072221_1x1_OOO.jpg\"','1 14-ounce package of extra-firm tofu, drained and pressed||¼ cup lime juice (from 2 limes)||1 tablespoon lime zest (from 2 limes)||1½ tablespoons soy sauce||1½ teaspoons chili powder||½ teaspoon ground cumin||¼ teaspoon ground coriander||2 tablespoons brown sugar||½ teaspoon kosher salt||1 tablespoon canola oil, plus more for greasing||','one_pot_or_pan||fusion||freezer||stove_top||cutting_board||mixing_bowl||grill||lunch||weeknight||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||dinner||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian'),('4d-6ccad7b3cdc5','\"Block Party Ribs By Marcus Samuelsson\"','{\"0\":\"Whisk together all the rub ingredients in a small bowl.\",\"1\":\"Spread the rub evenly over the pork ribs and place on a wire rack set over a baking sheet with meat side up. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.\",\"2\":\"For the BBQ sauce, heat oil in a large pot or dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add poblano chile, red onion, garlic, ginger, and a pinch of salt, then cook until onions begin to soften.\",\"3\":\"Add the remaining sauce ingredients and bring the mixture to a simmer.\",\"4\":\"Turn the heat down to medium-low and cook at an active simmer until the mixture is reduced to about 2 cups (470 ml), about 30-45 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Once reduced, cool slightly then transfer mixture to a blender. Puree until smooth.\",\"6\":\"Preheat oven to 275˚F (140˚C).\",\"7\":\"Uncover the ribs. Spread 1 cup (290g) of the BBQ sauce over each rack of ribs.\",\"8\":\"Keeping them raised over the baking sheet on the wire rack. Pour water into the bottom of the baking sheet.\",\"9\":\"Bake in a preheated oven for 3-3 ½ hours.\",\"10\":\"Remove ribs from oven and preheat the broiler to high.\",\"11\":\"Broil the ribs for 5-10 minutes to finish, until the sauce caramelizes.\",\"12\":\"Cut into individual ribs.\",\"13\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":6,\"fat\":16,\"calories\":379,\"sugar\":28,\"carbohydrates\":50,\"fiber\":3}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/3c918e8d8a2b4dacb7d4363c19e1f134/FBUPLOAD.jpg\"','n/a||','oven||broiler||american||comfort_food||kid_friendly||fourth_of_july||dinner||bake||game_day||bbq||casual_party||special_occasion||big_batch||summer||contains_alcohol||dairy_free'),('4e-06bb73eb2c08','\"Maple Mustard Salmon\"','{\"0\":\"Place butter, French’s Spicy Brown Mustard, maple syrup, apple cider vinegar, orange juice, ½ teaspoon salt, and paprika in a small pot. Heat over low heat and whisk until butter has fully melted and the sauce starts to simmer. Continue simmering for a few minutes until sauce reduces to a glaze. Remove from heat and set aside.\",\"1\":\"Rub salmon with olive oil and sprinkle evenly with 1 teaspoon salt. Drizzle with a bit of the glaze.\",\"2\":\"Heat an oiled grill pan (or heat up a grill) over high heat. When hot, place the salmon flesh-side down into the pan. Cook until the salmon has clear grill marks, then carefully flip to cook on the other side. Brush with more glaze. Once salmon is cooked to your liking, remove from pan.\",\"3\":\"For salsa, lightly toss peach, avocado, jalapeño, cilantro, lime juice, and pinch of salt in bowl.\",\"4\":\"Top the salmon fillets with the peach-avocado salsa and serve immediately.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":15,\"carbohydrates\":25,\"fiber\":30,\"protein\":47,\"fat\":49,\"calories\":738}','\"\"','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/214971.jpg\"','2 tablespoons unsalted butter||1½ tablespoons French’s Spicy Brown Mustard||2 tablespoons maple syrup||1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar||1 tablespoon orange juice||1½ teaspoons kosher salt plus a pinch, divided||½ teaspoon paprika||1 pound salmon, cut into fillets||1 teaspoon olive oil||1 teaspoon salt||1/2 peach, diced small||1/2 avocado, diced small||¼ cup torn cilantro leaves||1/2 jalapeño pepper, thinly sliced||Juice of 1 lime||Pinch of salt||','seafood||grill||baking_pan||pan_fry||cast_iron_pan||spatula||cutting_board||dinner||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||tongs||chefs_knife||pyrex||mixing_bowl||date_night||special_occasion||high_protein||high_fiber||pescatarian'),('4e-2b8ce5100102','\"Chicken And Asparagus Pasta\"','{\"0\":\"In a pot, cook pasta according to package instructions, drain, then set aside.\",\"1\":\"In the same pot, heat 2 tablespoons olive oil and sauté 2 garlic cloves.\",\"2\":\"Add chicken breasts, season with salt and pepper, and fully cook. Remove cooked chicken from pot and set aside.\",\"3\":\"In the same pot, pour the chicken broth, then add asparagus, salt, pepper, and the remaining garlic and stir. Cover and reduce heat to a simmer for 5 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Add cooked chicken, penne, remaining olive oil, parmesan, and tomatoes, and stir until fully incorporated and the cheese has melted.\",\"5\":\"Serve while hot.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":34,\"fat\":17,\"calories\":400,\"sugar\":3,\"carbohydrates\":32}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/59eaab8552db4b42959108167093717b/BFV11688_ChickenAndAsparagusPenne-ThumbTextless1080.jpg\"','1 pound penne pasta||2 tablespoons olive oil and ¼ cup olive oil||4 cloves garlic, diced||1 pound chicken breasts, cubed||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||½ cup chicken broth||1 pound asparagus||1 cup grated parmesan cheese||2 cups cherry or grape tomatoes||','comfort_food||italian||fusion||weeknight||spring||pan_fry||one_pot_or_pan||stove_top||dinner||easy||american||sauce_pan||wooden_spoon||mixing_bowl||liquid_measuring_cup'),('4e-674ae5562447','\"Coconut Chicken Curry\"','{\"0\":\"In a large mixing bowl, combine the chicken with the onion, scallions, garlic, cilantro, curry powder, thyme, parsley, salt, and pepper.  Mix and let marinate for at least 1 hour in the refrigerator.\",\"1\":\"Heat the oil in a medium skillet over medium heat until shimmering, and add the onion and garlic. Cook for 1-2 minutes, until fragrant.\",\"2\":\"Add the curry powder and stir well, cooking for 3-4 minutes more.\",\"3\":\"Add the scallions and coconut milk, increase the heat to medium-high, and cook for 8-10 minutes, until the coconut milk is boiling and begins to thicken.\",\"4\":\"Add the marinated chicken and stir well. Cook the chicken for 5 minutes, or until starting to brown. Season with pepper.\",\"5\":\"Add the chicken broth to the pot and stir.\",\"6\":\"Bring to a rolling boil and cover the pot. Simmer for 30 minutes, until the sauce thickens into a gravy.\",\"7\":\"Garnish with cilantro.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":73,\"fat\":24,\"calories\":565,\"sugar\":5,\"carbohydrates\":11,\"fiber\":5}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/87af163ab7ed4dac9c6bf1c0535fa5b3/BFV39082TrinidadianRotifb2.jpg\"','3 lb chicken, cubed||','stove_top||dinner||pan_fry||wooden_spoon||comfort_food||spatula||liquid_measuring_cup||pyrex||casual_party||dutch_oven||weeknight||plastic_wrap||mixing_bowl||measuring_spoons||oh_so_rose||high_protein||low_sugar||trinidad_african_cuisine'),('4e-add3574e698b','\"Broccoli Cheddar Chicken Rollups\"','{\"0\":\"In a small bowl, microwave 1½ cups (225 g) of broccoli for 1 minute. Add the cheddar cheese, garlic powder, onion powder, and cream cheese. Mix thoroughly, and set aside until ready to use.\",\"1\":\"On a cutting board, butterfly the chicken breasts with a knife. Cut through the chicken breast so you have 6 thinner chicken cutlets. Cover in plastic wrap, and tenderize by beating with a rolling pin or a heavy pan.\",\"2\":\"Remove the plastic wrap, and season with salt and pepper. Place a scoop of the broccoli cheddar mixture on top of a chicken cutlet, and spread until the chicken is covered.\",\"3\":\"Roll the chicken up starting from the tapered end. Use 2 toothpicks to keep the chicken tightly rolled. Repeat with the rest of the chicken.\",\"4\":\"Preheat the oven to 325˚F (165˚C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\",\"5\":\"In a plastic bag, crush the cheddar crackers until they have a coarse, sand-like texture. Pour the cracker crumbs into a large bowl. Add the rest of the minced broccoli. Stir to combine.\",\"6\":\"Put the flour into a medium bowl.\",\"7\":\"Whisk the eggs in another medium bowl.\",\"8\":\"Using tongs, place one of the pieces of chicken into the flour. Turn the chicken in the flour until it is fully coated, tap off any excess flour. Place the chicken in the egg, turn until the chicken is coated. Place the chicken in the broccoli cracker crumb mixture, turn until the chicken is fully coated. Repeat with the remaining chicken rolls.\",\"9\":\"Transfer the pieces of chicken to the prepared baking sheet. Bake for 40-45 minutes.\",\"10\":\"Let the chicken cool slightly, then remove the toothpicks.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":48,\"fat\":45,\"calories\":880,\"sugar\":5,\"carbohydrates\":66,\"fiber\":4}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/143322.jpg\"','3½ cups finely chopped broccoli, divided||2 cups shredded cheddar cheese||1 teaspoon garlic powder||1 teaspoon onion powder||1 8-ounce package cream cheese, softened||3 chicken breasts||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||1 13.7-ounce package cheddar crackers||1 cup all-purpose flour||2 eggs||','oven||dinner||cutting_board||chefs_knife||comfort_food||mixing_bowl||spatula||bake||weeknight||stuffed||easy||tongs||dry_measuring_cups||measuring_spoons||oven_mitts||american||cheese_grater||kid_friendly||baking_pan||parchment_paper||rolling_pin||pyrex||high_protein||low_sugar'),('4f-0526accdc6d7','\"Ukrainian Holubtsi Or Stuffed Cabbage Rolls\"','{\"0\":\"Cook rice according to package directions and set aside to cool completely once done.\",\"1\":\"Adjust oven rack to lower half of oven to allow for height of roasting pan. Preheat the oven to 350°F.\",\"2\":\"Boil water in a large pot. While water is heating, remove tough outer leaves of the cabbage and reserve. Core around the stem of the cabbage at enough of an angle to remove. Gently place cabbage into boiling water core side down. Add additional water to ensure cabbage is not touching the bottom of pot.\",\"3\":\"Reduce heat just a little and boil cabbage for about 5 minutes or until outer leaves become soft. Using kitchen tongs, remove the outer 2 or 3 leaves intact to a colander placed over a bowl to catch the water. Continue with remaining cabbage leaves one by one, allowing a minute or two between leaves for underlying leaves to soften. You want them to peel apart in one in-tact piece.\",\"4\":\"In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, cooked rice, chopped onion, eggs, and salt. Using your hands, work the mixture until combined.\",\"5\":\"Position your cooked cabbage leaves alongside your bowl with the mixture in preparation for rolling/stuffing the dumplings. Before stuffing, prepare a large roasting pan by emptying one can of condensed tomato soup or a bit of the canned tomatoes in the bottom and spreading to coat. You do not need much.\",\"6\":\"Begin rolling/stuffing the cabbage leaves one at a time. Repeat until all of the meat mixture has been used.\",\"7\":\"Once all of the cabbage rolls are tucked tightly in the roasting pan, scatter the pepper strips and the cherry tomatoes on top. If there are remaining unstuffed cabbage leaves left, chop them finely and scatter atop as well. Pour the canned tomatoes, the remaining can of tomato soup, and the Heinz Chili Sauce atop the dumplings. Sprinkle with dried basil and add bay leaves. Dunk the reserved outer leaves detached from the cabbage at the beginning of the recipe into the still hot water used to soften the cabbage. This is simply to remove any grit from the surface of the leaves. Use the outer leaves as a \\u0027blanket\\u0027 and cover the dumplings completely.\",\"8\":\"Place the lid on the roasting pan and bake at 350°F for 2 hours. When 2 hours is up, turn off the oven heat, crack the oven door, and leave the roasting pan in the oven, undisturbed, for an additional hour.\",\"9\":\"Let rest until rolls are set. Then, spoon sauce over the cabbage rolls and serve alongside fresh bread of choice.\"}','{\"calories\":343,\"sugar\":9,\"carbohydrates\":27,\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":25,\"fat\":14}','\"\"','12','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/cca392963ae44639bb79fb75631b4c33.jpeg\"','1 large green cabbage||2 ½ pounds ground beef||2 cups cooked rice||2 large eggs||1 medium onion, roughly chopped||1 medium green bell pepper, julienned||10 cherry tomatoes, quartered||1 tbsp Kosher salt||(2) 10 3/4 ounce cans condensed tomato soup||(1) 1-pound can of tomatoes||1 bottle chili sauce||1 tablespoon dried basil||4 dried bay leaves||','stove_top||oven||dinner||special_occasion||high_protein||dairy_free'),('4f-37abf7164cdf','\"Orange Chicken Meatballs\"','{\"0\":\"Meatballs: Preheat the oven to 350°F.\",\"1\":\"In a large bowl, combine ground chicken, egg, panko breadcrumbs, minced onion, ginger paste, minced garlic, salt, and pepper. Mix ingredients until well-combined.\",\"2\":\"Spray the baking sheet with cooking spray or use parchment paper to keep the meatballs from sticking. Then, roll the mixture into 16 small meatballs and place on a baking sheet. Bake for 15 minutes,  turning once halfway through.\",\"3\":\"While the meatballs are cooking, prepare the sauce.\",\"4\":\"Sauce: In a medium size skillet, heat 1 tsp sesame oil. Add ½ cup sliced red bell pepper and cook until the peppers begin to soften.\",\"5\":\"Add rice wine vinegar, orange juice, soy sauce, brown sugar, sweet chili sauce, and red pepper flakes.Then, simmer sauce for 5 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Mix cornstarch with water and slowly add mixture to the sauce, continuing to cook until sauce thickens. Then, remove sauce from heat.\",\"7\":\"Coat each meatball in the sauce.\",\"8\":\"Serve over rice or with the vegetable of choice and garnish with green onion and toasted sesame seeds.\"}','{\"fat\":13,\"calories\":289,\"sugar\":7,\"carbohydrates\":19,\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":23}','\"\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/d61cb267fa4d43c296d4afdce5a97ed4.jpeg\"','1 lb ground chicken||1 egg||¾ cup panko breadcrumbs||3 tbsp onion, minced||1 tsp ginger paste||2 cloves garlic, minced||½ tsp salt||¼ tsp pepper||','oven||chinese||dinner||special_occasion||weeknight||dairy_free'),('4f-b5e023beb562','\"Instant Pot Summer Corn And Bacon Soup\"','{\"0\":\"Turn the Instant Pot to sauté mode and set the time for 20 minutes. Add bacon to the pot and cook until crispy and the fat has rendered, stirring occasionally to prevent burning, 10–12 minutes. Transfer the bacon to a baking sheet or plate lined with paper towels and set aside until ready to serve. Leave the rendered fat behind in the pot.\",\"1\":\"To the Instant Pot, add the onion and season with salt. Sauté for 3 minutes, until translucent. Add the garlic and cayenne, if using, and sauté for 2 minutes, until fragrant.\",\"2\":\"Whisk in the flour, making sure to break up any clumps. Cook for 3 minutes, until the flour is light golden in color. Turn off sauté mode by pressing cancel.\",\"3\":\"Pour in the chicken stock to deglaze the pot, scraping the bottom with a wooden spoon to loosen any browned bits. Add the potatoes and corn.\",\"4\":\"Secure the lid of the Instant Pot and set the valve to sealing. Select pressure cooking and set the timer for 10 minutes. Manually release the pressure from the Instant Pot after the cooking time has elapsed and let vent naturally for 15 minutes. Be careful when releasing the valve, as hot steam will come out. Remove the lid of the Instant Pot carefully, as the soup will be very hot.\",\"5\":\"Stir in the red bell pepper and heavy cream.\",\"6\":\"Ladle the warm soup into bowls and top with the bacon and chives.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":7,\"protein\":9,\"fat\":54,\"calories\":876,\"sugar\":24,\"carbohydrates\":95}','\"This light summer vegetable chowder is a breeze to make in the Instant Pot. Sprinkle on the bacon right before you eat so it stays crispy.\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/216338.jpg\"','4 slices thick-cut bacon, cut into ½-inch strips (about 1 cup)||10 ounces white onion, diced||Kosher salt, to taste||4 cloves garlic, minced||Pinch of cayenne, optional||3 tablespoons all-purpose flour||4 cups chicken stock||1¼ pounds red potatoes, chopped||2½ cups fresh yellow corn kernels (from about 4 large ears)||1 cup red bell pepper, diced (about 1 pepper)||¾ cup heavy cream||Fresh chives, chopped, for garnish||','summer||comfort_food||wooden_spoon||tongs||oven_mitts||dinner||high_fiber||under_1_hour||walmart_meal_planning'),('50-c4b963449c25','\"Hiroshima Okonomiyaki\"','{\"0\":\"Combine the flour, water, and mirin in a bowl and whisk until combined.\",\"1\":\"Brush oil on an electric griddle heated to 350˚F (180℃).\",\"2\":\"Pour the batter onto the griddle into a paper-thin circle 8 inches (20 cm) wide.\",\"3\":\"Place cabbage, tempura, bean sprouts, and scallions on top of the batter to fully cover it.\",\"4\":\"Top with 4 slices of pork belly and drizzle a little batter on top.\",\"5\":\"Gently flip the pan