dd beef, salt, and pepper, cooking until all the moisture has evaporated and the beef is browned.\",\"2\":\"Add crushed tomatoes, vodka, and chili flakes, stirring and cooking until half of the liquid has evaporated and the sauce has reduced.\",\"3\":\"Add cream, stirring until evenly incorporated.\",\"4\":\"Stir in pasta until evenly coated.\",\"5\":\"Serve with parsley and parmesan.\",\"6\":\"Nutrition  Calories: 1753 Fat: 69 grams  Carbs: 193 grams Fiber: 13 grams  Sugars: 22 grams  Protein: 93 grams\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":70,\"fat\":65,\"calories\":1299,\"sugar\":18,\"carbohydrates\":104,\"fiber\":6}','','3','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/b225fb9eeca24294971fa3b9e48e9be0/BFV10008_Penne4Ways.jpg\"','2 Tbsp. olive oil||1 onion, chopped||1 lb ground beef||1 tsp salt||1 tsp pepper||1 28-ounce can crushed tomatoes||½ cup vodka||½ tsp red chili flakes||½ cup heavy cream||4 cups cooked penne||Parsley and Parmesan to garnish||n/a||','stove_top||italian||dinner||weeknight||comfort_food||kid_friendly||easy||chefs_knife||cutting_board||wooden_spoon||pyrex||dry_measuring_cups||measuring_spoons||liquid_measuring_cup||strainer||contains_alcohol||high_protein||high_fiber'),('53-454c35e55719','\"Mac \\u0026 Cheese \\u0026 Corn Coconut Pudding\"','{\"0\":\"In a 9-10 inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add macaroni and corn. Sauté about 30 seconds. Stir in flour and coconut milk. Cook, stirring occasionally until macaroni are al dente or your desired doneness.\",\"1\":\"Stir in eggs until eggs become fluffy. Then, stir in parmesan cheese and mozzarella cheese until well blended. Add salt and black pepper to taste.\",\"2\":\"Cover with a lid, reduce heat to low and cook until the cheese melts.\",\"3\":\"Turn off the heat, uncover and sprinkle cilantro or parsley over the top.\",\"4\":\"Serve warm.\"}','{\"protein\":24,\"fat\":41,\"calories\":607,\"sugar\":3,\"carbohydrates\":37,\"fiber\":1}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/b21704e70093440db5f37eb405e51acb.png\"','1 tbsp unsalted butter||¾ cup Shells pasta, uncooked||1 cup Yellow corn kernels, frozen or canned (if frozen, thawed, if can, drained)||1 tbsp All-purpose flour||2 cups coconut milk in a carton, unsweetened||3 large eggs, beaten||¼ cup grated parmesan cheese||1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese||Salt and black pepper to taste||Chopped cilantro for garnish||','stove_top||dinner||special_occasion||low_sugar||vegetarian'),('53-8319bc4188bb','\"Vegetarian \\u201CLobster\\u201D Rolls\"','{\"0\":\"Cut the hearts of palm into oblique chunks and add them to a large bowl.\",\"1\":\"Mince the celery and add to the bowl with the hearts of palm.\",\"2\":\"Add the dill, chives, Old Bay seasoning, salt, pepper, lemon juice, and mayonnaise and stir to combine.\",\"3\":\"Brush the insides of the potato buns with the melted butter.\",\"4\":\"Toast in a medium skillet over low heat for 2-3 minutes, until golden.\",\"5\":\"Fill the buns with the hearts of palm mixture.\",\"6\":\"Garnish with chives.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":3,\"carbohydrates\":31,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":9,\"fat\":23,\"calories\":355}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/171751.jpg\"','2 14-ounce jars of hearts of palm, drained||1 large or 2 small celery stalks||2 tablespoons chopped fresh dill||2 tablespoons minced fresh chives, plus more for garnish||1 teaspoon Old Bay seasoning||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||Juice of 1½ lemons||⅓ cup mayonnaise||4 long potato rolls||2 tablespoons melted butter||','fourth_of_july||mixing_bowl||spatula||summer||special_occasion||dinner||cutting_board||chefs_knife||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||pyrex||saute_pan||low_sugar||high_fiber||vegetarian'),('53-9f95265cd8b3','\"Shrimp Tempura Rice Burger\"','{\"0\":\"Whisk the egg in a small bowl. Add 120 grams (1 cup) of flour and water. Whisk to combine. Cover with plastic wrap and transfer to the refrigerator.\",\"1\":\"Add flour to a shallow dish. Dip each shrimp in the flour, shaking off any excess.\",\"2\":\"Dip the floured shrimp into the batter.\",\"3\":\"Heat oil in a pot to 350°F (180˚C).\",\"4\":\"Fry the shrimp until they float to the top and become golden brown in color. Use a slotted spoon to transfer the shrimp to a paper towel-lined plate to drain.\",\"5\":\"For the mayonnaise sauce, combine mayonnaise, ketchup, honey, and vinegar.\",\"6\":\"Line a ramekin with plastic wrap, and mold ¼ of the rice into a patty. Repeat until you have 6 rice “buns.”\",\"7\":\"Heat a pan over medium-high heat and add a splash of sesame oil. Add the rice “buns” and cook until the outside is crispy, about 5 minutes.\",\"8\":\"Top the rice \\u0022bun\\u0022 with a piece of green leaf lettuce, fried shrimps, mayonnaise sauce, and top with another rice “bun.” Repeat with remaining ingredients.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":604,\"sugar\":4,\"carbohydrates\":60,\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":15,\"fat\":32}','','3','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/8339410cb3874330b7857d99c4a02149/FB.jpg\"','1 egg||120 grams flour||100 milliliters cold water||Flour, to cook||6 shrimp||Oil, to cook||','japanese||sauce_pan||sieve||plastic_wrap||mixing_bowl||cutting_board||easy||comfort_food||casual_party||date_night||deep_fry||stove_top||seafood||mashup||dry_measuring_cups||measuring_spoons||spider||paper_napkins||pyrex||dinner||low_sugar||dairy_free||pescatarian'),('54-1f181e670dfa','\"Cauliflower Gnocchi\"','{\"0\":\"Add the cauliflower to a steamer basket set over a medium pot of boiling water. Cover and steam for 10 minutes, or until fork-tender.\",\"1\":\"Transfer the cauliflower to a clean dish towel and squeeze the excess water into a bowl.\",\"2\":\"Transfer the squeezed cauliflower to a food processor. Add the flour, salt, and olive oil and pulse until the dough forms a ball.\",\"3\":\"Transfer the dough to a lightly floured surface and knead for 3-4 minutes, or until the dough bounces back when poked.\",\"4\":\"Shape the dough into a ball, then cut into 4 equal pieces. \",\"5\":\"Working 1 piece at a time, cut in half again, then roll out a rope about 6 inches (3-cm) long and 1 inch (2-cm) wide. Slice each rope into ½-inch (1-cm) pieces.\",\"6\":\"Roll each piece along the back of a fork to create a line pattern.\",\"7\":\"Transfer the gnocchi to a large pot of salted boiling water. Boil until the gnocchi float to the surface, 3-5 minutes, then remove with a slotted spoon.\",\"8\":\"Toss the gnocchi with pesto sauce and serve immediately.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":290,\"sugar\":7,\"carbohydrates\":52,\"fiber\":9,\"protein\":11,\"fat\":5}','\"\"','3','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/180839.jpg\"','5 cups cauliflower, roughly chopped||1¾ cups all-purpose flour or gluten-free flour||¾ teaspoon salt||1 tablespoon olive oil||Pesto sauce, for serving||','stove_top||food_processor||cutting_board||comfort_food||measuring_spoons||strainer||chefs_knife||dinner||dry_measuring_cups||italian||healthy||pyrex||sauce_pan||special_occasion||high_fiber||5_ingredients_or_less||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian'),('54-219c4d1f8a28','\"Spaghetti Squash Casserole\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 400˚F (200°C). Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick spray.\",\"1\":\"On a cutting board, cut the spaghetti squash in half lengthwise. Scoop out the seeds and discard. Drizzle 1 tablespoon of olive oil over the cut sides of the squash, then transfer to a rimmed baking sheet, cut side-down.\",\"2\":\"Bake the squash until fork-tender, about 1 hour. Let the spaghetti squash cool for 5 minutes, then use a fork to pull the strands of spaghetti squash and transfer to a medium bowl.\",\"3\":\"In a large pot or Dutch oven, heat the remaining tablespoon of olive oil over medium-high heat. Once the oil begins to shimmer, add the onion and cook until softened and light golden, about 5 minutes. Add the garlic and red pepper flakes and cook, stirring constantly, until aromatic, about 1 minute.\",\"4\":\"Add the ground beef and cook, breaking up the meat with a wooden spoon, until browned and cooked through, about 5 minutes. Add the tomato paste and cook, stirring often, until combined, about 1 minute.\",\"5\":\"Add the diced tomatoes, salt, and pepper, and stir to combine. Bring to a simmer, cover, and cook for 5 minutes. Stir in the spaghetti squash until well combined.\",\"6\":\"Transfer the mixture to the prepared baking dish and spread in an even layer. Sprinkle the cheese over the casserole.\",\"7\":\"Bake until the cheese is melted and golden brown, about 20 minutes. Remove from the oven and let the casserole cool for 5 minutes.\",\"8\":\"Top with the basil, then serve.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":12,\"fiber\":19,\"protein\":22,\"fat\":17,\"calories\":298,\"sugar\":5}','\"This spaghetti squash casserole is hearty and comforting, but won\\u2019t weigh you down. Strands of spaghetti squash stand in for pasta--they\\u2019re tossed with a quick beef and tomato sauce, topped with cheese, and baked to gooey, golden brown perfection.\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/331253.jpg\"','Nonstick cooking spray, for greasing||1 medium spaghetti squash||2 tablespoons olive oil, divided||1 medium yellow onion, diced||2 cloves garlic, minced||½ teaspoon red pepper flakes||1 pound ground beef||¼ cup tomato paste||1 28-ounce can of diced tomatoes||2 teaspoons kosher salt||1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper||2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese||½ cup torn fresh basil leaves, for serving||','dry_measuring_cups||liquid_measuring_cup||comfort_food||dutch_oven||oven||american||measuring_spoons||lunch||dinner||pyrex||baking_pan||wooden_spoon||weeknight||bake||big_batch||cutting_board||high_protein'),('54-7091349d7f62','\"Vegan Spaghetti Carbonara\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).\",\"1\":\"Cook pasta according to package instructions.\