d\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).\",\"1\":\"In a small bowl, combine the garlic, maple syrup, lemon juice, olive oil, salt, and pepper.\",\"2\":\"Brush the marinade over the salmon fillets. Cover with plastic wrap and marinate in the fridge for 1 hour.\",\"3\":\"In a medium bowl, combine the chickpeas, 2 tablespoons of olive oil, the smoked paprika, turmeric, pepper, cumin, salt, cayenne, and cinnamon. Toss to combine. Set aside.\",\"4\":\"Add the butternut squash and sweet potatoes to a baking sheet. Season with salt and pepper and drizzle with 2 tablespoons of olive oil. Bake for 1 hour, or until the vegetables are soft.\",\"5\":\"Pour the spiced chickpeas onto a second sheet pan and spread out into an even layer. Toss to coat. Bake for 40 minutes, or until chickpeas are browned and crispy.\",\"6\":\"In a liquid measuring cup or small bowl, combine the tahini, maple syrup, garlic, lemon juice, remaining ¼ cup of olive oil, salt, and pepper. Whisk well.\",\"7\":\"In a large bowl, add the chopped kale, roasted squash and sweet potatoes, barley, roasted chickpeas, shallot, pecans, and tahini dressing. Toss to combine.\",\"8\":\"Heat the canola oil in a large skillet over medium heat. In batches, sear the salmon skin-side down for 3 minutes, then flip and cook on the other side for 3 minutes.\",\"9\":\"Arrange the salad on a platter and top with the seared salmon.\",\"10\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":14,\"fat\":22,\"calories\":507,\"sugar\":15,\"carbohydrates\":67,\"fiber\":14}','\"\"','12','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/179895.jpg\"','2 cloves garlic, minced||¼ cup maple syrup||¼ cup lemon juice||¼ cup olive oil||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||6 large 6-8 ounce skin-on fillets of salmon, patted dry||2 tablespoons canola oil||','stove_top||mixing_bowl||whisk||special_occasion||american||fish_spatula||parchment_paper||big_batch||casual_party||healthy||liquid_measuring_cup||bake||oven||spatula||dinner||baking_pan||pyrex||oven_mitts||measuring_spoons||epoca_walmart||seafood||high_fiber||dairy_free||pescatarian'),('5a-ae857f29e78f','\"Fried Plantain Salad\"','{\"0\":\"Trim the ends of the plantain, then peel and slice on the bias into ½-inch (1.24) pieces.\",\"1\":\"In a large skillet, heat about ⅛ inch (3 mm) canola oil over medium-high heat.\",\"2\":\"Add the plantains and fry until golden brown, 2–3 minutes per side. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate and season with salt.\",\"3\":\"Remove all but 1 tablespoon of oil from the skillet. Add the onion and red bell pepper and cook until they are slightly softened, but still have some crunch, 3–4 minutes. Remove the pan from the heat.\",\"4\":\"Make the honey dressing: In a small bowl, whisk together the apple cider vinegar, honey, Dijon, and salt. While whisking, slowly drizzle in the oil until the dressing is emulsified.\",\"5\":\"When ready to serve, divide the arugula between 2 bowls. Top with the sautéed peppers and onions, fried plantains, sliced avocado, green onions, pistachios, and cilantro. Season with salt and pepper. Drizzle the dressing over the salad.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":9,\"fat\":59,\"calories\":815,\"sugar\":30,\"carbohydrates\":73,\"fiber\":26}','\"This isn\\u2019t just any date night salad. Tayo kicks it up a notch by frying up sweet plantains to add crunch and an unexpected twist, then pairs them with peppery arugula, creamy avocado, salty pistachios, and a simple honey Dijon dressing to bring it all together.\"','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/2e272057fe8b47d2ad4b6080b912722a/BFV71724_ThePerfectTropicalDinnerForAStaycation_MJC_100520_v05_YT.jpg\"','1 large ripe plantain||Canola oil, for frying||Kosher salt, to taste||¼ medium yellow onion, sliced||1 red bell pepper, seeded and sliced||2 cups arugula||1 avocado, sliced||2 green onions, sliced on the bias||3 tablespoons chopped pistachios||¼ cup chopped fresh cilantro||Freshly ground black pepper to taste||','easy||measuring_spoons||fusion||chefs_knife||stove_top||liquid_measuring_cup||cutting_board||mixing_bowl||date_night||pan_fry||whisk||dinner||special_occasion||high_fiber||under_30_minutes||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||dairy_free||vegetarian'),('5b-51c1ae7aa4c6','\"Bacon Ranch Chicken Bake\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 400˚F (200˚C).\",\"1\":\"Place chicken breast in a baking dish. Season chicken with salt and pepper, to taste.\",\"2\":\"Spread 1-2 Tbsp. ranch on each chicken breast.\",\"3\":\"Layer two slices of bacon on top of each chicken breast.\",\"4\":\"Top with cheese.\",\"5\":\"Bake for 40 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":1,\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":43,\"fat\":22,\"calories\":393,\"sugar\":0}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/d7c5851541ea46309cfdc0f8b1548d92/BFV9176_Chicken_Bake_4-ways_YT1080.jpg\"','3-4 chicken breasts||salt and pepper to taste||n/a||6-8 Tbsp. ranch dressing||6-8 slices bacon||4 oz cheddar cheese||','oven||comfort_food||dinner||weeknight||bake||american||easy||kid_friendly||game_day||baking_pan||oven_mitts||measuring_spoons||low_carb||high_protein||keto'),('5b-667871af5963','\"Farro Lentil Salad\"','{\"0\":\"In a medium bowl, combine the farro, lentils, tomatoes, cucumber, yellow pepper, red pepper, and parsley.\",\"1\":\"In a liquid measuring cup or small bowl, combine the olive oil, red wine vinegar, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, garlic, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper, and whisk until well-combined.\",\"2\":\"Pour the vinaigrette over the farro salad and toss until well-combined.\",\"3\":\"Distribute the farro salad into airtight containers with the arugula, if using. Refrigerate for up to 5 days.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":25,\"fat\":20,\"calories\":758,\"sugar\":5,\"carbohydrates\":127,\"fiber\":22}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/feb04c3df39f41d6b62905a92d94950d/MakeAheadPlantBasedLunchesFBFINAL.jpg\"','3½ cups farro, cooked||1½ cups lentils, cooked||1 cup grape tomatoes, halved||1 cup cucumber, diced||½ cup yellow bell pepper, diced||½ cup red bell pepper||⅓ cup fresh parsley, chopped||⅓ cup olive oil||2 tablespoons red wine vinegar||2 tablespoons lemon juice||1 teaspoon Dijon mustard||1 clove garlic, minced||1 teaspoon Italian seasoning||½ teaspoon salt||¼ teaspoon pepper||Arugula, to taste (optional)||','big_batch||healthy||meal_prep||easy||dry_measuring_cups||cutting_board||chefs_knife||tupperware||measuring_spoons||dinner||mixing_bowl||weeknight||liquid_measuring_cup||whisk||nynm_meal_prep||high_protein||low_sugar||high_fiber||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian||walmart_meal_planning'),('5b-9278aa9940a2','\"Lasagna Dome\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\",\"1\":\"Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large pot over high heat. Add the onion and garlic. Cook until starting to brown, stirring occasionally, 3-4 minutes.\",\"2\":\"Add the beef, salt, and pepper. Cook until all of the moisture has evaporated and the meat is starting to brown on the edges, breaking the meat up as you stir, 10-12 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Add the tomato sauce and tomato paste, then reduce the heat to medium and bring the sauce to a simmer. Cook it down until the mixture becomes thick, about 15 minutes. Remove the pot from the heat and set aside.\",\"4\":\"In a small bowl, combine the ricotta, basil, egg, and Parmesan. Stir until smooth. Set aside.\",\"5\":\"Grease a large oven-safe metal bowl with the remaining tablespoon of olive oil, then lay about 25 lasagna noodles along the sides and bottom of the bowl, fanning them out in an overlapping pattern. The ends of the noodles should hang over the sides of the bowl.\",\"6\":\"Slice the remaining lasagna noodles in half crosswise. These will serve as the layers between the meat and the cheese mixtures.\",\"7\":\"Sprinkle half of the mozzarella into the bottom of the bowl on top of the noodles. This will help bind the noodles together when cooked. Spread half of the meat mixture evenly over the mozzarella, then lay half of the cut noodles over the sauce.\",\"8\":\"Spread all of the ricotta mixture over the noodles, then layer with the rest of the noodles, then the rest of the mozzarella, and the rest of the meat sauce.\",\"9\":\"Fold the edges of the lasagna noodles hanging over the sides of the bowl back towards the center, creating another overlapping pattern.\",\"10\":\"Cover with foil and bake for about 45 minutes, until cooked through.\",\"11\":\"Meanwhile, make the béchamel: In a saucepan over medium heat, melt the butter. Add the flour and cook, whisking continuously, for about 2 minutes until a paste forms.\",\"12\":\"Add the hot milk and continue to whisk as the sauce thickens and comes to a boil. Season with salt and pepper and add the Parmesan. Reduce the heat to low, and cook, still whisking, for 2-3 minutes more.\",\"13\":\"Invert the lasagna dome onto a cutting board.\",\"14\":\"Pour the béchamel sauce over the dome and top with basil.\",\"15\":\"Slice the dome, then top with more Parmesan and basil, if desired.\",\"16\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":28,\"fat\":26,\"calories\":479,\"sugar\":5,\"carbohydrates\":24,\"fiber\":1}','','10','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/160586.jpg\"','3 tablespoons olive oil, divided||½ medium yellow onion, diced||4 cloves garlic, minced||1 pound ground beef||1 teaspoon salt||1 teaspoon black pepper||15 ounces tomato sauce||3 ounces tomato paste||15 ounces (425 grams) ricotta cheese||½ cup chopped fresh basil||1 large egg||½ cup shredded Parmesan cheese||30 lasagna noodles, boiled until al dente,||2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese||','kid_friendly||italian||oven||sauce_pan||american||comfort_food||stove_top||casual_party||dinner||bake||big_batch||special_occasion||fusion||pyrex||mixing_bowl||dry_measuring_cups||liquid_measuring_cup||measuring_spoons||wooden_spoon||oven_mitts||whisk||cutting_board||chefs_knife||stuffed||mashup||pan_fry||saute_pan||high_protein||low_sugar'),('5b-ce7825a6b0b3','\"Elegant Braised Lamb Shank Dinner\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\",\"1\":\"Season the lamb shanks all over with salt and pepper.\",\"2\":\"Heat the canola oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.\",\"3\":\"Sear 2 lamb shanks at a time until a dark brown crust forms on one side, 3-5 minutes. Sear the other sides of the meat until evenly browned. Remove the shanks from the pan and set aside. Remove all but 2 tablespoons of fat from the pan.\",\"4\":\"Add the minced carrots, onion, celery, and minced garlic to the pot. Season with salt and pepper, and cook until the vegetables are deeply caramelized, 15-20 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Add the tomato paste and cook until it browns and is aromatic, 5 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Add the red wine and scrape the bottom of the pot to release the flavorful browned bits stuck to the bottom. Cook until the wine reduces by half and thickens slightly, 3 minutes.\",\"7\":\"Add the chicken stock, orange juice, lemon juice, rosemary, thyme, and bay leaves. Stir and bring to a boil.\",\"8\":\"Return the lamb shanks to the Dutch oven, cover, and place in the oven for 2 hours, turning the shanks halfway through, until the lamb is tender and the braising liquid has thickened.\",\"9\":\"About halfway through the lamb cooking time, add the oblique-cut carrots, Brussels sprouts, red pearl onions, and whole garlic cloves to a baking sheet. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Toss to combine. Roast in the oven for 1 hour, or until the vegetables are tender.\",\"10\":\"Right after the potatoes finish boiling, drain and transfer to a large bowl. Season with plenty of salt and a bit of white pepper, and mash the potatoes until as smooth as possible.\",\"11\":\"Fold in the butter, sour cream, and heavy cream until smooth and light.\",\"12\":\"Make the citrus gremolata: In a small bowl, combine the parsley, lemon zest, flaky salt, garlic, chives, horseradish, and orange zest.\",\"13\":\"To serve, scoop mashed potatoes onto a plate. Add roasted vegetables and a lamb shank. Top with the braising liquid and citrus gremolata.\",\"14\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":78,\"fat\":51,\"calories\":983,\"sugar\":12,\"carbohydrates\":61,\"fiber\":7}','\"\"','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/176964.jpg\"','6 1-pound lamb shanks||Kosher salt, to taste||Freshly ground black pepper, to taste||2 tablespoons canola oil||2 medium carrots, minced, plus 1 pound, oblique-cut||1 medium white onion, minced||2 stalks celery, minced||5 cloves garlic, minced, plus 15 whole, divided||2 tablespoons tomato paste||1 cup red wine||4 cups chicken stock||Juice of 1 orange||Juice of 1 lemon||5 sprigs of fresh rosemary||10 sprigs of fresh thyme||3 bay leaves||1 pound Brussels sprouts, halved||1 pound red pearl onions, peeled||Olive oil, for drizzling||3 pounds Yukon Gold potatoes, peeled, chopped, and boiled||White pepper, to taste||½ cup (1 stick) unsalted butter, cubed and chilled||1 cup sour cream||½ cup heavy cream||','american||big_batch||oven||tongs||dutch_oven||oven_mitts||comfort_food||mixing_bowl||spatula||sauce_pan||wooden_spoon||special_occasion||dinner||bake||christmas||date_night||baking_pan||liquid_measuring_cup||pyrex||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||contains_alcohol||passover||high_protein||high_fiber'),('5c-288d320a7a33','\"Vegan Lasagna Soup\"','{\"0\":\"In a large pot, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Once the oil begins to shimmer, add the onion and cook for 3-4 minutes, until semi-translucent.\",\"1\":\"Add the garlic, tomato paste, basil, and oregano, and cook for 2-3 more minutes, or until the onions are translucent and herbs are fragrant.\",\"2\":\"Add the crushed tomatoes, vegetable broth, and lentils, and bring to a boil. Increase heat to medium-high and cook for 10 minutes or until lentils are halfway tender.\",\"3\":\"Break apart the lasagna noodles into about 2-inch-long (5-cm) pieces and add to the pot. Let the soup cook for another 10-15 minutes, or until the pasta is al dente and the lentils are tender.\",\"4\":\"Stir in the spinach and let wilt, then serve immediately.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":87,\"fiber\":5,\"protein\":10,\"fat\":64,\"calories\":1049,\"sugar\":24}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/7041188b99254834baa326731d068eb0/One-PotVeganDinnersFBFinal.jpg\"','1 tablespoon olive oil||1 onion, diced||3 cloves garlic, minced||2 tablespoons tomato paste||1 teaspoon dried basil||1 teaspoon dried oregano||28 ounces crushed tomatoes||6 cups vegetable broth||⅓ cup green lentils, rinsed||8 ounces lasagna noodles, uncooked||3 cups spinach||Chiffonade basil, for serving||','stove_top||one_pot_or_pan||weeknight||kid_friendly||liquid_measuring_cup||big_batch||measuring_spoons||comfort_food||dinner||wooden_spoon||healthy||sauce_pan||spatula||pyrex||dry_measuring_cups||pan_fry||nynm_veggie||high_fiber||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian||walmart_meal_planning'),('5c-d58cc3b1f224','\"BBQ Pulled Pork Rolls\"','{\"0\":\"Add the ketchup, molasses, apple cider vinegar, yellow mustard, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, and pepper in a saucepan over medium heat, whisking to combine.\",\"1\":\"Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring frequently. For thicker sauce, cook for additional 5 minutes\",\"2\":\"Cool for 20 minutes. Store in an airtight container in refrigerator for up to 1 week.\",\"3\":\"Add pork, salt, pepper, paprika, onion and 1 cup (290g) of prepared bbq sauce to a slow cooker.\",\"4\":\"Cover and cook on high for 5-6 hours.\",\"5\":\"Preheat oven to 375°F (180°C).\",\"6\":\"Using a rolling pin, roll the dough into a 16x12-inch (40x30-cm) rectangle, about ¼-inch (6 mm) thick on a well-floured surface.\",\"7\":\"Shred pork using two forks.\",\"8\":\"Distribute pulled pork over the dough, leaving a 1-inch (2 cm) open strip on the short side facing you.\",\"9\":\"Roll the dough into a log shape, pinching the seams to seal it.\",\"10\":\"With a serrated knife, evenly cut roll into 6-8 slices. Arrange slices in a greased cake pan.\",\"11\":\"Bake for 20-25 minutes.\",\"12\":\"Cool for 10-15 minutes.\",\"13\":\"Brush more BBQ sauce on rolls and top with chives, if desired.\",\"14\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":22,\"calories\":474,\"sugar\":15,\"carbohydrates\":42,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":26}','','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/114821.jpg\"','½ cup ketchup||½ cup molasses||¼ cup apple cider vinegar||¼ cup yellow mustard||2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce||1 clove garlic, minced||¼ teaspoon pepper||2 pounds boneless pork loin chops||2 teaspoons salt||1 teaspoon pepper||1 tablespoon paprika||½ onion, sliced||1 pound pizza dough||Chives, chopped, for serving||','rolling_pin||slow_cooker||comfort_food||tongs||sauce_pan||whisk||oven||bake||tupperware||stove_top||game_day||baking_pan||measuring_spoons||wooden_spoon||american||dinner||casual_party||spatula||cutting_board||chefs_knife||high_protein||dairy_free'),('5d-5e7ab8ea816d','\"Kingklip With Eggplant, Ragout and Capers\"','{\"0\":\"Drizzle the olive oil in a pan at medium-high heat, and sauté the onions till soft. Add the tomatoes, eggplant, oregano, garlic, olives, tomato paste and wine, and allow the mixture to come to a gentle simmer.\",\"1\":\"Cook until the ragout has reduced and is slightly thickened.\",\"2\":\"In another pan on high heat, drizzle a little olive oil and, when hot, add the capers. Fry the capers, tossing to prevent them from sticking to the pan.\",\"3\":\"Remove the crispy capers from the pan and place on a paper towel to drain the excess fat.\",\"4\":\"Season the kingklip with salt and pepper. Add the butter to the same pan used for the capers and, once slightly brown, place the fish skin side down for 4 minutes until golden brown and crispy. Turn the fish and cook for another 2–3 minutes.\",\"5\":\"As the fish cooks, spoon the butter over the top.\",\"6\":\"Remove the fish from the heat, 