er\":19,\"protein\":22,\"fat\":21,\"calories\":500}','\"\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/40a7f6ac9759436894768568da0b9a11.jpeg\"','4 poblano peppers (if you do not want to roast them, you can use 2 cans diced green chilis)||1 yellow onion, diced||1 c grated carrots (or 2 carrots, peeled and diced)||6 cloves garlic, roughly chop||1 bay leaf||2 ½ tbsp cumin||1 28 oz can crushed tomatoes||4 c broth (chicken or vegetarian)||2 chipotle peppers in adobo (do not drain)||1 lb frozen butternut squash cubes||3 cans black beans, drained, not rinsed||1 c frozen fire-roasted corn||⅛ c heavy cream||Additional toppings – cheese, scallions, cilantro, avocado||','dinner||stove_top||special_occasion||high_fiber'),('78-72ebf82a88f8','\"Lemon Chicken \\u0026 Spaghetti Squash\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 400˚F (200˚C).\",\"1\":\"Poke several holes in the spaghetti squash around the lengthwise center of the squash. Microwave on high for 5 minutes.\",\"2\":\"Cut the squash in half along the holes. Remove the seeds and pulp with a spoon. Drizzle the squash with olive oil, and season with salt and pepper.\",\"3\":\"Place the squash cut-side down on baking sheet and bake for 40 minutes, until tender. Let cool.\",\"4\":\"Heat a bit of olive oil in a medium skillet over medium high heat. Add the chicken breast and cook for 6-8 minutes, until the chicken is golden brown and cooked through. Remove the chicken from the pan and set aside.\",\"5\":\"Add a bit more oil and the onion and sauté for a few minutes, until starting to brown. Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.\",\"6\":\"Add the salt, pepper, and tomatoes and cook for a couple minutes, until the tomatoes start to release their juices.\",\"7\":\"Add the lemon juice and chicken broth and cook until the liquid reduces by about half, 20 minutes.\",\"8\":\"Add the chicken and cook for 2 minutes, then add the spinach and cook for 2 minutes, until wilted. Remove the pan from the heat.\",\"9\":\"Using 2 forks, shred the spaghetti squash and scoop out onto serving plates.\",\"10\":\"Pour the sauce over the squash. Serve immediately.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":29,\"fat\":11,\"calories\":305,\"sugar\":12,\"carbohydrates\":26,\"fiber\":5}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/f95e9668e30e41a8abe9c54c3bfc790b/Thumb_1.jpg\"','1 spaghetti squash||Olive oil||Sea salt, to taste||Black pepper, to taste||2 chicken breast, cut into 1-2 in pieces||','oven||microwave||stove_top||american||healthy||gluten_free||dinner||cutting_board||baking_pan||oven_mitts||cast_iron_pan||tongs||liquid_measuring_cup||spatula||pan_fry||date_night||special_occasion||chefs_knife||pyrex||fall||measuring_spoons||thanksgiving'),('78-942556d8823e','\"Steak Eggs Benedict\"','{\"0\":\"Make the steak: Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C).\",\"1\":\"Season the steak on both sides with kosher salt, black pepper, and garlic powder.\",\"2\":\"Heat the olive oil in a large cast-iron skillet over medium heat until it shimmers. Sear the steak for 2 minutes on each side, then transfer skillet with the steak to the oven and cook for 6–10 minutes, or until the internal temperature reaches 135°F (57°C). Remove the steak from the oven and let it rest for 5 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Meanwhile, poach the eggs: Fill a 12-inch high-walled skillet with 2 inches of water and add the white vinegar. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. When bubbles start to break the surface of the water, crack one egg at a time into a small bowl, then gently drop into the water at the center of the pan. Cook the eggs for 3–4 minutes, or until the yolks are still runny, but the whites are set. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the eggs to a paper towel-lined plate to drain.\",\"4\":\"Make the hollandaise sauce: Add the egg yolks, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, salt, pepper, and paprika to a blender. Blend on medium-high speed for 10 seconds, until combined. With the blender running, slowly drizzle in the hot melted butter until emulsified, about 2 minutes.\",\"5\":\"To assemble, slice the steak against the grain into ¼–½-inch-thick slices. Divide the steak slices between the halved English muffins. Top each with ¼ cup of arugula, a poached egg, a generous spoonful of the hollandaise sauce, and a sprinkle of flaky sea salt.\",\"6\":\"Serve immediately.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":23,\"fat\":18,\"calories\":328,\"sugar\":1,\"carbohydrates\":14,\"fiber\":19}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/396560.jpg\"','1 10–12-ounce New York strip steak||1 teaspoon kosher salt||1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper||½ teaspoon garlic powder||2 teaspoons olive oil||','stove_top||dinner||low_carb||low_sugar||high_fiber'),('78-98bd9cb2e702','\"Chicken Salad Sandwich\"','{\"0\":\"In a bowl, combine chicken, celery, onion, sliced tomatoes, apple, yogurt, salt and pepper.\",\"1\":\"Spread the chicken salad on one of the pieces of bread and place the lettuce on the other piece. Top with desired condiments and bring the two pieces of bread together. Cut in half and place in a reusable container with some fruits and veggies.\",\"2\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":7,\"protein\":37,\"fat\":9,\"calories\":433,\"sugar\":15,\"carbohydrates\":49}','','1','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/b2f4d9f6423f4c04be7a626aa5ddd51c/BFV21597_1RotisserieChicken4Lunches_FB1080SQ.jpg\"','½ cup shredded chicken||2 tablespoons celery, diced||1 tablespoon white onion, finely diced||6 cherry tomatoes, sliced in half||2 tablespoons apple, diced||3 tablespoons Greek yogurt||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||2 pieces whole wheat bread||1 leaf romaine lettuce||','american||kid_friendly||healthy||easy||lunch||meal_prep||cutting_board||measuring_spoons||mixing_bowl||dry_measuring_cups||pyrex||chefs_knife||tupperware||high_protein||high_fiber'),('78-ee3e043c6c64','\"Buffalo Chicken Lettuce Wraps\"','{\"0\":\"In a medium bowl, add the chicken and buffalo sauce. Stir to combine.\",\"1\":\"Add the celery, red onion, salt, and pepper. Stir to combine and set aside.\",\"2\":\"Make the Greek yogurt ranch dressing: in a small bowl, add the Greek yogurt, dried parsley, garlic powder, dried dill, onion powder, salt, pepper, and lemon juice. Stir to combine.\",\"3\":\"Lay each lettuce leaf flat on a plate and scoop the chicken mixture into the middle. Top with a spoonful of Greek yogurt ranch dressing. Garnish with blue cheese crumbles and sliced green onion, if desired.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":54,\"fat\":31,\"calories\":589,\"sugar\":13,\"carbohydrates\":17}','','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/6dfa21e6c292450794d06139b361f25d/BFV44999_4EasyNo-CookDinners_FB.jpg\"','2 cups shredded rotisserie chicken||1 cup buffalo sauce||½ cup diced celery||¼ cup diced red onion||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||2 leaves of greenleaf lettuce||Crumbled blue cheese, for garnish (optional)||Sliced green onion, for garnish (optional)||','liquid_measuring_cup||mixing_bowl||measuring_spoons||healthy||kid_friendly||easy||spring||weeknight||summer||spatula||pyrex||dinner||mccormick_game_day||spring_eat||high_protein'),('79-6df5c74e1399','\"One-Pan Chicken Fajita\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\",\"1\":\"Place bell peppers and onions into mixing bowl and thoroughly coat with olive oil, salt, and pepper.\",\"2\":\"Tear off a sheet of parchment paper, large enough to fold into a packet.\",\"3\":\"Place bell peppers and chicken breast on top of parchment paper. Season with the fajita seasoning.\",\"4\":\"Fold the edges of the parchment paper widthwise 2-3 times then twist the ends until fully closed.\",\"5\":\"Bake for 20-25 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C).\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":12,\"fat\":8,\"calories\":135,\"sugar\":0,\"carbohydrates\":3}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/df1cf818cec84da4b62f945be2237177/BFV18394_One-Pan_Chicken_Meal_Prep_4_Ways_-_FB_1080x1080.jpg\"','½ green bell pepper, sliced||½ red bell pepper, sliced||¼ onion, sliced||Olive oil||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||1 chicken breast||Parchment paper||','oven||one_pot_or_pan||meal_prep||dinner||weeknight||bake||healthy||easy||parchment_paper||tongs||cutting_board||chefs_knife||pyrex||mixing_bowl||measuring_spoons||oven_mitts||baking_pan||walmart_holiday_bundle||low_carb||low_calorie||dairy_free||keto'),('79-7babc4d7d581','\"Salmon And Garlic Pasta\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat stainless steel or nonstick pan to medium high heat with olive oil.\",\"1\":\"Pat dry salmon filets and season to taste with salt and pepper.\",\"2\":\"Place salmon in pan skin side down. Cook each side approximately 5-6 minutes until salmon reaches 145°F and is flaky.\",\"3\":\"Remove salmon from the pan and add half the butter and garlic. Saute until fragrant, add lemon zest and juice of half the lemon as well as fresh parsley.\",\"4\":\"Re-introduce salmon to pan and coat in butter sauce.\",\"5\":\"Remove salmon from pan and add all remaining ingredients except parmesan to pan.\",\"6\":\"Bring to a boil and cook approximately 12-14 minutes or until pasta is tender.\",\"7\":\"Slowly stir in parmesan until incorporated.\",\"8\":\"Serve on a plate with fresh parsley and a lemon wedge.\"}','{\"fat\":42,\"calories\":949,\"sugar\":4,\"carbohydrates\":90,\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":49}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/44367ac88c6c456b9fb21c794ac18c93.png\"','4 salmon filets||3-5 tbsp fresh garlic||Salt and pepper, to taste||1 lemon||Fresh parsley, to taste||¼ cup butter||2-3 tbsp olive oil||1 lb. linguine or fettuccine||4 cups water||1 cup fresh parmesan||','stove_top||seafood||fusion||italian||dinner||weeknight||high_protein||low_sugar||pescatarian'),('79-a1ce7f295116','\"Turkey Shepherd\\u2019s Pie\"','{\"0\":\"Make the mashed potato topping: Add the potatoes to a large stockpot and fill with cold water until the potatoes are covered by about 1 inch. Add 1 tablespoon salt. Bring to a boil over medium heat and cook until the potatoes are fork-tender, 10–12 minutes.\",\"1\":\"Drain the potatoes, then return to the pot. Add the butter, milk, and remaining ½ teaspoon salt, and mash until the potatoes are smooth and creamy. Fold in 2 ounces of cheddar cheese. Set aside.\",\"2\":\"Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C).\",\"3\":\"Make the filling: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the ground turkey and cook for 6–8 minutes, until browned. Remove the turkey from the pan and set aside.\",\"4\":\"Melt the remaining tablespoon of butter in the same skillet. Add the onion, celery, carrot, and ½ teaspoon salt, and cook for 5–6 minutes, until the onion is translucent and the vegetables are beginning to brown. Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute more, until fragrant.\",\"5\":\"Add the parsnips, green beans, and cooked ground turkey and stir to combine.\",\"6\":\"Add the McCormick® Turkey Gravy Mix, flour, pepper, thyme, sage, milk, and chicken stock, and fold into the filling until well incorporated. Bring to a simmer and cook for 3–4 minutes, until the sauce begins to thicken. Remove the pan from the heat and transfer the filling to a 2-quart casserole dish.\",\"7\":\"Spread the potatoes evenly over the filling, smoothing the top. Top with the remaining 2 ounces shredded cheese.\",\"8\":\"Bake the shepherd’s pie for 30 minutes, or until bubbling and browned on the top. Let rest for 10 minutes before serving.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":23,\"fat\":29,\"calories\":570,\"sugar\":8,\"carbohydrates\":51,\"fiber\":4}','\"\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/289589.jpg\"','2 pounds Yukon Gold potatoes, peeled if desired, diced||1 tablespoon plus ½ teaspoon kosher salt, divided||2 tablespoons unsalted butter||¼ cup milk||4 ounces shredded cheddar cheese, divided||','bake||oven||comfort_food||