n salt||1 red onion, diced, for topping||½ cup cilantro, chopped, for topping||4-6 corn tortillas||','american||mexican||comfort_food||easy||weeknight||stove_top||fusion||dinner||game_day||pan_fry||saute_pan||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||chefs_knife||cutting_board||wooden_spoon||pyrex||high_protein||dairy_free||dole_crowd_pleasers'),('7e-a98ba0619ebd','\"Scalloped Potato Dome\"','{\"0\":\"Using a mandolin, slice the red potatoes to about 3 millimeter-thick slices.\",\"1\":\"Slice the gold potatoes to about 5-6 millimeters thick.\",\"2\":\"In a large bowl, combine the red potatoes with the salt, pepper, and heavy cream, and stir until evenly coated.\",\"3\":\"Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C).\",\"4\":\"Butter an oven-safe, 8 or 9-inch (20 or 23-cm), stainless steel mixing bowl.\",\"5\":\"Starting from the center, lay the red potatoes in an overlapping, circular fashion, making sure they make good contact and are sticking to the bowl. Repeat the circular pattern up until roughly ½-inch (1-cm) from the top of the bowl.\",\"6\":\"Place the sliced gold potatoes into the cream, stirring until fully coated with cream.\",\"7\":\"Shake off the excess cream, then layer the potato slices at the bottom of the bowl, building in a similar circular fashion.\",\"8\":\"After 2-3 rotations, place down 2 slices of cheddar. To fill the gaps, you might need to cut 2 more slices into halves and use those strips near the edges.\",\"9\":\"Layer another 2 rotations of gold potatoes.\",\"10\":\"Place the strips of bacon in a single layer across the potatoes.\",\"11\":\"Layer another 2 rotations of gold potatoes.\",\"12\":\"Sprinkle the chives in an even layer across the potatoes.\",\"13\":\"Layer another 2 rotations of gold potatoes.\",\"14\":\"Fan out the rest of the cheddar slices in a circular pattern on top of the potatoes.\",\"15\":\"Layer another 2 rotations of gold potatoes.\",\"16\":\"Place the circle of puff pastry on top, pressing it lightly into the potatoes.\",\"17\":\"Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour and 30 minutes. If the pastry or the edges of potatoes near the top are starting to get too dark, cover the dish with foil and continue baking.\",\"18\":\"Cool until the bottom of the dish is no longer warm.\",\"19\":\"While the potatoes bake, prepare the garlic cream sauce by transferring the cream from the soaked potatoes into a medium saucepan or pot.\",\"20\":\"Add the onion powder, garlic powder, and Parmesan, stirring while bringing to a boil. Set aside and reheat when serving.\",\"21\":\"Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\",\"22\":\"Run a knife along the sides of the bowl to make sure the potatoes are release, then invert it onto a baking tray.\",\"23\":\"Bake for another 10 minutes or so, until the slices start to turn golden brown and slightly crispy.\",\"24\":\"Transfer the dome to a cutting board, then slice into wedges.\",\"25\":\"Serve with the cream sauce, a sprinkle of chives.\",\"26\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":779,\"sugar\":4,\"carbohydrates\":61,\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":21,\"fat\":54}','','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/123833.jpg\"','5-7 medium red potatoes||2 teaspoons salt||1 teaspoon black pepper||2 cups heavy cream||2 tablespoons butter, softened||6-8 medium or large Yukon gold potatoes||10 slices cheddar cheese||6 strips bacon, cooked until crispy||¼ cup chives, finely chopped plus more to serve||1 sheet puff pastry, cut into a 9-inch circle||1 teaspoon onion powder||1 teaspoon garlic powder||¼ cup grated Parmesan cheese||','big_batch||saute_pan||chefs_knife||american||dinner||tongs||bake||pyrex||oven||mixing_bowl||comfort_food||casual_party||baking_pan||oven_mitts||cooling_rack||measuring_spoons||liquid_measuring_cup||dry_measuring_cups||low_sugar'),('7f-0f4b35d7d86a','\"Copycat Olive Garden Chicken Gnocchi Soup\"','{\"0\":\"In a large pot, heat the oil over medium-high heat until shimmering. Add the onion, carrots, and celery and sauté until tender, about 6 minutes.\",\"1\":\"Add the garlic and chicken and toss to incorporate, then pour in the chicken stock and season with the salt, garlic powder, onion powder, pepper, and thyme. Bring to a boil and cook for about 10 minutes, until fragrant.\",\"2\":\"Stir in the half-and-half and gnocchi and cook for 2 minutes, until beginning to thicken slightly.\",\"3\":\"In a small bowl, whisk together the cornstarch and water.\",\"4\":\"Reduce the heat to medium-low. Stir in the cornstarch slurry and cook for another 3 minutes, until the soup has thickened. Stir in the spinach, then remove the pot from the heat.\",\"5\":\"Ladle the soup into bowls and garnish with the Parmesan cheese, then serve immediately.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":0,\"carbohydrates\":0,\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":0,\"fat\":4,\"calories\":39}','\"Bring the memories of Olive Garden home with this copycat Chicken Gnocchi Soup recipe. It\\u2019s a cozy, comforting dish that the whole family will love.\"','6','\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/video-api-prod/assets/4eb383d115244b9b99747806e6bb363b/Gnochisoup.jpg\"','2 tablespoons neutral oil, such as canola or vegetable||1½ cups diced yellow onion||1 cup diced carrots||1 cup diced celery||6 garlic cloves, grated||1½ medium chicken breasts, cooked and chopped||5 cups chicken stock||1 tablespoon kosher salt||1 tablespoon garlic powder||1 tablespoon onion powder||1 tablespoon black pepper||1 tablespoon dried thyme||1½ cups half-and-half||1 pound gnocchi||1 tablespoon cornstarch||1 tablespoon water||1½ cups chopped fresh spinach or kale||Parmesan cheese, for garnish||','stove_top||comfort_food||one_pot_or_pan||dinner||big_batch||under_1_hour||dairy_free'),('7f-61662d1f08af','\"The Best Crispy Chicken Parmesan\"','{\"0\":\"Cut the chicken breasts in half widthwise to make 4 thin breasts.\",\"1\":\"Season the chicken with salt, pepper, and onion powder.\",\"2\":\"Coat the chicken in flour, then egg, and then bread crumbs.\",\"3\":\"Pour oil in a cast-iron skillet to come ¼ inch (½ cm) up the side. Heat the oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and fry on both sides until brown, about 4 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate to drain.\",\"5\":\"Preheat oven to 450°F (230°C).\",\"6\":\"Place the fried chicken breasts in a baking dish. If they don’t fit side by side, gently overlap them. Pour the marinara over the chicken.\",\"7\":\"Top with mozzarella slices and Parmesan.\",\"8\":\"Bake for 10-15 minutes, or until the cheese is browned and bubbling.\",\"9\":\"Serve with freshly chopped basil.\",\"10\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":46,\"fat\":25,\"calories\":719,\"sugar\":8,\"carbohydrates\":72,\"fiber\":4}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/60ab4f4486644ae7a1d908298fc5881a/fb.jpg\"','2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts.||1 teaspoon salt||½ teaspoon pepper||½ teaspoon onion powder||1 cup flour||2 eggs||1 cup seasoned bread crumbs||2 cups marinara sauce||8 slices of fresh mozzarella||½ cup grated Parmesan||Basil, thinly sliced, to serve||n/a||','oven||stove_top||cast_iron_pan||italian||american||fusion||kid_friendly||comfort_food||dinner||bake||pan_fry||weeknight||one_top_friendly||cutting_board||chefs_knife||tongs||baking_pan||oven_mitts||spatula||high_protein'),('7f-68f29ae05920','\"Sheet Pan Gnocchi\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).\",\"1\":\"In a large bowl, combine the gnocchi, tomatoes, olive oil, salt, pepper, red pepper flakes, and rosemary and toss to coat. Spread the mixture on a rimmed baking sheet in an even layer.\",\"2\":\"Bake until the gnocchi is light golden and the tomatoes are beginning to burst, about 25 minutes. Discard the rosemary sprigs. Transfer the mixture to a serving bowl and let cool for 5 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Add the mozzarella and basil and toss to combine.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":113,\"fiber\":10,\"protein\":42,\"fat\":55,\"calories\":1112,\"sugar\":14}','\"You\\u2019re 30 minutes and one pan away from dinner with this tasty gnocchi dish. Toss store-bought gnocchi with cherry tomatoes, olive oil, and seasonings until golden brown, then stir in mini mozzarella pearls and basil before serving.\"','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/332311.jpg\"','1 16-ounce package of shelf-stable gnocchi||2 pints of cherry tomatoes||¼ cup olive oil||1 teaspoon kosher salt||½ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper||¼ teaspoon red pepper flakes||3 fresh rosemary sprigs||1 8-ounce container of mozzarella pearls||1 cup of fresh basil leaves, roughly torn||','comfort_food||oven||big_batch||italian||dinner||baking_pan||oven_mitts||mixing_bowl||healthy||weeknight||easy||wooden_spoon||bake||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||high_protein||high_fiber||under_30_minutes||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||vegetarian'),('7f-a76b480c31dc','\"Shrimp And Rice Skillet\"','{\"0\":\"On a cutting board, blot the shrimp dry with paper towels. Season the shrimp all over with ½ teaspoon of salt and the black pepper. Set aside.\",\"1\":\"Add the olive oil to a medium pot over medium-high heat. Once the oil begins to shimmer, add the shallot and cook, stirring often, until starting to soften, 1 minute. Add the garlic and red pepper flakes and cook, stirring constantly, until aromatic, about 30 seconds.\",\"2\":\"Add the rice and stir to combine. Add the wine wine and cook, stirring often, until the smell of alcohol has burned off, about 1 minute.\",\"3\":\"Add the water and the remaining teaspoon of salt and bring to a boil. Place the lid on the pot, reduce heat to low, and simmer for 15 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Remove the lid from the pot and stir in the shrimp. Place the lid on the pot and continue cooking until the rice is cooked through and the shrimp are bright pink and opaque, about 3–4 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Add the butter, lemon juice, and parsley, and stir to combine.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":20,\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":24,\"fat\":11,\"calories\":299,\"sugar\":0}','\"One skillet shrimp dinner, right this way! The shrimp is steamed in a pot of tender rice that\\u2019s been cooked with aromatic white wine, garlic, and shallot, then finished with butter, lemon, and parsley.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/332481.jpg\"','1 pound shrimp, peeled and deveined||1½ teaspoon kosher salt, divided||½ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper||1 tablespoon olive oil||1 large shallot, minced||3 garlic cloves, minced||½ teaspoon red pepper flakes||1½ cups white rice, rinsed||½ cup white wine||1¾ cups water||2 tablespoons unsalted butter||Juice of 1 lemon||½ cup parsley, finely chopped||','big_batch||one_pot_or_pan||dry_measuring_cups||measuring_spoons||seafood||stove_top||dinner||cutting_board||liquid_measuring_cup||lunch||weeknight||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||pescatarian'),('7f-e843ae400f17','\"Prime Rib With Garlic Herb Butter\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 500°F (260°C).\",\"1\":\"Mix together the butter, garlic, herbs, salt, and pepper in a bowl until evenly combined.\",\"2\":\"Rub the herb butter all over the rib roast, then place on a roasting tray with a rack.\",\"3\":\"Bake for 5 minutes per pound (10 minutes per kilo) of meat, so a 5-pound (2.2 kg) roast would bake for 25 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Turn off the heat and let the rib roast sit in the oven for 2 hours, making sure you do not open the oven door or else the residual heat will escape.\",\"5\":\"Once the 2 hours are up, remove the roast from the pan and pour the pan drippings into a saucepan over medium heat.\",\"6\":\"Add the flour, whisking until there are no lumps, then add the beef stock, stirring and bringing the sauce to a boil.\",\"7\":\"Remove from heat and strain the sauce into a gravy dish.\",\"8\":\"Carve the prime rib into ¾-inch (20 mm) slices.\",\"9\":\"Serve with the mashed potatoes, green beans, and sauce!\",\"10\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":80,\"fat\":89,\"calories\":1208,\"sugar\":3,\"carbohydrates\":18,\"fiber\":0}','','7','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/3cfe5cbbb6f248f89a39cc578138f2ee/BFV15675_PrimeRibWithGarlicHerbButter-ThumbA1080.jpg\"','1 cup butter, softened||7 cloves garlic, minced||2 tablespoons fresh rosemary, finely chopped||2 tablespoons fresh thyme, finely chopped||2 tablespoons salt||1 tablespoon pepper||5-7 pound boneless ribeye roast, trimmed||2 tablespoons flour||2 cups beef stock||Mashed potatoes, to serve||Green beans, to serve||','dinner||comfort_food||stove_top||american||casual_party||date_night||oven||bake||fall||winter||big_batch||christmas||special_occasion||oven_mitts||mixing_bowl||sauce_pan||chefs_knife||valentines_day||tasty_s_5th_birthday_recipe||tasty_s_5th_birthday_savory||live_shop_all'),('80-e8bbc412f4e1','\"Easy Stout Beer Chili\"','{\"0\":\"In a large heavy bottomed pot, brown the beef in a little bit of olive oil. Season with the salt and pepper.\",\"1\":\"Once browned, remove the beef and set aside.\",\"2\":\"In the same pot, add the chopped onions. Cook until slightly softened. Add the browned beef back to the pan. Mix to incorporate.\",\"3\":\"Add the kidney beans, crushed tomato, cumin, paprika, red pepper flakes, chili powder, water and stout beer. Give it stir. Bring to a boil. Cover and let it simmer for an hour.\",\"4\":\"Serve with shredded cheddar, sour cream and chives.\",\"5\":\"Nutrition  Calories: 4377 Fat: 226 grams  Carbs: 306 grams Fiber: 79 grams  Sugars: 55  grams  Protein: 254 grams\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":821,\"sugar\":13,\"carbohydrates\":78,\"fiber\":22,\"protein\":55,\"fat\":30}','\"This content is intended solely for users of legal drinking age. Drink responsibly.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/9d8a645144b74f97a4b2ea61b85435dc/BFV5076-Stout-Chili-Thumb.jpg\"','Drizzle of olive Oil||1 lb of ground beef||2 tsp of pepper||2 tsp of salt||1 large onion, chopped||30 oz can of kidney beans||28 oz can of crushed tomato||2 Tbsp. of cumin||1 Tbsp. of paprika||1 Tbsp. of red pepper flakes||8 Tbsp. of chili powder||1/4 cup of water||14.9 fl oz of stout beer||Shredded cheddar cheese||Sour cream||Chopped chives||','gluten_free||game_day||big_batch||one_pot_or_pan||american||winter||bake||dinner||stove_top||dry_measuring_cups||liquid_measuring_cup||wooden_spoon||mixing_bowl||measuring_spoons||weeknight||contains_alcohol||st_patrick_s_day'),('81-36dbf4570d18','\"Hack Your Dinner\"','{\"0\":\"Classic American Cheeseburger\",\"1\":\"In a medium bowl, gently mix together the ground chuck, short rib, and brisket with 2 teaspoons salt and 1 teaspoon ground pepper.\",\"2\":\"Shape the meat into 4 equal patties about 4½ inches wide and 1 inch thick. Use your thumb to press an indentation into the center of each patty to prevent a bubble from forming in the center when cooking. Generously season the tops and sides of the patties with salt and pepper.\",\"3\":\"Heat a large cast iron skillet over medium heat. Spread about ½ tablespoon of butter onto each cut side of the hamburger buns. Working in batches, toast the buns, buttered-side down, for about 2  minutes, until golden brown. Set aside.\",\"4\":\"Increase the heat to medium-high. Add a thin layer of canola oil to the pan and cook the burgers for 4 minutes on one side, until nicely browned. Flip and cook for another 2 minutes on the other side. Top each burger with a slice of cheese and cover the pan with a lid. Cook until the cheese is melted and the internal temperature of the burgers reaches 135°F (57°C), another 1–2 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Assemble the burgers: Place a burger patty on each toasted bun, then top tomato, red onion, lettuce, ketchup, mayonnaise, and mustard. Serve immediately.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\",\"7\":\"Zesty French Fries\",\"8\":\"Preheat the oven to 450°F (230°C). Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper. Place a wire rack on top of the baking sheet.\",\"9\":\"Arrange the fries in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet. Bake until golden brown, tossing halfway through, 25–30 minutes.\",\"10\":\"In a small bowl, stir together the salt, garlic powder, onion powder, smoked paprika, cumin, chili powder, black pepper, and sugar.\",\"11\":\"Add the cooked fries and the spice blend to a large paper bag. Fold the bag tightly to seal and shake until the fries are well-coated.\",\"12\":\"Serve immediately.\",\"13\":\"Enjoy!\",\"14\":\"Ice Cream In a Bag\",\"15\":\"Add the heavy cream, sugar and vanilla bean paste to a quart-sized zip-top bag. Stir with a fork or small whisk to evenly combine. Squeeze out all of the excess air from the bag and seal shut.\",\"16\":\"Add the crushed ice and rock salt to a gallon-sized zip-top bag. Gently shake to combine.\",\"17\":\"Add the cream-filled bag to the ice-filled bag and seal shut. Shake vigorously for 7–10 minutes, until the ice cream has hardened.\",\"18\":\"Carefully remove the ice cream bag from the larger bag. Serve immediately with rainbow sprinkles on top.\",\"19\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":129,\"fiber\":46,\"protein\":65,\"fat\":62,\"calories\":1314,\"sugar\":22}','\"Hack Your Dinner with these simple recipes . The secret to these burgers is using a blend of different types of ground meat to give the burgers amazing flavor, while keeping them tender. Upgrade store bought fries using a homemade spice mix. And make a creamy homemade ice cream in under 10 minutes!\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/2bef74818fec4c1289790f5a497d8dd1.jpeg\"','12 ounces ground 80/20 beef chuck||6 ounces ground beef short rib||6 ounces ground beef brisket rib||2 teaspoons kosher salt, plus more to taste||1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, plus more to taste||4 large hamburger buns||4 tablespoons (½ stick) unsalted butter, softened||4 slices of sharp cheddar cheese||1–2 tablespoons canola oil||','american||desserts||dinner||summer'),('81-5ee44abb8d2a','\"Blackened Curried Goat With Potatoes\"','{\"0\":\"Marinade the meat with the yoghurt, the aromatics, 2 tablespoons of mustard oil and the spices with the exception of black pepper, chili powder and whole spices.\",\"1\":\"In a Dutch oven, heat 2 tablespoons of ghee or 5 tablespoons of mustard oil and temper it with the whole spices. Once the spices have lightly browned and the oil is fragrant, throw in the onion. Sweat the onion on high heat till it is translucent and add in the marinated mutton. On low to medium heat, cook it for about 40 minutes or till onion is caramelized, the meat has turned dark and most of the fat from the meat is rendered. Stir often and deglaze the bottom now and again with a splash of water as this gravy tends to stick to the bottom towards the end. In between add the chili powder. At the end of 40 minutes or so, sprinkle the freshly cracked pepper powder, toss in the potatoes and mix everything up.\",\"2\":\"Pour in hot water till everything is submerged ¾  of the way. Cover the pot and cook on low heat till potatoes are cooked through. Pull out the potatoes and continue cooking till the meat is tender and falling off the bone. Add water if the gravy dries up.\",\"3\":\"When the meat is done to the right point, return the potatoes and mix everything up with a gentle hand.\",\"4\":\"Serve warm with rice or naan/roti.\"}','{\"fiber\":11,\"protein\":6,\"fat\":2,\"calories\":219,\"sugar\":4,\"carbohydrates\":49}','\"\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/bff3a742ed7848309d85a5f11e2cf12f.jpeg\"','2.5lbs of bone-in goat meat||5 medium size potatoes||1 large red onion, thinly sliced||Paste of 8 fat cloves of garlic or 2 heaping tbsp garlic paste||Paste of 1.5 inch ginger||1 tbsp hot green chili paste (optional)||4 ounces beaten yogurt||1 tsp coriander powder||½  tsp cumin powder||1 sp turmeric powder||1 tsp red chili powder||½ tsp freshly cracked black pepper powder||¼ tsp sugar||3 bay leaves||3 green cardamom pods||3 cloves garlic||2 black cardamom pods||1 inch cinnamon stick||2 dried red chilies||Salt to taste||Mustard oil or clarified butter (ghee)||','oven||dinner||special_occasion||easy||comfort_food||low_sugar||low_fat||high_fiber'),('81-6dd1fccd62ef','\"Beef Beer Goulash\"','{\"0\":\"Heat half of the butter in large pot or Dutch oven.\",\"1\":\"Add the beef, in batches, browning all sides of the meat. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and pepper. Transfer the beef to a bowl and set aside. Clean the pot.\",\"2\":\"In the same pan, heat remaining butter, then add in the onion, celery, and carrot. Cook until softened.\",\"3\":\"Add in the beer.\",\"4\":\"With a wooden spatula, scrape off the browned bits on the bottom of the pan to further flavour the stock.\",\"5\":\"Add in the seared beef, tomato purée, bay leaves, juniper berries, and 2 teaspoons each of salt and pepper.\",\"6\":\"Bring the stew to a boil, cover, and simmer for 2-4 hours, until the beef becomes tender.\",\"7\":\"Serve topped with parsley.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":13,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":81,\"fat\":20,\"calories\":625,\"sugar\":4}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/114453.jpg\"','20 grams butter||1 kilograms stewing beef||3 teaspoon salt, divided||3 teaspoon pepper, divided||1 onion, diced||1 stalk of celery, diced||1 carrot, diced||700 milliliters dark beer||2 tablespoons tomato puree||2 bay leaves||5 juniper berries||Parsley, chopped, to garnish||','cutting_board||cast_iron_pan||comfort_food||spatula||measuring_spoons||one_pot_or_pan||german||peeler||stove_top||chefs_knife||winter||oven_mitts||dinner||wooden_spoon||dutch_oven||special_occasion||low_carb||high_protein||low_sugar||keto'),('81-a12bff152f68','\"Sausage \\u0026 Veggie Quiche\"','{\"0\":\"Cook sausage over medium-high until lightly browned, about 5-7 minutes, being sure to break up the meat into a fine mince.\",\"1\":\"Remove cooked sausage from pan and wipe away excess fat with a paper towel.\",\"2\":\"Add onion and sauté until softened and translucent, about 2 to 3 minutes. Add mushrooms, salt, and pepper and continue to cook for an additional 2-3 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Add chopped spinach and cook until wilted and no extra liquid has accumulated in the bottom of the pan.\",\"4\":\"NOTE: Do your best to use the excessive moisture of the spinach and mushrooms to deglaze the bottom of the pan, scraping away any browned bits from cooking the sausage earlier.\",\"5\":\"Preheat oven to 350˚F (180˚C).\",\"6\":\"Once cooked, remove the spinach and mushroom mixture from the pan and combine it with the reserved cooked sausage. Stir to mix evenly.\",\"7\":\"Combine eggs and milk. Lightly whisk until just combined.\",\"8\":\"Add sausage and spinach mixture to the bottom of a prepared 9-inch (23cm) pie crust, making sure to spread it evenly.\",\"9\":\"Pour in beaten eggs to fill the rest of the pie crust and top with a generous sprinkle of parmesan cheese.\",\"10\":\"Bake at 350˚F (180˚C) for 25 minutes or until the eggs are set and the top is lightly browned. Allow to cool for 10 minutes before slicing and serving.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":18,\"fat\":18,\"calories\":324,\"sugar\":4,\"carbohydrates\":21}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/aad4aeb4027f4b6caed31e0bbcd31574/FB_1.jpg\"','½ pound chicken sausage||½ cup onion, chopped||½ cup mushroom, chopped||4 ounces spinach, chopped||½ teaspoon salt||½ teaspoon black pepper||6 eggs||1 cup milk||1 premade pie crust, thawed||Parmesan cheese||','oven||bake||easter||american||dinner||weeknight||healthy||easy||brunch||mixing_bowl||wooden_spoon||saute_pan||chefs_knife||dry_measuring_cups||cutting_board||cheese_grater||whisk||tongs||pie_dish||measuring_spoons||stove_top||liquid_measuring_cup'),('81-c34eb2167b5e','\"Scalloped Potato Roll\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 350˚F (180˚C).\",\"1\":\"Using a knife or mandolin cut the potatoes into slices ⅛-inch (3 mm) thick.\",\"2\":\"On a parchment paper-lined baking sheet, sprinkle half of the Parmesan cheese and spread until it is evenly covering the parchment paper.\",\"3\":\"Place the potatoes over the parmesan so each potato is overlapping the previous potato both vertically and horizontally. Continue until the entire pan is filled with potatoes.\",\"4\":\"Sprinkle to rest of the Parmesan evenly over the potatoes. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt. Bake for 30 minutes, until golden and the potatoes are flexible and slightly crispy.\",\"5\":\"In a skillet heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil over medium heat. Once the oil begins to shimmer, add the onions, and cook until caramelized, about 15 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Add the beef break up and mix with the onion until cooked. Mix in the tomatoes, 3 tablespoons of parsley, paprika, 1 teaspoon of salt, and pepper. Stir, cooking until the beef is browned and cooked through. Remove from heat.\",\"7\":\"In a skillet heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil over medium heat. Add the spinach, cook until wilted. Add 1 teaspoon of salt and the garlic. Stir to combine. Remove from heat.\",\"8\":\"In a bowl combine the spinach mixture and the ricotta. Set aside.\",\"9\":\"Evenly spread the spinach mixture over the cooked potato sheet.\",\"10\":\"Evenly spread the beef mixture over the spinach. Sprinkle mozzarella over the beef.\",\"11\":\"Take one end of the potato sheet holding the parchment paper begin rolling upward, making sure the ingredients are not coming out the ends.\",\"12\":\"Once the it is completely rolled place the potato roll on the parchment paper and bake for 15 minutes.\",\"13\":\"Sprinkle with parsley for garnish. Slice and serve immediately.\",\"14\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":26,\"calories\":464,\"sugar\":3,\"carbohydrates\":28,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":27}','','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/124532.jpg\"','6 potatoes, peeled||2 cups grated parmesan, divided||3 teaspoons salt, divided||4 tablespoons olive oil, divided||1 sweet onion, diced||1 pound ground beef||1 14½-ounce can diced tomatoes, drained||4 tablespoons parsley, chopped, divided||n/a||½ teaspoon pepper||6 cups spinach||2 cloves garlic, minced||1 cup ricotta||n/a||','oven||cutting_board||kid_friendly||stove_top||peeler||parchment_paper||mixing_bowl||chefs_knife||american||saute_pan||tongs||bake||dinner||special_occasion||wooden_spoon||pan_fry||oven_mitts||spatula||baking_pan||cheese_grater||lunch||casual_party||mccormick_easy_dinner||tasty_s_5th_birthday_recipe||tasty_s_5th_birthday_savory||high_protein||low_sugar'),('81-cb83343b7c25','\"Garlic And Herb Leg Of Lamb With Potatoes\"','{\"0\":\"2-3 hours before roasting, prepare the lamb. Use a small, sharp knife to make 15 to 20 incisions, each about 2 inches (5 cm) deep, through the fat cap on top of the meat. Thinly slice 3 cloves of garlic and use your fingers to press the slices into the incisions.\",\"1\":\"In a blender, combine the remaining 9 garlic cloves, the olive oil, mustard, lemon juice, rosemary leaves, thyme leaves, salt, and pepper. Blend until a paste forms.\",\"2\":\"Spread the paste evenly all over the lamb. Let marinate at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours.\",\"3\":\"Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).\",\"4\":\"Place the lamb on a roasting rack in a roasting pan and pour the wine into the bottom of the pan. Roast for 15 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Remove the pan from the oven and reduce the heat to 325°F (160°C).\",\"6\":\"Arrange the potatoes, cut side down, in the roasting pan and place the lamb on the rack on top. Roast for 2 hours, tossing the potatoes and basting the lamb with the roasting liquid halfway through.\",\"7\":\"Transfer the potatoes to a platter, baste the lamb again with the remaining pan juices, and return the lamb to the oven. Continue to roast, basting often, until an instant-read thermometer inserted into thickest part of the leg reaches 130°F (for medium-rare), 45 minutes to 2 hours more, depending on thickness. (As a general rule, the lamb should roast 20 minutes per pound for medium-rare).\",\"8\":\"Transfer the lamb to a platter and set aside to rest for 20 