dd the brown sugar, fish sauce, vegetable broth, and coconut milk. Bring to a boil.\",\"12\":\"Add the clams, return to a boil, and cook for 5-8 minutes, or until all of the clams are fully opened. If any clams remain closed, discard them.\",\"13\":\"Discard the lemongrass stalks and divide the clams and broth between serving bowls. Garnish with scallions and cilantro and serve with the grilled bread for dipping.\",\"14\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":66,\"calories\":1273,\"sugar\":14,\"carbohydrates\":90,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":69}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/186536.jpg\"','2 pounds littleneck clams or 1½ pounds manila clams, scrubbed||Cold water, for soaking||3-4 tablespoons sea salt||','wok||liquid_measuring_cup||healthy||measuring_spoons||colander||stove_top||tongs||date_night||wooden_spoon||dinner||special_occasion||cutting_board||chefs_knife||mixing_bowl||pyrex||seafood||thai||contains_alcohol||high_protein||pescatarian'),('8a-0c4bff74c5e0','\"One-Pot Spinach And Tomato Pasta\"','{\"0\":\"Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over high heat and cook the pasta according to the package instructions. Reserve ¾ cup (175 ml) of pasta cooking water, then drain the pasta in a colander and place the pot back on the stove over medium heat\",\"1\":\"To the pot, add the olive oil, onion, red pepper flakes, and garlic. Cook until fragrant, about 2 minutes. Add the tomatoes and reserved pasta water, and simmer until reduced by half, about 4 minutes. Season with the salt and pepper.\",\"2\":\"Add the pasta back to the pot, along with the shredded chicken and spinach, and stir to combine and wilt the spinach.\",\"3\":\"Store the leftovers in the fridge for the rest of the week.\",\"4\":\"*Vegan/Vegetarian Substitution: Omit the shredded chicken.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":15,\"protein\":29,\"fat\":14,\"calories\":350,\"sugar\":6,\"carbohydrates\":31}','','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/vi