ss, skinless, chicken thighs||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||1 tablespoon garlic, minced||1 tablespoon dried parsley||1 tablespoon butter||6 large onions, thinly sliced||1 teaspoon fresh thyme,||1 cup beef stock||2 cups shredded Gruyère cheese||Bread, sliced and toasted, to serve||','american||french||stove_top||oven||cast_iron_pan||comfort_food||one_pot_or_pan||tongs||spatula||saute_pan||dinner||bake||tasty_cookbook||fusion||pan_fry||broiler||weeknight||mixing_bowl||dry_measuring_cups||liquid_measuring_cup||measuring_spoons||wooden_spoon||casual_party||pyrex||chefs_knife||cutting_board||oven_mitts||high_protein'),('8b-dfbb04b77232','\"Pastry-Wrapped Holiday Ham\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C).\",\"1\":\"Mix the brown sugar and mustard in a small bowl.\",\"2\":\"Score the pre-cooked ham and brush the mustard mixture over the ham. Roast the ham for 20 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Wrap the ham in crescent roll dough.\",\"4\":\"Place the wrapped ham on parchment-lined baking sheet and brush with egg wash. Bake for another 20 minutes.\",\"5\":\"While the ham is baking, make the apple cider sauce. In a medium pot, bring the apple cider, cider vinegar, honey, mustard, and chili powder to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce the heat to medium-low and let the sauce thicken.\",\"6\":\"Slice the ham and serve with the apple cider sauce.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":49,\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":25,\"fat\":7,\"calories\":366,\"sugar\":45}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/54feabae0db24e2cb7bb7cf39d74d226/BFV5264_Christmas-Ham_ThumbC.jpg\"','1/4 cup of brown sugar||1/4 cup of dijon mustard||1 1/2 lb of pre-cooked, boneless ham||Pre-made crescent dough||Egg wash||','american||christmas||british||oven||fusion||comfort_food||baking_pan||parchment_paper||pyrex||mixing_bowl||sauce_pan||dry_measuring_cups||chefs_knife||cutting_board||liquid_measuring_cup||tongs||stove_top||dinner||bake||casual_party||special_occasion||easy||tasty_holiday_christmas'),('8c-5572cced00a1','\"Cheesy Egg Toast Perfect For Breakfast\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven or a toaster oven to 400°F (200°C).\",\"1\":\"With a spoon, press down on the center of the bread to form a pocket. Spread the butter around the edges of the bread, then crack the egg into the pocket.\",\"2\":\"Sprinkle the cheese around the egg, then season with salt and pepper.\",\"3\":\"Bake the toast for 10–15 minutes, depending on how runny you like the yolk.\",\"4\":\"Serve immediately.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":19,\"calories\":242,\"sugar\":0,\"carbohydrates\":3,\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":13}','','1','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/bd2e246b2883465abaad8fb68739f6db/BFV4562_CheesyEggToast-Thumb1080.jpg\"','1 slice of bread||1/2 Tbsp. butter||1 egg||3 Tbsp. shredded cheese||Salt & pepper||n/a||','oven||breakfast||american||comfort_food||kid_friendly||easy||bake||brunch||british||baking_pan||oven_mitts||walmart_meal_planning||incredible_egg_breakfasts'),('8c-a17e2c2ddcc4','\"Roasted Veggie Summer Salad\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 400˚F (200˚C).\",\"1\":\"On a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, add carrots, potatoes, yellow squash, and zucchini.\",\"2\":\"Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt, pepper, oregano, and garlic, and mix to evenly coat the coat the vegetables. *Note: You may need to quarter the potatoes if they are too thick so they roast faster.\",\"3\":\"Bake for 25-30 minutes, until the vegetables are golden brown.\",\"4\":\"Make the chimichurri dressing: combine the cilantro, parsley, garlic, salt, pepper, olive oil, lime juice, and red wine vinegar in a food processor and blend until smooth.\",\"5\":\"Add a large handful of greens to a large bowl. Top with the roasted vegetables and sliced radishes.\",\"6\":\"Pour over the chimichurri dressing and toss until evenly distributed.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":55,\"fiber\":11,\"protein\":7,\"fat\":41,\"calories\":598,\"sugar\":10}','','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/b117b68b750b495db5663b5fc300edaa/BFV44744_RoastedVeggieSummerSaladWithChimichurriDressing-Thumb.jpg\"','2 cups carrots, sliced diagonally||2 cups baby potatoes, halved*||1 cup yellow squash, roughly chopped||1 cup zucchini, roughly chopped||Olive oil, to taste||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||1 tablespoon minced fresh oregano||3 cloves garlic, chopped||½ cup sliced radishes||Mixed salad greens||','food_processor||oven||healthy||easy||dinner||bake||parchment_paper||baking_pan||oven_mitts||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||cutting_board||chefs_knife||liquid_measuring_cup||high_fiber||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian'),('8c-b840ac8535b4','\"Pumpkin-Shaped Gnocchi\"','{\"0\":\"In a large bowl, use a whisk or potato masher to mash the sweet potatoes until completely smooth. Add the egg and mix to incorporate, then mix in the shredded Parmesan and ricotta until combined. Add the flour and salt and pepper to taste. Mix with a rubber spatula until the flour is mostly incorporated, then continue mixing with your hands until fully combined. Let the dough rest for 15 minutes.\",\"1\":\"Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over medium-high heat.\",\"2\":\"On a generously floured surface, divide the dough into 24–28 portions, then roll into 2-inch balls. Press a toothpick across the top of each gnocchi ball 3 times, rotating 60° each time, to create a pumpkin shape.\",\"3\":\"Add the gnocchi to the boiling water and cook for 2–3 minutes, or until they begin to float to the surface. Remove from the pot with a slotted spoon and transfer to a plate.\",\"4\":\"Meanwhile, melt the butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Continue cooking until the butter browns and smells nutty, about 4 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Add the cooked pumpkin gnocchi and sage leaves to the browned butter and cook for 45 seconds, until the gnocchi is well-coated and the sage is crispy. Remove the pan from the heat.\",\"6\":\"Divide the pumpkin gnocchi between serving plates and insert a rosemary leaf into the top of each to resemble a pumpkin stem. Pour the browned butter over the gnocchi and garnish with the fried sage leaves and grated Parmesan cheese. Serve immediately.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":463,\"sugar\":5,\"carbohydrates\":51,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":12,\"fat\":22}','\"Wow your guest at your next fall dinner party with these stunning pumpkin-shaped gnocchi!\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/411318.jpg\"','2 large sweet potatoes, peeled and boiled until tender, then drained||1 large egg||⅓ cup shredded Parmesan cheese||½ cup ricotta cheese||2 cups all-purpose flour||Kosher salt, to taste||½ cup unsalted butter||8 fresh sage leaves||Fresh rosemary leaves||Grated Parmesan cheese, for garnish||','dinner||comfort_food||stove_top||date_night||casual_party||winter||weeknight||fall||low_sugar||under_1_hour||vegetarian'),('8c-efdfacf4f408','\"Strawberries And Cream Cake In A Jar\"','{\"0\":\"Add the angel food cake mix and yellow cake mix to a jar. Place a cupcake liner over the cake mix and add the freeze-dried strawberries. Cover with the lid.\",\"1\":\"Store in the pantry for up to 3 months.\",\"2\":\"When ready to eat, remove the lid and cupcake liner with the strawberries from the jar. Pour the water into the dry cake mix. Mix thoroughly, making sure to scrape the dry mix from the bottom of the jar.\",\"3\":\"Microwave for 20 seconds.\",\"4\":\"Pour the freeze-dried strawberries into the jar and gently stir to distribute throughout, being careful not to push all of the strawberries to the bottom.\",\"5\":\"Microwave for another 40 seconds, until cooked through.\",\"6\":\"Top with whipped cream and freeze-dried strawberries, if desired.\",\"7\":\"Serve immediately.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":2,\"fat\":0,\"calories\":161,\"sugar\":22,\"carbohydrates\":36,\"fiber\":0}','','1','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/8c5a43dadc5e4ad9827ba3db32b8ce03/BFV44252PantryPrepCakeInAJar4WaysFBFinalupdated.jpg\"','2 tablespoons angel food cake mix||2 tablespoons yellow cake mix||1 tablespoon freeze-dried strawberries, plus more for serving (optional)||2 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon water||Whipped cream, for serving (optional)||','microwave||easy||indulgent_sweets||kid_friendly||no_bake_desserts||meal_prep||american||weeknight||desserts||baking_cups||oven_mitts||measuring_spoons||epoca_walmart||low_calorie'),('8d-2d4ffb4726b0','\"Curry Shrimp \\u0026 Spaghetti\"','{\"0\":\"Dry season the shrimps by rubbing them with, curry powder, garlic powder, fish seasoning, salt, and Lawry\\u0027s seasoning salt.\",\"1\":\"Pour olive oil in a deep frying pot, place shrimps in the pot while stirring continuously. To this pot, add butter, parsley flakes, and crushed red pepper flakes.\",\"2\":\"Add bell peppers and ¾ of the prepared onion pieces to the pot and stir to combine. Cook until slightly softened.\",\"3\":\"Pour the water in the pot and add the spaghetti. Cover and let simmer until spaghetti is cooked and water has combined with spices and veggies to achieve a gravy-like consistency.\",\"4\":\"Simmer further, adding remaining onions. If the sauce is too thick, thin out with milk or cream.\",\"5\":\"Serve warm.\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":33,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":36,\"fat\":10,\"calories\":377,\"sugar\":5}','\"\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/5020f9d226a84eef8c9f760d273b312e.png\"','2 lbs shrimps, washed in water, drained, and cleaned with a little vinegar||2 boxes spaghetti||3 bell peppers, seeded and coarsely chopped||1 tsp garlic powder||1 tbsp Old Bay seasoning||1 tbsp curry powder||1 tsp fish seasoning||1 tsp Lawry\'s seasoning salt||½ tsp salt||4 tsp butter||2 tbsp olive oil||½ tsp parsley flakes||½ tsp black pepper||½ onion, coarsely chopped||1 tsp crushed red pepper flakes||4 cups water||','lunch||dinner||fusion||high_protein||low_sugar||pescatarian'),('8d-40e05d3f777f','\"Buffalo Mac \\u2018N\\u2019 Cheese\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C). Grease a 10-inch cast-iron skillet with nonstick spray.\",\"1\":\"Melt the butter in a medium saucepan over medium-high heat. Add the flour and cook, stirring frequently to break up any clumps, for 5 minutes, or until the roux is light golden brown. Reduce the heat to medium, then slowly pour in the milk and cook, whisking constantly, until thickened, about 8 minutes. Do not let the mixture come to a boil.\",\"2\":\"Remove the pot from the heat, add the mild cheddar cheese, and whisk until melted and smooth. Stir in the salt. Add the cooked macaroni to the cheese sauce and toss to coat well.\",\"3\":\"Transfer half of the mac and cheese mixture to the prepared skillet. Top with 1 cup sharp cheddar cheese, then the remaining mac and cheese and remaining cup of sharp cheddar.\",\"4\":\"In a medium bowl, mix together the shredded rotisserie chicken and Frank’s® RedHot® Buffalo Wings Sauce. Spoon on top of the mac and cheese.\",\"5\":\"Bake the mac and cheese for 30–35 minutes or until the cheese is bubbling around the edges of the pan. Remove from the oven and let cool for at least 5 minutes.\",\"6\":\"While the mac and cheese bakes, make the celery ribbons: Using a vegetable peeler, peel the backs of the celery stalks lengthwise into ribbons. Transfer the ribbons to a large bowl filled with ice water and let sit for at least 30 minutes or up to 1 hour.\",\"7\":\"Drizzle the mac and cheese with more Frank’s® RedHot® Buffalo Wings Sauce and the ranch dressing, then top with the crumbled blue cheese, red onion, scallions, and celery ribbons.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":65,\"fat\":47,\"calories\":1068,\"sugar\":7,\"carbohydrates\":92}','\"\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/280841.jpg\"','Nonstick cooking spray, for greasing||2 tablespoons unsalted butter||2 tablespoons all-purpose flour||1½ cups whole milk||2 cups shredded mild cheddar cheese||1 teaspoon kosher salt||4½ cups dried macaroni noodles, cooked for 2 minutes less than the package instructs||2 cups shredded sharp cheddar cheese||4 cups shredded rotisserie chicken||½ cup Frank’s® RedHot® Buffalo Wings Sauce, plus more for serving||','cast_iron_pan||comfort_food||oven||bake||mixing_bowl||spatula||whisk||oven_mitts||dinner||frank_s_cheesy_apps||high_protein'),('8d-5d035bf1da03','\"Cacio e Pepe (Spaghetti with Cheese and Pepper)\"','{\"0\":\"Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Cook the pasta for 1 minute less than the package instructs, until al dente. Save 1 cup (240 ml) pasta water, then drain.\",\"1\":\"Heat a large sauté pan over medium heat. Add the olive oil, butter, and pepper, and stir to combine.\",\"2\":\"Stir in the reserved pasta water.\",\"3\":\"Toss in the cooked pasta. Reduce the heat to low.\",\"4\":\"Add the Parmesan and toss until the cheese is melted and the pasta is well-coated.\",\"5\":\"Season with salt, if desired.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":436,\"sugar\":1,\"carbohydrates\":46,\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":15,\"fat\":21}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/57ae237823b4405f8910299960514033/BFV44742_PantryPasta_FB_Final.jpg\"','Salt, to taste||½ pound dry spaghetti||2 tablespoons olive oil||2 tablespoons unsalted butter||2 teaspoons coarsely ground black pepper||4 ounces grated Parmesan or Pecorino Romano cheese||','stove_top||dinner||tongs||comfort_food||italian||date_night||weeknight||wooden_spoon||strainer||sauce_pan||liquid_measuring_cup||pyrex||epoca_walmart||budget_four||low_sugar||vegetarian'),('8d-5ee4f7e4807d','\"Spinach Mac \\u0026 Cheese\"','{\"0\":\"In a blender, combine spinach and 1 cup of milk and blend to combine. Simultaneously, in a separate pot of boiling water, cook pasta according to package directions. Drain once done and reserve pasta water.\",\"1\":\"Melt butter in a saucepan and, once melted, whisk in flour to combine. Then, slowly add milk and spinach mixture, whisking to combine.\",\"2\":\"Once sauce is slightly simmering, add cheese and other spices, stirring frequently until the sauce has thickened. Add pasta water if needed.\",\"3\":\"Toss pasta in sauce and serve warm.\"}','{\"protein\":12,\"fat\":18,\"calories\":249,\"sugar\":4,\"carbohydrates\":8,\"fiber\":0}','\"\"','3','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/771ba0e0a35d4643b8cd360808495d68.jpeg\"','1 tbsp butter||1 tbsp flour||1 cup milk (plus more as needed)||4 cups fresh spinach||1 ½ cups grated cheddar||Penne or elbow pasta||1 tsp garlic powder||Salt to taste||Pepper to taste||','stove_top||blender||one_pot_or_pan||dinner||special_occasion||low_carb||low_sugar||vegetarian'),('8d-9fab68e72f83','\"Aloo Gosht (Mutton And Potato Curry)\"','{\"0\":\"Heat 1 tbsp oil in a pressure cooker. Add potatoes and fry until they turn slightly brown. Remove the potatoes and put aside on a plate. Add remaining oil and add in the whole garam masala. Once the seeds begin to crackle, add in the chopped onions and fry till they turn golden brown. Add ginger-garlic paste and fry again for about two minutes or till the raw smell goes away.\",\"1\":\"Lower heat and add remaining spice powders and dry spices. Roast until the aroma is fragrant, then add mutton and cilantro and stir fry on high heat for 2 minutes.\",\"2\":\"Pour in hot water and add salt. Lock the lid in place and cook for 5-6 whistles. Then, turn off heat and let the apparatus release pressure on its own.\",\"3\":\"Once the pressure is released, slowly open the lid and ensure that the mutton is cooked through by checking tenderness with a fork. Add more water if necessary.\",\"4\":\"Season to taste with salt and pepper and then add fried potatoes and cook on low heat until potatoes are softened but not mashed.\",\"5\":\"Serve warm alongside white rice or roti.\"}','{\"calories\":215,\"sugar\":7,\"carbohydrates\":35,\"fiber\":7,\"protein\":5,\"fat\":7}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/e1d5acf58b39484388bfce9879ce58ba.png\"','1 kg mutton(goat meat ) - washed, cleaned, and set aside||5 tbsp mustard or vegetable oil||2 onions, finely chopped||2 tbsp ginger paste||2 tbsp garlic paste||1½ tsp Kashmiri red chilli powder||2 tbsp coriander powder||1 tbsp cumin powder||Whole garam masala||1 tsp black peppercorns||1 tsp Black Cumin Seeds||5-6 green cardamom||2 sticks cinnamon||Few threads of mace||1-2 Dry Red Chillies||2 tsp Kashmiri red chilli powder||1 tsp Mutton Masala||2-3 potatoes (Peeled and cut into large chunks )||A handful of cilantro /coriander leaves||Salt to taste||Water for Gravy||','dinner||weeknight||stove_top||high_fiber||dairy_free'),('8d-fea8b774ea2d','\"Show-Stopping Beef Wellington\"','{\"0\":\"Let the beef tenderloin come to room temperature. Season with kosher salt and pepper on all sides.\",\"1\":\"Add canola oil to a large pan on high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the tenderloin. Without moving the tenderloin, cook until a dark brown crust forms, about 3 minutes per side. Repeat searing on all sides, including the tenderloin ends.\",\"2\":\"Remove the tenderloin from the pan and transfer to a cutting board or wire rack and remove ties.\",\"3\":\"Brush the mustard on all sides of the meat while it’s still warm. Let the meat rest for while making the duxelle (mushrooms cooked and reduced until dry).\",\"4\":\"To the same pan, add the butter, mushrooms, minced shallot, and minced garlic over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring occasionally, until all the liquid evaporates and the mushroom mixture becomes a thick 25-30 minutes, dry-like paste. Season with salt and pepper to taste.\",\"5\":\"Remove the mushrooms from the pan and let cool completely.\",\"6\":\"Place a large layer of overlapping sheets of plastic wrap on your work surface that is twice the length and width of the tenderloin.\",\"7\":\"Lay overlapping strips of prosciutto on the plastic into an even square layer.\",\"8\":\"Spread a layer of the mushrooms evenly over the prosciutto.\",\"9\":\"Tightly and evenly wrap the tenderloin with the prosciutto, using the plastic wrap to wrap it even tighter and seal ends. Tie the ends of the plastic wrap together to hold the Wellington’s shape. Place in the refrigerator for 15 minutes.\",\"10\":\"Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\",\"11\":\"Place a new layer of plastic wrap on the work surface and lay a sheet of puff pastry over it. Unwrap the prosciutto-wrapped beef tenderloin onto the puff pastry, wrapping until the ends meet. Cut off any extra puff pastry, making sure there is no overlap.\",\"12\":\"Wrap the puff pastry in plastic wrap, tying the ends together to form a log shape. Place in the refrigerator for 15 minutes.\",\"13\":\"Place the beef Wellington on a greased, parchment paper-lined baking sheet. Brush the surface with the beaten eggs. With a fork, score a decorative design onto the surface of the puff pastry.\",\"14\":\"Decorate with additional pastry (optional). Sprinkle with kosher salt.\",\"15\":\"Bake for 40 minutes or until the puff pastry is a dark golden brown and the internal temperature of the beef is 135°F (57°C) for medium-rare.\",\"16\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":1,\"carbohydrates\":13,\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":35,\"fat\":21,\"calories\":387}','\"The ultimate beef Wellington can seem difficult to make, but each step is actually pretty simple. After cooking the seasoned beef, brush it with mustard and store in the fridge. Then fry up some chopped mushrooms and shallots in butter before wrapping the beef in prosciutto and the mushroom mixture. All that\\u2019s left is unraveling some store-bought puff pastry and making a beautiful, woven, floral design before baking. It\\u2019s hard to cut into this masterpiece, but the taste is worth it!\"','12','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/114506.jpg\"','1 3-poumd center-cut beef tenderloin||Kosher salt, to taste||Black pepper, to taste||2 tablespoons canola oil||¼ cup English mustard||1 tablespoon butter||2 shallots, minced||2 pounds cremini mushrooms, minced||5 cloves garlic, minced||½ pound prosciutto, thinly sliced||1 sheet puff pastry||2 eggs, beaten||','stove_top||tongs||thanksgiving||christmas||cast_iron_pan||parchment_paper||comfort_food||french||special_occasion||american||tasty_cookbook||british||pyrex||dinner||spatula||baking_pan||cake_pan||bake||cooling_rack||oven||fusion||casual_party||plastic_wrap||oven_mitts||measuring_spoons||one_top_friendly||kitchen_shears||saute_pan||dry_measuring_cups||chefs_knife||cutting_board||tasty_s_5th_birthday_recipe||thanksgiving_classics||low_carb||high_protein||low_sugar'),('8e-4500b6c20dd5','\"Cajun Beef And Grits\"','{\"0\":\"Make the beef: Season the beef with 2 teaspoons of salt.\",\"1\":\"Heat the oil in an Instant Pot on “Sauté” mode. Add the beef and sear on all sides, using tongs to turn the meat, 7–9 minutes total. Remove the beef from the Instant Pot and set aside.\",\"2\":\"Add the bell pepper, onion, celery, and garlic to the Instant Pot and sauté for 5 minutes, until softened. Stir in the tomatoes, tomato paste, Frank’s RedHot® Original Cayenne Pepper Hot Sauce, McCormick Cajun Seasoning, and the remaining teaspoon of salt.\",\"3\":\"Return the beef to the Instant Pot and stir well. Put the lid on the Instant Pot, set the pressure valve to “Sealing,” and pressure-cook for 50 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Turn the pressure valve to “Venting” to release the pressure quickly. (Be sure to read all Instant Pot instructions carefully for safety.) Carefully remove the lid.\",\"5\":\"Remove the beef mixture from the Instant Pot and set aside. Clean the Instant Pot insert.\",\"6\":\"Make the grits: Generously coat the Instant Pot insert with nonstick spray. Add the butter and melt on “Sauté” mode. Add the grits and cook, stirring frequently, for 2 minutes, until fragrant. Whisk in the milk, water, and salt. Bring mixture to a simmer, then whisk well.\",\"7\":\"Put the lid on the Instant Pot, set the pressure valve to “Sealing,” and pressure-cook for 10 minutes.\",\"8\":\"Let pressure naturally release for 15 minutes, then turn the pressure valve to “Venting” to release the rest of the pressure. Carefully remove the lid.\",\"9\":\"Carefully hold the Instant Pot with an oven mitt and use a silicone spatula or wooden spoon to move the grits around and release from the bottom of the pot, then whisk well to incorporate.\",\"10\":\"Stir in the cheddar cheese. Let cheese melt for 1 minute, then stir again. (If the grits get too thick before serving, stir in a bit of milk to loosen.)\",\"11\":\"To serve, spoon the grits into shallow bowls. Scoop the beef mixture on top. Drizzle with Frank’s RedHot® and garnish with the scallions.\",\"12\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":33,\"calories\":572,\"sugar\":13,\"carbohydrates\":24,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":42}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/309113.jpg\"','1½ pounds boneless beef chuck roast, cut into 1-inch cubes||3 teaspoons kosher salt, divided||2 teaspoons neutral oil, such as canola||1 large or 2 small red bell peppers, seeded and diced||½ yellow onion, diced||2 celery stalks, diced||3 garlic cloves, roughly chopped||1 cup canned diced tomatoes, drained||2 tablespoons tomato paste||2 tablespoons Frank’s RedHot® Original Cayenne Pepper Hot Sauce, plus more for drizzling||1 tablespoon McCormick Cajun Seasoning||','mccormick_seasoned_pro||instant_pot||spatula||tongs||dinner||special_occasion||fusion||high_protein'),('8e-73cef25b70f3','\"Devil\\u0027s Curry\"','{\"0\":\"Blend the dried chilli, red onions, garlic, candlenuts, lemongrass, blue ginger, and mustard seeds with some oil to form a paste. Then, in a separate bowl, dry rub the pork with 5-spice powder and salt.\",\"1\":\"In a large frying pan on high heat, add 1 tbsp of oil. Once heated, sear the pork and cook halfway, then remove, learning the grease in the pan. Then, reduce heat to medium and toss in 2 tbsp whole mustard seeds. Toast for a minute, then gently add in spice paste from step and stiry fry for 15 minutes until oil appears around the sides.\",\"2\":\"Add chicken to the pan, coat thoroughly for a minute, then add the pre-fried pork belly and mix well. Then, add water, submerging the meat completely.\",\"3\":\"Add chilli powder, stir, and bring mixture to a boil, simmering for 15 minutes. Then, add potatoes, stir, and simmer for an additional 30 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Next, add 3 tsp salt, 10 tbsp white vinegar, stir and taste.\",\"5\":\"Season as desired, simmer for an additional 5 minutes, and serve alongside rice or sliced baguette bread.\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":128,\"fiber\":43,\"protein\":85,\"fat\":63,\"calories\":1367,\"sugar\":61}','\"\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/4e85cf49e4ce464d94eed3cb2ca03a7b.jpeg\"','4 lbs chicken thighs, chopped into single-serving pieces||1 ½ lbs pork belly, sliced ¾-inch thick||4 large potatoes, cut in eighths||1 head of cabbage, quartered & cut 2 inches||Chilli Powder||White Vinegar||1 tbsp 5-Spice Powder||3 tbsp Salt||Sugar||Water||50 Stalks of Dried Chilli||4 large red onions||5 bulbs of garlic||8 candlenuts||3 stalks of lemongrass||2-Inch cube blue ginger||2 tsp mustard seeds||Oil||','blender||stove_top||easy||dinner||special_occasion||high_protein||high_fiber||dairy_free'),('8e-928a5566d77a','\"Slow Cooker Shredded Chicken Sliders\"','{\"0\":\"Add all ingredients to a slow cooker and stir until chicken and onions are coated with seasonings.\",\"1\":\"Cook on high for 3-4 hours, or until chicken is cooked and shreddable.\",\"2\":\"With a set of tongs or two forks, shred the chicken and stir into the juices.\",\"3\":\"Distribute evenly between slider buns.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":18,\"fat\":3,\"calories\":246,\"sugar\":15,\"carbohydrates\":35,\"fiber\":1}','','10','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/c59b728acd3a46449beb6fb806220dd9/BFV23223_S