"\"','10','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/276051.jpg\"','1 pound bacon, cut into half-inch pieces||2 tablespoons water||½ white onion, diced small||1 tablespoon fresh thyme, chopped||1 cup whole milk||1 8-ounce can cream of chicken soup||1 8-ounce can cream of mushroom soup||2 teaspoons kosher salt||3 cups grated Colby-Jack cheese, divided||½ cup grated Parmesan cheese, divided||1 pound deli-sliced Charter Reserve® Goldenroast Special Recipe Turkey Breast, cut into ½ inch pieces||1 14-ounce bag frozen broccoli||1 pound penne, cooked for 2 minutes less than package instructions||½ cup panko bread crumbs||2 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted||2 tablespoons parsley, chopped||','italian||fusion||oven||stove_top||mixing_bowl||wooden_spoon||baking_pan||oven_mitts||whisk||dinner||special_occasion||weeknight||sponsored_recipe||high_protein||low_sugar'),('8f-0ea6652f7be2','\"Easy Chicken Fajita Rice And Veggie Bake\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).\",\"1\":\"In a medium bowl, combine spices to make fajita seasoning, or use store-bought.\",\"2\":\"In a large bowl, combine, onion, peppers, and chicken.\",\"3\":\"Add oil and seasoning, and mix until seasoning is fully incorporated.\",\"4\":\"In a casserole dish, add rice and chicken broth. Then lay down all veggies and chicken.\",\"5\":\"Cover the dish with foil and bake for 50-55 minutes until rice is fully cooked.\",\"6\":\"Serve with tomatoes, cilantro, and cheese, if desired.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":53,\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":27,\"fat\":26,\"calories\":573,\"sugar\":5}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/703dec1886cc4e0f85cfbf9e963d653a/FBC.jpg\"','1 tablespoon chili powder||1 teaspoon cumin||1 teaspoon paprika||¼ teaspoon cayenne pepper||½ teaspoon garlic powder||1 teaspoon salt||1 teaspoon black pepper||½ onion, sliced||1 red bell pepper, sliced||1 green bell pepper, sliced||2 tablespoon olive oil||1 cup rice, long grain||2 cups chicken broth||1½ pounds chicken tenders||','fusion||mexican||big_batch||comfort_food||casual_party||american||oven||gluten_free||dinner||kid_friendly||pyrex||mixing_bowl||measuring_spoons||chefs_knife||cutting_board||tongs||dry_measuring_cups||baking_pan||liquid_measuring_cup||oven_mitts'),('8f-16d256a395d3','\"Tteokbokki (Spicy Korean Rice Cakes)\"','{\"0\":\"Make the rice cakes (alternatively, if using store-bought, jump to step 5): In a medium, microwave-safe bowl, combine the rice flour, salt, and boiling water and mix until well-combined. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap, leaving an opening for steam to escape.\",\"1\":\"Microwave the dough for 2 minutes. Knead the dough with a spatula, cover again with the plastic wrap, and microwave for another 2 minutes.\",\"2\":\"Grease a flat surface with sesame oil. Pound and knead the dough with a pestle until the dough is smooth and stretchy, about 5 minutes (if you don’t have a pestle, you can use another heavy object covered in oiled plastic wrap).\",\"3\":\"Divide the dough into 8 equal portions. Coat the dough in sesame oil, then cover with plastic wrap to prevent them from drying out. Working one at a time, roll each portion into a log, then cut into bite-size pieces and shape each piece as desired. The most common shape for tteokbokki are cylinders, or you can make fun shapes like hearts. Coat the rice cakes in more sesame oil and spread them out so they don’t touch and stick together, then repeat with the remaining dough. You should have about 1 pound. If not using immediately, the rice cakes can be stored in a zip-top freezer bag or wrapped tightly in plastic wrap and frozen for up to three months.\",\"4\":\"Make the tteokbokki: If using frozen rice cakes, soak in room temperature water for 20 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Add the water to a medium skillet and bring to a boil over medium heat. Add the dashi powder and stir until completely dissolved, 1–2 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Add the gochugaru, sugar, gochujang, fish cakes, and rice cakes to the broth. Stir until the gochujang and gochugaru are well-incorporated, then simmer until the broth has reduced to a thick sauce and the rice cakes are soft and squishy, about 5 minutes. During the last 2 minutes of cooking, add the hard-boiled eggs, mozzarella, if using, and green onions. Cover the pan and cook until the cheese is melted.\",\"7\":\"Remove the pan from the heat and serve warm.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":6,\"carbohydrates\":129,\"fiber\":16,\"protein\":20,\"fat\":17,\"calories\":773}','\"Tteokbokki is an iconic Korean street food staple. It\\u2019s chewy, spicy, and savory and makes a quick weekday meal or snack. You can always adjust the gochugaru and gochujang amounts to meet your spice preference. Get creative by adding vegetables, meat, or whatever you\\u2019re craving!\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/426433.jpg\"','4 cups sweet rice flour||1 teaspoon kosher salt||1½ cups boiling water||Sesame oil, for greasing||','gluten_free||lunch||easy||measuring_spoons||stove_top||dinner||mixing_bowl||valentines_day||dry_measuring_cups||comfort_food||spatula||saute_pan||korean||under_30_minutes||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||pescatarian||casual_party||date_night'),('8f-27ab6dc6cbc3','\"Thanksgiving Monte Cristo\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 250°F (120°C).\",\"1\":\"In a medium bowl, toss together the turkey and gravy until well combined.\",\"2\":\"Spread 1 tablespoon of cranberry sauce over each of 4 slices of brioche. Spread 1 tablespoon of whole-grain mustard over each of the remaining slices of brioche. Place a slice of cheese on top of each piece of bread.\",\"3\":\"Divide the turkey between 4 slices of bread, pressing down into a flat, even layer. Distribute the stuffing atop the turkey, spreading into a flat even layer. Place the other slices of bread, cheese-side down, over the stuffing and press down to adhere.\",\"4\":\"In a 2-inch-deep, square baking dish, whisk together the eggs, milk, and salt until well combined.\",\"5\":\"Melt 1 tablespoon of butter in a small skillet over medium heat.\",\"6\":\"Dip a sandwich in the egg mixture and press down to coat. Flip the sandwich to coat the other side. Lift the sandwich from the egg mixture, letting the excess drip off, then transfer the sandwich to the pan and cook until the bottom is golden and crispy, about 3 minutes. Flip and continue cooking until the other side is golden and crispy, 3 minutes more. Transfer the sandwich to a baking sheet and place in the oven to warm through while you repeat with the remaining sandwiches, adding more butter to the pan between each.\",\"7\":\"Serve immediately.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":41,\"fat\":19,\"calories\":524,\"sugar\":11,\"carbohydrates\":43}','\"Upgrade your Thanksgiving leftovers with this sweet and savory Monte Cristo! Tender turkey meets sweet and tangy cranberry sauce, stuffing, and melty Swiss cheese, all sandwiched between slices of French toast!\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/350929.jpg\"','10 ounces roasted turkey, shredded||1 cup gravy||8 slices of brioche bread||¼ cup cranberry sauce||¼ cup whole-grain mustard||8 slices of Swiss or Gouda cheese||1 cup stuffing||6 large eggs||⅔ cup milk||1½ teaspoons kosher salt||4 tablespoons (½ stick) unsalted butter, divided||','oven||mixing_bowl||offset_spatula||tupperware||pyrex||baking_pan||weeknight||dinner||high_protein||under_30_minutes||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour'),('8f-6ad83f8224e8','\"Sweet \\u0026 Sour Pork\"','{\"0\":\"Cube the pork and place in a medium bowl.\",\"1\":\"Add the garlic, pepper, green onions, and ¼ cup soy sauce. Toss to coat the pork. Cover with plastic wrap and marinate in the refrigerator for 1-2 hours.\",\"2\":\"Heat about 2 inches of vegetable oil in a large pan over medium heat until it reaches 350˚F (180˚C).\",\"3\":\"Add the eggs and cornstarch to 2 separate small bowls. Coat the pork in the egg, then in the cornstarch. fry until crispy and golden (about 2 minutes).\",\"4\":\"Fry the pork in the hot oil until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.\",\"5\":\"Heat the remaining 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil in a clean large pan over medium-high heat. Add the onion and bell peppers and sauté until tender.\",\"6\":\"Once the vegetables are tender, add the pineapple and syrup. Stir for 30 seconds, then add the vinegar, remaining ¼ cup soy sauce, sugar, and ketchup. Stir constantly for 3-4 minutes, until the liquid evaporates and the sauce thickens.\",\"7\":\"Add the pork to the pan and toss to coat evenly.\",\"8\":\"Serve the pork over rice and garnish with green onions, if desired.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":41,\"fat\":39,\"calories\":674,\"sugar\":14,\"carbohydrates\":36}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/1831c6afb2314c78bdfab43835f1643b/FB_1.jpg\"','2 pound pork shoulder or butt||2 cloves garlic, minced||1 teaspoon black pepper||¼ cup green onion||¼ cup soy sauce||1 tablespoon vegetable oil||3 eggs, beaten||1½  cups cornstarch||1 white onion, cut into wedges||1 red bell pepper||1 green bell pepper||1 8-ounce can chopped pineapple with syrup||¼  cup vinegar||¼ cup sugar||¼ cup ketchup||White rice||','casual_party||kid_friendly||stove_top||chinese||comfort_food||pan_fry||weeknight||dinner||measuring_spoons||liquid_measuring_cup||dry_measuring_cups||pyrex||mixing_bowl||chefs_knife||cutting_board||tongs||spatula||cooling_rack||paper_napkins'),('8f-73c3961431d7','\"Poached Salmon\"','{\"0\":\"Fill a pan with enough water to submerge a fillet. Bring the water to a simmer.\",\"1\":\"Add salt, peppercorns, sliced lemon, and thyme to water.\",\"2\":\"Add salmon, cover the pan, and cook for 20 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Remove salmon from pan, and season with salt, pepper, and fresh lemon.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":11,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":34,\"fat\":22,\"calories\":385,\"sugar\":3}','','1','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/3815cefcf1ca4a338edc124504a20682/BFV17423_4_Ways_To_Cook_Salmon_FB1080SQ.jpg\"','6 ounces skinless salmon fillet||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||Peppercorns, to taste||1 lemon, sliced||Fresh thyme||','stove_top||seafood||healthy||easy||dinner||weeknight||cutting_board||chefs_knife||saute_pan||tongs||spatula||one_pot_or_pan||low_carb||high_protein||low_sugar||dairy_free||pescatarian'),('8f-7afe22675b76','\"Roasted Veggie Skewers\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat grill to medium heat.\",\"1\":\"Combine the oil, lemon juice, oregano, salt, and pepper, stirring until mixed.\",\"2\":\"Slide a zucchini slice down the skewer, followed by pieces of mushroom, red onion, and peppers, until there is a 1-inch gap at the top of the skewer. Brush each skewer liberally with the oil mixture.\",\"3\":\"Repeat with the remaining skewers and vegetables.\",\"4\":\"Grill the skewers for 12-18 minutes with the lid closed, flipping halfway.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":11,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":2,\"fat\":7,\"calories\":106,\"sugar\":5}','','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/240ec2f8edc64e80871f56242addce52/BFV10195_Skewers4Ways.jpg\"','¼ cup olive oil||2 tablespoons lemon juice||1 tablespoon dried oregano||1 teaspoon salt||1 teaspoon pepper||2 zucchinis, sliced into rounds||3 cups cremini mushrooms||2 medium red onions, cut into 1-inch pieces||2 red bell peppers, cut into 1-inch pieces||2 yellow bell peppers, cut into 1-inch pieces||','american||easy||dinner||lunch||grill||weeknight||bbq||summer||spring||gluten_free||healthy||fourth_sides||low_carb||low_calorie||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian'),('8f-9d4422156510','\"Jerk Chicken And Pineapple Skewers\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 375ºF (190ºC). Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.\",\"1\":\"In a food processor, combine the scallions, habanero peppers, garlic, ginger, brown sugar, soy sauce, allspice, cinnamon, and thyme. Puree until broken down into a into a thick paste, about 1 minute.\",\"2\":\"In a medium bowl, toss the chicken with 2-4 tablespoons of the jerk paste until well coated. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.\",\"3\":\"Meanwhile, make the jerk sauce: Combine 2-4 tablespoons of the jerk paste with the pineapple juice and ketchup. Season to taste with salt.\",\"4\":\"Thread the skewers with 2 pieces each of the marinated chicken, red onion, bell pepper, and pineapple, alternating ingredients.\",\"5\":\"Arrange the skewers on the prepared baking sheets. Season with salt. Brush about ⅓ cup (85 G) of the jerk sauce over the skewers. Reserve the remaining sauce.\",\"6\":\"Roast the skewers for 22-25 minutes, turning halfway, until the chicken is cooked to an internal temperature of 165ºF (75ºC).\",\"7\":\"Remove the baking sheets from the oven and discard the parchment paper, then return the skewers to the pans. Turn the broiler to high.\",\"8\":\"Baste the skewers on all sides with the jerk sauce.\",\"9\":\"Broil for 3-4 minutes, until the vegetables just begin to char and the sauce is slightly caramelized.\",\"10\":\"Transfer the skewers to a platter. Squeeze the lime wedges over the hot skewers and garnish with the cilantro.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":38,\"fat\":4,\"calories\":387,\"sugar\":34,\"carbohydrates\":49}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/216806.jpg\"','2 cups scallions, cut into 2-inch pieces (about 7 scallions)||3-4 habanero peppers, seeded||8 cloves garlic||1 1-inch piece of fresh ginger, peeled and thinly sliced||⅓ cup dark brown sugar, tightly packed||2 tablespoons soy sauce||1 tablespoon ground allspice||1 teaspoon cinnamon||1 tablespoon dried thyme||1½ pounds boneless, skinless chicken breasts (about 2 large breasts), cut into 1½-inch pieces||8 ounces pineapple juice||¼ cup plus 2 tablespoons ketchup||Kosher salt, to taste||1 large red onion, cut into 1½-inch pieces||2 red bell peppers, cut into 1½-inch pieces||2 cups pineapple, cut into 1½