ddar cheese||Chives, for garnish||','kid_friendly||easy||american||oven||weeknight||comfort_food||dinner||big_batch||mashup||bake||oven_mitts||cheese_grater||chefs_knife||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||baking_pan||cutting_board||pyrex'),('94-970142f3a9fe','\"Weeknight Chicken Curry\"','{\"0\":\"Mix McCormick curry powder with 2 teaspoons of olive oil in a bowl. Stir this with chicken, coating evenly. Refrigerate for 24-48 hours to marinate.\",\"1\":\"In a large frying pan, saute chicken until cooked through (~7-10 minutes). Drain to remove excess liquid.\",\"2\":\"Add 2 tsp olive oil to a pan and on medium heat, saute onion and peppers until soft.\",\"3\":\"Add tikka masala sauce and cream. Stir well. Then, add cooked chicken, stir, and let simmer 5 minutes to combine flavors.\",\"4\":\"Spoon over warm rice and serve.\"}','{\"protein\":31,\"fat\":13,\"calories\":534,\"sugar\":6,\"carbohydrates\":69,\"fiber\":3}','\"\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/d4d05f05f4194c5f9889b21e6d3cc2af.png\"','3 medium-sized chicken breasts, cut into bite-sized pieces||2 tsp McCormick curry powder||4 tsp olive oil||1 small onion, diced||1 cup mixed bell peppers, diced||1 jar tikka masala sauce||½ cup cream or half and half||6 cups cooked rice||','indian||fusion||easy||weeknight||dinner||high_protein||dairy_free'),('94-c96621ee64ab','\"Squid Ink Fettuccine With Black Mussels\"','{\"0\":\"Make the pasta: In a large bowl, whisk together the flour and salt, then turn out onto a clean surface and make a large well in the center.\",\"1\":\"Add the eggs, egg yolks, olive oil, and squid ink to the well and mix with a fork until combined, slowly incorporating more and more flour into the mixture by moving the fork along the edges of the well. Once almost all of the flour is incorporated, start bringing the dough together with your hands. (The dough should be malleable, but not sticky--add more flour if the dough is sticking too much to your hands or the surface. Alternatively, if it’s too dry and tough, whisk another egg with 1 tablespoon of water and use your hand to sprinkle a bit of the mixture over the dough, continuing to do so until the dough is easier to knead.)\",\"2\":\"Knead the dough for 7–10 minutes, until smooth and elastic. When you poke the dough, it should spring back. Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and let rest at room temperature for 30–60 minutes, or until it does not spring back when poked.\",\"3\":\"On a lightly floured surface, divide into 4 equal portions. Using a pasta roller, laminate and roll out 1 portion of the dough to setting #6. Repeat with the remaining dough.\",\"4\":\"Dust the dough sheets with flour and fold each sheet onto itself 4–5 times. With a sharp knife, cut a dough sheet into ¼-inch (6 mm) strips. Unravel and place onto a floured baking sheet. Repeat with the remaining dough sheets.\",\"5\":\"Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Cook the pasta in the boiling water until al dente, about 4 minutes. Reserve ¼ cup (60 ml) of the cooking water, then drain the pasta and set aside.\",\"6\":\"Cook the mussels: Melt the olive oil and butter together in a large pot over medium-high heat. Add the garlic, shallot and salt and cook until the garlic is fragrant and the shallot is translucent, about 5 minutes. Add the wine and olives and cook until the wine is reduced by half, about 5 minutes more. Add the mussels, cover the pot with a lid, and cook until the mussels have opened fully, about 6–8 minutes. Discard any mussels that do not open. Remove the pot from the heat.\",\"7\":\"Add the cooked pasta to the pot with the mussels and stir until the pasta is coated in the wine reduction. Add the reserved pasta water a bit at a time until a silky sauce is created.\",\"8\":\"Divide the pasta and mussels between 4 plates, garnish with the parsley, and serve warm.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":17,\"protein\":37,\"fat\":32,\"calories\":738,\"sugar\":1,\"carbohydrates\":67}','\"Take dinner time deep down under the sea with these ink-hued dishes. Start with crispy fried calamari dredged in an activated charcoal batter and served with a garlicky squid ink aioli. Then for the main course, it\\u2019s homemade squid ink fettuccine in a white wine sauce with plenty of mussels. Finish with a no-bake activated charcoal cheesecake studded with black sesame seeds.  The food may be dark, but the flavors are anything but!\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/258063.jpg\"','2 cups all-purpose flour, plus more for dusting||Pinch of kosher salt, plus more for boiling||2 large eggs||6 large egg yolks||1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil||2 teaspoons squid ink||','mixing_bowl||tongs||colander||seafood||dinner||special_occasion||pan_fry||high_protein||low_sugar||pescatarian'),('95-642243eb9c59','\"One Pan Dinner\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\",\"1\":\"Make the jalapeño poppers: Halve the jalapeños lengthwise and use a spoon to scrape out the seeds and ribs. Fill each jalapeño half with 1 tablespoon of cream cheese. Wrap a halved bacon strip around each stuffed jalapeño half.\",\"2\":\"To make a tray for the jalapeño poppers, take a piece of aluminum foil and fold in 2 inches of each short side. Dog-ear the corners and fold up to lift the remaining sides. The tray should fill ¼ of the baking sheet. Arrange the jalapeño poppers in the tray.\",\"3\":\"Make the pizza: Grease the empty half of the baking sheet with nonstick spray.\",\"4\":\"Unroll the pizza dough and place on the greased half of the pan. Spread the sauce evenly across the dough, then sprinkle with the cheese and top with the pepperoni and sliced jalapeño.\",\"5\":\"Make the s’mores pie: Unfold the thawed puff pastry on a lightly floured surface. Gently roll out to remove any creases. Cut out a 6x8-inch rectangle, reserving the excess pastry for another use. Using a sharp knife, gently score a ½-inch border all the way around the pastry rectangle, being careful to not cut all the way through. Prick holes in the center of the pastry with a fork. Transfer the pastry to the remaining quarter of the baking sheet.\",\"6\":\"Spread the chocolate-hazelnut spread evenly over the inner rectangle of the pastry, then top with half of the marshmallows and graham crackers.\",\"7\":\"In a small bowl, whisk together the egg and water. Brush the egg wash over the pastry border.\",\"8\":\"Transfer the pan to the oven and bake for 20–25 minutes, until the pizza dough is cooked through and bacon is crispy.\",\"9\":\"Remove the pan from the oven. Garnish the pizza with the basil leaves. Top the s’mores pie with the remaining marshmallows and graham crackers, then drizzle with the melted chocolate.\",\"10\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":32,\"carbohydrates\":128,\"fiber\":5,\"protein\":27,\"fat\":55,\"calories\":1114}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/266069.jpg\"','3 jalapeños||6 tablespoons whipped cream cheese, softened||3 slices of bacon, halved||','oven_mitts||rolling_pin||baking_pan||dinner||measuring_spoons||oven||comfort_food||one_pot_or_pan||chefs_knife||weeknight||bake||date_night||high_protein||high_fiber'),('96-1dc1068d3750','\"One-Pan Chicken And Broccoli Stir Fry\"','{\"0\":\"Make the stir-fry sauce: In a small bowl, mix together the soy sauce, honey, garlic, ginger, and sesame seeds.\",\"1\":\"Make the stir fry: Heat the canola oil oil in a large nonstick pan over medium-high heat. Season with the salt and pepper, then stir until the chicken is browned, about 5 minutes.\",\"2\":\"Pour the sauce into pan and stir to coat the chicken, then bring the sauce to a boil. Once the sauce is bubbling, add the broccoli and red bell pepper to the pan and toss to coat in the sauce. Cook until the chicken is cooked through and the vegetables are tender, 5-8 minutes more.\",\"3\":\"Serve over rice, if desired.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":10,\"calories\":606,\"sugar\":44,\"carbohydrates\":50,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":75}','','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/c6630a4d04074d11ab60bfa0cb4b03d1/BFV16130_Stir-Fry_4_Ways_FB.jpg\"','½ cup soy sauce||¼ cup honey||2 cloves garlic||1 teaspoon ginger||1 tablespoon sesame seeds||','chinese||dinner||pan_fry||date_night||weeknight||stove_top||easy||one_pot_or_pan||cooking_kit||saute_pan||pyrex||chefs_knife||cutting_board||measuring_spoons||wooden_spoon||mixing_bowl||liquid_measuring_cup||spatula||dry_measuring_cups||high_protein||high_fiber||dairy_free'),('96-3a557b0e4bce','\"Cheese Maker\\u2019s Mac And Cheese\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 350˚F (180˚C).\",\"1\":\"In a large pan, melt 4 tablespoons of butter over medium heat. Whisk in the flour, reducing heat to medium-low, cooking for 1 minute.\",\"2\":\"Gradually whisk in the milk and water. Add the macaroni and cook over medium-high heat until boiling. Stir frequently for 8 to 10 minutes, until the pasta is al dente.\",\"3\":\"Remove the pan from the heat and add the cream cheese, cheddar cheese, fontina, Gouda, and cayenne, and season with salt and pepper. Stir until fully combined.\",\"4\":\"Transfer the mixture to a grease baking dish.\",\"5\":\"In a medium skillet, melt the remaining 3 tablespoons of butter over medium-low heat. Add the garlic and cook for 30 seconds, stirring frequently.\",\"6\":\"Add the crushed crackers and stir to combine. Toast the crumbs until browned, stirring for 3 to 5 minutes. Remove the pan from the heat.\",\"7\":\"Sprinkle the toasted crumbs over the macaroni and cheese, and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.\",\"8\":\"Remove from the oven and rest for 5 minutes.\",\"9\":\"Serve with fresh basil\",\"10\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":53,\"calories\":957,\"sugar\":10,\"carbohydrates\":80,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":37}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/128093.jpg\"','7 tablespoons unsalted butter||¼ cup flour||3 cups milk||2 cups water||1 pound elbow macaroni||4 ounces cream cheese, cubed||1¼ cups shredded sharp white cheddar cheese||1¼ cups shredded fontina cheese||1 cup shredded Havarti cheese||1 cup shredded smoked Gouda cheese||¼ teaspoon cayenne||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||1 clove garlic, minced||1½ cups crushed Ritz Crackers||Fresh basil leaves, to serve||','licensed_video||thanksgiving||one_pot_or_pan||dinner||american||easy||mixing_bowl||wooden_spoon||whisk||sauce_pan||christmas||bake||stove_top||big_batch||dry_measuring_cups||measuring_spoons||weeknight||oven_mitts||high_protein||vegetarian'),('96-a81e3cc28fb3','\"Chicken Teriyaki Chow Mein\"','{\"0\":\"In a medium bowl, season the cubed chicken with salt and pepper. Add ¼ cup (of 60 ml) teriyaki sauce and mix until the chicken is well-coated. Cover with plastic wrap and marinate in the refrigerator for 30 minutes to 1 hour.\",\"1\":\"In a wok or deep skillet over medium-high heat, heat 2 tablespoons of cooking oil, then add the par-cooked noodles. Cook for 1-2 minutes, allowing the noodles to crisp, then flip and cook for another 1-2 minutes. Transfer to a plate and set aside.\",\"2\":\"In the same wok, heat 1 tablespoon of cooking oil, then add the chicken. Cook for 3-4 minutes, until browned on one side, then stir and cook for another 3-4 minutes, until fully cooked through. Set the chicken aside.\",\"3\":\"In the same wok, add 1 tablespoon of oil, the onion, and carrot. Cook for 2-3 minutes, or until the onions are translucent. Add the broccoli and cabbage. Stir and cook for 1-2 minutes, then season with salt and pepper and cook for 3 minutes more, until the vegetables are soft.\",\"4\":\"Add the cooked chicken and crispy noodles back to the wok, along with the remaining ¼ cup (60 ml) teriyaki sauce. Toss well and cook for 2-3 minutes, until everything is well-combined. Garnish with sesame seeds.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":346,\"sugar\":5,\"carbohydrates\":29,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":29,\"fat\":12}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/d7f0a66959f544f5b885f3bd993f072f/BFV43733_ChowMein4Ways_FB1080SQ.jpg\"','1 pound cubed chicken breast||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||½ cup teriyaki sauce, divided||4 tablespoons cooking oil, divided||1 6-ounce package Hong Kong-Style Pan-Fried (Chow Mein) Noodles, par cooked according to package instructions||¾ cup sliced onion||½ cup julienned carrots||1 cup broccoli florets||1 cup sliced green cabbage||Sesame seeds, for garnish||','chinese||wok||dinner||weeknight||date_night||spatula||pan_fry||tongs||mixing_bowl||stove_top||one_pot_or_pan||cutting_board||chefs_knife||measuring_spoons||liquid_measuring_cup||dry_measuring_cups||pyrex||epoca_walmart||high_protein||dairy_free'),('96-a9271ff90684','\"Cast Iron Paella\"','{\"0\":\"Add the chicken stock to a microwave-safe liquid measuring cup and microwave on high power for 3 minutes, until hot. Stir in the saffron threads and set aside.\",\"1\":\"On a cutting board, pat the shrimp dry with paper towels. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and the pepper on both sides and set aside.\",\"2\":\"Heat the olive oil in a 12-inch (30 cm) cast-iron skillet over medium-high heat until it begins to shimmer. Add the chorizo and cook, stirring, until browned in spots, 3 minutes. Add the onion and cook until softened, about 3 minutes. Add the garlic and paprika and cook, stirring, until aromatic, about 30 seconds. Add the rice and stir until lightly toasted, 1 minute.\",\"3\":\"Add the tomatoes and reserved chicken stock and stir to combine. Reduce the heat to low and cover the pan with a lid. Cook without stirring until the rice is al dente, 15 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Remove the lid and arrange the shrimp, mussels, and peas on top of the rice. Cover and increase the heat to medium-high. Cook until the shrimp are opaque and the mussels are open, 5 minutes. Discard any mussels that do not open.\",\"5\":\"Remove the lid and pour the lemon juice over the paella. Sprinkle with the remaining teaspoon of salt and the parsley and serve.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":607,\"sugar\":10,\"carbohydrates\":57,\"fiber\":29,\"protein\":38,\"fat\":27}','\"This simplified version of the popular Spanish rice and seafood dish will leave you scraping your bowl clean. Because of cast iron\\u2019s high heat retention, a delicious crusty layer of rice will develop on the bottom, and serving the dish straight from the pan makes for a beautiful centerpiece at the dinner table. You and your guests won\\u2019t be able to resist scooping for seconds.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/215478.jpg\"','3 cups chicken stock||Pinch of saffron threads||½ pound shrimp (16 to 20 count), peeled and deveined||2 teaspoons kosher salt, divided||½ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper||2 tablespoons olive oil||1½ cups hard chorizo, thinly sliced (6 ounces)||1 medium yellow onion, finely chopped (about 1 cup)||3 cloves garlic, minced||1 teaspoon paprika||1½ cups Arborio rice||1 14.5-ounce can of diced tomatoes, drained||½ pound mussels, scrubbed and debearded||½ cup frozen peas, thawed||Juice of ½ lemon||¼ cup fresh parsley leaves, finely chopped||','stove_top||dry_measuring_cups||wooden_spoon||cast_iron_pan||spatula||microplane||seafood||liquid_measuring_cup||tongs||cutting_board||chefs_knife||dinner||measuring_spoons||one_pot_or_pan||oven_mitts||pyrex||pan_fry||date_night||special_occasion||high_protein||high_fiber||dairy_free'),('97-e9917cd6b7ae','\"Cinnamon Toast Crunch Baked Oats\"','{\"0\":\"Add your oats, apple sauce, egg, baking powder, cinnamon, vanilla extract, 3 tbsp of cinnamon toast crunch and your almond milk to a blender and blend until smooth. Set aside leftover cinnamon toast crunch for garnish.\",\"1\":\"Transfer the baked oats mixture to a ramekin or loaf dish. Set your air fryer or oven to 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Halfway through add your cinnamon toast crunch to the top!\",\"2\":\"Remove and let cool for 5 minutes. Add more Cinnamon Toast Crunch on top as desired.\",\"3\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":4,\"carbohydrates\":29,\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":8,\"fat\":5,\"calories\":205}','\"Cinnamon Toast Crunch Baked Oats is a perfect breakfast or dessert! This recipe is filled with energy, protein and a little extra sweetness. The Crunchy Cinnamon Toast cereal top compliments the molten peanut butter center. Try this in your oven or an air fryer for convenience.\"','2','\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/video-api-prod/assets/dd580f27433c4171a452339d02fdaab9/CinnamonToastCrunchBakedOats.jpeg\"','½ Cup of Oats||⅓ Cup of Unsweetened Apple Sauce||1 Egg||½ tsp baking powder||½ tsp cinnamon||1 ½ tsp vanilla extract||5 tbsp cinnamon toast crunch||½ almond milk||','american||oven||healthy||comfort_food||easy||shoppable_recipes_desserts||cooling_rack||breakfast||meal_prep||dry_measuring_cups||bake||shoppable_recipes_meal_prep||oven_mitts||desserts||weeknight||brunch||baking_cups||air_fryer||under_30_minutes||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour'),('97-f193a17ef2de','\"Sweet Potato Chickpea BBQ Veggie Burgers\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 375˚F (190˚C).\",\"1\":\"In a large bowl, microwave chickpeas for 1 minute, or until softened.\",\"2\":\"Peel the cooked sweet potato, and add it to the bowl of chickpeas, along with the garlic, chili powder, and salt. Mash until chickpeas are finely mashed. Add cornmeal and scallions, and set aside.\",\"3\":\"For the barbecue sauce: In a medium-size bowl, combine tomato paste, water, maple syrup, apple cider vinegar, chili powder, garlic powder, and salt. Mix to combine.\",\"4\":\"Add barbecue sauce to the mashed chickpea mixture and mix until thoroughly combined.\",\"5\":\"Using a ½ cup (120 ml) measuring cup, portion 5 patties from the mixture. Place onto a lightly greased parchment-lined sheet pan.\",\"6\":\"Bake for 40 minutes, or until firm and browned, flipping over halfway through.\",\"7\":\"Serve with the remaining barbecue sauce and favorite fixins.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":54,\"fiber\":10,\"protein\":10,\"fat\":2,\"calories\":274,\"sugar\":19}','','5','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/cbeef384d7fd4d8e8622e26dc1ed86d5/Final_final.jpg\"','1 15-ounce can chickpeas, drained and rinsed||1 medium-sized sweet potato, cooked||1 clove garlic, minced||1 teaspoon chili powder||½ teaspoon salt||¼ cup barbecue sauce (recipe below)||¼ cup cornmeal||¼ cup scallions, chopped||','oven||healthy||gluten_free||easy||dinner||bake||weeknight||casual_party||bbq||pyrex||mixing_bowl||spatula||dry_measuring_cups||measuring_spoons||liquid_measuring_cup||parchment_paper||baking_pan||oven_mitts||chefs_knife||cutting_board||low_fat||high_fiber||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian'),('98-25481918f9fa','\"Jazzy Orange-Glazed Drumsticks\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\",\"1\":\"In a small bowl, whisk together the orange marmalade, sambal olek, kosher salt. Set aside.\",\"2\":\"Season the drumsticks all over with the Jazzy spice blend and place on the prepared baking sheet.\",\"3\":\"Bake the drumsticks for 35-40 minutes, brushing liberally with the marmalade mixture during the last 10 minutes of cooking, until well-glazed and the internal temperature reaches 165°F (75°C).\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":23,\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":25,\"fat\":12,\"calories\":313,\"sugar\":21}','\"Your usual drumsticks, but easily jazzed up to perfection.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/232198.jpg\"','½ cup orange marmalade||1 tablespoon sambal olek (chili paste)||1 teaspoon kosher salt||8 chicken drumsticks||2 tablespoons McCormick® TASTY Jazzy Spice Blend||','cutting_board||tongs||parchment_paper||baking_pan||oven_mitts||whisk||mixing_bowl||dinner||comfort_food||oven||stove_top||high_protein||5_ingredients_or_less||under_1_hour||dairy_free'),('98-2d7bf5bffddb','\"Spinach Pesto Pasta Bake\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\",\"1\":\"In a blender or food processor, add the spinach, basil, pine nuts, parmesan, garlic, salt, lemon juice, and olive oil.\",\"2\":\"Blend until you reach a creamy consistency. Set aside.\",\"3\":\"Add the pasta to a large bowl then add the tomatoes. Pour the pesto onto the pasta and mix well to combine.\",\"4\":\"Transfer the mixture to a baking dish and top with mozzarella.\",\"5\":\"Cover with foil and bake for 10-15 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Carefully remove and allow to cool for 5 minutes.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":6,\"fat\":25,\"calories\":291,\"sugar\":2,\"carbohydrates\":12}','','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/f8127795c528486a8c7074a2a76e3c71/BFV30903_LighterDinnerBakes4Ways_FB.jpg\"','3 cups spinach||1 cup basil||¾ cup pine nuts||¼ cup parmesan cheese||3 cloves garlic||Salt, to taste||¼ cup lemon juice||½ cup olive oil||1 box whole wheat pasta, prepared||2 cups cherry tomatoes, halved||½ cup mozzarella cheese||','oven||blender||american||italian||fusion||dinner||bake||easy||big_batch||weeknight||healthy||dry_measuring_cups||oven_mitts||pyrex||mixing_bowl||wooden_spoon||chefs_knife||cutting_board||baking_pan||low_carb||low_sugar||vegetarian'),('99-08e32cdda262','\"One-Pan Shrimp Fajitas\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\",\"1\":\"Wrap the tortillas in foil and place on the corner of a baking sheet.\",\"2\":\"Add the bell peppers, red onion, and shrimp to the sheet and season with olive oil, salt, pepper, garlic powder, cumin, and lime.\",\"3\":\"Toss to coat.\",\"4\":\"Place in the oven and bake for 10 minutes, flipping the shrimp halfway through.\",\"5\":\"Serve with warm tortillas, salsa, guacamole, cilantro, and lime.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":3,\"calories\":251,\"sugar\":3,\"carbohydrates\":31,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":22}','','5','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/2a58b10a187b48a19172b2e42a3785b4/Thumb.jpg\"','5 flour tortillas||½ red bell pepper, sliced||½ green bell pepper, sliced||½ orange bell pepper, sliced||½ red onion, sliced||n/a||1 teaspoon salt||½ teaspoon pepper||1 teaspoon garlic powder||1 teaspoon cumin||1 lime, juiced||','bake||weeknight||dinner||mexican||fusion||healthy||american||oven||one_pot_or_pan||baking_pan||pyrex||chefs_knife||cutting_board||measuring_spoons||tongs||oven_mitts||cinco_de_mayo'),('99-0dccf92c5928','\"Spinach And Cheese Pork Roll\"','{\"0\":\"In a small mixing bowl, combine the herb and olive oil rub ingredients. Set aside until ready for use.\",\"1\":\"Over low heat, cook spinach with olive oil, garlic cloves and salt \\u0026 pepper to taste. Cook spinach 1-2 minutes just until wilted.\",\"2\":\"Transfer the cooked spinach to a large bowl. Add ricotta, parmesan, salt and pepper. Mix until well combined.\",\"3\":\"Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).\",\"4\":\"Lay out the pork loin, butterfly and pound until flat and even. Spread the spinach and cheese mix on the pork loin.\",\"5\":\"Roll so that the spinach and cheese mix is on the inside. Secure with cooking twine.\",\"6\":\"Rub the herb and oil mix all over the rolled pork. Sear on all sides until golden and slightly crispy. Set aside.\",\"7\":\"Spread carrots, onions and potatoes on baking sheet. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt \\u0026 pepper. Place rolled pork on top of the bed of carrots, onions and potatoes.\",\"8\":\"Roast at 425°F (220°C) for 45 minutes, or until the internal temperature reads 145°F (65°C) for medium rare or 160°F (70°C) for medium.\",\"9\":\"Remove from oven and let the pork rest for 15 minutes before you remove the twine and slice.\",\"10\":\"Serve with carrots, onions and potatoes.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":758,\"sugar\":8,\"carbohydrates\":46,\"fiber\":5,\"protein\":44,\"fat\":44}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/3b98f8abda03476399f25d6b98ce8edd/BFV8589_Spinach_and_Cheese_Pork_Roll_Thumb.jpg\"','⅓ cup olive oil||2 tablespoons rosemary||1 tablespoon thyme||2 teaspoons salt||2 teaspoons pepper||3 garlic cloves, minced||','stuffed||bake||oven||comfort_food||american||gluten_free||dinner||weeknight||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||mixing_bowl||baking_pan||tongs||chefs_knife||cutting_board||saute_pan||spatula||pyrex||mashup||stove_top||pan_fry||special_occasion||thanksgiving'),('99-15c3e737ad94','\"Hearty Thanksgiving Leftover Bake\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C). Grease a 9x13-inch (22 x 33 cm)  baking dish with the olive oil.\",\"1\":\"In a large bowl, whisk together Campbell’s® Cream of Mushroom Soup and chicken broth until smooth. Fold in the onion, rice, thyme, and garlic.\",\"2\":\"Pour the mixture into the prepared baking dish. Then distribute the shredded turkey over the rice, gently pressing down to partially submerge.\",\"3\":\"Tightly cover the baking dish with foil, then bake for 1 hour.\",\"4\":\"Remove the bake from the oven and uncover. Top with the roasted vegetables in an even layer, then spoon the stuffing evenly on top.\",\"5\":\"Return to the oven and bake for another 30 minutes, or until the rice is tender and the stuffing is golden brown. (If the stuffing is browning too quickly, cover loosely with foil.)\",\"6\":\"Remove the bake from the oven and let rest for 10 minutes before serving.\",\"7\":\"Top each serving with parsley and a spoonful of cranberry sauce.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":15,\"fat\":25,\"calories\":538,\"sugar\":10,\"carbohydrates\":59,\"fiber\":2}','\"\"','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/288511.jpg\"','2 tablespoons olive oil, for greasing||1 10.5-ounce can of Campbell’s® Cream of Mushroom Soup||2 cups chicken broth||1 large yellow onion, chopped||2 cups white rice, rinsed well and drained||2 teaspoons fresh thyme leaves||1 clove garlic, finely minced||2 cups cooked turkey, shredded||2 cups roasted vegetables, chopped||2 cups stuffing||1 tablespoon fresh, chopped parsley, for garnish||½ cup cranberry sauce, for garnish||','baking_pan||oven_mitts||dinner||thanksgiving||oven||american'),('99-ca8ce203b11b','\"Banana Oat Freezer-Prep Smoothie\"','{\"0\":\"Add the arugula, banana, almond butter, oats, cinnamon, turmeric, and salt to a resealable container. Cover and store in the freezer for up to 3 months.\",\"1\":\"When ready to prepare, add the contents from the container and the almond milk to a blender and blend until smooth.\",\"2\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":10,\"fat\":12,\"calories\":394,\"sugar\":20,\"carbohydrates\":66,\"fiber\":10}','\"\"','1','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/18e0b8571a4d43cb870bc7fe740f0023/YT.jpg\"','1 cup arugula||1 banana, sliced||1 tablespoon almond butter||¼ cup oats||½ teaspoon cinnamon||½ teaspoon ground turmeric||¼ teaspoon kosher salt||½ cup unsweetened almond milk||','blender||healthy||chefs_knife||liquid_measuring_cup||big_batch||drinks||meal_prep||snacks||easy'),('9a-53436cd3cd36','\"Matzo Ball Pho\"','{\"0\":\"Lightly char onion halves and shallot on open flame.\",\"1\":\"In a large pot on high, add  star anise, cloves, coriander seeds, cardamom, and cinnamon. When the spices are brown and fragrant, take them off the heat and place them into a tea ball strainer.\",\"2\":\"In the same pot on high, add chicken wings, water, and salt. Boil, then add chicken thighs, tea ball strainer with spices, charred onion, charred scallion, and ginger slices. Boil together, then lower heat and let simmer for 30 minutes. Remove any impurities, whole items, or foam that rises to the top.\",\"3\":\"After 30 minutes, remove and cool chicken thighs and reserve and cool 3 tbsp of stock. Allow the remaining stock to simmer for 1.5 more hours.\",\"4\":\"In a large bowl, beat 3 eggs until no streaks remain. Then add vegetable oil, chopped basil and sawtooth, cooled 3 tbsp of Pho stock (that you reserved), 1 tsp salt, ¼ tsp black pepper, and ½ tsp of sugar. Whisk together, then add in Matzo meal. Combine and let batter rest for 40 minutes.\",\"5\":\"After 40 min, remove batter and roll into 8-10 Matzo balls.\",\"6\":\"Once the chicken thighs are cooled, take them out and shred them.\",\"7\":\"After 2 hours, remove and discard all solids from the stock. Add matzo balls and green onion heads. Let the mixture simmer together for 40 minutes. At this point, season stock with 2 tsp sugar, 2 tsp chicken bouillon powder, and 2 tsp fish sauce. Remove from heat.\",\"8\":\"Ladle 1 portion soup with broth, shredded chicken, and green onion heads. Top with diced and sliced onions. Serve with a side of bean sprouts, Thai basil, sawtooth herbs, a slice of lime, Sriracha, and hoisin sauce.\"}','{\"protein\":53,\"fat\":40,\"calories\":774,\"sugar\":9,\"carbohydrates\":48,\"fiber\":5}','\"Matzo Ball Soup! You\\u0027ve heard of it everywhere - pop culture, Bat Mitzvahs, what have you. You\\u0027ve heard of pho everywhere too, especially recently. How many friends want to grab a bowl of pho after a long day? It\\u0027s become the new ramen. So we\\u0027re here to put those phenomena together and we\\u0027ve created the perfect culmination of the two: Matzo. Ball. Pho. Try it now.\\n\\n(This Matzo Ball Pho was 1 of 3 winners in our latest recipe \\u003Ca href=\\u0022https://www.buzzfeed.com/mccormickspice/tasty-mccormick-contest-april-2021\\u0022\\u003Echallenge\\u003C/a\\u003E. Find more of our community recipes \\u003Ca href=\\u0022https://tasty.co/topic/community\\u0022\\u003Ehere\\u003C/a\\u003E.)\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/8cb28aa8ac4d4518aa0b418074b27e20.png\"','2 onions, halved - thinly slice half for garnish||1 shallot, halved||1 inch piece ginger, sliced||4-6 stalks green onions, diced, with heads reserved||2 star anise seeds||7 cloves||1 tsp coriander seeds||1 dried cardamom pod||1 carton cinnamon stick||1 lb chicken wings||3 chicken thighs||10 cups water||1 bunch Thai basil, chopped||1 bunch sawtooth herb, chopped||3 eggs||¼ cup vegetable oil||¾ cups Matzo Meal||¼ tsp black pepper||2 ½ tsp sugar, divided||2 tsp fish sauce||2 tsp chicken bullion powder||Salt||Lime||Bean Sprouts||Sriracha||Hoisin sauce||','vietnamese||fusion||dinner||special_occasion||stove_top||mccormick_ugc_one_pot_winners||high_protein||high_fiber||dairy_free'),('9a-77caf7d954e0','\"Satay Beef Skewers\"','{\"0\":\"In a food processor, combine the red onion, scallions, garlic, ginger, curry powder, turmeric, cumin, salt, soy sauce, lemongrass, lime juice, coconut milk, peanut oil, and peanut butter. Purée until smooth.\",\"1\":\"Divide the sauce between 2 small bowls. Add the chopped peanuts to one of the bowls and stir to combine. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to use.\",\"2\":\"Pour the remaining sauce over the cubed beef in a medium bowl. Toss well to coat. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and let marinate in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours, up 6 hours.\",\"3\":\"Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C). Line a 9-inch (23 cm) square baking dish with parchment paper.\",\"4\":\"Thread the beef cubes onto skewers and set over the baking dish.\",\"5\":\"Bake for 20 minutes, until the beef is seared and juicy.\",\"6\":\"Serve the satay beef with the reserved sauce alongside.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":620,\"sugar\":4,\"carbohydrates\":17,\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":35,\"fat\":48}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/123cf6784ad04f89840f16db135ccbdd/BFV51455_KetoDinner_FINALFB_v3.jpg\"','½ small red onion, finely chopped||4 scallions, roughly chopped||n/a||n/a||n/a||n/a||n/a||n/a||n/a||n/a||n/a||n/a||n/a||n/a||n/a||n/a||','oven||mixing_bowl||plastic_wrap||oven_mitts||baking_pan||tongs||dinner||special_occasion||high_protein||low_sugar'),('9a-aea571b0888e','\"High-Protein Baked Quinoa Bites\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 350˚F (180˚C). Grease a baking sheet with nonstick spray.\",\"1\":\"Finely chop the Tuscan kale. Mince the garlic.\",\"2\":\"Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a medium pan over medium heat. Sauté the minced garlic and red pepper flakes for 1 minute, until fragrant. Add the kale and cook until softened, about 3 minutes. Remove from the heat and set aside.\",\"3\":\"Chop the sun-dried tomatoes and add to the kale mixture.\",\"4\":\"In a large bowl, beat the eggs, then add the quinoa, oat flour, kale mixture, oregano, basil, parsley, salt, and Parmesan cheese. Mix well.\",\"5\":\"Shape the quinoa mixture into 20 small patties. Place on the prepared baking sheet.\",\"6\":\"Bake for 20 minutes, until the patties are golden brown and crispy.\",\"7\":\"Serve as desired. The bites will keep in the fridge for up to 6 days, or in the freezer for up to 1 month.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":118,\"fiber\":16,\"protein\":36,\"fat\":23,\"calories\":812,\"sugar\":6}','\"\"','5','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/201925.jpg\"','Nonstick cooking spray, for greasing||2 cups Tuscan kale||4 cloves garlic||Olive oil, to taste||½ teaspoon red pepper flakes||⅓ cup sun-dried tomatoes, in oil||4 large eggs||4 cups cooked quinoa, cooled||1 cup oat flour||1 tablespoon dried oregano||1 tablespoon dried basil||1 tablespoon dried parsley||1 tablespoon kosher salt||¼ cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese||','stove_top||oven||spatula||american||italian||gluten_free||freezer||meal_prep||healthy||cutting_board||saute_pan||big_batch||wooden_spoon||whisk||chefs_knife||easy||cheese_grater||baking_pan||bake||one_top_app_eggs||one_top_app_veggies||lunch||tongs||oven_mitts||high_protein||high_fiber||vegetarian'),('9b-7917ec0ac283','\"Black Bean Vegetarian Soup \"','{\"0\":\"Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add the onion, garlic, and chili powder and cook until fragrant, about 3 minutes.\",\"1\":\"Add the tomatoes, black beans, water, salt, and pepper and let simmer for about 20 minutes.\",\"2\":\"Use an immersion blender to puree the soup until slightly chunky, or transfer half of the soup to a blender and puree, then transfer back to the pot.\",\"3\":\"Ladle half of the soup into a bowl and garnish with red onion, cilantro, and a lime wedge. Store the remaining soup in the fridge.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":9,\"fat\":9,\"calories\":244,\"sugar\":4,\"carbohydrates\":32,\"fiber\":11}','','3','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/8452e746f0d345faaa92f48f6f33dd0e/BFV43066_TastyMakeAheadMealPlan_FB_V2.jpg\"','2 teaspoons olive oil||½  medium yellow onion, diced||2 cloves garlic, minced||1 teaspoon chili powder||1 cup canned tomatoes with juice||2 15-ounce can black beans, drained||3 cups water||1 teaspoon kosher salt||½ teaspoon ground black pepper||','stove_top||hand_mixer||easy||meal_prep||wooden_spoon||big_batch||healthy||sauce_pan||weeknight||measuring_spoons||liquid_measuring_cup||dinner||low_sugar||high_fiber||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian||walmart_meal_planning'),('9b-f76b29742474','\"Creamy Cajun Pasta\"','{\"0\":\"In a large, heavy-bottomed pot, melt the butter over medium heat until just bubbling. Add the sausage and then season with salt. Brown for 2 minutes on 1 side, then stir and brown on the other side for 2 minutes more.\",\"1\":\"Add the onion, season with salt, and cook for 2 minutes, until starting to soften. Add the jalapeño, garlic, and tomato paste. Stir to distribute the tomato paste. Add the Jazzy spice blend and stir to combine.\",\"2\":\"Add the pasta, red and green peppers, mushrooms, and salt and stir to combine. Pour in the tomatoes and stock. Bring to a gentle boil, then reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 10-12 minutes, until the pasta is cooked through and the peppers are tender but not mushy.\",\"3\":\"Mix in the cream cheese to create a thick, creamy sauce.\",\"4\":\"Serve garnished with scallions, if desired.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":18,\"fat\":52,\"calories\":887,\"sugar\":12,\"carbohydrates\":83}','\"\"','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/6d9b54963ad9442aa9320076a7bbf0bf.jpeg\"','2 tablespoons unsalted butter||1 pound spicy Italian sausage links, cut into rounds||Kosher salt, to taste||1 medium yellow onion, thinly sliced||1 jalapeño, seeded and minced||1 tablespoon minced garlic||1 tablespoon tomato paste||2 tablespoons McCormick® Jazzy Spice Blend||1 pound dried penne pasta||1 red bell pepper, seeded and thinly sliced||1 green bell pepper, seeded and thinly sliced||8 ounces button mushrooms, stemmed and sliced||1 14.5-ounce can of fire-roasted tomatoes||4 cups chicken stock||5 ounces cream cheese, cubed||2 scallions, thinly sliced, for garnish||','mccormick_seasoned_pro||schwartz_seasoned_pro||club_house_seasoned_pro||italian||american||comfort_food||meal_prep||dinner'),('9c-1105adbfadd0','\"Chicken Cordon Bleu Bake\"','{\"0\":\"Sprinkle the chicken breasts with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder, tossing to coat evenly.\",\"1\":\"On a cutting board, place a chicken breast between two sheets of plastic wrap and pound until about ½-inch (1 cm) thick with a meat mallet, rolling pin, or heavy pan.\",\"2\":\"Remove the plastic wrap and place a layer of Swiss cheese, then ham, then one more layer of Swiss cheese.\",\"3\":\"Evenly roll the chicken, and place onto a new sheet of plastic wrap.\",\"4\":\"Wrap the chicken in the plastic wrap, twist the excess plastic, and roll the chicken while twisting the sides in to tighten and firm up the roll of chicken cordon bleu. Tie the excess and chill in the fridge to set for 30 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\",\"6\":\"Cut the puff pastry sheets in half and gently roll out width-wise.\",\"7\":\"Brush the pastry with mustard and place the chicken on to the bottom edge of the pastry.\",\"8\":\"Tightly roll the chicken in the puff pastry, pinching the seams together to close and folding the sides under the bottom.\",\"9\":\"Place the chickens rolls on a greased baking sheet and brush all sides with egg wash.\",\"10\":\"With a fork, score a decorative design onto the surface of the puff pastry.\",\"11\":\"Sprinkle with salt.\",\"12\":\"Bake for 35-40 minutes or until the puff pastry is a dark golden brown and the internal temperature of the chicken is 165°F (75°C).\",\"13\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":61,\"fat\":51,\"calories\":902,\"sugar\":1,\"carbohydrates\":48,\"fiber\":2}','','5','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/126101.jpg\"','4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||1 tablespoon garlic powder||1 tablespoon onion powder||16 slices Swiss cheese||½ pound ham, sliced||2 sheets puff pastry||¼ cup English mustard||1 egg, beaten||','rolling_pin||christmas||easy||big_batch||baking_pan||thanksgiving||kid_friendly||plastic_wrap||dinner||mashup||bake||oven||comfort_food||winter||special_occasion||stuffed||american||spatula||measuring_spoons||oven_mitts||bread_pan||casual_party||pyrex||mixing_bowl||high_protein||low_sugar'),('9c-2fe3c463546a','\"Garlic Pork Cauliflower Fried Rice\"','{\"0\":\"Remove all leaves and cut the cauliflower into small florets.\",\"1\":\"Place the florets in a food processor and blend until they are a rice-like texture. Be careful not to over process or it may turn mushy. Set aside, and drain excess moisture with a towel, if desired.\",\"2\":\"In a large saucepan over medium-high heat, cook the pork until no pink is showing, then add the garlic, onions, salt, pepper, soy sauce, and honey, stirring until the sauce has started to brown.\",\"3\":\"Stir until most of the liquid has reduced, then add the cauliflower rice. Cook for about 3-4 minutes until the pork is incorporated evenly into the cauliflower.\",\"4\":\"Spread the rice towards the edge of the pan, creating a well in the center.\",\"5\":\"Pour the beaten eggs into the well, stirring only the eggs until they are cooked.\",\"6\":\"Fold the eggs into the rice, then mix in the green onions\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":33,\"fat\":27,\"calories\":519,\"sugar\":33,\"carbohydrates\":38,\"fiber\":2}','','3','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/f5691662d6c74e26b9a366d8dcbf6706/BFV13716_CauliflowerFriedRice4Ways-FB1080SQ.jpg\"','1 cauliflower head||2 pork chops, diced||4 cloves garlic, finely diced||½ onion, sliced||1 teaspoon salt||1 teaspoon pepper||2 tablespoons soy sauce||¼ cup honey||3 eggs, beaten||½ cup green onions, sliced||','stove_top||chinese||dinner||weeknight||pan_fry||kid_friendly||easy||cutting_board||chefs_knife||measuring_spoons||pyrex||wooden_spoon||sauce_pan||dry_measuring_cups||liquid_measuring_cup||high_protein||high_fiber||dairy_free'),('9c-c881b981bd09','\"Taco-Stuffed Peppers\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).\",\"1\":\"Cut off the tops of the bell peppers, then run a paring knife around the inside edges to remove the seeds and ribs. Place the peppers upright in a baking dish. Bake for 20 minutes.\",\"2\":\"While the peppers are roasting, heat the vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add ground beef and break up with a wooden spoon, then add the taco seasoning and mix to combine. Cook until the beef is browned, 5–6 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Add the onion and cook until softened, 4–5 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Reduce the heat to medium, then mix in the black beans, brown rice, corn, and salsa. \",\"5\":\"Add 1 cup (100 g) of cheese, then stir until incorporated and the cheese has melted. Remove the pan from the heat.\",\"6\":\"Spoon the beef filling into the peppers, then top with the remaining ½ cup (50 g) of shredded cheese.\",\"7\":\"Return the peppers to the oven for 15 minutes, until the cheese has melted.\",\"8\":\"Top each pepper with generous scoops of guacamole and sour cream and more cheese.\",\"9\":\"TACO SEASONING: In an airtight container, mix together the chili powder, cumin, salt, black pepper, cornstarch, paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, cayenne, and dried oregano. Store in a cool, dark place for up to 6 months.\",\"10\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":22,\"calories\":491,\"sugar\":9,\"carbohydrates\":42,\"fiber\":9,\"protein\":31}','\"I