 cheese and parsley, and stir. Remove from the heat.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":82,\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":51,\"fat\":45,\"calories\":938,\"sugar\":18}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/1d48779ad14f4626b7a8ef3e7586967f/BF_THUMB_Square.jpg\"','2 chicken breasts, sliced||1 pound cooked andouille sausage||4 tablespoons olive oil||3 cloves garlic, minced||3 bell peppers, diced||1 medium onion, diced||6 cups milk (whole preferred)||1 pound fettuccine pasta, uncooked||¾ cup parmesan cheese, plus more for serving||3 tablespoons chopped parsley, plus more for serving||','one_pot_or_pan||pan_fry||comfort_food||dutch_oven||american||weeknight||italian||fusion||dinner||stove_top||measuring_spoons||mixing_bowl||pyrex||whisk||wooden_spoon||liquid_measuring_cup||chefs_knife||cutting_board||dry_measuring_cups||easy'),('9e-4fac276a8164','\"Sweet Potato Gnocchi\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 400ºF (200ºC).\",\"1\":\"Prick the sweet potato with a fork several times and bake for 40 minutes (or microwave for 5 minutes).\",\"2\":\"Allow potato to cool at least 5 minutes before peeling skin off.\",\"3\":\"In a large bowl, mash potato with masher or fork until smooth.\",\"4\":\"Add parmesan cheese, egg, and flour. Knead the dough until it is firm and no longer sticky, adding flour as needed, forming a ball with the dough.\",\"5\":\"Divide the dough into four equal parts. Take one part and roll it out into a long rope, about a 1-inch (2 ½ cm) wide.\",\"6\":\"Slice into ½-inch (1 cm) rectangles and set aside.\",\"7\":\"Using an overturned fork, slide each gnocchi over the fork prongs so they become serrated in a corkscrew shape.\",\"8\":\"Bring a large pot of water to a boil and add the gnocchi. Boil until the gnocchi float to the top, about 1-2  minutes. Drain in a colander.\",\"9\":\"In a pan over medium heat, melt butter and add sage. Simmer for 1 minute without letting butter burn.\",\"10\":\"Add gnocchi to pan with the sage and butter, tossing until lightly golden.\",\"11\":\"Top with more Parmesan cheese.\",\"12\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":67,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":17,\"fat\":16,\"calories\":494,\"sugar\":3}','\"Gnocchi are something you probably order all the time at restaurants but never think about making from scratch. Well, now\\u2019s the time to start. These lightened-up homemade gnocchi call for sweet potato in place of regular potato. The sweet potato is mashed with flour, egg, and Parmesan and boiled into little dumplings. Then, the gnocchi get tossed in a simple sauce of butter and sage until just golden.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/125259.jpg\"','1 sweet potato||½ cup grated vegetarian parmesan cheese||1 egg||2 cups flour, plus more to dust||2 tablespoons butter||2-3 leaves of sage||','stove_top||weeknight||baking_cups||measuring_spoons||dinner||dry_measuring_cups||comfort_food||steam||pan_fry||date_night||healthy||saute_pan||mixing_bowl||spatula||walmart_holiday_bundle||chefs_knife||cutting_board||pyrex||srsly_sauv_blanc||tasty_holiday_christmas||low_sugar||vegetarian'),('9e-62e5eb4a631f','\"Cajun Seafood Pasta\"','{\"0\":\"Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.\",\"1\":\"Make the Cajun spice mix: In a small bowl or resealable container, mix together the paprika, black pepper, salt, garlic powder, onion powder, cayenne, oregano, and thyme until well combined. The spice mix will keep in an airtight container for up to 1 month.\",\"2\":\"Make the pasta: Cook the pasta in the boiling water according to the package instructions until al dente. Reserve ¼ cup of the pasta water, then drain the noodles.\",\"3\":\"While the pasta cooks, toss the shrimp in a medium bowl with 2 tablespoons of Cajun spice mix. Toss the scallops in a separate medium bowl with 1 tablespoon of the Cajun spice mix as well.\",\"4\":\"Heat 1 tablespoon of the olive oil in a large, deep skillet over medium-high heat until nearly smoking. Add the shrimp to the pan and cook, flipping once until they just turn pink, 2–3 minutes per side, being careful not to overcook. Transfer the shrimp back to the bowl and wipe the pan clean.\",\"5\":\"Heat the remaining tablespoon of olive oil in the same pan until nearly smoking. Add the scallops to the pan and sear on each side for about 2 minutes, until they are easy to flip without resistance. Transfer the scallops to the bowl with the shrimp. Wipe out the pan.\",\"6\":\"Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in the same pan over medium heat. Add the yellow and orange bell peppers, season with 1 tablespoon of Cajun spice mix, and cook for 7–10 minutes, until the peppers are soft and tender. Add the red bell peppers and scallions and cook for another 5 minutes, until warmed through. Transfer the vegetables to the bowl with the shrimp and scallops.\",\"7\":\"In the same pan (do not wipe out!), combine the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter, 2 tablespoons Cajun spice mix, and the heavy cream. Bring to a boil and cook for 7–10 minutes, or until reduced by at least half, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom of the pan.\",\"8\":\"Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the Parmesan cheese. Add the cooked linguine, sautéed vegetables, shrimp, and scallops and toss to coat in the sauce, adding 1–2 tablespoons of the reserved pasta water if the sauce is too thick. Garnish with the parsley.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":66,\"fiber\":5,\"protein\":62,\"fat\":52,\"calories\":942,\"sugar\":8}','\"Music artist, \\u003Ca href=\\u0022https://www.instagram.com/roywoods/\\u0022\\u003ERoy Woods\\u003C/a\\u003E, shares how to make this flavorful Cajun seafood pasta.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/d003433fdbd542f7a3bcc5e212b78ad6.jpeg\"','3 tablespoons smoked paprika||2 tablespoons freshly ground black pepper||2 tablespoons kosher salt||2 tablespoons garlic powder||1 tablespoon onion powder||1 tablespoon cayenne pepper||1 teaspoon dried oregano||1½ teaspoons dried thyme||','dinner||seafood||high_protein||high_fiber||under_1_hour||pescatarian'),('9e-bfb1dbc777d6','\"Bacon, Avocado, \\u0026 Brussels Sprout Salad With Lemon Vinaigrette\"','{\"0\":\"Slice the stems off the Brussels sprouts and cut each one in half, then thinly slice. Transfer the shaved sprouts to a medium bowl and break apart with your hands.\",\"1\":\"To prepare the vinaigrette, juice the lemons into a small bowl and remove the seeds.\",\"2\":\"Add the mustard, oregano, pepper, and salt. Whisk to combine.\",\"3\":\"Slowly add the olive oil while continuing to whisk until evenly blended.\",\"4\":\"Slice the avocado and remove the pit, then dice.\",\"5\":\"Trim the ends of the scallions, then dice.\",\"6\":\"In a large bowl, combine the Brussels sprouts and spinach.\",\"7\":\"Add the avocado, bacon, scallions, Parmesan cheese, cranberries, and almonds.\",\"8\":\"Pour the dressing evenly over the salad.\",\"9\":\"Toss thoroughly until well mixed.\",\"10\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":324,\"sugar\":6,\"carbohydrates\":17,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":8,\"fat\":26}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/5c915974599840a0bc316d9972df9cff/IMG_0071_FB.jpg\"','20 brussels sprouts, shaved||1 avocado, diced||n/a||1 cup spinach||7 bacon slices cut into ½-inch pieces||⅓ cup parmesan||¼ cup dried cranberries||¼ cup sliced almonds (slicing optional)||','gluten_free||american||lunch||healthy||weeknight||easy||chefs_knife||cutting_board||pyrex||mixing_bowl||measuring_spoons||whisk||dry_measuring_cups||wooden_spoon||liquid_measuring_cup||bbq||walmart_holiday_bundle||walmart_meal_planning'),('9f-864026f2fb4b','\"Sherry Mushrooms With Creamy Polenta And Gremolata\"','{\"0\":\"Make the polenta: Bring salted water to boil in a medium pot over medium-high heat. Pour in the polenta and stir for 2 minutes. Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes to make sure the polenta isn’t sticking or burning.\",\"1\":\"Right before serving, stir the milk, Parmesan, and butter into the polenta. Season with salt and pepper to taste.\",\"2\":\"Meanwhile, make the mushrooms: Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the shallots and sweat until softened and slightly translucent, about 2 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Season with salt, then add the thyme leaves and mushrooms. Cook until the mushrooms are caramelized and softened, about 5 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Pour in the sherry to deglaze the pan and stir to loosen any browned bits from the bottom. Cook off the alcohol, about 1 minute. Add the vegetable stock and season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then let the liquid reduce for about 10 minutes. Remove from the heat.\",\"5\":\"Make the gremolata: In a small bowl, combine the garlic, parsley, and lemon zest. Season with salt to taste.\",\"6\":\"Divide the hot polenta between serving bowls and top with the mushrooms and gremolata.\",\"7\":\"Nutrition, all included\\n\\nCalories: 413\\nTotal fat: 22 grams \\nSodium: 1351 mg\\nTotal carbs: 42 grams\\nDietary fiber: 6 grams\\nSugars: 6 grams\\nProtein: 15 grams\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":28,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":11,\"fat\":18,\"calories\":338,\"sugar\":9}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/193100.jpg\"','3 cups water||Kosher salt, to taste||1 cup polenta||1 cup milk of choice||½ cup grated Parmesan cheese||1 tablespoon unsalted butter||Pepper, to taste||','stove_top||dry_measuring_cups||italian||gluten_free||liquid_measuring_cup||comfort_food||measuring_spoons||cutting_board||mixing_bowl||one_top_app_veggies||winter||fall||wooden_spoon||dinner||chefs_knife||pyrex||spatula||vegetarian'),('9f-f174ba2aa9b7','\"Strawberry Banana Smoothie Meal Prep\"','{\"0\":\"Put fruit in a freezer bag. Seal and store in freezer for up to 8 -12 months.\",\"1\":\"When ready to use, put milk, Greek yogurt, and frozen fruit into a blender and mix until consistency is smooth.\",\"2\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":53,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":17,\"fat\":3,\"calories\":299,\"sugar\":39}','','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/013e3dfd6a1949dc9ddcb2357ade5f97/BFV16378_BreakfastSmoothieMealPrep4Ways_FB1080SQ.jpg\"','2 cups strawberries, sliced||1 banana, sliced||1½ cups milk of choice||1 cup plain Greek yogurt||','blender||freezer||healthy||meal_prep||breakfast||drinks||american||zipper_storage_bags||liquid_measuring_cup||dry_measuring_cups||pyrex||chefs_knife||cutting_board||kid_friendly||brunch||5_ingredients_or_less'),('a0-2a14c56d7c12','\"Calamari Fra Diavolo Over Linguine\"','{\"0\":\"Bring a large pot of well-salted water to a boil of medium-high heat.\",\"1\":\"While the water is boiling, make the sauce: In a separate large pot, heat the olive oil over medium heat until shimmering. Add the onion and ½ teaspoon salt and sauté for 4–6 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the onion is softened and translucent. Add the garlic, oregano, and red pepper flakes and sauté for 1 minute, until the garlic is fragrant.\",\"2\":\"Add the tomato paste and mix until evenly combined with the aromatics. Cook for 6–8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the tomato paste has darkened and thickened. It is okay if some of the paste begins to stick to the bottom of the pot. Deglaze with the red wine and clam juice, scraping up any browned bits. Simmer for 4–6 minutes, until the liquid is reduced by half.\",\"3\":\"Add the whole peeled tomatoes and, using a potato masher, break up the tomatoes into bite-sized chunks. Bring the sauce to a simmer.\",\"4\":\"Add the calamari and stir to coat in the sauce. Reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer for about 25 minutes, until the calamari is very tender and the sauce has thickened. Season with the remaining teaspoon of salt, plus more to taste.\",\"5\":\"When the calamari has 6–8 minutes cooking time left, drop the linguine into the boiling water and until just shy of al dente. Reserve ¼ cup (60 ml) of the pasta water.\",\"6\":\"Using tongs, transfer the linguine directly to the calamari sauce. Add the reserved pasta water and toss well to combine. Cook for 2–3 minutes, until the linguine is al dente and well coated in the sauce. Remove the pot from the heat and stir in the lemon juice and half of the parsley.\",\"7\":\"Transfer the pasta to a large serving platter and garnish with remaining parsley and red pepper flakes.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":28,\"fat\":21,\"calories\":759,\"sugar\":10,\"carbohydrates\":109,\"fiber\":7}','\"In this classic Italian pasta dish, tender squid rings and tentacles simmer in a thick and spicy tomato sauce\\u2013fra diavolo means \\u201Cbrother devil\\u201D in Italian. Toss it with linguine, top with more parsley and red pepper flakes, and serve family style. We recommend using clam juice to enhance the seafood flavor, but chicken stock works too! This content is intended solely for users of legal drinking age. Drink responsibly.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/312124.jpg\"','2 tablespoons olive oil||½ medium yellow onion, finely diced (about 1 cup)||1½ teaspoons kosher salt, divided, plus more as needed||3–4 garlic cloves, minced (about 1 tablespoon)||1 tablespoon dried oregano||1½ teaspoons red pepper flakes, plus more for garnish||¼ cup tomato paste||½ cup full-bodied red wine, such as Cabernet Sauvignon||½ cup clam juice or chicken broth||1 32-ounce can of whole peeled tomatoes, drained||1 pound calamari rings and tentacles, cleaned||¾ pound dried linguine||Juice of 1 lemon (about 2 tablespoons)||½ cup Italian parsley, roughly chopped, divided||','date_night||sauce_pan||italian||stove_top||comfort_food||tongs||dinner||contains_alcohol||special_occasion||high_protein||high_fiber||dairy_free||pescatarian'),('a1-0bb63415c616','\"Herb Sea Salt-Rubbed Chicken Thighs\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 425˚F (220˚C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and set a wire rack inside.