ns freshly grated ginger||1 tablespoon honey||1 teaspoon sriracha||¼ cup lime juice||¼ cup reduced-sodium soy sauce||1 block extra-firm tofu||4 tablespoons sesame oil, divided||1 small onion, sliced||1 large carrot, sliced||1 red bell pepper, sliced||½ cup edamame, frozen, thawed||3 cups soba noodles, cooked||1 tablespoon sesame seeds||Green onions, chopped, to serve||','dry_measuring_cups||stove_top||cutting_board||dinner||chefs_knife||american||japanese||pan_fry||fusion||lunch||date_night||weeknight||cooking_kit||high_protein||high_fiber||dairy_free||vegetarian||walmart_meal_planning'),('ae-68b50d7420bb','\"Creamy Tuscan Chicken\"','{\"0\":\"Season the chicken all over with salt and pepper.\",\"1\":\"Heat the oil in a skillet over medium-low heat.\",\"2\":\"Place the chicken thighs skin side down in the skillet and cook for about 13 minutes to crisp up the skin. Move the chicken around from time to time to ensure it cooks evenly. The skin should be hard to the touch.\",\"3\":\"Flip the chicken, then cook for about another 15 minutes, until the chicken is cooked through. Remove from pan.\",\"4\":\"Add the garlic and onion, stirring until onions are translucent. Stir in the tomatoes and spinach until the spinach is wilted.\",\"5\":\"Add the heavy cream, salt, and pepper, bringing to a boil.\",\"6\":\"Add the Parmesan cheese and parsley, stirring until the sauce has thickened slightly.\",\"7\":\"Place the chicken back in the pan, spooning the sauce on top of the chicken.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":39,\"fat\":64,\"calories\":721,\"sugar\":6,\"carbohydrates\":11,\"fiber\":1}','\"Picture yourself on the coast of Tuscany, Italy. Flowy clothes, a beautiful breeze, and a view of the Tuscan Sea: you\\u2019re ready to book your next vacation, aren\\u2019t you? Well, we\\u2019re here to bring Tuscany to you. How, you may ask? Well, that\\u2019s what our easy Tuscan chicken is here for. Loaded with fresh veggies, herbs, and rich Parmesan cheese, it\\u2019ll have you saying \\u2018That\\u2019s amore!\\u2019\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/1c4c0c0dece7467c9c4175cb759ed6a7/BFV14220_3CourseTuscanChickenDinner-FB.jpg\"','4 chicken thighs, bone-in & skin-on||2 teaspoons salt (for the chicken)||1 teaspoon pepper (for the chicken)||1 tablespoon oil||3 cloves garlic, chopped||½ onion, diced||1 tomato, diced||2 cups spinach||2 cups heavy cream||1 teaspoon salt||1 teaspoon pepper||½ cup grated parmesan||2 tablespoons parsley, chopped||','italian||american||comfort_food||easy||one_pot_or_pan||date_night||weeknight||pan_fry||dinner||cast_iron_pan||stove_top||saute_pan||wooden_spoon||tongs||mccormick_easy_dinner||best_of_tasty||tasty_s_5th_birthday_recipe||tasty_s_5th_birthday_savory||shoppable_recipes_family_dinner||low_carb||high_protein||under_1_hour||keto'),('b0-3401833681fc','\"Sancocho (Puerto Rican Meat Stew)\"','{\"0\":\"Season the meat with all purpose seasoning and boil for 35 minutes in a deep pot.\",\"1\":\"Drain the meat and lower heat to medium.\",\"2\":\"Add the sofrito, oil, and sazón. Stir 2-3 minutes until the meat browns and all the ingredients come together.\",\"3\":\"Add the tomato sauce and cook for 1-2 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Add water and mix well.\",\"5\":\"Add all the vegetables, stir, and let simmer for 35-45 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Taste after 25 minutes and add more sazón or salt and pepper to taste.\",\"7\":\"Serve warm.\"}','{\"protein\":3,\"fat\":5,\"calories\":299,\"sugar\":5,\"carbohydrates\":60,\"fiber\":4}','\"\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/0837da6fbb114828af7b3b456feb49ae.png\"','1 pound stew meat||2 tbsp sofrito||2 tbsp cooking oil||5 cups water||2 tbsp tomato sauce||1 pack sazón||1 medium yuca root, cubed||3 carrots, cut into 1-inch rounds||2 corn cobs, cut into thirds||1 taro root, cubed||1 Japanese yam, cubed||1 cup cubed pumpkin||All purpose seasoning||Salt||Pepper||','stove_top||latin_american||comfort_food||dinner||weeknight||low_sugar||dairy_free'),('b0-37472d9d8cc2','\"Fried Carrot Cake\"','{\"0\":\"Add daikon to a pot of boiling water and cook for five minutes until translucent. Drain then set aside.\",\"1\":\"In a mixing bowl, add rice flour, tapioca flour, and chicken stock. Mix until fully combined then add the daikon.\",\"2\":\"Place a wok on medium heat, then add 1 tbsp of cooking oil. Once it heats up add 1 tbsp of garlic and fry for 1 minute before adding in the daikon mixture. Stir constantly until the mixture thickens up. This will happen rapidly so be careful not to take it too far or it will dry out. The mixture should look like a thick cake batter.\",\"3\":\"Pour the daikon mix into a round cake pan, then place inside a steaming pot and steam for one hour.\",\"4\":\"Once the cake has become a solid mass, remove from the steamer and allow to cool. Then refrigerate for three hours or overnight.\",\"5\":\"Remove the cake from the fridge and set on a chopping board then slice into small rectangular cubes.\",\"6\":\"Add 2 tbsp of cooking oil to a wok and place on high heat, then once the oil starts to smoke add the cubes of cake and fry, stirring occasionally until every side has browned.\",\"7\":\"Lower the heat to medium, then add garlic, pickled radish (chai poh), light soy sauce, and fish sauce. Stir for a minute until each cube is coated in sauce, then add eggs and allow it to set for a moment. Break up the eggs partially once they are cooked then flip onto a plate.\",\"8\":\"Garnish with sliced spring onion, and chilli paste.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":6,\"fat\":8,\"calories\":197,\"sugar\":2,\"carbohydrates\":26,\"fiber\":10}','\"If you thought \\u003Ca href=\\u0022https://www.visitsingapore.com/dining-drinks-singapore/?cmp=EDC_GMPNowContent-May-Aug_XX_BR_ENG_NA_NA_1x1_NA_BF-RECIPE_BUZZ_SCON_AW_NA_NA\\u0022\\u003ESingapore\\u2019s\\u003C/a\\u003E Carrot Cake dish was a twist on the classic dessert \\u2014 think again.\"','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/269167.jpg\"','1½ cups daikon, grated||1 cup rice flour||½ cup tapioca flour||2 cups chicken stock||3 tbsps cooking oil||1 tbsp garlic, minced||2 tbsps pickled radish (chai poh)||1 tbsp fish sauce||1 tbsp light soy sauce||3 eggs, beaten||','cutting_board||chefs_knife||spatula||mixing_bowl||brunch||fusion||stove_top||wok||lunch||dinner||pan_fry||weeknight||chinese||steam||low_sugar||dairy_free'),('b0-6d68ced90163','\"Jerk Cauliflower\"','{\"0\":\"Bring a large pot of water to a boil, then add the salt, garlic powder, allspice, and cauliflower florets. Cook for 3-4 minutes, until the cauliflower is almost cooked through (a knife should still meet a bit of resistance when trying to pierce the stem). Remove the cauliflower form the water and drain and cool slightly on a kitchen towel.\",\"1\":\"Meanwhile, make the jerk sauce: In a food processor, combine the onion, scotch bonnet peppers, garlic, ginger, thyme, lime juice, vinegar, nutmeg, allspice, sugar, salt, black pepper, and olive oil. Blend until smooth.\",\"2\":\"In a large bowl, toss the blanched cauliflower with 1½ cups (360 ml) of the jerk sauce. Let sit for 30-60 minutes. Reserve the remaining ¾ cup (180 ml) of jerk sauce.\",\"3\":\"Transfer the cauliflower to a clean large bowl, leaving any remaining marinade behind. Sprinkle the cornstarch over the cauliflower and toss until well coated.\",\"4\":\"Heat the canola oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Working in batches, sear the cauliflower for 1-2 minutes, until a brown crust forms. Flip florets over with tongs to sear on the other side for 1-2 minutes. Transfer to a plate and repeat with the remaining cauliflower, adding more oil as needed.\",\"5\":\"Add the reserved jerk sauce to pan and bring to a simmer, about 1 minute. Return the cauliflower to the pan and toss to coat well.\",\"6\":\"Transfer the cauliflower to a serving dish, or let cool to room temperature, cover, and refrigerate until ready to serve. Before serving, garnish with the cilantro and lime wedges.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":254,\"sugar\":12,\"carbohydrates\":42,\"fiber\":9,\"protein\":8,\"fat\":8}','\"This jerk cauliflower is a great appetizer option for any crowd. Coated with flavorful jerk sauce, then pan-fried until golden brown, you\\u2019ll love this new take on cauliflower whether you eat vegetarian or not.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/1bee9dfe4da14eb69b4e96427de46369/FB.jpg\"','3 tablespoons kosher salt||1 teaspoon garlic powder||1 teaspoon allspice||2 medium heads of cauliflower, cut into large florets||1 tablespoon canola oil, plus more as needed||6 tablespoons cornstarch||¼ cup chopped fresh cilantro leaves||1 lime, cut into wedges, for serving||','food_processor||stove_top||healthy||spatula||mixing_bowl||dinner||weeknight||high_fiber||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian'),('b0-7277f8c2c426','\"Kenyan Beef And Potato Pilau By Kiano Moju\"','{\"0\":\"Make the pilau masala: In a medium bowl, combine the cumin, paprika, cardamom, black pepper, and cloves. Set aside.\",\"1\":\"Heat a large pot over medium-high heat. Add the oil and red onion and sauté for 10-15 minutes, until dark brown.\",\"2\":\"Add the garlic, ginger, serrano chile, pilau masala, beef stock cubes, cinnamon stick, and cilantro. Cook for 1-2 minutes, until fragrant.\",\"3\":\"Add the beef and cook until browned, about 8 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Add the tomatoes and cook for 4-5 minutes, until the tomatoes have released their liquid.\",\"5\":\"Add the potatoes and the water. Bring to a boil and cook for 10 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Add the rice, stir, and cover. Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 20 minutes, until the rice is cooked and the liquid is absorbed.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":588,\"sugar\":9,\"carbohydrates\":82,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":18,\"fat\":17}','','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/9b3cd1b6c9f74e4e89604e94c3951bd0/BFV43575_PartyRiceAroundAfrica-FB-V2.jpg\"','2 teaspoons ground cumin||1 tablespoon paprika||1 teaspoon ground cardamom||1 teaspoon black pepper||¼ teaspoon ground cloves||','casual_party||pan_fry||comfort_food||big_batch||special_occasion||stove_top||dinner||measuring_spoons||liquid_measuring_cup||dry_measuring_cups||mixing_bowl||pyrex||whisk||wooden_spoon||strainer||sauce_pan||epoca_walmart||chefs_knife||cutting_board||kenyan||low_sugar||dairy_free||east_africa_african_cuisine'),('b0-880a2cb6205a','\"Banana Muffin Mug\"','{\"0\":\"Mix together egg white and honey in a greased coffee mug.\",\"1\":\"Add oat flour, baking powder, and cinnamon, and mix until combined.\",\"2\":\"Add in fresh bananas.\",\"3\":\"Microwave on high for 90 seconds (times may vary).\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":106,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":15,\"fat\":9,\"calories\":542,\"sugar\":64}','','1','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/1ad3eaa777404ba7909eda11ccd732bd/Final.jpg\"','1 banana||¼ cup oat flour||½ teaspoon baking powder||2 tablespoons honey||1 egg white||½ teaspoon cinnamon||','microwave||easy||breakfast||brunch||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||spatula||pyrex||high_fiber||dairy_free||vegetarian||walmart_meal_planning'),('b0-ad9224a98cc3','\"Chicken Parm Bake With Roasted Broccoli\"','{\"0\":\"Season both sides of chicken breasts with salt, pepper, garlic powder, onion powder, oregano, and basil.\",\"1\":\"Sear in an oiled pan over high heat until the outside is brown and crisp, about 5 minutes per side.\",\"2\":\"Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\",\"3\":\"Transfer chicken to a cutting board and dice.\",\"4\":\"Place spaghetti in a greased 9x13 (23x32 cm) glass baking dish. Spread 2 cups (510g) of marinara over spaghetti.\",\"5\":\"Layer on the chicken, remaining marinara, mozzarella, parmesan, and bread crumbs. Bake for 35 minutes.\",\"6\":\"In a bowl, combine broccoli, oil, salt, and pepper. Place on a baking sheet, and bake 15 minutes.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":47,\"fat\":18,\"calories\":569,\