. Toss until well coated, adding some of the reserved pasta water as needed to loosen the sauce. Add about half of the crisped pancetta and sage and stir to incorporate.\",\"8\":\"Transfer the pasta to serving bowls and garnish with the remaining sage and pancetta.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":31,\"fat\":85,\"calories\":1441,\"sugar\":13,\"carbohydrates\":137}','\"This quick and easy creamy butternut squash Alfredo will become your new favorite pasta.\"','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/0cc5a87831094945becec61033edb0e1/BFV74895_20Minmeals_Episode002_YT.jpg\"','Kosher salt, to taste||1 tablespoon olive oil, plus more as needed||4 ounces pancetta, diced||12 fresh sage leaves||1 shallot, thinly sliced||3 garlic cloves, smashed||¼ cup dry white wine||10 ounces frozen butternut squash||1 cup chicken stock||¼ cup heavy cream||8 ounces dried pappardelle noodles||½ cup grated Parmesan cheese, plus more for serving||','stove_top||comfort_food||italian||chefs_knife||dinner||easy||date_night||weeknight||high_protein||high_fiber||under_30_minutes||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour'),('b0-ea1d40c04538','\"Eggplant Parm Penne\"','{\"0\":\"Line a baking sheet with paper towels. Spread the eggplant on the prepared baking sheet and season with the salt. Let sit for 20–30 minutes to draw out excess moisture.\",\"1\":\"While the eggplant drains, add the bread crumbs and flour to 2 separate small bowls. Beat the eggs in a third small bowl.\",\"2\":\"Pat the eggplant dry with paper towels. Dredge each piece of eggplant in the flour to coat thoroughly, shaking off any excess. Dip each piece in the eggs, then coat in the bread crumbs, pressing to adhere.\",\"3\":\"Heat the canola oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until it shimmers. Working in batches to avoid overcrowding the pan, add the eggplant to the hot oil and fry until golden brown on all sides, about 5 minutes. Transfer to a paper towel–lined sheet tray to drain.\",\"4\":\"*Tip: Eggplant can alternatively be oven or air fried. Cooking times will vary.\",\"5\":\"Heat the Prego® Traditional Italian Sauce in a medium pot over medium heat for about 5 minutes, or until warmed through.\",\"6\":\"Add the cooked penne, fried eggplant, mozzarella, and half of the basil to the sauce, and toss to combine.\",\"7\":\"Garnish with remaining basil.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":10,\"carbohydrates\":91,\"fiber\":7,\"protein\":25,\"fat\":21,\"calories\":661}','\"Upgrade your pasta night with this easy spin on a classic dish!\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/343655.jpg\"','1 large eggplant, cut into 1-inch pieces||1 tablespoon kosher salt||½ cup Italian-style bread crumbs||½ cup all-purpose flour||2 large eggs||¼ cup canola oil||16 ounces dried penne pasta, cooked according to package instructions||1 24-ounce jar of Prego® Traditional Italian Sauce||8 ounces fresh mozzarella cheese, torn into 1-inch pieces||¼ cup roughly chopped fresh basil, divided||','stove_top||mixing_bowl||wooden_spoon||baking_pan||dinner||special_occasion||weeknight||comfort_food||italian||high_protein||high_fiber||vegetarian'),('b1-29d2ad57ab28','\"Mushroom Wellington\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\",\"1\":\"Add the mushrooms to a food processor and pulse until crumbly, 10-12 times. Be careful not to over-process.\",\"2\":\"Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a medium pan over medium heat. Add the onion and sauté for 3-5 minutes. Add the vegetable broth and sauté until the onions are translucent and most of the broth has evaporated.\",\"3\":\"Add the garlic and sauté for 3 minutes more, or until fragrant.\",\"4\":\"Add the mushrooms and soy sauce and sauté until most of the liquid has released from the mushrooms and evaporated, 10-12 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Push the sautéed veggies to the sides of the pan and add a bit more olive oil to the center. Sauté the thyme in the oil until fragrant, then incorporate into the rest of mixture.\",\"6\":\"Add the spinach and sauté until wilted.\",\"7\":\"Grease an 18 x 13-inch baking sheet with nonstick spray. On a lightly floured surface, use a rolling pin to roll out puff pastry sheet to fit the baking sheet. Transfer the puff pastry to the pan.\",\"8\":\"In center third of the pastry, add a layer of potato slices. Top with half of the mushroom mixture and spread in an even layer, about ¾-inch thick. Add another layer of potatoes and the rest of the mushrooms, and top with a final layer of potatoes.\",\"9\":\"Fold one side of pastry over the filling, then the other side. Seal the top and bottom ends over the filling. Score the top of the Wellington diagonally with a sharp knife.\",\"10\":\"In a ramekin or small bowl, combine the non-dairy milk with the remaining tablespoon of olive oil. Brush over the Wellington. Decorate with more pastry, if desired. Poke air vents in the side of the Wellington.\",\"11\":\"Bake for 35-40 minutes. until golden brown and puffed.\",\"12\":\"Let rest for 10 minutes before cutting into thick slices.\",\"13\":\"Serve with vegan gravy.\",\"14\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":48,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":9,\"fat\":34,\"calories\":528,\"sugar\":5}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/768d4857b8974a03aa46b23c41871439/HolidayMainsNEWESTFB.jpg\"','16 ounces cremini mushrooms||3 tablespoons olive oil, divided||1 onion, thinly sliced||¼ cup vegetable broth||3 cloves garlic, minced||2 tablespoons soy sauce||1 tablespoon fresh thyme||4 ounces spinach||n/a||1 sheet puff pastry||Flour, for rolling out puff pastry||n/a||1 tablespoon non-dairy milk||n/a||','stove_top||cutting_board||christmas||cooling_rack||spatula||rolling_pin||special_occasion||baking_pan||food_processor||wooden_spoon||american||liquid_measuring_cup||pyrex||saute_pan||bake||cast_iron_pan||thanksgiving||dinner||parchment_paper||oven_mitts||peeler||comfort_food||stuffed||chefs_knife||pan_fry||thanksgiving_vegetarian||shoppable_recipes_holiday_dinners||low_sugar||vegetarian'),('b1-5f7c10fc1504','\"Birthday Cake In A Jar\"','{\"0\":\"Add the angel food cake mix and yellow cake mix to a jar. Place a cupcake liner over the cake mix and add the rainbow sprinkles. Cover with the lid.\",\"1\":\"Store in the pantry for up to 3 months.\",\"2\":\"When ready to eat, remove the lid and cupcake liner with the sprinkles from the jar. Pour the water into the dry cake mix. Mix thoroughly, making sure to scrape the dry mix from the bottom of the jar.\",\"3\":\"Microwave for 20 seconds.\",\"4\":\"Pour the sprinkles into the jar and gently stir to distribute, being careful not to push all of the sprinkles to the bottom.\",\"5\":\"Microwave for another 40 seconds, until cooked through.\",\"6\":\"Top with whipped cream and rainbow sprinkles, if desired.\",\"7\":\"Serve immediately.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":2,\"fat\":1,\"calories\":165,\"sugar\":23,\"carbohydrates\":36}','','1','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/879fa890fcd64f02a25d58f94613ca49/BFV44252PantryPrepCakeInAJar4WaysFBFinalupdated.jpg\"','2 tablespoons angel food cake mix||2 tablespoons yellow cake mix||1 teaspoon rainbow sprinkles, plus more for serving (optional)||2 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon water||Whipped cream, for serving (optional)||','microwave||kid_friendly||american||measuring_spoons||one_pot_or_pan||baking_cups||no_bake_desserts||indulgent_sweets||oven_mitts||meal_prep||weeknight||easy||desserts||epoca_walmart||low_calorie||low_fat'),('b1-bfa35787ab8a','\"Braised Chicken Thighs With Red Rice As Made By Hugh Acheson\"','{\"0\":\"Season the chicken thighs on both sides with the salt and pepper.\",\"1\":\"Heat the oil in a wide, heavy-bottomed pot with a lid over medium heat. When the oil is hot, add the chicken thighs, skin-side down and let cook without disturbing for 10 minutes. This will allow the skin to caramelize and develop a ton of flavor in the process. Turn the thighs over, cook for 1 minute more, then transfer to a plate.\",\"2\":\"Add the onion, tomatoes, poblano, garlic, and paprika to the pan. Cook for 5 minutes, until the vegetables are softened.\",\"3\":\"Carefully add the vinegar and stir to loosen any browned bits stuck to the bottom of the pot. Cook until the vinegar is reduced by half, 2-4 minutes, then pour in the stock.\",\"4\":\"Return the chicken to the pan, skin-side up. Cover and reduce the heat to low. Cook for 20 minutes, then remove lid and continue cooking until the internal temperature of the chicken thighs reaches 165˚F (75˚C).\",\"5\":\"Meanwhile, make the red rice: In a large pan, cook the slab bacon over medium heat until the fat renders and it begins to crisp, 5-8 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Add the onion, bell pepper, celery, and jalapeño and cook until softened, about 10 minutes.\",\"7\":\"Add the rice and stir until toasted, about 2 minutes.\",\"8\":\"Stir in the tomatoes, ½ cup (100 G) of the reserved tomato juice, bay leaves, and season with salt. 9. Add the chicken broth.  Bring to a boil, then cover, reduce the heat to low, and simmer for 20 minutes, until the liquid is absorbed and the rice is tender.\",\"9\":\"Serve the chicken over the rice with some of the braising jus and vegetables ladled over.\",\"10\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":24,\"fat\":14,\"calories\":456,\"sugar\":6,\"carbohydrates\":56}','\"My father who has Alzheimer\\u2019s was born in Havana, Cuba and this recipe is something that he and I would make. I partnered with the Alzheimer\\u2019s Association to tell my story about gathering around the table and sustaining family history through food. I firmly believe in getting people to cook, no matter what. When we cook and share food together, we build indelible memories of conversations and stories. Through some love and heart, this easy recipe blends the thriftiness of chicken thighs, simple vegetables, and rice into something nourishing\\u2026 and really tasty.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/221280.jpg\"','4 bone-in, skin-on chicken thighs, 5-6 ounces each (about 1½ pounds total)||½ teaspoon sea salt||¼ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper||1 tablespoon canola oil||1 cup minced yellow onion||1 cup diced fresh tomatoes||1 poblano chile, seeded and minced||3 cloves garlic, thinly sliced||¼ teaspoon hot smoked paprika||½ cup red wine vinegar||1 cup low-sodium chicken stock||','chefs_knife||wooden_spoon||liquid_measuring_cup||measuring_spoons||dinner||dry_measuring_cups||stove_top||tongs||saute_pan||cutting_board||pyrex||spatula||pan_fry||date_night||special_occasion||dairy_free'),('b2-0b520c910141','\"Simple Veggie Curry\"','{\"0\":\"Place potatoes into a large pot or dutch oven and cover with well-salted water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to a simmer, cover and let the potatoes cook until fork tender–about 12 minutes. Once cooked, drain the potatoes and set them aside.\",\"1\":\"Return the pot to the stove and add 1 tablespoon of oil. Add onion and garlic and sauté over medium heat until onion is tender and starts to turn translucent, about 3-5 minutes.\",\"2\":\"Add cumin, cayenne, curry powder, salt, pepper and ginger. Stir to combine before adding tomatoes, chickpeas, and peas.\",\"3\":\"Increase heat to medium-high and stir in the coconut milk. Bring to a simmer before adding the potatoes back to the pot. Reduce heat to low and cook everything together for 3-5 minutes before serving.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":25,\"carbohydrates\":110,\"fiber\":22,\"protein\":24,\"fat\":25,\"calories\":735}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/7ab114a20dec46c2a25a23f75c845b85/FB_1_.jpg\"','2 tablespoons salt, for water||2 pounds potatoes, cut to 1-inch cubes||1 tablespoon vegetable oil||1 medium onion, diced||4 cloves garlic, minced||2 teaspoons cumin||1 teaspoon cayenne||4 teaspoons curry powder||1 teaspoon salt||1 teaspoon black pepper||1-inch piece of ginger, minced||1 14-ounce can diced tomatoes||1 15-ounce can chickpeas, drained||1 15-ounce can peas, drained||1 14-ounce can coconut milk||','easy||weeknight||indian||dinner||gluten_free||healthy||dutch_oven||stove_top||american||one_pot_or_pan||cutting_board||chefs_knife||pyrex||wooden_spoon||measuring_spoons||sauce_pan||strainer'),('b2-356096dfab2a','\"Parchment Teriyaki Salmon\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C).\",\"1\":\"Fold the parchment paper in half, then open up.\",\"2\":\"On one half, lay down the broccoli and carrots. Drizzle on oil and sprinkle on salt \\u0026 pepper.\",\"3\":\"Lay the salmon on the veggies, and pour on teriyaki sauce.\",\"4\":\"Fold the parchment paper over the salmon, and cinch the paper together by folding it over itself along the edges.\",\"5\":\"Bake for 20 minutes or until internal temperature of salmon reaches 145˚F (63˚C).\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":8,\"carbohydrates\":21,\"fiber\":7,\"protein\":39,\"fat\":49,\"calories\":693}','','1','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/90a44ed9ca0b470b8638257ab2855d77/BFV10813_ParchmentBakedSalmon4Ways-FB1080SQ.jpg\"','½ cup carrots, thinly sliced||1 cup broccoli florets||Olive oil to taste||Salt & pepper to taste||n/a||200 grams skinless salmon||2 tablespoons teriyaki sauce||','oven||healthy||easy||one_pot_or_pan||dinner||bake||weeknight||seafood||fusion||parchment_paper||japanese||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||pyrex||baking_pan||oven_mitts||high_protein||high_fiber||dairy_free||pescatarian'),('b2-b851dac3b67c','\"Zesty Panko-Crusted Salmon And Asparagus\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 400˚F (200˚C). Grease a baking sheet with 1 tablespoon olive oil.\",\"1\":\"In a medium bowl, mix together the zesty seasoning and bread crumbs. In a separate medium bowl, beat the eggs.\",\"2\":\"Coat the salmon fillets in the egg, then the bread crumb mixture. Lay the salmon on the prepared baking sheet.\",\"3\":\"In another medium bowl, toss the asparagus with 1 tablespoon of olive oil, the salt, and pepper. Lay asparagus beside the salmon. Drizzle everything with the remaining tablespoon olive oil, then season with more salt to taste.\",\"4\":\"Bake for 10–12 minutes, until the salmon and asparagus are slightly golden. Switch the oven to broil and toast for 1-2 minutes until the breadcrumbs are a dark golden brown.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":34,\"fat\":29,\"calories\":484,\"sugar\":2,\"carbohydrates\":19,\"fiber\":2}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/243094.jpg\"','3 tablespoons olive oil, divided||1 1-ounce package of Tasty Zesty Spice Blend||¾ cup panko bread crumbs||2 large eggs||4 6-ounce boneless, skinless salmon fillets||1 pound asparagus||1½ teaspoons kosher salt, plus more to taste.||½ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper||','healthy||dinner||date_night||mccormick_seasoned_pro||weeknight||oven_mitts||bake||easy||oven||high_protein||low_sugar||under_30_minutes||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||dairy_free||pescatarian||walmart_meal_planning'),('b3-23302d94958e','\"Rustic German Potato Noodles\"','{\"0\":\"Peel potatoes. Cut them into 1-inch (2 ½ cm) slices and boil them in salted water for 25 minutes or until they are tender. \",\"1\":\"After boiling, take them out and let them cool for 10 minutes, allowing them to steam to remove excess moisture.\",\"2\":\"Mash potatoes until no lumps remain. \",\"3\":\"Add eggs, salt, nutmeg, and 2 cups (250 grams) flour, and knead into a dough. If dough is too sticky, add more flour until it holds its shape but is still smooth.\",\"4\":\"Put a piece of dough on a floured surface and roll into a 1-inch (2.5 cm) thick log.\",\"5\":\"Cut in 1-inch (2.5 cm) pieces and roll them carefully in your floured palm for a noodle shape. Repeat with the remainder of the dough.\",\"6\":\"Boil noodles in a large pot with salted water. Stir carefully once or twice to make sure noodles don’t stick to bottom of the pan. Once they float on the surface, they are cooked and ready to be taken out.\",\"7\":\"In a medium-sized pan, melt the butter.\",\"8\":\"Add noodles and bacon and fry until both are golden brown on all sides.\",\"9\":\"Add chicken broth and white wine and let reduce for a few minutes until sauce becomes slightly creamy.\",\"10\":\"Top with green onions before serving.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":27,\"fat\":16,\"calories\":726,\"sugar\":3,\"carbohydrates\":115,\"fiber\":5}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/6d7104be28e241cb8ccf9e8f72fa3b43/BFV13538_RolledPotatoNoodles-Schupfnudeln-ThumbTextless1080.jpg\"','4 yellow potatoes (we used yukon gold potatoes)||2 eggs||1 teaspoon salt||¼ teaspoon nutmeg||2-3 cups flour||1 tablespoon butter||½ cup bacon, diced||1 cup chicken broth||1/2 cup white wine||1 bunch green onion, chopped||n/a||Salt, for boiling water||','comfort_food||dinner||weeknight||stove_top||kid_friendly||pan_fry||german||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||liquid_measuring_cup||chefs_knife||cutting_board||saute_pan||pyrex||spatula||wooden_spoon||strainer||contains_alcohol'),('b3-2ca1d6da00ee','\"Chicken Alfredo Pizza\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 450°F (230°C).\",\"1\":\"Roll out dough to about 10-12 inches (25-30 cm) in diameter.\",\"2\":\"Top pizza with alfredo sauce, mozzarella cheese, chicken, and tomatoes.\",\"3\":\"Bake in oven for 15-20 minutes, or until crust is crispy and cheese is melted and turning golden brown.\",\"4\":\"Garnish with parsley and cut into 8 slices.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":29,\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":9,\"fat\":6,\"calories\":215,\"sugar\":1}','','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/0aab1ca281d840b982cfc858e075c1e3/BFV13268_ChickenAlfredoPizza-ThumbTextless1080.jpg\"','1 pizza dough||3 tablespoons alfredo sauce||½ cup mozzarella cheese||½ cup cooked chicken||1 cubed roma tomato||','oven||comfort_food||dinner||weeknight||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||baking_pan||rolling_pin||pyrex||easy||italian||fusion||american||oven_mitts'),('b3-4ccbb74b93be','\"One-Pan Salmon And Egg Bake\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 325°F (160°C).\",\"1\":\"Pour oil into a small, oven-safe skillet. Place the spinach and garlic in the skillet, season with a pinch of salt and pepper, and mix well so that everything is evenly coated.\",\"2\":\"Place the salmon on 1 side of the pan, then form a well on the other side and crack an egg, making sure it stays intact.\",\"3\":\"Season the tops of the salmon and the egg with another pinch of salt and pepper.\",\"4\":\"Bake for 20-25 minutes, until the salmon reaches an internal temperature of 140°F (60°C). (The temperature will continue to rise once it rests out of the oven.)\",\"5\":\"Squeeze a bit of fresh lemon juice over the salmon fillet for more flavor and let the salmon rest for 5 minutes before serving.\",\"6\":\"NOTE: If you want a runny egg yolk, follow steps 1-3, then place the skillet in the preheated oven. Halfway through the cooking process (about 10 minutes in), crack a cold egg into the well of the spinach and replace the skillet in the oven for another 10-15 minutes.  The salmon will be cooked through, the egg white will show color, and the yolk will be gloriously runny.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":41,\"calories\":603,\"sugar\":3,\"carbohydrates\":13,\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":43}','','1','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/1942a8682dfa4740bfd98b4cd0721286/BFV15167_SalmonAndEggBakeThumb.jpg\"','1 6-ounce (170 grams) fillet of salmon||1 egg||1 tablespoon olive oil||3 cups spinach, roughly chopped||1 clove garlic, minced||1 lemon, cut into wedges||Salt, to taste||Black pepper, to taste||','oven||american||healthy||gluten_free||dinner||bake||weeknight||one_pot_or_pan||measuring_spoons||chefs_knife||cutting_board||pyrex||dry_measuring_cups||oven_mitts||baking_pan||mccormick_ugc_one_pot_others'),('b3-4f8bd1e5acc3','\"Stir Fry Inspired By Migos\"','{\"0\":\"In a bowl, add the soy sauce, sesame oil, honey, rice vinegar, peanut butter, garlic, and ginger, and whisk to combine.\",\"1\":\"Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a wok or large pan over high heat. Once the oil begins to shimmer, add the cubed chicken and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the chicken is cooked through, about 5 to 7 minutes.\",\"2\":\"Transfer the chicken to the bowl, and wipe the wok clean.\",\"3\":\"Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in the cleaned wok over high heat.\",\"4\":\"Once the oil begins to shimmer, add the red onion, broccoli, and red cabbage, and cook, stirring frequently, for 3 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Add the red bell peppers and snap peas and cook for 3 minutes, stirring frequently, until the peppers begin to soften.\",\"6\":\"Add the carrots and cook for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.\",\"7\":\"Add the chicken, cooked rice noodles, and sauce, and stir until fully incorporated.\",\"8\":\"Serve with cilantro, scallions, and sesame seeds.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":22,\"carbohydrates\":126,\"fiber\":8,\"protein\":51,\"fat\":24,\"calories\":931}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/137484.jpg\"','1 cup soy sauce||4 cloves garlic, grated||2 teaspoons ginger, grated||2 tablespoons sesame oil||2 tablespoons rice vinegar||2 tablespoons honey||¼ cup creamy peanut butter||','wok||healthy||whisk||one_pot_or_pan||cooking_kit||easy||pan_fry||chinese||dinner||big_batch||weeknight||mixing_bowl||cutting_board||chefs_knife||colander||dry_measuring_cups||measuring_spoons||tongs||spatula||peeler||high_protein||high_fiber'),('b3-9a52917e7e57','\"Beef Rag\\u00F9\"','{\"0\":\"Season the meat on all sides with salt and pepper.\",\"1\":\"Heat a large heavy pot with a lid over medium-high heat. Add a tablespoon of olive oil and brown the meat in batches until a crust forms, turning to ensure even color on all sides.\",\"2\":\"Once one batch is done, set aside in a bowl or plate with a lip, add another fresh tablespoon of olive oil and continue until all the meat is brown.\",\"3\":\"Add another tablespoon of oil to the pan and sauté the onion, carrot, celery, and garlic until softened, about 3-4 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Pour in the wine and let it boil off and reduce until barely any remains in the pan.\",\"5\":\"Next, add the browned meat back to the pan, along with the tomato paste. Stir until tomato paste is coating all the ingredients and allow the paste to toast slightly.\",\"6\":\"Pour in the tomatoes, stock, and herb bundle and stir, bring to a simmer and cover with a lid.\",\"7\":\"Allow to simmer for 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Alternatively, if your pot and lid are oven safe, cook in a 325˚F (170˚C) oven for 3 hours.\",\"8\":\"Remove the herb bundle and beef shank.\",\"9\":\"Pull the meat from the oxtail. Using a fork or tongs, discarding the bone and any extra cartilage or extra fat. Add the meat back to the ragu and stir.\",\"10\":\"Skim off any extra fat from the top of the ragu.\",\"11\":\"Cook pasta in boiling salted water until al dente. Reserve 1 cup (120 ml) of the pasta water before draining.\",\"12\":\"Add a few ladlefuls of ragu, the pasta, and a splash of pasta water to a large pot, gently stir to coat the pasta in the ragu.\",\"13\":\"Add a handful of cheese and stir to melt into the sauce.\",\"14\":\"Garnish with more cheese and fresh parsley before serving.\",\"15\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":995,\"sugar\":18,\"carbohydrates\":111,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":57,\"fat\":30}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/936010f87a7e46609b65dcb765556584/FB-FinalReview-Revised.jpg\"','1 pound large tube or ribbon pasta (we used paccheri)||4 tablespoons olive oil||1 pound beef chuck roast, diced (or any stew meat at your supermarket)||1 pound oxtail (or beef shank||1 onion, diced||1 carrot, diced||1 stalk celery, diced||3 cloves garlic, minced||2 tablespoons tomato paste||½ cup red wine (we used zinfandel. Malbec or cabernet sauvignon would be great too!)||32 ounces beef stock||28 ounces diced tomatoes||3 sprigs each thyme, rosema