the desired amount of bone broth depending on how soupy you like your ramen!\",\"2\":\"Let cook for another 1-2 minutes while stirring occasionally. Season with Everything Bagel Seasoning of whatever you would like! (Ex: Green Onion, Egg, Hot Sauce)\",\"3\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":70,\"fiber\":16,\"protein\":11,\"fat\":15,\"calories\":475,\"sugar\":6}','\"Bone Broth Ramen is the perfect lazy meal for one! Curl up on the couch with a warm bowl of this protein packed recipe. Add leftover or frozen veggies to your pan to mix it up. Make sure to throw in any leftover protein you have in the fridge like chicken, tofu or bacon!\"','1','\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/video-api-prod/assets/fa8e717bf37d4a83abf7b2869810c2f9/BoneBrothRamen.jpeg\"','1 1/2 Cup of water||1 Cup of frozen vegetables||1 Ramen Packet with seasoning||¼  Bone Broth||Everything Bagel Seasoning to garnish||','wok||stove_top||japanese||one_pot_or_pan||healthy||easy||lunch||pan_fry||dinner||comfort_food||steam||high_fiber||5_ingredients_or_less||under_30_minutes||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian'),('b4-4e7eaa76f62d','\"Teriyaki Steak Roll-ups\"','{\"0\":\"In a baking dish with the steak, mix the soy sauce, garlic, ginger, honey, lime juice, and Sriracha sauce (optional).\",\"1\":\"Lightly massage the marinade into the steak and cover. Refrigerate 1-4 hours.\",\"2\":\"Place toothpicks in a bowl and pour water over toothpicks until completely submerged. Water will prevent toothpicks from burning.\",\"3\":\"Once marinated, cut the steak into 8 equal rectangles. You may need to pound the steak thinner if using a thicker cut.\",\"4\":\"Place a few slices of each of the vegetables on a slice of steak, making sure they are all about the same length.\",\"5\":\"Roll the steak up over the vegetables and secure it with a toothpick.\",\"6\":\"In a small saucepan over medium heat, pour in the leftover marinade and bring to a boil.\",\"7\":\"Boil for about one minute, take off the heat, and set aside to use as a glaze.\",\"8\":\"In a grill pan or on the grill over medium high heat, place your steak roll-ups and cook for 2-3 minutes.\",\"9\":\"Flip the roll over and use a heat-safe brush to brush the glaze on each roll.\",\"10\":\"Cook for about one minute longer and remove from heat. Top with sesame seeds.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":13,\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":18,\"fat\":4,\"calories\":166,\"sugar\":8}','','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/3c21ae2aab744479ac08dd7d7c43ada8/BFV21906_Teriyaki_Steak_Roll_Ups-FB.jpg\"','1 pound skirt or flank steak||½ cup soy sauce||3 cloves garlic, minced||1 tablespoon ginger, grated||2 tablespoons honey||1 lime, juiced||1 teaspoon Sriracha sauce, optional||1 bell pepper, cut into matchsticks||1 carrot, cut into matchsticks||½ zucchini, cut into matchsticks||16 asparagus stalks, halved||1 red onion, sliced||Sesame seeds, for serving||n/a||','stove_top||american||comfort_food||easy||dinner||weeknight||bbq||liquid_measuring_cup||chefs_knife||cutting_board||baking_pan||tongs||pyrex||sauce_pan||spatula||measuring_spoons||low_carb||low_calorie||dairy_free'),('b4-57d88f18cccd','\"Spaghetti Squash Stir Fry\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\",\"1\":\"Place the squash halves, cut-side up, on a baking sheet. Coat the exposed flesh with the canola oil, then sprinkle with ¼ teaspoon salt. Flip over so the cut side is down, then bake for 40–50 minutes, until the squash is just barely tender when pierced with a fork. Remove from the oven and let cool slightly.\",\"2\":\"Line a baking sheet with 2 clean kitchen towels.\",\"3\":\"Use a fork to scrape out the “spaghetti” strands from the squash onto the prepared baking sheet and season with the remaining ¼ teaspoon salt, tossing to distribute. Let cool for 30 minutes. The spaghetti squash can be made ahead and stored in the refrigerator in an airtight container for up to 2 days. If using from the cold, remove the squash from the refrigerator 30 minutes before cooking.\",\"4\":\"While the squash is cooling, make the sauce: In a medium bowl, whisk together the cornstarch and cold water until smooth. Grate the garlic on a microplane directly into the bowl. Add the ginger, red pepper flakes, soy sauce, honey, sesame oil, and rice vinegar and stir to incorporate. Whisk in the water until smooth.\",\"5\":\"Make the stir fry: Heat 1 tablespoon canola oil in a 12-inch skillet or wok over medium-high heat. Add 1 clove of garlic and stir for about 30 seconds, until fragrant. Add the chicken, ⅛ teaspoon red pepper flakes, and ½ teaspoon salt and stir to coat. Cook the chicken for 6–8 minutes, letting it brown without stirring, until no pink remains and the chicken is cooked through. Transfer the chicken to a plate or bowl.\",\"6\":\"Reduce the heat to medium. Without wiping out the pan, add the remaining tablespoon canola oil, remaining garlic clove, and remaining ⅛ teaspoon red pepper flakes and cook for 30 seconds, until fragrant. Add the bell peppers and broccoli, stir to coat, then deglaze the pan with the water, scraping up all the browned bits stuck to the bottom of the pan. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the broccoli is starting to soften, 8–10 minutes.\",\"7\":\"Add the carrots and cook for another 2 minutes, then add the snow peas and season with a pinch of salt. Cook for another 2–3 minutes, until all of the vegetables are tender. Transfer the vegetables to the plate with the chicken.\",\"8\":\"Roll up the spaghetti squash in the kitchen towels and wring to squeeze as much water as possible.\",\"9\":\"Add 2 tablespoons of sauce to the pan and let come to a simmer, then add the spaghetti squash and stir constantly until heated through, 1–2 minutes. Divide the squash among serving bowls.\",\"10\":\"Pour the remaining sauce into the pan and let simmer for about 1 minute, until thickened. Return the chicken and vegetables to the pan and toss to coat evenly in the sauce and heat everything through, 2-3 minutes. Divide among the bowls atop the squash. Garnish each bowl with thinly sliced scallions. Serve immediately.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":22,\"calories\":497,\"sugar\":18,\"carbohydrates\":36,\"fiber\":7,\"protein\":41}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/298427.jpg\"','1 3–4 pound spaghetti squash, halved lengthwise and seeded||2 tablespoons canola oil||½ teaspoon kosher salt, divided||','mixing_bowl||wooden_spoon||baking_pan||oven_mitts||dinner||special_occasion||oven||stove_top||fusion||high_protein||high_fiber||dairy_free'),('b4-5e4ce40e5db5','\"Sheet-Pan Steak Fajitas\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 450°F (230°C).\",\"1\":\"Lay the flank steak in the middle of a baking sheet. Arrange the bell peppers and red onion around it. Drizzle everything with olive oil and season with salt, pepper, chili powder, garlic powder, and cumin.\",\"2\":\"Using your hands, rub the seasoning into the vegetables, then into the steak. Flip the steak and season the other side.\",\"3\":\"Squeeze the lime juice over the top of the steak and veggies.\",\"4\":\"Cook for 12 minutes, or until the meat has reached your desired doneness.\",\"5\":\"Transfer the steak to a cutting board and let it rest for 10 minutes, then slice it into pieces, going against the grain.\",\"6\":\"Fill up a warm tortilla with the steak, bell peppers, and onion.\",\"7\":\"Garnish with cilantro, and serve.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":19,\"fat\":10,\"calories\":287,\"sugar\":3,\"carbohydrates\":28}','','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/77f049ac834b48e2bfb307821778c000/BFV39745_Low-StressDinners_FB.jpg\"','1 pound flank steak||1 green bell pepper, sliced||1 yellow bell pepper, sliced||1 red bell pepper, sliced||½ red onion, sliced||Olive oil, to taste||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||Chili powder, to taste||Garlic powder, to taste||Cumin, to taste||Juice of ½ lime||Chopped cilantro, for garnish||8 whole grain tortillas, warmed||','oven||easy||baking_pan||healthy||dinner||one_pot_or_pan||game_day||bake||weeknight||oven_mitts||chefs_knife||cutting_board||mexican||tongs||measuring_spoons||low_sugar||dairy_free'),('b4-a3369d6cb92b','\"Tofu Buddha Bowl\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 400˚F (200˚C).\",\"1\":\"Make the tofu marinade: In a medium bowl, mix together the sesame oil, mirin, Fiery spice blend, and salt.\",\"2\":\"Cut the tofu lengthwise into ½-inch (1 ¼ cm) wide slabs, then cut each slab in half lengthwise. Cut each strip into ½-inch (1 ¼ cm) wide cubes. Toss with the marinade, then cover with plastic wrap marinate in the fridge for at least 1 hour.\",\"3\":\"Fill a large pot with cold water, season well with salt, and add the sweet potatoes. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce the heat to low and simmer until the sweet potatoes can be pierced with a fork but still give some resistance, about 20 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Remove sweet potatoes from the pot and set aside to cool. Drop in the broccoli florets and blanch for 90 seconds. Remove the broccoli and shock in an ice bath to stop the cooking. Cool completely, about 60 seconds, then transfer to a paper towel-lined plate to drain.\",\"5\":\"Cut the cooled sweet potato into ½-inch (1 ¼ cm) wide half moons and season with salt to taste.\",\"6\":\"On a lightly greased baking sheet, spread out the marinated tofu and sweet potato. Bake for 20 minutes, until sweet potatoes and tofu begin to brown.\",\"7\":\"While the sweet potatoes and tofu cook, make the peanut sauce: In a medium bowl, whisk together the peanut butter, apple cider vinegar, Fiery spice blend, and ¼ cup water. Add more water as necessary to achieve a pourable, but not runny, consistency. Season with salt to taste.\",\"8\":\"Assemble the bowls: Add 1 cup (170 G) of quinoa to the bottom of a serving bowl, then arrange about 2½ ounces (70 G) of tofu, ½ cup (112 G) sweet potato, ½ cup (75 G) broccoli florets, ½ cup (50 G) purple cabbage, ¼ cup (30 G) cucumber, and 4-5 slices of avocado on top. Drizzle with 2-3 tablespoons peanut sauce and top with crushed peanuts, cilantro, and mint.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":39,\"fat\":32,\"calories\":998,\"sugar\":12,\"carbohydrates\":143,\"fiber\":23}','\"\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/78fe6fc3f4bc41edbf75174aaa20618b.jpeg\"','2 tablespoons sesame oil||2 tablespoons sweet mirin||1 tablespoon McCormick® Fiery Spice Blend||1 teaspoon kosher salt, plus more to taste||1 16-ounce package of extra-firm tofu, drained and patted dry||2 medium sweet potatoes, peeled||2 medium broccoli crowns, cut into florets||6 cups cooked quinoa||3 cups purple cabbage, thinly sliced||1 English cucumber, julienned||1 large avocado, thinly sliced||⅓ cup crushed roasted peanuts, for garnish||3 tablespoons fresh cilantro leaves, for garnish||3 tablespoons torn fresh mint leaves, for garnish||','club_house_seasoned_pro||healthy||meal_prep||lunch||high_protein||high_fiber||under_1_hour||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian||contains_alcohol||american||jamaican||kenyan'),('b4-a44deeafcde3','\"The Best Layered Lasagna\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\",\"1\":\"Add the olive oil and butter to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Once warmed, add the onion, carrot, celery, and garlic. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown, 10-12 minutes. Once the vegetables have caramelized, add the beef, pork, salt, pepper, and tomato paste. Stir to combine, breaking up the pieces of meat, until the meat has browned, 15-20 minutes.\",\"2\":\"Once the sauce is dark brown and starting to stick slightly to the bottom of the pan, add the red wine. Scrape the bottom of the pan with a wooden spoon to release all the cooked brown bits. Once the wine comes to a simmer, add the diced canned tomatoes, and stir to combine. Bring the sauce to a simmer and cook for at least 30 minutes (the longer the better!) stirring occasionally.\",\"3\":\"In a large bowl, mix together the ricotta, basil, Parmesan, parsley, egg, salt, and pepper.\",\"4\":\"In a 9x13-inch (23x33 cm) glass baking dish, add a layer of bolognese to the bottom. Top with noodles, then spread a layer of the ricotta mixture on top. Repeat with another layer of bolognese, noodles, ricotta, noodles, bolognese, then top with mozzarella and additional Parmesan. Cover the pan with foil and bake for 25 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Remove the foil and bake for another 15 minutes, until the cheese on top has browned and the bolognese is bubbling. Slice and serve.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":35,\"fat\":29,\"calories\":590,\"sugar\":5,\"carbohydrates\":31,\"fiber\":2}','','12','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/01cfdd3c80844c63baae4784b53df3f4/FB_2.jpg\"','2 tablespoons olive oil||2 tablespoons butter||1 onion, finely chopped||½ cup carrots, finely chopped||½ cup celery, finely chopped||1 pound ground beef||1 pound ground pork||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||½ cup tomato paste||2 cups red wine||4 cups diced canned tomatoes||','comfort_food||easy||italian||american||oven||dinner||kid_friendly||bake||weeknight||casual_party||stove_top||fusion||big_batch||lunch||pan_fry||spatula||wooden_spoon||pyrex||one_top_friendly||contains_alcohol||high_protein'),('b4-d395eaa76002','\"Carne Asada Tacos\"','{\"0\":\"In a large bowl, whisk together the oil, vinegar, lime juice, orange juice, garlic, jalapeño, chopped cilantro, salt, coriander, cumin, pepper, and chili powder.\",\"1\":\"Place the steak in a gallon-size resealable bag. Pour in 1 cup (240 ml) of the marinade and set the rest aside. Seal the bag and shake to evenly coat the steak in the marinade. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour, or up to 4 hours.\",\"2\":\"In a small saucepan, bring the reserved ½ cup (120 ml) of marinade to a boil over medium-high heat. Cook until thickened and reduced by half, about 5 minutes. Remove from the heat and set aside.\",\"3\":\"Heat a large grill pan over high heat until very hot. Remove the steak from the bag and discard the marinade. Cook the steak on 1 side until there are dark grill marks and it is beginning to caramelize around the edges, about 6 minutes. Flip and cook on the other side for 5 minutes for medium rare, or 7 minutes for medium. Transfer to a cutting board and let rest for 5 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Working in batches, heat the corn tortillas in a pan over medium-high heat, turning with tongs, until softened and just beginning to brown in spots, about 1 minute per side. Wrap the toasted tortillas in foil to keep warm.\",\"5\":\"Thinly slice the steak against the grain, then cut the slices in half. Transfer to a large bowl and toss with the reduced marinade to coat.\",\"6\":\"Serve the steak with the warm tortillas, pico de gallo, guacamole, sour cream, cotija cheese, and cilantro leaves, if desired.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":34,\"fat\":28,\"calories\":497,\"sugar\":2,\"carbohydrates\":26,\"fiber\":29}','\"These carne asada tacos come together easily as a hearty dinner or lunch for 4. The orange juice and lemon juice fill the marinade with flavor. Reserve some marinade, then reduce it down and use it to glaze the grilled steak at the end. Serve the tacos with your favorite toppings like pico de gallo and guacamole!\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/215431.jpg\"','⅓ cup canola oil||⅓ cup distilled white vinegar||⅓ cup fresh lime juice (about 4 limes)||⅓ cup fresh orange juice (about 1½ navel oranges)||4 teaspoons minced garlic (about 4 cloves)||3 tablespoons minced jalapeño (about 1 medium)||¼ cup fresh cilantro, finely chopped, plus whole leaves for serving (optional)||2 teaspoons kosher salt||1 teaspoon ground coriander||½ teaspoon ground cumin||1 teaspoon ground black pepper||1 teaspoon chili powder||1 1-pound flank steak||8 5-inch white corn tortillas||Pico de gallo, for serving||Guacamole, for serving||Sour cream, for serving||Cotija cheese, crumbled, for serving||','dinner||stove_top||mexican||cutting_board||weeknight||tongs||measuring_spoons||whisk||liquid_measuring_cup||mixing_bowl||date_night||comfort_food||kid_friendly||chefs_knife||pyrex||pan_fry||saute_pan||cast_iron_pan||dry_measuring_cups||high_protein||low_sugar'),('b4-f11a4ecb4630','\"Seafood Casserole As Made By Betsy\\u2019s Gammy\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 350˚F (180˚C).\",\"1\":\"Spread the bread in a single layer on a rimmed baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes, until lightly toasted. Let cool to room temperature. Leave the oven on.\",\"2\":\"Add the toasted bread to a food processor and pulse until finely ground. You should have about 4 cups (460 G) of bread crumbs.\",\"3\":\"In a large bowl, combine the bread crumbs, 4 tablespoons of melted butter, the cheddar cheese, and 1 teaspoon of salt and toss to combine. Set aside.\",\"4\":\"In a medium pot, combine 4 cups (960 ml) of white wine and a generous pinch of salt and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Add the shrimp and cook until bright pink, about 1 minute. Use a spider or slotted spoon to transfer the shrimp to a colander to drain.\",\"5\":\"Return the wine to a boil. Add the scallops and cook until just opaque, about 2 minutes. Transfer the scallops to a colander to drain.\",\"6\":\"Chop the shrimp and scallops into bite-size pieces. Transfer to large bowl, along with the crab and 1 teaspoon of salt. Toss to combine.\",\"7\":\"In a liquid measuring cup or medium bowl, whisk together the half-and-half, 3 tablespoons of melted butter, the flour, Worcestershire sauce, paprika, lemon juice, ketchup, remaining tablespoon of white wine, and remaining teaspoon of salt.\",\"8\":\"Brush the remaining tablespoon of melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch (22 x 33 cm) baking dish.\",\"9\":\"Scatter the artichokes in an even layer over the bottom of the baking dish. Scoop the seafood mixture over the artichokes. Pour the sauce over the seafood. Top with the bread crumb mixture.\",\"10\":\"Bake the casserole for 20-25 minutes, or until bubbling and golden brown.\",\"11\":\"Top with chives and serve with lemon wedges.\",\"12\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":61,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":52,\"fat\":40,\"calories\":842,\"sugar\":6}','\"Take your taste buds on a trip to the East Coast with this creamy casserole from Betsy\\u2019s grandmother. Get creative by using your favorite seafood, but if you decide to stick with shrimp and scallops, keep an eye on them, as they cook quickly. For extra crunch, don\\u2019t over-pulse the bread crumbs. Serve the casserole with a light salad and watch as your guests gush over what\\u2019s sure to be your new summer staple.\"','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/209837.jpg\"','1 medium loaf of sourdough bread (about 1 pound), roughly torn||8 tablespoons (1 stick) unsalted butter, melted, divided||1 cup shredded cheddar cheese||3 teaspoons kosher salt, divided, plus more to taste||4 cups plus 1 tablespoon dry white wine, divided||1 pound 16/20-count shrimp, peeled and deveined||1 pound large scallops||1 pound jumbo lump crabmeat||2 cups half-and-half||3 tablespoons all-purpose flour||1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce||1 teaspoon paprika||1 tablespoon lemon juice||2 tablespoons ketchup||2 14-ounce cans of artichoke hearts, drained and chopped||Chopped fresh chives, for garnish||Lemon wedges, for serving||','cutting_board||stove_top||big_batch||cheese_grater||seafood||bake||whisk||oven||colander||chefs_knife||liquid_measuring_cup||oven_mitts||measuring_spoons||comfort_food||dinner||mixing_bowl||spider||food_processor||tongs||baking_pan||spatula||contains_alcohol||high_protein||high_fiber||pescatarian'),('b5-8c75fcd3318c','\"Caprese Zucchini-Wrapped Quiche\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C). Grease a 12-cup muffin tin with nonstick spray.\",\"1\":\"Trim the ends from the zucchini, then slice lengthwise with a vegetable peeler.\",\"2\":\"Line the muffin cups with the zucchini strips.\",\"3\":\"In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, tomato, milk, salt, and pepper.\",\"4\":\"Add a few pieces of mozzarella to each zucchini cup.\",\"5\":\"Divide the egg mixture evenly among the cups. Sprinkle the basil on top.\",\"6\":\"Bake for 18 minutes, until the edges are slightly browned.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":4,\"calories\":80,\"sugar\":1,\"carbohydrates\":2,\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":6}','','12','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/e0c40e0b65ea4222b56ca85d5c434a49/V3.jpg\"','Nonstick cooking spray||2 medium zucchini||6 large eggs||½ cup diced tomato||½ cup milk||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||½-¾ cup diced fresh mozzarella cheese||Chopped fresh basil, for sprinkling||','brunch||one_top_app_veggies||oven||healthy||cupcake_pan||kid_friendly||one_top_app_eggs||meal_prep||baking_cups||liquid_measuring_cup||bake||easy||breakfast||peeler||whisk||american||appetizers||big_batch||chefs_knife||cutting_board||mixing_bowl||pyrex||oven_mitts||low_carb||low_calorie||low_sugar||vegetarian'),('b5-d7c49d32f461','\"Grilled Cauliflower Tacos\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C).\",\"1\":\"In a wide, shallow dish, combine the avocado oil, lime juice, brown sugar, cumin, oregano, paprika, chipotle powder, chile powder, garlic powder, and salt and whisk well. Add the cauliflower to the dish and coat each piece thoroughly with the marinade. Cover and refrigerate while you prepare the poblano-pepita sauce, or for up to 2 hours.\",\"2\":\"On a rimmed baking sheet, toss the poblanos, garlic, and jalapeños with 1 tablespoon of avocado oil. Roast for 30 minutes, or until the skin is beginning to pull away from the flesh of the peppers and the garlic is soft and golden brown. Add the pepitas to the pan and return to the oven for another 5–8 minutes, until beginning to brown.\",\"3\":\"Transfer the poblanos, jalapeños, and garlic to a medium bowl and cover with a plate or plastic wrap. Set aside to cool for 30 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Once cool enough to handle, carefully remove the skins, stem, and seeds from the poblanos and skins and stems from the jalapeños (remove the seeds too, if desired, for a more mild sauce, or keep them in for a little more heat). Peel the garlic.\",\"5\":\"Add the poblanos, jalapeños, garlic, pepitas, cilantro, remaining tablespoon of avocado oil, the lime juice, and salt to a blender. Blend on high speed until completely smooth. If the sauce is very thick, add cold water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until the consistency is smooth and spreadable. Transfer to a serving bowl and set aside until ready to serve. Alternatively, cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.\",\"6\":\"Grill the cauliflower: Brush a cast-iron griddle pan with avocado oil and turn the heat to high. When the pan starts to smoke, add a few pieces of the marinated cauliflower. Grill for 7–8 minutes, until the cauliflower lifts easily from the pan and grill marks are visible. Flip and grill for another 4–5 minutes on the other side, until the cauliflower is easily pierced with a fork. Repeat with the remaining cauliflower.\",\"7\":\"Transfer the cauliflower to a cutting board and roughly chop into ½-inch pieces. Discard any slightly tough or undercooked pieces of stem.\",\"8\":\"Assemble the tacos: Spread about 1 tablespoon of the poblano-pepita sauce across a warm tortilla and top with cauliflower, cabbage, cilantro, and crema. Serve with lime wedges alongside.\",\"9\":\"Store any leftover poblano-pepita sauce in the refrigerator for up to 5 days. It can be served with eggs, in rice bowls, or tossed with grilled shrimp or your favorite protein.\",\"10\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":26,\"protein\":9,\"fat\":24,\"calories\":400,\"sugar\":8,\"carbohydrates\":41}','\"These cauliflower tacos are spiced to perfection and oh so satisfying. Cauliflower is marinated in a zesty, savory blend of lime juice, brown sugar, and tons of spices, then grilled to charred perfection. To build the tacos, layer the cauliflower on warm tortillas with plenty of the creamy, smoky poblano-pepita sauce, cabbage, cilantro, and crema.\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/63a32d85f1da4960a438d8e456f579ee.jpeg\"','⅓ cup avocado oil, plus more for grilling||¼ cup fresh lime juice||2 tablespoons light brown sugar||2 teaspoons ground cumin||1 tablespoon dried oregano||2 teaspoons paprika||½ teaspoon chipotle powder||1 teaspoon chili powder||1 teaspoon garlic powder||1½ teaspoons kosher salt||2 small heads of cauliflower, stems trimmed, cut into ½-inch-wide slabs||','dinner||mixing_bowl||whisk||casual_party||mexican||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||vegetarian||stove_top||lunch||tongs||healthy||weeknight||high_fiber'),('b6-8f0083d66a79','\"Scalloped Potato Loaf\"','{\"0\":\"In a large skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat until shimmering. Add the onion and cook until golden, about 5 minutes.\",\"1\":\"Add the ground beef and break apart, then cook for 3 minutes until the meat is no longer pink. Add the pepper, salt, garlic powder, paprika, and tomatoes. Mix thoroughly.\",\"2\":\"Add the spinach and cook until just wilted, about 2 minutes. Remove the pan from the heat, cover, and set aside until ready to use.\",\"3\":\"Preheat the oven to 350˚F (180˚C).\",\"4\":\"Peel the potatoes and cut into ⅛-inch (3 mm) thick slices.\",\"5\":\"In a 9x5-inch (23x13-cm) loaf pan, arrange overlapping potato slices on the bottom of the pan so the entire bottom is covered. Line the perimeter of the pan with overlapping potato slices.\",\"6\":\"Place 2 slices of mozzarella over the bottom layer of potatoes. Cut 5 slices of mozzarella in half. Place 2 half slices of cheese against the potatoes on both of the longer sides of the pan and one half on both of the shorter sides. Place one half in each of the corners of the pan.\",\"7\":\"Spread ⅓ of the beef mixture on top of the cheese. Arrange another layer of overlapping potato slices over the beef mixture. Place 2 more slices of cheese on top of the potatoes.\",\"8\":\"Spread another third of the beef mixture over the cheese, then add another layer of potatoes. Place 2 more slices of cheese on top of the potatoes. Spread the rest of the beef mixture on top of the cheese.\",\"9\":\"Tuck potato slices around the sides of the pan until all of the gaps are filled. Place the last 2 slices of cheese on top of the beef mixture. Cover the cheese with overlapping potato slices.\",\"10\":\"Bake for 90 minutes, until the top is golden brown and crisp. Let cool a bit.\",\"11\":\"Place a cutting board over the loaf pan and invert the loaf.\",\"12\":\"Slice and garnish with parsley.\",\"13\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":26,\"calories\":573,\"sugar\":7,\"carbohydrates\":47,\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":37}','','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/148794.jpg\"','1 tablespoon olive oil||1 large white onion, chopped||1 pound lean ground beef||½ teaspoon pepper||1 teaspoon salt||2 teaspoons garlic powder||2 teaspoons paprika||1 14-ounce can diced tomatoes||6 cups fresh spinach||5 russet potatoes||13 slices mozzarella cheese||2 tablespoons chopped parsley, for garnish||','cast_iron_pan||peeler||kid_friendly||cutting_board||saute_pan||dry_measuring_cups||oven||measuring_spoons||american||bake||stove_top||oven_mitts||comfort_food||weeknight||bread_pan||wooden_spoon||chefs_knife||casual_party||mashup||epoca_walmart||pyrex||chop_champ||dinner||high_protein'),('b6-f94d1fae8684','\"Grilled Lemongrass Pork B\\u00E1nh M\\u00EC\"','{\"0\":\"Make the pickled vegetables: Set a large colander in a large bowl. Add the carrots and daikon to the colander. Toss with the salt, then add just enough water to cover the vegetables, about 6 cups (1.4 L). Let sit at room temperature for 30 minutes.\",\"1\":\"Lift the colander out of the soaking liquid, then rinse the vegetables well. Shake the colander a few times to allow any excess water to drain away. Let the vegetables sit at room temperature for 30 minutes to dry out a bit.\",\"2\":\"Add the sugar and vinegar to the bowl with the vegetables. Season to taste with more salt, if needed. Transfer to an airtight container and refrigerate overnight.\",\"3\":\"Make the lemongrass pork: Trim the bottoms and green tops from the lemongrass stalks. Slice the light parts in half lengthwise, then remove any tough outer layers. Mince and transfer to a medium bowl.\",\"4\":\"Finely chop the onion and add to the bowl with the lemongrass.\",\"5\":\"In a large bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, fish sauce, sugar, wine, and pepper.\",\"6\":\"Add the sliced pork butt to the marinade and toss to coat. Cover with plastic wrap and let marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour, up to 4 hours.\",\"7\":\"Heat the canola oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add the onion and lemongrass and cook until the onion is tender and beginning to brown, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.\",\"8\":\"Heat a large grill pan over medium-high heat. Working in batches, remove the pork from the marinade, letting any excess liquid to drip off, then grill the pork until lightly charred on both sides and just cooked through, about 2 minutes per side. Transfer to a cutting board and let rest for 10 minutes.\",\"9\":\"Cut the pork into bite-sized pieces and transfer to a large bowl. Add the lemongrass and onion mixture and stir to combine.\",\"10\":\"To assemble, slice the toasted French rolls in half lengthwise almost all the way through, leaving a long end intact. Slather the bottom of the rolls with a generous amount of mayonnaise, then spread on a layer of pâté. Top with the pork mixture, cucumber, sliced onion, jalapeño, the pickled vegetables, and cilantro.\",\"11\":\"Close the sandwiches and serve.\",\"12\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":25,\"carbohydrates\":52,\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":56,\"fat\":68,\"calories\":1046}','\"This recipe makes it easy to recreate a classic Vietnamese b\\u00E1nh m\\u00EC at home. Pork butt is a cut of meat that usually requires a longer cooking time in order to make it tender, but by slicing it thinly, you cut the cooking time down to just a few minutes on a hot grill pan.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/216366.jpg\"','2 large carrots, peeled and cut into large matchsticks (about 1 pound)||1 12-ounce daikon root, peeled and cut into large matchsticks||3 tablespoons kosher salt, plus more to taste||2 tablespoons sugar||¼ cup distilled white vinegar||','chefs_knife||stove_top||lunch||dinner||mixing_bowl||weeknight||vietnamese||cutting_board||tongs||whisk||spatula||pyrex||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||contains_alcohol||high_protein||dairy_free'),('b7-4e2dc9e38e83','\"Green Sauce Shrimp Pasta\"','{\"0\":\"In a large pan, add the butter, thyme and rosemary. Stir.\",\"1\":\"Add the shrimp and cook for 3 minutes. Take them out of the pan and set aside.\",\"2\":\"Sprinkle the flour and mix until it becomes slightly brown.\",\"3\":\"Pour the warm milk slowly while mixing.\",\"4\":\"Add salt, pepper, and ground nutmeg. Stir and add the chopped onion. Cook for 5 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Add the fresh parsley and green onion (or chives). Blend everything with a mixer.\",\"6\":\"Cook until the sauce is bubbling, turn off the heat. Add the shrimp. Stir and then add the lime juice\",\"7\":\"Stir in the pasta. Serve right away.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":25,\"fat\":17,\"calories\":404,\"sugar\":11,\"carbohydrates\":41,\"fiber\":1}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/c5c0d290a0ea45c4b9c35f7b2e5e9e9a/BFV12831_GreenSauceShrimpPasta_ThumbA.jpg\"','4 tablespoons butter||1 tablespoon thyme||1 tablespoon rosemary||10 ounces shrimp, peeled and deveined||13 tablespoons flour||25 ounces warm milk||½ onion, chopped||1 cup parsley||½ cup green onions||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||1 teaspoon nutmeg||½ lime, squeezed||10 ounces cooked pasta||','blender||dinner||pan_fry||easy||american||stove_top||date_night||summer||sauce_pan||measuring_spoons||wooden_spoon||dry_measuring_cups||tongs||whisk||liquid_measuring_cup||microplane||chefs_knife||cutting_board||spatula'),('b7-81f2761ff419','\"Loaded Bacon Mac \\u0027n\\u0027 Cheese\"','{\"0\":\"Prepare 1 box of Mac \\u0027N\\u0027 Cheese according to instructions on box.\",\"1\":\"Add cooked bacon, monterey jack cheese, mozzarella cheese and pepper, stir until fully incorporated.\",\"2\":\"Top with desired garnish. Serve immediately.\",\"3\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":50,\"fat\":45,\"calories\":878,\"sugar\":8,\"carbohydrates\":64,\"fiber\":2}','','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/2c717bbbcd2c4d0396ce2ab4e2d72fb5/BFv24153BetterBoxedMacNCheeseFBFinal.jpg\"','1 box of Mac \'N\' Cheese||1 cup bacon, cooked||¼ cup monterey jack cheese, grated||¼ cup mozzarella cheese, grated||Pepper||','stove_top||american||kid_friendly||comfort_food||dinner||weeknight||easy||one_pot_or_pan||saute_pan||cheese_grater||spatula||mixing_bowl||dry_measuring_cups||high_protein||5_ingredients_or_less'),('b7-fe817e5c2b48','\"Baked Potato Wedges \\u0026 Fish Sticks\"','{\"0\":\"In a small bowl, combine all the paprika seasoning ingredients, stir.\",\"1\":\"Cut the potatoes in half lengthwise, and cut each half into quarters lengthwise, making 16 total wedges.\",\"2\":\"Place wedges in a bowl of water to remove the extra starch from the potatoes. Drain.\",\"3\":\"Preheat oven to 400˚F (200˚C).\",\"4\":\"Place wedges on a baking sheet and pour olive oil, 3 spoonfuls of the paprika seasoning, and parmesan over the potatoes.\",\"5\":\"Using clean hands, mix together to coat potatoes, then arrange potatoes in rows, without overlapping, so they bake evenly.\",\"6\":\"Bake for 30 minutes, flipping halfway, or until crispy.\",\"7\":\"Cut cod fillet down the middle and into 3 to 4-inch (8-10 cm) long pieces. Some of the thicker pieces may need to be cut in half.\",\"8\":\"Mix the paprika seasoning into the panko.\",\"9\":\"Dredge each fish stick through the eggs, flour, back in the egg, and finally, panko. Place on a baking sheet\",\"10\":\"Bake with the potato wedges for 15 minutes, flipping halfway, or until golden brown and cooked through.\",\"11\":\"Serve with your favorite dipping sauces.\",\"12\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":448,\"sugar\":3,\"carbohydrates\":75,\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":24,\"fat\":5}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/e672462ace114711ac41fc27d84515db/BFV13566_EasyBakedPotatoWedegsFishSticksTastyJr_ThumbA.jpg\"','2 teaspoons paprika||1 teaspoon garlic powder||1 teaspoon onion powder||½ teaspoon salt||½ teaspoon pepper||','bake||weeknight||american||comfort_food||dinner||oven||seafood||kid_friendly||pyrex||measuring_spoons||mixing_bowl||chefs_knife||cutting_board||colander||baking_pan||oven_mitts||dry_measuring_cups'),('b8-09bc235a423f','\"Meatloaf Layered Cake\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 350˚F (180˚C). Grease 2 8-inch (20 cm) round cake pans with nonstick spray.\",\"1\":\"Heat the oil in a medium pan over medium heat. Add the celery, onion, and carrot and sauté until translucent, about 10 minutes. Set aside to cool.\",\"2\":\"In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, Dijon mustard, paprika, Worcestershire sauce, tomato paste, eggs, panko, milk, and salt (if using). Stir to combine, add the cooled sautéed veggies, and mix until homogeneous.\",\"3\":\"Divide the meatloaf between the prepared pans and spread the mixture evenly.\",\"4\":\"Bake for 20-25 minutes, until golden brown. Let cool for 30 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Add 1 meatloaf layer to a serving plate. Spread a thin layer of tomato paste over the top. Add 2 cups (500 g) of mashed potatoes to the center and spread evenly. Top with the other meatloaf layer and spread with a layer of tomato paste and 2 cups (500 g) mashed potatoes. Use an offset spatula to cover the sides of the “cake” and spread the potatoes over the whole cake in an even layer.\",\"6\":\"Add another cup (250 g) of mashed potatoes to the top of the cake and spread evenly over the whole cake.\",\"7\":\"Add the remaining mashed potatoes to a piping bag fitted with a star tip. Pipe rosettes around the base and top of the cake.\",\"8\":\"Slice and serve.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":141,\"fiber\":8,\"protein\":50,\"fat\":24,\"calories\":1026,\"sugar\":11}','\"\"','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/7866481de5b74078aee43ca4563382b9/FB_FINALSWEETSAVORY.jpg\"','Nonstick cooking spray, for greasing||2 tablespoons vegetable oil||½ cup minced celery||½ cup minced onion||1 medium carrot, minced||2 pounds ground beef||1 teaspoon Dijon mustard||1 teaspoon paprika||2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce||1 tablespoon tomato paste||2 large eggs||1 cup panko bread crumbs||½ cup milk||Salt, to taste||⅓ cup tomato paste||6 cups prepared mashed potatoes||','oven||american||bake||easy||comfort_food||casual_party||special_occasion||dinner||spatula||cake_pan||oven_mitts||mashup||dry_measuring_cups||liquid_measuring_cup||cutting_board||chefs_knife||offset_spatula||pyrex||measuring_spoons||epoca_walmart||saute_pan||high_protein||high_fiber'),('b8-41afca4aefd0','\"Slow-Cooked Asian Pork\"','{\"0\":\"Place the pork roast in a slow cooker.\",\"1\":\"Combine the apple juice (or water),\\u00A0Sun-Bird Stir Fry Seasoning Mix, soy sauce, sesame oil (or canola oil), garlic, and hoisin sauce in a medium bowl. Stir well, then pour over the roast.\",\"2\":\"Cover the slow cooker and cook on low setting for 8–10 hours.\",\"3\":\"Remove the meat from the slow cooker and shred using 2 forks, reserving the liquid.\",\"4\":\"Spoon the pork onto kaiser rolls, then top with coleslaw.\",\"5\":\"Serve with the reserved juices on the side as a dipping sauce. Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":39,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":44,\"fat\":49,\"calories\":786,\"sugar\":14}','\"Presented by \\u003Ca href=\\u0022https://sunbirdseasonings.com/\\u0022\\u003ESun-Bird\\u003C/a\\u003E\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/b99369a597704f2c934363f23f24cd7b.jpeg\"','3 pounds boneless pork roast||1 cup apple juice or water||1 packet Sun-Bird Stir Fry Seasoning Mix||⅓ cup soy sauce||⅓ cup sesame oil or canola oil||2 tablespoons minced garlic||3 tablespoons hoisin sauce||6–8 kaiser rolls, split and toasted||1 ½ cups coleslaw mix||','slow_cooker||bbq||dinner||dairy_free||sponsored_recipe'),('b8-6ba12c69db26','\"One-Tray Garlic Primavera Pasta\"','{\"0\":\"Take two sheets of aluminum foil, about 12x12-inch, (30x30 cm) and stack them on top of each other.\",\"1\":\"Fold one side of the foil about ⅓ of the way across sheet, repeat for opposite side.\",\"2\":\"Pinch the corner to form a point and then flatten it to the short side of the foil, forming a raised corner. Repeat for all four sides, and make four of these.\",\"3\":\"Preheat oven to 400ºF (200ºC).\",\"4\":\"Add all of the ingredients to one of the foil boats, then stir.\",\"5\":\"Bake for 12 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Allow to cool for 10 minutes.\",\"7\":\"Eat or pack into tupperware and refrigerate 3-5 days.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":302,\"sugar\":2,\"carbohydrates\":56,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":11,\"fat\":8}','','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/bfa83779a7a74f63a2cf71e079e14275/FBFinal.jpg\"','2 cups pasta, cooked al dente||½  cup carrots, sliced||¾ cup peppers, chopped||¾ cup asparagus||1 tablespoon garlic, minced||1 tablespoon olive oil||1 teaspoon salt||1 teaspoon pepper||Parmesan cheese (optional)||','oven||easy||meal_prep||dinner||bake||weeknight||italian||colander||cheese_grater||saute_pan||oven_mitts||strainer||pyrex||cutting_board||chefs_knife||baking_pan||high_protein||high_fiber||vegetarian'),('b8-b1c2afd7fe57','\"Sweet \\u0026 Spicy Peach Sticky Wings\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C). Line a large baking sheet with foil and grease with nonstick spray.\",\"1\":\"Make the dry rub: Add the chipotle powder, paprika, baking powder, onion powder, garlic powder, salt, cayenne, Italian seasoning, cumin, and black pepper to a bowl and whisk until evenly combined.\",\"2\":\"Make the wings: Add the chicken wings to a large bowl and toss with the oil. Sprinkle in the dry rub and use your hands to massage it into the chicken wings.\",\"3\":\"Arrange the wings on the prepared baking sheet, spacing evenly. Bake for 15 minutes, then flip and continue baking for another 15 minutes.\",\"4\":\"While the chicken wings are baking, make the glaze: Add the peaches in syrup, brown sugar, apple cider vinegar, soy sauce, Sriracha, cinnamon, black pepper, salt, bay leaf, and water to a medium pan. Stir to combine, then bring to a boil over medium-high heat, then reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15 minutes, until the peaches have softened and sauce has thickened.\",\"5\":\"Remove the bay leaf, then transfer the peach mixture to a blender and purée on high speed for 30–60 seconds. Strain the glaze through a fine-mesh strainer back into the pan. Turn the heat to high and cook until the glaze has thickened, about 5 minutes. Whisk in the butter until fully incorporated. The glaze should coat the back of a spoon.\",\"6\":\"Carefully remove the wings from the oven and brush on both sides with about ⅓ of the glaze. Return to the oven and cook for another 5 minutes.\",\"7\":\"Remove wings from the oven brush with another ⅓ of the glaze. Turn the oven to high broil, return the wings to the oven, and broil for 2–3 minutes, or until the glaze is bubbling.\",\"8\":\"Remove from the oven and toss wings in a large bowl with the remaining glaze.\",\"9\":\"Transfer to a serving plate and garnish with the cilantro.\",\"10\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":35,\"fat\":44,\"calories\":601,\"sugar\":14,\"carbohydrates\":17}','\"They\\u2019re sweet, they\\u2019re smoky, they\\u2019re crunchy, and YES they\\u2019re sticky! These wings are insanely delicious and super easy to make\\u2013don\\u2019t let the long ingredient list fool you.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/280470.jpg\"','1½ teaspoons chipotle powder||1½ teaspoons smoked paprika||1½ teaspoons baking powder||1½ teaspoons onion powder||1½ teaspoons garlic powder||1½ teaspoons kosher salt||½ teaspoon cayenne||½ teaspoon Italian seasoning||½ teaspoon cumin||¼ teaspoon black pepper||','blender||liquid_measuring_cup||dry_measuring_cups||stove_top||oven||baking_pan||comfort_food||american||mixing_bowl||game_day||oven_mitts||sieve||dinner||sauce_pan||casual_party||bake||snacks||high_protein'),('b8-d8fb7669bf41','\"Black Garlic Honey Butter Lobster Tail\"','{\"0\":\"Bring 700ml (3 cups) of water to a boil, add 2 tbsp salt and your lobster tails. Simmer for 5 mins. Remove from the water and plunge into an ice bath.\",\"1\":\"Melt 50g butter in a saucepan and when bubbling, add shallot \\u0026 garlic, season with a pinch of salt \\u0026 pepper and cook until soft and caramelised\",\"2\":\"Now, deglaze the pan by adding 100ml white wine and reduce to half.\",\"3\":\"Turn the heat to low. Add a pinch of salt \\u0026 pepper, parsley, parmesan, honey, and remaining butter. Stir to combine and set aside.\",\"4\":\"Cut down the length of your lobster tails and place on a baking tray\",\"5\":\"Brush the flesh with the sauce and grill for 10 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Serve the tails on a bed of salad dressed with wedges of lemon and the remaining sauce.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":47,\"calories\":587,\"sugar\":0,\"carbohydrates\":4,\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":35}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/d370d8fa0e474669a07a6f6cf9425acd/BFV74958_3SeafoodStarters_FB_1080x1080.jpg\"','2 Lobster tails||½ Shallot, diced||5 cloves black garlic, crushed||100ml white wine||1 tbsp parsley, finely chopped||1 tbsp parmesan, grated||2 tsp Lemon juice||200g Butter||Salt & pepper to taste||','mixing_bowl||tongs||dinner||special_occasion||seafood||stove_top||low_carb||high_protein||pescatarian||keto'),('b9-51d7ca647fa3','\"Gluten-Free Wild Rice Stuffing\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a 9 x 13-inch (22.5 x 32.5 cm) baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter.\",\"1\":\"In a medium pot over medium-high heat, cook the sausage until browned and cooked through, about 8 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the sausage to a bowl, leaving the rendered fat behind in the pan. Set aside.\",\"2\":\"Lower the heat to medium and melt the remaining 5 tablespoons of butter in the pan with the sausage fat. Once the butter begins to bubble, add the onion, carrot, celery, and ½ teaspoon of salt. Cook for 5–8 minutes, until the onion is translucent and the carrots begin to soften.\",\"3\":\"Add the garlic, thyme leaves, sage, and black pepper and cook for 2–3 minutes, until the garlic is fragrant. Mix in the dried cranberries, pecans, Parmesan, rice, and sausage and stir well to combine. Remove the pot from the heat.\",\"4\":\"Transfer the stuffing mixture to the prepared baking dish.\",\"5\":\"In a liquid measuring cup, use a fork to whisk together the chicken stock, eggs, egg yolk, and remaining teaspoon of salt.\",\"6\":\"Pour the stock mixture evenly over the stuffing and stir to incorporate. Cover the dish with foil.\",\"7\":\"Bake the stuffing for 40 minutes. Remove the foil and bake for another 10 minutes, until slightly crispy on top. Remove the stuffing from the oven and let cool for 15–20 minutes before serving.\",\"8\":\"Serve warm.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":19,\"fat\":27,\"calories\":556,\"sugar\":12,\"carbohydrates\":59,\"fiber\":6}','\"Who said stuffing had to be made with bread? In this recipe, we\\u2019ve swapped out bread with a wild rice blend and mixed it with all of our favorite fixings. There\\u2019s a perfect balance of sweet and savory in every bite.\"','10','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/34afde9d6cfd4932a44b1e311d8b97d8/BFV61760_GlutenFreeThanksgivingHacks_111219_KP_OO_V001.jpg\"','6 tablespoons (¾ stick) unsalted butter, divided||1 pound sweet Italian sausage, casings removed and broken up||1 medium white onion, diced (about 2 cups)||1 large carrot, diced (about 1 cup)||2-3 stalks of celery, diced (about 1 cup)||1½ teaspoons kosher salt, divided||3 cloves garlic, minced||5 sprigs of fresh thyme, leaves picked (about 1 tablespoon)||5 small fresh sage leaves, minced||½ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper||1¼ cups unsweetened dried cranberries||1 cup pecan pieces, toasted||½ cup grated Parmesan cheese||4 cups cooked wild rice medley||1¼ cups chicken stock||2 large eggs||1 large egg yolk||','cutting_board||mixing_bowl||oven||gluten_free||baking_pan||thanksgiving||bake||liquid_measuring_cup||chefs_knife||dry_measuring_cups||measuring_spoons||oven_mitts||wooden_spoon||spatula||pyrex||dinner||big_batch||mashup||weeknight||thanksgiving_sides||high_fiber'),('b9-71c5b5c9e4df','\"Zucchini Cheddar Muffins\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 350˚F (180˚C). Grease a 12-cup muffin tin with nonstick spray.\",\"1\":\"Make the batter: In a large bowl, stir together the whole wheat flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, pepper, and sugar. Set aside.\",\"2\":\"In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs, buttermilk, and butter.\",\"3\":\"Add the zucchini, carrot, cheddar cheese, and chives the egg mixture and stir to combine.\",\"4\":\"Pour the egg mixture into the dry ingredients and fold to combine, being careful not to overmix.\",\"5\":\"Using an ice cream scoop, divide the batter between the muffin cups, filling almost completely.\",\"6\":\"Sprinkle more cheddar cheese on top of the muffins.\",\"7\":\"Bake for 18 minutes, rotating the muffin tin halfway through baking, until browned on top and a toothpick inserted in the center of a muffin comes out clean.\",\"8\":\"Let cool for 10 minutes before removing the muffins from the tin. Serve or store in the refrigerator for up to 5 days.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\",\"10\":\"Nutrition, per muffin - Calories: 182, Total fat: 10 grams, Sodium: 433 mg, Total carbs: 17 grams, Dietary fiber: 3 grams, Sugars: 2 grams, Protein: 7 grams\"}','{\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":8,\"fat\":10,\"calories\":201,\"sugar\":2,\"carbohydrates\":20}','\"\"','12','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/81f18a65bed24a40bc26b4ac85d0c5f2/BFV50702_SavoryBreakfastMuffins3Ways_FB1080SQ.jpg\"','Nonstick cooking spray, for greasing||2 cups whole wheat flour||1 teaspoon baking powder||½ teaspoon baking soda||1 teaspoon kosher salt||1 teaspoon black pepper||Pinch of sugar||3 large eggs||1 cup buttermilk or 1 cup milk mixed with 1 teaspoon white vinegar||5 tablespoons melted unsalted butter or olive oil||1 cup shredded zucchini||1 cup shredded carrots||1 cup shredded cheddar cheese, plus more for topping||¼ cup thinly sliced chives||','big_batch||breakfast||meal_prep||bake||oven||american||comfort_food||dry_measuring_cups||mixing_bowl||pyrex||spatula||liquid_measuring_cup||chefs_knife||cutting_board||oven_mitts||measuring_spoons||whisk||brunch||low_sugar||vegetarian'),('b9-a5e7f1c9c04a','\"Meatball Sub Boats\"','{\"0\":\"In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs, ¼ cup (10 g) parsley, 3 cloves garlic, salt, and pepper.\",\"1\":\"Shape the ground beef mixture into golf ball-sized balls.\",\"2\":\"Heat a cast-iron pan or skillet with oil over medium-high heat.\",\"3\":\"Cook the meatballs until browned on all sides. Transfer meatballs to a plate then remove pan from heat.\",\"4\":\"Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C).\",\"5\":\"Place the soft rolls in a baking sheet.\",\"6\":\"Cut the top of the rolls with a knife and press the inside down to create a boat.\",\"7\":\"Mix together the melted butter, 3 cloves garlic, and 2 tablespoons of parsley.\",\"8\":\"Brush the rolls with the garlic butter.\",\"9\":\"Bake for 5 minutes, or until toasted.\",\"10\":\"Place two slices of mozzarella in the rolls. Place a spoonful of marinara on top of the cheese.\",\"11\":\"Place three meatballs in the boat and top with more marinara.\",\"12\":\"Bake for 25 minutes, or until cheese is melted.\",\"13\":\"Top with Parmesan.\",\"14\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":58,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":75,\"fat\":64,\"calories\":1135,\"sugar\":7}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/6f1ab55467694fff83e567133c60dae0/fb.jpg\"','2 pounds ground beef||2 eggs||1 cup bread crumbs||¼ cup parsley plus 2 tablespoons, chopped, divided||6 cloves garlic, minced||1 teaspoon salt||½ teaspoon pepper||Oil||4 soft rolls||8 slices mozzarella||1 cup marinara||¼ cup butter, melted||Grated Parmesan||','dinner||bake||cast_iron_pan||oven||comfort_food||american||kid_friendly||mashup||easy||game_day||stuffed||lunch||casual_party||stove_top||fourth_of_july||pan_fry||one_top_friendly||pyrex||dry_measuring_cups||mixing_bowl||measuring_spoons||saute_pan||tongs||baking_pan||oven_mitts||chefs_knife||high_protein'),('ba-0dbdb8973d16','\"Philadelphia Roll\"','{\"0\":\"Season the sushi rice with the rice vinegar, fanning and stirring until room temperature.\",\"1\":\"On the rolling mat place one sheet of nori with the rough side facing upwards.\",\"2\":\"Wet your hands and grab a handful of rice and place it on the nori. Spread the rice evenly throughout the nori without smushing the rice down.\",\"3\":\"Arrange, in a horizontal row 1 inch (2 cm) from the bottom, smoked salmon, cream cheese, and cucumber.\",\"4\":\"Grabbing both nori and the mat, roll the mat over the filling so the extra space at the bottom touches the other side, squeezing down to make a nice tight roll. Squeeze down along the way to keep the roll from holding its shape.\",\"5\":\"Transfer the roll onto a cutting board. Rub a knife on a damp paper towel before slicing the roll into six equal portions.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":7,\"fat\":10,\"calories\":446,\"sugar\":56,\"carbohydrates\":64}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/114292.jpg\"','2 cups sushi rice, cooked||¼ cup seasoned rice vinegar||4 half sheets sushi grade nori||4 ounces smoked salmon||4 ounces cream cheese, cut into matchsticks||1 small cucumber, cut into matchsticks||','japanese||casual_party||dinner||american||date_night||fusion||healthy||liquid_measuring_cup||dry_measuring_cups||plastic_wrap||pyrex||pescatarian'),('ba-20f9f8e0432f','\"Almond Butter Honey Oat Bars\"','{\"0\":\"In a medium bowl, add oats, nut butter, and honey or maple syrup, and mix until well combined.\",\"1\":\"Spray baking dish with cooking spray. Pour in mixture and spread evenly.\",\"2\":\"Cover and place in freezer until firm.\",\"3\":\"Cut into bars. Keep in the fridge until ready to eat.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":40,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":10,\"fat\":18,\"calories\":355,\"sugar\":12}','','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/d21894ee3bfb43b0bacf7924135f0fee/BFV30507_Kid-FriendlyBreakfastMealPrep.jpg\"','2 cups rolled oats||⅔ cup almond butter or nut butter of choice||¼ cup honey or maple syrup||','easy||healthy||freezer||kid_friendly||breakfast||meal_prep||liquid_measuring_cup||mixing_bowl||spatula||baking_pan||dry_measuring_cups||pyrex||cutting_board||chefs_knife||snacks||qfp_recipes||high_fiber||5_ingredients_or_less||vegetarian'),('ba-852ab661ee2b','\"Crispy Air Fryer Chicken Thighs\"','{\"0\":\"Generously season the chicken thighs with salt on both sides, including under the skin.\",\"1\":\"In a large bowl, whisk together the Dijon mustard, balsamic vinegar, olive oil, garlic powder, Italian seasoning.\",\"2\":\"Add chicken thighs to the marinade and toss to coat. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 4 hours, preferably overnight. Let the chicken come to room temperature before cooking.\",\"3\":\"Preheat the air fryer to 380°F (195°C) for 3 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Remove the chicken from the marinade and pat dry with a paper towel. Lightly spray with cooking spray or rub with a bit of olive oil.\",\"5\":\"Add the chicken thighs (as many as will fit) to the air fryer, skin-side down, and cook for 5–7 minutes. Flip the chicken and cook 5 –7 minutes more, until the internal temperature reaches 165°F (75°C). Repeat with the remaining chicken thighs, if needed.\",\"6\":\"Garnish with herbs of choice and serve.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":63,\"fat\":65,\"calories\":886,\"sugar\":4,\"carbohydrates\":6,\"fiber\":0}','\"Meet your latest weeknight dinner. Chicken thighs are soaked in a zesty balsamic marinade to tenderize and add tons of flavor to the meat. They\\u2019re then cooked in an air fryer until crispy and golden brown. It\\u2019s a super easy recipe and minimal clean up with the help of the air fryer!\"','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/321577.jpg\"','4 large bone-in, skin-on chicken thighs||Kosher salt, to taste||Freshly ground black pepper, to taste||1 tablespoon Dijon mustard||¼ cup balsamic vinegar||½ cup olive oil||½ teaspoon garlic powder||½ teaspoon dried Italian seasoning||Nonstick cooking spray, for greasing||Chopped fresh herbs, for garnish||','dinner||air_fryer||american||liquid_measuring_cup||measuring_spoons||lunch||weeknight||mixing_bowl||whisk||low_carb||high_protein||low_sugar||dairy_free||keto'),('ba-9cb7cfd30872','\"Instant Pot Chicken Noodle Soup\"','{\"0\":\"Set the Instant Pot to sauté and add the olive oil. Once the oil begins to shimmer, add the onion, carrots, and celery and cook, stirring often, until just starting to soften, about 10 minutes. Add the garlic, thyme, salt, and pepper and cook, stirring constantly, until aromatic, about 30 seconds.\",\"1\":\"Add the chicken and chicken stock and cover with the lid. Place the lid on the Instant Pot and set to Soup/Broth for 5 minutes. Once the timer goes off, release the pressure naturally for 10 minutes.\",\"2\":\"Remove the lid, then add the egg noodles. Cover and turn the Instant Pot to sauté. Cook for about 7 minutes, or according to the package instructions, until the noodles are al dente.\",\"3\":\"Ladle the soup into bowls and serve with crackers, if desired.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":85,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":27,\"fat\":66,\"calories\":1063,\"sugar\":13}','\"Is there anything better than chicken noodle soup when you are feeling chilly or under the weather? Use homemade chicken stock for a deeper flavor or store-bought for a quick and easy fix\\u2013either way, this soup is comforting and delicious.\"','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/322003.jpg\"','1 tablespoon olive oil||1 medium yellow onion, diced||4 carrots, thinly sliced||4 celery stalks, thinly sliced||3 garlic cloves, minced||1 teaspoon dried thyme||1½ teaspoons kosher salt||1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper||4 cups shredded rotisserie chicken||8 cups chicken stock||8 ounces egg noodles||Crackers, for serving (optional)||','measuring_spoons||dinner||comfort_food||dry_measuring_cups||liquid_measuring_cup||one_pot_or_pan||instant_pot||lunch||american||weeknight||high_protein||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||dairy_free'),('bb-1fe34758cc52','\"Steamed Whole Fish With Fresh Ginger\"','{\"0\":\"Bring a large pan of water to boil and set a steamer basket on top. Place a plate inside the steamer basket.\",\"1\":\"Peel the ginger with a spoon, then slice. Julienne half and set aside.\",\"2\":\"Cut the green onions into 2-3 inch (5-7 cm) pieces. Thinly slice half and set aside.\",\"3\":\"On the plate in the steamer, place the sliced ginger and cut green onions. Place the whole fish on top and cover with the lid. Steam for 8-10 minutes, or until the fish is cooked through--check by poking a chopstick through the thickest part of the flesh. Remove the fish from the steamer and transfer to a serving platter.\",\"4\":\"Make the sauce: In a small bowl, combine the sugar, soy sauce, and sesame oil. Mix well.\",\"5\":\"Scatter the sliced green onions and julienned ginger over the fish, then pour the hot oil and sauce on top.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":4,\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":57,\"fat\":13,\"calories\":381,\"sugar\":2}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/203504.jpg\"','1 2-inch piece of fresh ginger||6 green onions||1 2 pounds whole red snapper||3 tablespoons canola oil, hot||','chinese||steam||winter||stove_top||cutting_board||chefs_knife||mixing_bowl||special_occasion||dinner||measuring_spoons||saute_pan||pyrex||date_night||lunar_new_year||low_carb||high_protein||low_sugar||dairy_free||pescatarian||keto'),('bb-401091afa524','\"BBQ Smoker Pork Ribs\"','{\"0\":\"Using a charcoal chimney or lighter fluid, light 6-8 pieces of lump charcoal and let them come to a full burn. Add to your firebox and preheat the smoker to roughly 225°F (105°C), adding charcoal to the fire as necessary.\",\"1\":\"Add the ginger, cayenne, garlic powder, paprika, minced garlic, onion powder, black pepper, and mustard powder in a medium bowl and mix thoroughly.\",\"2\":\"Place ribs on a large sheet of aluminum foil and coat liberally with spice rub on all sides.\",\"3\":\"Place a metal pan filled with water at the end of the smoker’s cooking chamber closest to the firebox. Place ribs directly on the grate of your cooking chamber and close the smoker. Open the vents at both ends of the smoker.\",\"4\":\"Add a chunk or two of smoking wood to the firebox each half hour to create a stream of thin but visible smoke that is somewhat blue in appearance. Too much wood may result in thick, gray smoke. If this happens, open the smoker and clear the smoke out, waiting to close it until you’re able to achieve manageable smoke again.\",\"5\":\"Maintain the heat by adding additional charcoal as necessary.\",\"6\":\"Smoke ribs for 3-5 hours, spraying each hour with water to keep the surface from drying out.\",\"7\":\"Cook time will vary based on the size and type of rib (baby backs will cook faster than spareribs). Use a meat thermometer to gauge doneness.\",\"8\":\"At 170°F (75°C), remove the ribs from the smoker and place onto a large sheet of aluminum foil. If using barbecue sauce, apply now with a basting brush. Wrap the aluminum foil up to enclose the ribs, and place them back in your smoker for an additional 30 minutes.\",\"9\":\"Let meat rest at least 15 minutes off the heat before slicing. Serve with remaining barbecue sauce and preferred sides.\",\"10\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":21,\"fat\":30,\"calories\":635,\"sugar\":47,\"carbohydrates\":65,\"fiber\":3}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/115993.jpg\"','1 rack pork ribs, St. Louis-style or baby back||2 cups barbecue sauce, optional||','bbq||grill||mixing_bowl||dinner||pyrex||american||kid_friendly||comfort_food||fourth_of_july||game_day||liquid_measuring_cup||tongs||dairy_free'),('bb-55a50231c248','\"Double Cheeseburger Bread Bowl\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 350˚F (180˚F).\",\"1\":\"In a circular cake pan, add half of the ground beef and season with half of the garlic powder, half of the onion powder, half of the pepper, and half of the salt. Mix to combine then press the beef into patty form.\",\"2\":\"Bake for 12 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Repeat this process for the second patty.\",\"4\":\"Slice off the top of the sourdough loaf and scoop out the inside.\",\"5\":\"Begin by laying down slices of cheese at the bottom, then add your first burger patty.\",\"6\":\"Layer more cheese on top of the patty and continue by adding bacon, sauteed mushrooms \\u0026 onions, spinach, and tomato.\",\"7\":\"Add a second burger patty and repeat step 7.\",\"8\":\"Place the top of the loaf back on the bread and wrap in aluminum foil.\",\"9\":\"On a level surface, use a heavy object to press the sandwich down for at least 30 minutes.\",\"10\":\"Remove aluminum foil.\",\"11\":\"Bake for 25 minutes.\",\"12\":\"Slice and serve.\",\"13\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":7,\"carbohydrates\":50,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":53,\"fat\":33,\"calories\":728}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/4166f18095b74b0286a9355e3bf9da76/BFV21600_Double_Cheeseburger_Bread_Bowl_FB.jpg\"','1 sourdough loaf||1½ - 2 pounds ground beef||1 teaspoon garlic powder||1 teaspoon onion powder||1 teaspoon black pepper||1 teaspoon salt||1 tomato, sliced||1 onion, sliced and sauteed||1 8 oz package of sliced mushrooms, sauteed||½ cup packed spinach||8 pieces bacon, cooked||n/a||n/a||','oven||american||comfort_food||mashup||fourth_of_july||dinner||bake||game_day||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||cake_pan||oven_mitts||cutting_board||chefs_knife||pyrex||special_occasion||high_protein');
INSERT INTO `Recipe` VALUES ('bb-5e82d4aa80bd','\"Tuna Melt\"','{\"0\":\"In a medium bowl, mix together the tuna, mayonnaise, celery, pickle relish, salt, and pepper until well combined.\",\"1\":\"On a cutting board, butter one side of each slice of bread. Flip the bread over so it is buttered-side down. Divide the tuna mixture between 2 slices of bread. Top with the cheddar cheese, then place the other slices of bread on top, buttered-side out.\",\"2\":\"Heat a large pan over medium heat. Place the sandwiches in the pan and cook, without moving, for about 2 minutes, until golden brown. Carefully flip the sandwiches over and continue to cook until the other side is golden brown and the cheese has melted, 2 minutes more.\",\"3\":\"Transfer the tuna melts to a cutting board and cut in half. Serve immediately.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":13,\"protein\":44,\"fat\":47,\"calories\":646,\"sugar\":2,\"carbohydrates\":8}','\"Cozy up with Tasty\\u2019s take on a classic tuna melt. Oil-packed tuna stays moist and succulent, while celery and sweet pickle relish provide a tangy crunch. Don\\u2019t skimp on the cheese for the ultimate melty sandwich.\"','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/330892.jpg\"','2 4-ounce cans of oil-packed tuna, drained||3 tablespoons mayonnaise||2 stalks of celery, finely chopped||1 tablespoon sweet pickle relish||½ teaspoon kosher salt||¼ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper||4 slices of bread||1 tablespoon unsalted butter, room temperature||4 ounces sliced sharp cheddar cheese||','american||liquid_measuring_cup||dinner||cutting_board||stove_top||weeknight||saute_pan||lunch||pan_fry||measuring_spoons||easy||dry_measuring_cups||mixing_bowl||low_carb||high_protein||low_sugar||under_30_minutes||under_15_minutes||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||pescatarian||keto'),('bb-87fa04dae40f','\"Johnny Marzetti As Made By Marisel Salazar\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C). Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with vegetable oil.\",\"1\":\"Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Cook the egg noodles according to the package instructions, then drain.\",\"2\":\"While the noodles cook, heat the vegetable oil in a large skillet or Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add the ground pork and cook, breaking up into small pieces, until beginning to brown, 5–7 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Reduce the heat to medium and add the green pepper, onion, garlic, celery, mushrooms, olives, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until the vegetables begin to soften and the meat is no longer pink, about 10 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Add the tomato sauce, Arturo sauce, and tomato paste and stir to combine.\",\"5\":\"Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the cooked noodles and 1 cup shredded cheddar cheese, mixing well. Transfer to the prepared baking dish, spreading evenly, and top with the remaining cup of shredded cheese.\",\"6\":\"Bake for 30–45 minutes, or until hot and bubbly around the edges. Serve immediately.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":46,\"fat\":41,\"calories\":783,\"sugar\":10,\"carbohydrates\":57}','\"This is the original hamburger casserole; a cheesy, beefy, and hearty pasta dish that dates back to the late 1800s. Created by Italian American Theresa Marzetti, the Johnny Marzetti was so popular it was served in school cafeterias and was the go-to dish at potlucks and community functions across the Midwest. It even made its way down to Panama. Add pimiento-stuffed olives give this dish a Latin American twist.\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/6cb750de7f62449ba3d167eda2ecf173.jpeg\"','2 tablespoons vegetable or olive oil, plus more for greasing||1 teaspoon kosher salt, plus more for water||12 ounces egg noodles||1 pound ground beef or pork||¾ cup diced green bell pepper||½ cup chopped yellow onion||1–2 garlic cloves, minced||1 stalk celery, chopped||1 8-ounce can of mushrooms, drained||1 8-ounce jar of pimento-stuffed green olives, drained||½ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper||1 16-ounce can tomato sauce||1 8-ounce can of Arturo sauce or tomato soup||1 8-ounce can of tomato paste||2 cups grated cheddar cheese, divided||','big_batch||american||baking_pan||stove_top||comfort_food||latin_american||cutting_board||cheese_grater||oven||dry_measuring_cups||measuring_spoons||spatula||wooden_spoon||bake||dinner||high_protein||high_fiber'),('bb-aefe0b76f8ee','\"Turkey \\u0026 Zucchini\\u2013Stuffed Jack-o\\u2019-lantern Bell Peppers\"','{\"0\":\"In a large skillet, heat the oil and cook onions and garlic for 3 minutes, or until they start to soften. Add the ground turkey to the pan, followed by salt, pepper, and oregano. Stir and cook for 3-4 minutes.\",\"1\":\"Then add zucchini and diced tomatoes. Cook until zucchini has begun to soften and remove from heat.\",\"2\":\"Cut the top off of the bell pepper low enough that the stem remains attached and remove the seeds. Save the top!\",\"3\":\"Preheat oven to 350˚F (180˚C).\",\"4\":\"Carefully, carve out your desired jack-o’-lantern face using a steak knife or paring knife. Repeat for the rest of the bell peppers.\",\"5\":\"Place carved bell peppers in a baking dish and spoon in a layer of cooked rice in the bottom followed by the turkey mixture, and top with mozzarella cheese. Put the top of the bell pepper back on top.\",\"6\":\"Bake for 35 minutes or until peppers are tender and the cheese has melted.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":25,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":13,\"fat\":8,\"calories\":222,\"sugar\":11}','','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/6804781ff5ed47efbfac16c66e96731e/BFV13284_Jack-O-LanternStuffedPeppers-FB1080SQ.jpg\"','2 tablespoons olive oil||1 cup onion, diced||2 cloves garlic, minced||1 pound ground turkey||½ teaspoon salt||1 teaspoon oregano||1 teaspoon pepper||1 zucchini, diced||1 cup diced tomatoes||8 orange bell peppers||1 ½ cups cooked rice||','oven||american||halloween||comfort_food||bake||wooden_spoon||saute_pan||measuring_spoons||cutting_board||chefs_knife||baking_pan||oven_mitts||stuffed||dinner||special_occasion||casual_party||dry_measuring_cups||pyrex'),('bb-d0221cc0d3a2','\"Feta-stuffed Falafel Burgers\"','{\"0\":\"Add all the burger ingredients, except for the feta, to a blender and blend until smooth. (Make sure your chickpeas are very dry first!)\",\"1\":\"Divide mixture into four balls, then make an indent in the middle.\",\"2\":\"Place a small block of feta in each indent and roll up again until the feta is completely covered.\",\"3\":\"Fry in sunflower oil for 5 minutes until brown on each side.\",\"4\":\"Add to a burger bun with lettuce, tomato, salsa, and coriander.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":16,\"fat\":19,\"calories\":453,\"sugar\":10,\"carbohydrates\":52,\"fiber\":6}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/97de44174496441c8dff073c2ddd6f83/BFV13316_Feta-StuffedFalafelBurgers-ThumbTextless1080.jpg\"','400 grams skinned chickpeas||2 garlic cloves, chopped||1 red onion, roughly chopped||1 teaspoon ground cumin||1 teaspoon harissa paste||2 tablespoons plain flour||Handful fresh parsley||Handful fresh coriander||50 grams feta cheese||','blender||stove_top||american||comfort_food||dinner||greek||fusion||dry_measuring_cups||chefs_knife||cutting_board||measuring_spoons||saute_pan||spatula'),('bd-6df1cfbee713','\"Egg Cups\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 350˚F (180˚C).\",\"1\":\"Fill a greased muffin tin with your favorite combination of fillings or use the ones we did!\",\"2\":\"Whisk eggs in measuring cup and fill up each tin.\",\"3\":\"Sprinkle with salt and pepper.\",\"4\":\"Bake for about 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":0,\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":9,\"fat\":7,\"calories\":113,\"sugar\":0}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/65aa8f286a824377938e8de159681477/BFV18899_HealthyMuffinTinBreakfasts4Ways_FB1080SQ.jpg\"','5 eggs||Salt||Pepper||','oven||american||kid_friendly||easy||bake||brunch||breakfast||liquid_measuring_cup||cupcake_pan||oven_mitts||chefs_knife||cutting_board||charcuterie_breakfast||low_calorie||walmart_meal_planning'),('bd-dc08a4ec15ce','\"Quick Korean Knife-Cut Noodle Soup (Kalguksu)\"','{\"0\":\"Make the broth: Add the water, anchovies, and kombu to a large pot. Bring to a simmer over medium heat.\",\"1\":\"Add the zucchini, carrots, and shiitake mushrooms and cook for 4–5 minutes, until the vegetables are tender. Remove the pot from the heat and set aside.\",\"2\":\"Make the soup: Meanwhile, bring a medium pot of water to a boil. Add the noodles and cook until tender, about 3 minutes, stirring to keep the noodles from sticking to each other. Rinse the noodles under cold water to stop the cooking process.\",\"3\":\"Add the cooked noodles to the broth and bring to a boil. Cook for about 1 minute to heat the noodles through.\",\"4\":\"Ladle the soup into bowls and top with green and red Thai chiles, garlic, soy sauce, salt and pepper.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":180,\"fiber\":15,\"protein\":39,\"fat\":7,\"calories\":923,\"sugar\":11}','\"Can\\u2019t get enough of BTS? Try one of RM\\u2019s favorite foods: Korean knife-cut noodle soup.\"','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/6a3ad463ece5442698d99b8010fb3e8f/BFV79142_IRecreatedSomeOfBTSFavoriteFoods_AB_050621_Final_16x9_YT.jpg\"','6 cups water||4–6 dried anchovies||1 3-inch square piece of dried kombu (kelp)||1 medium zucchini, cut into matchsticks||1 small carrot, cut into matchsticks||2–3 shiitake mushrooms, thinly sliced||','stove_top||easy||comfort_food||weeknight||lunch||dinner||korean||asian_pacific_american_heritage_month||high_protein||high_fiber||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||dairy_free'),('bd-fe1577399423','\"One-Pot Garlic Tomato Shrimp Pasta\"','{\"0\":\"In a 6-quart Dutch oven, bring 4 quarts of salted water to a boil over medium-high heat.\",\"1\":\"Add spaghetti, cooking about 6-7 minutes until al dente. Drain and set aside.\",\"2\":\"Return the Dutch oven to the stovetop and heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil over medium heat.\",\"3\":\"Add the shrimp, salt, and ½ teaspoon of the red pepper flakes. Spread evenly across the bottom of the pot and cook until the bottoms pink and slightly brown, about 45-60 seconds. Flip and repeat until shrimp are just cooked through.\",\"4\":\"Remove the shrimp and place in a small bowl to the side.\",\"5\":\"Reduce heat to medium-low, and add additional 1 tablespoon of oil to the pot, as needed.\",\"6\":\"Add onion and garlic to the oil and cook until onions have softened, about 3-5 minutes. Stir frequently to ensure the garlic does not burn.\",\"7\":\"Add the diced tomatoes, remaining 1 teaspoon of salt, sugar, remaining 1 teaspoon red pepper flakes, oregano, and white wine.\",\"8\":\"Stir and bring the sauce up to a simmer. Simmer for 5-10 minutes until the sauce has thickened.\",\"9\":\"Return the shrimp (and any accumulated juices) to the sauce. Add the parsley, stirring to incorporate.\",\"10\":\"Add the cooked spaghetti back into the pot, toss until evenly coated and heated, then remove from heat. Serve immediately.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":14,\"carbohydrates\":112,\"fiber\":7,\"protein\":41,\"fat\":13,\"calories\":769}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/95b9d47547e842ad89aec733891e1339/BFV12880_One-PotTomatoGarlicShrimpPasta-ThumbTextless1080.jpg\"','1 pound spaghetti||3 tablespoons olive oil||1 pound shrimp, peeled and deveined||2 teaspoons salt||1 ½ teaspoon red pepper flakes||1 small yellow onion||8 cloves garlic, finely chopped (about 3 tablespoons)||42 ounces canned diced tomatoes, drained of excess water||1 teaspoon sugar||1 teaspoon oregano||1 cup dry white wine||1/3 cup fresh parsley, chopped||n/a||','stove_top||italian||one_pot_or_pan||dinner||weeknight||seafood||kid_friendly||easy||pan_fry||colander||wooden_spoon||oven_mitts||measuring_spoons||pyrex||tongs||chefs_knife||cutting_board||liquid_measuring_cup||dry_measuring_cups||sauce_pan||contains_alcohol'),('be-8d57efc91cf0','\"Chicken Teriyaki Fried Rice\"','{\"0\":\"Marinate the chicken in teriyaki sauce in the refrigerator for at least an hour.\",\"1\":\"In a wok or deep skillet, add the chicken in the teriyaki marinade and cook thoroughly over high heat. Set aside.\",\"2\":\"In the same pan, add the oil and cook onions, garlic, and carrots until onions are translucent.\",\"3\":\"Add broccoli and cook an additional 3-4 minutes. Push all of the cooked vegetables to the side of the pan.\",\"4\":\"Beat the eggs and pour into the cleared half of the pan. Scramble the eggs and mix with the rest of the vegetables.\",\"5\":\"Add rice, cooked chicken, soy sauce, sesame oil, and pepper. Mix well and let the rice cook until slightly crispy.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":38,\"fat\":14,\"calories\":520,\"sugar\":11,\"carbohydrates\":55,\"fiber\":4}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/19983b4a5a7643e4be6471e8012b18ca/BFV24904_FriedRice4Ways_FB1080SQ.jpg\"','2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cubed||1 cup teriyaki sauce||2 teaspoons oil||½ cup onion, diced||1 tablespoon garlic, minced||½ cup carrots, diced||1 cup broccoli florets||3 eggs, beaten||3 cups cooked brown rice||2 tablespoons soy sauce||1 tablespoon sesame oil||Pepper, to taste||','stove_top||american||fusion||kid_friendly||comfort_food||easy||pan_fry||weeknight||one_pot_or_pan||wok||japanese||mixing_bowl||pyrex||wooden_spoon||measuring_spoons||cutting_board||chefs_knife||dry_measuring_cups||liquid_measuring_cup||oven_mitts||sides||high_protein||high_fiber||dairy_free||walmart_meal_planning'),('bf-1de3144d0dfd','\"Chicken Tinga Tacos (Tinga De Pollo)\"','{\"0\":\"Place chicken in a saucepan over medium heat with enough water to cover by 1 inch (3 cm).\",\"1\":\"Add the smashed garlic and cloves. Simmer until the chicken is cooked through, 12-15 minutes.\",\"2\":\"Remove the chicken from the pot, cool slightly, then shred with two forks.\",\"3\":\"Place a cast-iron skillet over medium-high heat, until smoking.\",\"4\":\"Add the tomatoes and roll slowly around until blackened on all sides, about 6 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Add the seared tomatoes to a blender with chipotle peppers, chicken stock, cumin, and nutmeg. Blend until smooth.\",\"6\":\"Heat the vegetable oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Add the garlic, onions, and chorizo. Cook 2-3 minutes until the onions have softened and the chorizo has rendered a little fat.\",\"7\":\"Add the lettuce and sauté 2-3 additional minutes, until softened.\",\"8\":\"Add the tomato-chili mixture and cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly to incorporate.\",\"9\":\"Add the shredded chicken and bring mixture to a simmer. Simmer, uncovered, until most of the liquid has cooked off, about 10-15 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste.\",\"10\":\"Serve on warm corn tortillas with sliced avocado.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":35,\"calories\":661,\"sugar\":6,\"carbohydrates\":51,\"fiber\":12,\"protein\":38}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/da44fcf619c2459aa44dbc5c665c22ca/FBthumb1.jpg\"','2 boneless, skinless, chicken breasts||6 garlic cloves (4 minced, 2 smashed)||2 whole cloves||2 tomatoes||5 chipotle peppers in adobo||½ cup chicken stock||2 teaspoons cumin||½ teaspoon nutmeg||2 tablespoons vegetable oil||2 white onions, halved and sliced||¼ pound chorizo||1 head iceberg lettuce, shredded||Kosher salt||Black pepper, freshly ground||2 avocados, sliced||12 corn tortillas||','cast_iron_pan||blender||stove_top||mexican||american||fusion||easy||dinner||pan_fry||weeknight||cinco_de_mayo'),('bf-bccc825a7253','\"Shrimp Summer Salad With Creamy Cilantro Dressing\"','{\"0\":\"Make the dressing: Add the cilantro, sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice,  garlic, nutritional yeast, chives, and water to a blender and blend until smooth. Season with salt and pepper to taste.\",\"1\":\"Assemble the salad: In a large bowl, combine the romaine, red onion, cucumber, jalapeño, cherry tomatoes, baby corn, mango, and avocado. Drizzle the cilantro dressing over the salad and toss until evenly coated.\",\"2\":\"Divide the salad between 4 serving bowls and top with the shrimp, feta, and chives. Season with salt and pepper.\",\"3\":\"Any leftover salad will keep in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 1 day.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":19,\"calories\":400,\"sugar\":15,\"carbohydrates\":27,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":28}','\"Summer is coming to an end, so we have to take advantage of all the bountiful seasonal produce while we still can. Enjoy this refreshing and delicious salad with all the flavors summer has to offer, like cucumbers, mini heirloom tomatoes, baby corn, mango, and avocado.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/dbccd3ca691b467185d910918146407c.jpeg\"','½ cup chopped fresh cilantro||¼ cup sour cream||¼ cup mayonnaise||Juice of 1 lemon||1 garlic clove||1 tablespoon nutritional yeast||1 tablespoon chopped fresh chives||2 tablespoons water||Kosher salt, to taste||Freshly ground black pepper, to taste||','easy||healthy||under_30_minutes||low_carb||dinner||lunch||low_calorie||low_sugar||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||pescatarian'),('c0-0496f02b63ec','\"Larb As Made By Aria\"','{\"0\":\"Place 3 cups (690 G) Thai sticky rice in a medium bowl and cover with cold water by at least 1 inch (2 ½ cm). Cover with plastic wrap and soak overnight at room temperature. After the rice has soaked, drain and set aside.\",\"1\":\"Fill the large pot with 3 inches (7 cm) of water and bring to a steady simmer over medium-high heat.\",\"2\":\"Cut out a circle of parchment paper large enough to line the steamer insert and come 2 inches (5 cm) up the sides.\",\"3\":\"Place the parchment in the insert, add the rice, and spread in an even layer. Place the insert in the pot, cover with the lid, and steam until the rice is translucent and tender, 20-30 minutes. Turn off the heat, but keep the rice covered so it stays warm while you prepare the larb.\",\"4\":\"Toast the remaining ⅓ cup (75 G) rice in a small pan over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until light golden brown, about 5 minutes. Immediately pour the rice into a small bowl and let cool completely.\",\"5\":\"Grind the toasted rice in a spice grinder or mortar and pestle until finely ground. Set aside.\",\"6\":\"Heat the chicken stock in a wok or large pan over medium heat. Once the stock is steaming, add the pork. Break up the meat with a wooden spoon and cook gently, stirring occasionally, until just cooked through and no longer pink, 8-10 minutes. Turn off the heat and stir in the garlic, shallots, lemongrass, and galangal.\",\"7\":\"Add the fish sauce, lime juice, chiles, scallions, mint, cilantro, and toasted rice to the pork mixture and stir to combine. Season with more fish sauce, if desired.\",\"8\":\"Serve the larb with the sticky rice, cabbage leaves, cucumbers, bean sprouts, and lime wedges.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":47,\"fat\":39,\"calories\":1073,\"sugar\":77,\"carbohydrates\":118}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/213136.jpg\"','3⅓ cups Thai sticky rice, divided||Cold water, for soaking rice||⅔ cup low-sodium chicken stock||2 pounds lean ground pork||4 cloves garlic, minced||2 large shallots, thinly sliced (about ½ cup)||2 stalks lemongrass, green tops discarded and pale yellow stalks minced (about ⅓ cup)||1 1½-inch piece galangal root, peeled and finely grated (about ⅓ cup)||⅓ cup fish sauce, plus more to taste||½ cup fresh lime juice||3-5 Thai bird chiles, minced||4 scallions, thinly sliced (about ¼ cup)||1½ cups fresh mint leaves, loosely packed, roughly chopped||1½ cups fresh cilantro leaves and soft stems, loosely packed, roughly chopped||Red or green cabbage leaves, for serving||Thinly sliced English cucumbers, for serving||Bean sprouts, for serving||Lime wedges, for serving||','stove_top||asian_pacific_american_heritage_month||summer||wooden_spoon||mixing_bowl||plastic_wrap||dinner||weeknight||high_protein||dairy_free'),('c0-0f179537d440','\"Cheesy Taquitos (Chequitos)\"','{\"0\":\"In a large saucepan over medium heat, brown the ground beef. Once the beef is browned, add the onion and garlic. Cook until the onion is translucent, about 5 minutes. Add the salt, cumin, chili powder, cayenne, paprika, and oregano. Cook for 2-3 minutes more to allow the flavors to meld and ensure the beef is cooked through. Remove the beef mixture from the pan and set aside.\",\"1\":\"In a clean large saucepan over medium heat, combine the shredded chicken and crushed tomatoes. Add the salt, cumin, chili powder, cayenne, paprika, and oregano. Cook until warmed through, about 5 minutes. Remove from the pan and set aside.\",\"2\":\"In a medium bowl, mix together the Parmesan and Mexican-blend cheeses.\",\"3\":\"Heat a medium nonstick pan over medium heat. Add about ¼ cup (25 G)  of cheese to the center of the pan and spread into a circle. Let the cheese melt, then add a spoonful of beef or chicken filling to the bottom of the circle.\",\"4\":\"Slide the cheese shell out of the pan onto a cutting board and let cool for 30 seconds, then roll tightly to encase the filling. The melted cheese should stick to the outside, sealing the taquito. Repeat with the remaining ingredients.\",\"5\":\"Serve the taquitos with lime wedges, sour cream, and fresh cilantro.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":7,\"protein\":20,\"fat\":15,\"calories\":256,\"sugar\":1,\"carbohydrates\":7}','\"\"','16','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/189166.jpg\"','1 pound 80/20 ground beef||1 cup diced white onion||3 cloves garlic, minced||1 teaspoon kosher salt||1½ teaspoons ground cumin||½ teaspoon chili powder||½ teaspoon cayenne||2 teaspoons paprika||1 teaspoon dried oregano||','stove_top||comfort_food||mashup||mexican||stuffed||dinner||weeknight||game_day||pan_fry||kid_friendly||easy||american||spatula||mixing_bowl||cutting_board||low_carb||low_sugar||keto'),('c0-74322b4acc31','\"Korean Grilled Pork Belly (Samgyeopsal)\"','{\"0\":\"Make the ssamjang: In a medium bowl, stir together the soybean paste, chile paste, mirin, sesame oil, garlic, and sugar.\",\"1\":\"Make the salt \\u0026 pepper sesame oil: In a small bowl, stir together the salt, sesame oil, and pepper.\",\"2\":\"Heat a Korean barbecue griddle or large pan over medium-high heat. When the pan is hot, rub a piece of pork belly around the pan to grease with the melted fat, then arrange the pork belly in the pan in a single layer, working in batches to avoid overcrowding the pan. Cook until the pork belly is golden brown and crispy and the internal temperature reaches at least 145°F (63°C), 2–3 minutes per side.\",\"3\":\"Cut the pork belly into bite-size pieces using kitchen shears, then arrange on a plate with the perilla leaves, red leaf lettuce, jalapeños, and garlic. Serve with the ssamjang and salt \\u0026 pepper sesame oil.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":687,\"sugar\":2,\"carbohydrates\":3,\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":10,\"fat\":69}','\"Can\\u2019t get enough of BTS? Try one of Suga\\u2019s favorite foods: Korean grilled pork belly (samgyeopsal). It\\u2019s simple, quick, and packed with flavor. Try a bite with a slice of garlic, jalape\\u00F1o, and the ssamjang dipping sauce; it\\u2019s delicious!\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/e7fba141ec8a437b8a8c4bf6be9f7509/BFV79142_IRecreatedSomeOfBTSFavoriteFoods_AB_050621_Final_16x9_YT.jpg\"','3 tablespoons soybean paste (doenjang)||1 tablespoons Korean chili paste (gochujang)||1 tablespoons mirin||1 tablespoons sesame oil||2 teaspoon minced garlic (about 2 large cloves)||1 teaspoon sugar||','asian_pacific_american_heritage_month||measuring_spoons||dinner||korean||stove_top||easy||comfort_food||bbq||lunch||grill||low_carb||low_sugar||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||dairy_free||keto'),('c1-58e6bef5778d','\"2-Day Crab And Pork Soup Dumplings\"','{\"0\":\"Make the pork broth: Add the pork necks and skin to a large pot. Cover with water by 2 inches and bring to a boil over high heat. Drain and rinse the necks and skin under cold water, then return to the pot.\",\"1\":\"Add 4 cups of water, the ginger, scallions, rice wine, and peppercorns. Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 2 hours, skimming the surface occasionally.\",\"2\":\"Strain the broth through a fine-mesh strainer into a shallow baking dish and stir in the salt. Let cool to room temperature, then cover with plastic wrap and chill in the refrigerator overnight, until set.\",\"3\":\"Make the chile oil: In a small pot, combine the star anise, cinnamon stick, bay leaves, Sichuan peppercorns, garlic, and canola oil. Cook over low heat until small bubbles appear around the garlic cloves, about 10 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Add the Sichuan red chile flakes and salt to a heat-proof jar. Strain the oil into the jar and stir to combine. Let cool, then cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.\",\"5\":\"Make the filling: Add the ground pork, ginger, scallions, soy sauce, sesame oil, rice wine, sugar, and water to a medium bowl and mix until evenly combined. If the filling feels too thick, add another tablespoon of water and stir until light and airy. Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.\",\"6\":\"Make the dough: In a medium bowl, combine the flour, salt, and warm water. Stir to combine, then turn out onto a floured surface. Knead for about 20 minutes, dusting with more flour as needed, until very soft and smooth. Cover the dough with plastic wrap and let rest at room temperature for 30 minutes.\",\"7\":\"Divide the dough in half and cover one portion with a damp towel. Roll the remaining portion into a 1-inch wide log, then cut into 12 pieces, rotating the log as you cut. Cover 11 pieces with the damp towel. Roll the remaining piece into a ball, then flatten with your palm. Dust with flour as needed to prevent sticking. Use a small rolling pin to roll the dough into a 3-inch round, then use the rolling pin to roll the edges thinner than the center, until the diameter of the wrapper is 3½–4 inches. Cover with the towel and repeat with the remaining dough.\",\"8\":\"Fill the dumplings: Remove the chilled pork broth from the refrigerator and cut into ½-inch cubes.\",\"9\":\"Scoop about 1 tablespoon of the filling on the center of a dumpling wrapper. Add about ½ teaspoon crab paste and 1 pork broth cube. Hold the dumpling in the palm of one hand and use the other to pleat the edges of the wrapper around the filling, pinching and twisting at the top to seal. Set on a baking sheet and repeat with the remaining filling and wrappers.\",\"10\":\"Fill a large pot ⅓ of the way with water to a boil over high heat. Place a bamboo steamer basket on top and line with Napa cabbage leaves. Place the dumplings on top of the cabbage, leaving space for them to expand. Stack a second steamer basket on top and repeat to add more dumplings. Cover and steam for about 8 minutes, until the wrappers are slightly translucent and the filling is cooked through.\",\"11\":\"Serve the dumplings with the chile oil, black vinegar, and ginger.\",\"12\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":8,\"fat\":14,\"calories\":187,\"sugar\":0,\"carbohydrates\":5,\"fiber\":0}','\"Have you ever wanted to make xiaolongbao at home, but felt intimidated or scared? Here we break down the 2-day process of making soup dumplings with ease and a bit of patience. Start with a homemade pork broth that chills overnight to gelatinize, which is then added to homemade dumpling wrappers along with delicious pork filling and crab paste. The dumplings are steamed to perfection and served with homemade chile oil for dipping,\"','24','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/a7209c5cbe7643dcbd63136a1cb56cf8/BFV81055_2MinVs20MinVs2DayDumplings_AB_071421_ForFinal.jpg\"','1 pound pork necks||½ pound pork skin or hocks||4 cups water, plus more as needed||4 slices of fresh ginger||2 scallions||1 tablespoon rice wine||3 whole black peppercorns||⅛ teaspoon kosher salt||','lunch||date_night||stove_top||dinner||taiwanese||asian_pacific_american_heritage_month||steam||special_occasion||low_carb||low_calorie||dairy_free'),('c1-8f3b34c0f68b','\"Scallops With Caper Pan Sauce\"','{\"0\":\"Season the scallops on both sides with salt and pepper.\",\"1\":\"In a large skillet, melt together 1 tablespoon butter and the olive oil over high heat. When the butter has melted, add the scallops to the pan and sear, flipping once halfway through, until golden brown on both sides and nearly opaque all the way through, 3–4 minutes total. Divide the scallops between 2 plates and return the skillet to medium-high heat.\",\"2\":\"Melt 2 tablespoons butter in the skillet. Add the shallots and garlic. Cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned, about 2 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Stir in the capers and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Pour in the wine and cook, stirring, until slightly reduced, about 3 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Remove the skillet from the heat and add the remaining tablespoon of butter, swirling the pan until it melts into the sauce. Season the sauce with salt and pepper, then spoon over the scallops. Serve hot.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":19,\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":26,\"fat\":8,\"calories\":263,\"sugar\":2}','\"Want to serve a show-stopping dinner that comes together in no time at all? Seared to golden brown perfection and bathed in a buttery pan sauce of fragrant shallots and white wine and briny capers, these scallops are sure to impress. And since the whole dish takes just 15 minutes to make, you don\\u2019t need to wait for a special occasion to indulge.\"','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/278187.jpg\"','1 pound large sea scallops (about 12)||Kosher salt, to taste||Freshly ground black pepper, to taste||4 tablespoons (½ stick) unsalted butter, divided||1 tablespoon olive oil||2 shallots, minced||1 garlic clove, minced||¼ cup drained capers, rinsed||½ cup white wine, such as Sauvignon Blanc||','cutting_board||tongs||casual_party||date_night||pan_fry||dinner||seafood||stove_top||every_occasion||high_protein||low_sugar||under_30_minutes||under_15_minutes||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||vegetarian'),('c1-a3de11dae72c','\"Taco Mac And Cheese\"','{\"0\":\"Bring 6 cups (1 liter) of water to a boil in a medium saucepan over medium-high heat. Stir in the macaroni and cook for 7–8 minutes, or until tender, stirring occasionally.\",\"1\":\"While the macaroni is cooking, heat a medium nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add the ground beef and cook for 5–6 minutes, until browned. Mix in 1 tablespoon of taco seasoning, then remove the pan from the heat.\",\"2\":\"Drain the macaroni in a colander (do not rinse), then return to the pot over low heat. Add the butter, milk, cheese sauce mix, ¼ cup (25 G) Kraft® Shredded Cheddar Cheese, and the remaining tablespoon of taco seasoning and stir well until creamy. Remove the pot from the heat.\",\"3\":\"Heat the broiler to high.\",\"4\":\"Fold the ground beef into the mac and cheese, then transfer to a medium oven-safe container. Sprinkle the remaining ½ cup (100 G) Kraft® Shredded Cheddar Cheese on top.\",\"5\":\"Broil the mac and cheese for 2–4 minutes, until the cheese is melted.\",\"6\":\"Remove from the oven and drizzle with the Cholula® Hot Sauce, then top with the tomato and green onion. Serve warm.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":46,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":35,\"fat\":40,\"calories\":703,\"sugar\":8}','\"\"','3','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/789f9084e3a041e19cfa5d9a7ca86af8/KRAFT_HEINZ_MacAndCheese_BoldMac4Ways_SQ_Hero.jpg\"','½ pound lean ground beef||½ teaspoon kosher salt||2 tablespoons taco seasoning, divided||1 7.25-ounce box Kraft® Macaroni and Cheese Blue Box Original||4 ta