d ground beef||½ pound sweet Italian sausage||1 teaspoon salt||1 teaspoon pepper||1 28-ounce can diced tomatoes||1 28-ounce can tomato sauce||15 ounces whole milk ricotta||1 cup grated parmesan cheese||½ cup fresh basil, chopped||1 egg||4-5 cooked lasagna noodles, quartered||1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese||n/a||','american||kid_friendly||italian||fusion||casual_party||stove_top||mashup||oven||weeknight||comfort_food||bake||chefs_knife||cutting_board||wooden_spoon||baking_pan||dry_measuring_cups||mixing_bowl||oven_mitts||dinner||pyrex||pan_fry'),('c5-e32863e50b07','\"Spaghetti And Meatballs\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C). Set a wire rack over a baking sheet and grease with nonstick spray.\",\"1\":\"Make the marinara sauce: Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add the onions and garlic and season with salt, pepper, and the red pepper flakes. Cook until soft and caramelized, about 15 minutes.\",\"2\":\"Set aside ⅓ cup (50 G) of the cooked onions and garlic for the meatballs and let cool.\",\"3\":\"Stir the tomato paste into the onions and cook until browned and aromatic, 3-5 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Add the crushed tomatoes, dried basil, dried oregano, and dried parsley. Stir together and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for at least 30 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Make the meatballs: In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, ground pork, reserved onion and garlic mixture, bread crumbs, ricotta, parsley, eggs, Parmesan, milk, salt, and pepper. Mix with your hands until well combined.\",\"6\":\"Shape about 2 ounces (55 G) of meat at a time into balls and set on the prepared wire rack.\",\"7\":\"Bake the meatballs for 20 minutes, until the outsides are browned and the centers are tender and juicy and reach about 155˚F (68˚C).\",\"8\":\"Bring a large pot of water to boil and add a generous pinch of salt. Cook the pasta according to the package instructions, 7-10 minutes, until al dente. Stir occasionally to keep the noodles 