rain of the meat is running horizontally. Use six toothpicks to secure the steak roll. Slice the steak roll into six equal rolls.\",\"5\":\"Heat the remaining oil in a pan over high heat. Sear the steak rolls on one side for one to two minutes, then flip. Sear the second side for about one minute, then bake for 10–15 minutes, until medium rare.\",\"6\":\"Remove the toothpicks, then serve!\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":5,\"fiber\":13,\"protein\":43,\"fat\":16,\"calories\":354,\"sugar\":3}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/f0ca1b8062ba402787c91137b3679c0f/bfv7231_Stuffed_Steak_Rolls-fb1080.jpg\"','2 tablespoons canola oil, divided||3 tablespoons chopped garlic||2 sweet onions, such as Vidalia, chopped||2 cups mushrooms, thinly sliced||½ tablespoon kosher salt||½ tablespoon freshly ground black pepper||2 pounds flank steak||1 (4-ounce) package baby spinach||9 slices provolone cheese||','bake||oven||stuffed||casual_party||dinner||stove_top||healthy||easy||american||pan_fry||gluten_free||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||saute_pan||cutting_board||tongs||wooden_spoon||oven_mitts||baking_pan||weeknight||pyrex||chefs_knife||mashup'),('d7-cf632d26622a','\"How To Cook A Perfect Risotto\"','{\"0\":\"Add the stock to a medium pot and bring to a boil over high heat. Once the stock is boiling, reduce the heat to low or remove the pan from the heat and keep nearby.\",\"1\":\"Heat the olive oil in a wide, tall pot over medium heat. Once the oil begins to shimmer, add the shallot and cook, stirring frequently, until translucent.\",\"2\":\"Add the shiitake mushrooms and butter. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the mushrooms have cooked down and browned.\",\"3\":\"Add the garlic, thyme, salt, and pepper, stir, and cook for 1 minute, until the garlic is fragrant.\",\"4\":\"Add the rice and stir until fully coated in the mushroom mixture. Let the rice toast for 1-2 minutes, until aromatic.\",\"5\":\"Add the white wine and cook until evaporated, stirring occasionally.\",\"6\":\"Add 1 cup (240 ml) of the hot stock and stir to combine. Cook, stirring frequently, until the stock is fully absorbed by the rice.\",\"7\":\"Continue to add the stock, ½ cup (120 ml) at a time, stirring continuously, until fully absorbed, 15-20 minutes. Depending on how fast the rice cooks, there may be leftover stock.\",\"8\":\"Once the rice is al dente, remove from the heat. Add the Parmesan and stir to combine.\",\"9\":\"Garnish the risotto with parsley, Parmesan, salt, and pepper.\",\"10\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":20,\"calories\":433,\"sugar\":3,\"carbohydrates\":48,\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":13}','\"Making risotto at home may seem like a daunting task, but our recipe breaks the process down into simple steps for a foolproof result. Aromatics like shallots, garlic, and thyme build layers of flavor, while gradually adding hot stock as you stir helps coax the starches out of the arborio rice for the creamiest risotto. We love incorporating mushrooms for added flavor, but feel free to make the dish without\\u2014or swap in your favorite vegetable! Savory and rich, risotto will make the perfect centerpiece dish for your next dinner party.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/d9e73830340c4d2fb0ec5075d8d7d26c/BFV38271_CC2017_11.1.2_FINAL.jpg\"','6 cups low-sodium chicken stock or vegetable stock||2 tablespoons olive oil||1 shallot, finely chopped||1 pound shiitake mushrooms, stemmed and thinly sliced||2 tablespoons unsalted butter||2 cloves garlic, minced||1 teaspoon fresh thyme, finely chopped||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||1½ cups arborio rice||½ cup white wine||1 cup grated Parmesan cheese, plus more for serving||¼ cup chopped fresh parsley, for serving||','stove_top||dinner||wooden_spoon||dry_measuring_cups||italian||cheese_grater||sauce_pan||liquid_measuring_cup||measuring_spoons||lunch||special_occasion||date_night||contains_alcohol'),('d7-d356691f2a1f','\"Spaghetti Pie\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 350˚F (180˚C).\",\"1\":\"Wrap pasta in a clean dish towel and fold twice, breaking pasta into smaller 1-3 inch  (2½ - 7½ cm) pieces.\",\"2\":\"Cook until al dente (about 3 minutes) and drain well.\",\"3\":\"In medium-sized bowl, mix warm cooked pasta with garlic, butter, grated parmesan, egg, and bread crumbs. Still until well incorporated and the butter and cheese have completely melted.\",\"4\":\"Press pasta mixture into a deep 10-inch (25-cm) pie plate or casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs.\",\"5\":\"Bake 15-20 minutes, until crust is set and edges have started to brown\",\"6\":\"Heat oil over medium heat in a large skillet. Add onions and cook until softened, about 3 minutes. Add in ground beef and cook until lightly browned. Using a spoon, drain off any excess fat that accumulates in the pan.\",\"7\":\"Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste, and sugar. Simmer until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat and mix in basil. Season with salt and pepper.\",\"8\":\"In a small bowl, mix together ricotta, egg, and oregano.\",\"9\":\"Spread ricotta mixture over the cooked pasta crust. Spread the meat sauce over the top of the ricotta mixture then cover with mozzarella. Bake at 350˚F (180˚C) for 25 minutes or until golden brown on top.\",\"10\":\"Let cool for 15-20 minutes before serving.\",\"11\":\"Fancy-Pants Parmesan Crisps (optional for garnish): Pour a tablespoon of parmesan cheese onto a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Bake at 400˚F (200˚C) until cheese has melted and become golden and crisp, about 5 minutes. Let cool before removing from parchment paper.\",\"12\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":466,\"sugar\":7,\"carbohydrates\":31,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":25,\"fat\":26}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/a8b55bb747994f5780fbb34980e1811f/Tumb_1.jpg\"','4 ounces angel hair (broken in half 2 times)||2 cloves garlic minced||2 tablespoons butter||1 cup parmesan cheese, grated||1 large egg, beaten||2 tablespoons bread crumbs||','ove