 minutes.\",\"2\":\"Add the noodles, reserved soaking water, and the chile-garlic paste to the wok and stir until the noodles are evenly coated in the sauce.\",\"3\":\"Transfer the noodles and sauce to serving bowls and top with the sliced scallion greens. Serve with more sesame oil and chile-garlic paste alongside.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":37,\"fat\":34,\"calories\":826,\"sugar\":3,\"carbohydrates\":89,\"fiber\":5}','\"What\\u2019s more comforting than a bowl of noodles with spicy and savory ground pork? With fragrant, flavorful sesame oil, scallions, and chile-garlic paste, this dish is a treat for all of the senses.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/369405.jpg\"','14 ounces flat rice noodles, such as for pad Thai||Boiling water, for soaking noodles||2 tablespoons toasted sesame oil, plus more for serving||1½ pounds ground pork||6 scallions, white and light green parts minced, dark green parts thinly sliced||Kosher salt, to taste||Freshly ground black pepper, to taste||2 tablespoons chile-garlic paste, plus more for serving||','wok||cast_iron_pan||spatula||weeknight||dinner||lunch||asian_pacific_american_heritage_month||one_pot_or_pan||big_batch||saute_pan||pan_fry||high_protein||under_30_minutes||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||dairy_free'),('de-f61d3b420feb','\"Protein-Packed Roasted Vegetable Salad\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 400℉ (200℃). Grease a baking sheet with nonstick spray.\",\"1\":\"Reserve a few broccoli florets, then place the remaining broccoli, chickpeas, Brussels sprouts, sweet potato, and tofu on the baking sheet in individual piles. Drizzle with the olive oil and season with salt, pepper, and chili powder. Bake for 25 minutes, until the vegetables are tender and the tofu is browned.\",\"2\":\"Make the dressing: In a large mason jar, combine the hummus, lemon juice, olive oil, thyme, salt, pepper, and water. Stir to combine.\",\"3\":\"Add the reserved raw broccoli, the roasted broccoli, sweet potato, chickpeas, Brussels sprouts, tofu, and spinach and screw on the lid.\",\"4\":\"Store in the refrigerator until ready to eat, up to 5 days.\",\"5\":\"Give the mason jar a good shake to mix and use a fork or spoon to stir as needed.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":14,\"carbohydrates\":54,\"fiber\":13,\"protein\":20,\"fat\":77,\"calories\":960}','','1','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/9f53d022dfa54ef8a6081c61226b5b7b/fb.jpg\"','2 tablespoons hummus||1 tablespoon lemon juice||1 tablespoon olive oil||1 teaspoon dried thyme||1 teaspoon salt||1 teaspoon pepper||½ teaspoon water||','oven||american||healthy||easy||baking_pan||oven_mitts||lunch||bake||weeknight||spatula||pyrex||cutting_board||measuring_spoons||chefs_knife||mixing_bowl||dry_measuring_cups||liquid_measuring_cup||nynm_meal_prep||high_fiber||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian||walmart_meal_planning'),('df-0d8db61ddcd6','\"Chicken Parmesan Bread Bowl\"','{\"0\":\"In a medium bowl, combine bread crumbs, parsley garlic powder, onion powder, oregano, salt, and pepper to bread crumbs.\",\"1\":\"Place flour and eggs in two other medium bowls.\",\"2\":\"Roll the chicken breast in the flour, dusting off any excess. Dip the chicken into the egg, then place into the breadcrumbs, coating it completely.\",\"3\":\"Heat the oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.\",\"4\":\"Once the oil begins to shimmer, fry the breaded chicken strips until both sides are golden brown.\",\"5\":\"Remove from heat and drain on a paper towel.\",\"6\":\"Preheat oven to 350°F (180˚C).\",\"7\":\"Slice the cooked chicken breast into ½-inch (1 cm) thick strips.\",\"8\":\"Slice the top of the bread bowl off and scoop out the insides. Save the top of the bowl.\",\"9\":\"Spoon and spread some of the marinara sauce on the bottom of the bowl, then layer on mozzarella, Parmesan cheese, chicken strips, marinara, remaining mozzarella, Parmesan, chicken strips, marinara, and remaining Parmesan.\",\"10\":\"Place the cap of the bread bowl on top.\",\"11\":\"Wrap the bread bowl in foil, then weigh it down with a heavy object for 30 minutes.\",\"12\":\"In a small bowl, mix together butter, garlic, parsley, and Parmesan cheese.\",\"13\":\"Remove the foil from the bread bowl and brush the garlic butter mixture evenly over it.\",\"14\":\"Bake for 30 minutes.\",\"15\":\"Cool for 10 minutes and slice.\",\"16\":\"Garnish with basil, if desired.\",\"17\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":722,\"sugar\":6,\"carbohydrates\":72,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":44,\"fat\":27}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/124203.jpg\"','1 cup bread crumbs||½ teaspoon parsley, chopped||½ teaspoon garlic powder||½ teaspoon onion powder||¼ teaspoon oregano||½ teaspoon salt||¼ teaspoon pepper||1 cup flour||3 eggs, beaten||2 boneless, skinless chicken breast, thinly sliced||Oil, for frying||1 bread boule||1 cup marinara sauce||8 ounces mozzarella||½ cup shredded Parmesan cheese||3 tablespoon butter, melted||3 cloves garlic, minced||1 tablespoon parsley, chopped||1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese, grated||Basil, for serving||','dry_measuring_cups||stove_top||chefs_knife||tongs||oven||comfort_food||mixing_bowl||italian||cutting_board||cheese_grater||parchment_paper||whisk||oven_mitts||bake||stuffed||dinner||special_occasion||high_protein'),('df-2ab47ae45576','\"Beef \\u0026 Bean Burritos\"','{\"0\":\"Add ground beef to a large skillet over high heat and sprinkle with taco seasoning. Cook, breaking up the meat, until browned. Drain the fat and set aside to cool.\",\"1\":\"Assemble the burritos by microwaving the flour tortilla for 20 seconds, and begin to layer burrito starting with refried beans, followed by the cooked beef and cheese.\",\"2\":\"Fold in the left and right sides of the tortilla and roll it up from the bottom, tucking the bottom edge under the filling. Wrap in parchment paper and label. Freeze up to 1 month.\",\"3\":\"To reheat from frozen, wrap the burrito in a damp paper towel and microwave for 2-3 minutes, flipping halfway or until the center is hot. Let stand 1 minute before eating.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":480,\"sugar\":1,\"carbohydrates\":34,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":31,\"fat\":22}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/58ef7d23dad14adc9898d73fc6330336/BFV28863_FreezerPrepBurritos_FB1080SQ.jpg\"','1 pound ground beef||2 tablespoons taco seasoning||6 flour tortillas||1 16-ounce can refried beans||1 cup shredded Mexican cheese blend||','freezer||microwave||comfort_food||kid_friendly||easy||big_batch||meal_prep||dinner||weeknight||mexican||lunch||budget_10||high_protein||low_sugar||5_ingredients_or_less'),('df-835988fbe673','\"Vegetarian Grain Bowl Meal Prep\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 425˚F (220˚C). Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.\",\"1\":\"On 1 baking sheet, season the vegetables and chickpeas for the Roasted Chickpea \\u0026 Veggie Brown Rice Bowl with olive oil, salt, pepper, and paprika.\",\"2\":\"On the other baking sheet, season the vegetables for the Roasted Veggie Quinoa Bowl  with olive oil, salt, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder.\",\"3\":\"Bake for 15 -20 minutes, or until the vegetables are roasted to your liking.\",\"4\":\"Fill 2 glass storage bowls with 1 cup cooked brown rice each. Fill 2 more glass storage bowls with 1 cup cooked quinoa each.\",\"5\":\"Fill the brown rice bowls with the roasted chickpea and vegetables. Fill the quinoa bowls with the other roasted vegetables. \",\"6\":\"Mix the cilantro-lime dressing ingredients and split the dressing between 2 small glass containers. Store in the refrigerator with the roasted vegetable and chickpea bowls for up to 4 days.\",\"7\":\"Mix the soy-maple dressing ingredients and split the dressing between 2 small glass containers. Store in the refrigerator with the roasted vegetable quinoa bowls for up to 4 days.\",\"8\":\"To serve, remove the containers with the dressing and heat the bowls in the microwave for 1 minute. Pour the dressing on top and mix everything together.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":1240,\"sugar\":28,\"carbohydrates\":218,\"fiber\":28,\"protein\":39,\"fat\":25}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/7baf11ef841f48a58d70fffae4ae57de/BFV19033_VegetarianGrainBowlMealPrep-ThumbTextless.jpg\"','1 sweet potato, peeled and quartered||½ pound Brussels sprouts, trimmed and halved||1 yellow bell pepper, chopped||½ red onion, chopped||1 can chickpeas, drained and rinsed||Olive oil, to taste||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||Paprika, to taste||2 cups brown rice, cooked||','stove_top||american||meal_prep||big_batch||healthy||bake||dinner||lunch||weeknight||high_protein||high_fiber||vegetarian'),('df-ca2a6f9e61ae','\"Sweet Potato Guerrilla Tacos\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).\",\"1\":\"Trim and discard the tough green parts from the leeks, then cut them in in half lengthwise. Swirl in water to remove any sand. Pat dry.\",\"2\":\"On a large baking tray, place the leeks, sweet potatoes and garlic. Pour melted butter and salt evenly over the vegetables.\",\"3\":\"Bake for 25 minutes.\",\"4\":\"In a large saucepan, bring the white wine, thyme and parsley to a boil and cook until it loses the raw alcohol smell, about 5 minutes. Reduce the heat to a bare simmer.\",\"5\":\"When the leeks are golden take both leeks and garlic off the tray. Place potatoes back in the oven for another 20 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Add leeks and garlic into the simmering wine sauce. Cook until leeks are tender, about 30 minutes.\",\"7\":\"Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Pull the leeks from the cooking liquid, pat them dry and add to the butter to cook briefly on both sides, about 3 minutes total.\",\"8\":\"Remove the stem ends from the leeks and cut into 2-inch (5 cm) lengths.\",\"9\":\"For each taco, heat 2 tortillas on a griddle or in a large skillet over medium-high heat with a little butter. Place 2 slices of Oaxaca cheese next to them 