\":10,\"protein\":47,\"fat\":53,\"calories\":1132,\"sugar\":18,\"carbohydrates\":115}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/217949.jpg\"','1 32-ounce package of Great Value® Italian-Style Meatballs||Kosher salt, to taste||1 pound Sam\'s Choice® Italia Tagliatelle Egg Pasta||3 cups marinara sauce||½ cup shredded mozzarella cheese||','sponsored_recipe||stove_top||oven||cheese_grater||oven_mitts||dry_measuring_cups||pyrex||sauce_pan||strainer||wooden_spoon||dinner||bake||weeknight||kid_friendly||eko_video||high_protein||high_fiber||5_ingredients_or_less'),('e1-f76b1f787106','\"Creamy Potato Kale Gratin\"','{\"0\":\"Thinly sliced the potatoes, roughly ¼-inch (5mm) thick.\",\"1\":\"Remove stems from kale and cut into ¾ inch-1 inch (2 cm) pieces.\",\"2\":\"For the Béchamel sauce, add butter and garlic to a saucepan on medium heat and sauté until aromatic.\",\"3\":\"Add flour and mix until mixture browns slightly.\",\"4\":\"Add milk, salt, and pepper and simmer on low heat until mixture thickens.\",\"5\":\"In a medium-sized oven dish, lay a hefty bed of kale adding olive oil, salt, and pepper and gently mixing.\",\"6\":\"Starting from one side layer your potatoes across the kale covering the entire dish.\",\"7\":\"Gently press the potatoes and kale mixture down to make more room in the dish.\",\"8\":\"Drizzle half of the Béchamel sauce across all of the potatoes.\",\"9\":\"Repeat the process and add another layer of kale, olive oil, salt, pepper, and potatoes and cover with remaining sauce.\",\"10\":\"Garnish to taste with parmesan, Gruyère, and bread crumbs\",\"11\":\"Bake at 350°F (180°C) for 30 minutes covered. Remove cover and bake an additional 30 minutes.\",\"12\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":13,\"fat\":12,\"calories\":402,\"sugar\":5,\"carbohydrates\":60,\"fiber\":4}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/065df47d92a94bd8bc8ae60c3546dcb2/IMG_0045_fb.jpg\"','1½ -2 pounds russet potatoes, washed and peeled||1 bunch kale, washed||¼ cup parmesan cheese, shredded||¼ cup Gruyère cheese, shredded||¼ cup bread crumbs||','weeknight||american||comfort_food||french||dinner||stove_top||oven||easy||bake||measuring_spoons||liquid_measuring_cup||dry_measuring_cups||cutting_board||chefs_knife||whisk||sauce_pan||oven_mitts||baking_pan||walmart_holiday_bundle'),('e2-4c17ccc0cd71','\"Turkey And Stuffing Meatloaf\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a 9 x 5-inch (22 x 12 cm) loaf pan with butter and line the pan with a piece of parchment paper, leaving overhang on the 2 long sides.\",\"1\":\"Melt the butter in a large pan over medium heat. Add the onion, celery, carrots, ½ teaspoon salt, ¼ teaspoon pepper, and ½ teaspoon ground sage. Cook for 4–5 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender. Transfer to a large bowl and let cool for 15 minutes.\",\"2\":\"While the vegetables cool, stir together the stuffing mix and chicken stock in a medium bowl.. Let sit for 15 minutes, until the stuffing mix is soggy and has absorbed all of the liquid.\",\"3\":\"Once the vegetables have cooled, add the soaked stuffing mix, ground turkey, remaining teaspoon salt, remaining ¼ teaspoon pepper, remaining ¾ teaspoon ground sage, and the egg. Mix until well combined. Transfer to the prepared loaf pan, pressing down to smooth the top.\",\"4\":\"Bake the turkey and stuffing loaf for 25 minutes.\",\"5\":\"While the meatloaf loaf bakes, make the glaze: In a medium bowl, mix together the cranberry sauce, ketchup, and mustard.\",\"6\":\"Pour the glaze over the meatloaf, then return to the oven and bake for another 20 minutes, or until the internal temperature 165°F (75°C).\",\"7\":\"Let cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then use the parchment to carefully lift out the meatloaf and transfer to a cutting board. Cut into 1-inch-thick slices and serve immediately.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":359,\"sugar\":11,\"carbohydrates\":31,\"fiber\":1,\"protein\":17,\"fat\":17}','\"\"','6','\"https://im