dles, calzones, etc..\",\"12\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":362,\"sugar\":12,\"carbohydrates\":36,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":7,\"fat\":20}','','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/153375.jpg\"','10 oz cremini mushrooms||1 white onion||2 tbsp oil||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||4 cloves garlic, minced||1 ½ teaspoons dried oregano||¼ cup tomato paste||1 28 ounce can crushed tomatoes||2 cups vegetable broth||1 15 ounce can chickpeas, drained||Basil, for garnish||','italian||healthy||dinner||stove_top||pan_fry||food_processor||saute_pan||pyrex||spatula||liquid_measuring_cup||sieve||fusion||american||measuring_spoons||dry_measuring_cups||weeknight||date_night||high_fiber||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian'),('e9-a366acf1cfd6','\"Unstuffed Cabbage\"','{\"0\":\"Place ⅓ of cabbage in the bottom of a Dutch oven or large pot.\",\"1\":\"In a bowl combine the meat, rice, onion, and pepper. Form the mixture into small meatballs and place ½ of the meatballs on top of the cabbage.\",\"2\":\"Cover with ⅓ of cabbage, then place the rest of the meatballs over the cabbage. Cover with the remaining cabbage.\",\"3\":\"Pour the brown sugar, tomato purée, vinegar and stock over the top of the layered cabbage and meatballs and bring the mixture to a boil.\",\"4\":\"Reduce heat, cover, and simmer for ½ hour or until the meat is cooked through and the cabbage is tender.\",\"5\":\"Serve warm.\"}','{\"calories\":688,\"sugar\":39,\"carbohydrates\":79,\"fiber\":10,\"protein\":37,\"fat\":22}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/195aaf270b32441abeb1b553e5d10b8e.png\"','1 small head cabbage, roughly chopped||1 lb lean ground beef||1 small onion, finely chopped||⅛ sp black pepper||1 14 oz carton beef stock||½ cup brown sugar||½ cup white rice (uncooked)||1 15 oz can tomato purée||¼ cup vinegar||','easy||oven||dinner||special_occasion||high_protein||high_fiber||dairy_free'),('ea-2aa3c2800639','\"Ramen Carbonara\"','{\"0\":\"In a small bowl, add one whole egg, one egg yolk, parmesan cheese, and pepper to taste. Whisk with fork until well combined.\",\"1\":\"Cut two strips of bacon crosswise into half-inch strips. Fry until cooked but not yet crispy.\",\"2\":\"Boil water and cook ramen very al dente, or just until it can be loosened from it’s block form.\",\"3\":\"Add 1-2 tablespoons of olive oil to the bacon and stir, lifting any bacon bits that are stuck to the pan. Once the oil is hot, remove the pan from heat.\",\"4\":\"Pour a small amount of the water the ramen was cooked in and stir. Add the ramen noodles and stir some more, coating the noodles in the bacon/olive oil mixture.\",\"5\":\"Next, add the egg mixture, making sure to pour it onto the noodles and not straight onto the pan. Stir vigorously. The heat from the pan and ingredients need to turn the egg mixture into a creamy sauce. But, if the eggs get too hot they will cook too much and become scrabbled eggs. Add additional ramen water as needed to create a smooth but creamy sauce.\",\"6\":\"Plate and top with additional parmesan cheese and pepper.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":90,\"calories\":1370,\"sugar\":2,\"carbohydrates\":63,\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":72}','','1','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/407fb60a4ce844ebb84a421b2fbd4029/BFV6427_RamenCarbonara-Thumb1080FB.jpg\"','1 egg||1 egg yolk||1/3 cup parmesan cheese||Some ground pepper||2 strips of bacon, sliced in||1 packet instant ramen||1-2 tablespoons of extra virgin olive oil||','dinner||pan_fry||weeknight||stove_top||easy||fusion||mashup||comfort_food||italian||japanese||kid_friendly||mixing_bowl||tongs||cutting_board||mccormick_world_hearty'),('ea-8132944ecfa4','\"Cozy Chicken And Dumplings\"','{\"0\":\"In a 6-quart Dutch oven, heat the vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and cook until browned on both sides. Remove from the pot and set aside.\",\"1\":\"Add carrot and onion and cook until just tender, about 3 minutes.\",\"2\":\"Add the garlic and stir for another minute, until fragrant.\",\"3\":\"Reduce the heat to medium-low and add the butter and flour, stirring constantly for 3 minutes to prevent lumps from forming.\",\"4\":\"Add the chicken and any accumulated juices back to the pot and stir to coat in the roux.\",\"5\":\"Add the chicken broth, cream, thyme, and bay leaves and bring to a simmer. Once soup is at a simmer, add the frozen peas, cover, and cook for 15 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Make the dumplings: In a large bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, salt, pepper, and cream. Stir until mixture comes together into single mass of dough.\",\"7\":\"Using a large spoon or ice cream scoop, form the dough into small round balls about 1 inch (2 ½ cm) in diameter (the dough should yield 14-16 dumplings).\",\"8\":\"Place the dough balls in the simmering soup (making sure they don’t touch), add the parsley, and cover. Let the soup simmer for 15 minutes, or until the dumplings are cooked through.\",\"9\":\"Ladle into bowls, giving 1-2 dumplings per serving.\",\"10\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":9,\"carbohydrates\":62,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":61,\"fat\":48,\"calories\":875}','\"It\\u2019s the end of yet another long day and well, you\\u2019re ready to put your feet up, relax, and tuck into a comforting meal. Delivery might be calling your name, but you\\u2019ve got a ton of chicken lying around and with not much else to do, now\\u2019s the perfect time to whip up a batch of these simple and cozy chicken and dumplings. Tuck in now. \"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/66b0e3ddd9db461c90196060a48b293a/FB_thumb-2.jpg\"','2 tablespoons oil||2 pounds chicken breasts||1 large onion, diced||4 carrots, sliced to ¼ in half rings||3 garlic cloves, minced||1 teaspoon salt||5 tablespoons unsalted butter||6 tablespoons all-purpose flour||6 cups chicken broth||½ cup heavy cream||½ teaspoons dried thyme||2 bay leaves||1 ½ frozen peas||4 tablespoons fresh minced parsley||','dutch_oven||comfort_food||weeknight||dinner||pyrex||mixing_bowl||spatula||tongs||measuring_spoons||liquid_measuring_cup||chefs_knife||cutting_board||oven_mitts||dry_measuring_cups||ice_cream_scoop||pan_fry||stove_top'),('ea-b28990a160ff','\"Avocado Carbonara\"','{\"0\":\"Blend avocado, egg yolk, garlic, and lemon juice in a powerful blender or food processor.\",\"1\":\"Pulse to blend and add heavy cream gradually. Blend the sauce until smooth and set aside.\",\"2\":\"Cut up strips of bacon and cook in a large pan. Set aside.\",\"3\":\"In a large pot, bring water to a boil and cook the spaghetti according to the package instructions.\",\"4\":\"Drain and coat with olive oil.\",\"5\":\"Add sauce, bacon, parmesan, salt and pepper, stirring until well-combined.\",\"6\":\"Serve and sprinkle with parmesan.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":8,\"protein\":58,\"fat\":85,\"calories\":1383,\"sugar\":5,\"carbohydrates\":102}','','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/2207.jpg\"','1 avocado||1 egg yolk||½ cup heavy cream||1 clove garlic||½ lemon, juiced||½ cup parmesan cheese, grated||3 pieces bacon||½ pound spaghetti||1 tablespoon olive oil||','dinner||date_night||italian||mashup||fusion||american||comfort_food||pan_fry||easy||stove_top||tongs||cheese_grater||colander||sauce_pan||wooden_spoon||saute_pan||measuring_spoons||liquid_measuring_cup||dry_measuring_cups||blender||weeknight||food_processor'),('ea-d27faf82f7f2','\"How To Make Handmade Pasta\"','{\"0\":\"On a clean, sturdy work surface, turn out your chosen flour(s) and salt and make a large well in the center with your hands.\",\"1\":\"Whisk the eggs, egg yolks, and olive oil together in a medium bowl until combined, then pour the mixture into the well.\",\"2\":\"Using the same fork, whisk the eggs, slowly incorporating more and more flour into the eggs by moving your fork along the edges of the well.\",\"3\":\"Once almost all of the flour is incorporated, start bringing the dough together with your hands. (The dough should be malleable, but not sticky–add more flour if the dough is sticking too much to your hands or the surface. Alternatively, if it’s too dry and tough, whisk another egg with 1 tablespoon of water and use your hand to sprinkle some of the mixture over the dough, continuing to do so until the dough is easier to knead.)\",\"4\":\"Knead the dough for 7–10 minutes, until smooth and elastic. When you poke the dough, it should spring back.\",\"5\":\"Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and let rest at room temperature for 30 minutes to an hour, or until the dough does not spring back when poked.\",\"6\":\"Unwrap the dough and cut into 8 equal pieces so that it’s easier to work with. Take 1 piece and wrap the rest in the plastic wrap so that they don’t dry out.\",\"7\":\"Lightly flour your work surface and begin rolling out the piece of dough into one long piece. Then, fold the top third down, and the bottom third over that, like a letter. Rotate the dough 90˚ and roll the piece back into a long shape. This helps form a more even rectangular shape and makes the dough a little bit easier to work with.\",\"8\":\"Continue rolling out the dough until it is very thin. When you lift the dough, you should be able to see your hands through it.\",\"9\":\"Fold the top and bottom of the rectangle to meet in the middle, then fold over again--this will make the dough easier to cut. Cut the dough to your ideal shape. Loosen or unravel the cut dough immediately, so it doesn’t stick, sprinkle with a bit of extra flour, or semolina, if using. Let the pasta sit out for about 30 minutes to dry out slightly.\",\"10\":\"Bring a large pot of heavily salted water to a boil. Add the pasta and stir to ensure it doesn’t clump. Cook for 2–3 minutes, or 30–60 seconds after the pasta comes to the surface (fresh pasta will cook much faster than dried pasta!). Take out a noodle and taste for doneness. Once cooked to your liking, remove the pasta from the water, being sure to save at least 1 cup (240 mL) of the pasta cooking water.\",\"11\":\"Add the cooked pasta into your preferred sauce and stir to coat, adding some of the reserved pasta water if needed to add a bit of body and silkiness to the sauce.\",\"12\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":1401,\"sugar\":2,\"carbohydrates\":163,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":69,\"fat\":48}','\"Making fresh, homemade pasta dough doesn\\u2019t have to be tedious! All you need is some flour, eggs, and a tiny bit of arm strength as you knead it all together \\u2014 no food processor or fancy stand-mixer required. And once your noodles are ready, all it takes is 2-3 minutes of cooking before you can add your sauce, sprinkle your cheese, and open that wine.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/171076.jpg\"','2 cups all-purpose flour, plus more for dusting||Pinch of kosher salt||2 large eggs||6 large egg yolks||1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil||','liquid_measuring_cup||measuring_spoons||rolling_pin||chefs_knife||italian||cutting_board||plastic_wrap||dinner||comfort_food||special_occasion||mixing_bowl||tongs||high_protein||low_sugar||high_fiber||dairy_free||vegetarian'),('ea-d41ba3ff9cc3','\"Paprika Shrimp Pasta\"','{\"0\":\"Bring a large pot of water to a boil.  Generously salt the water.\",\"1\":\"Cook pasta for 8-9 minutes, or until al dente, and drain.\",\"2\":\"In a skillet over medium heat, add olive oil.  Add the onion and cook until lightly browned and softened, about 3-4 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Add garlic, rosemary, thyme, smoked paprika, salt and pepper. Stir and cook an additional 2 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Add the shrimp and let them cook for 3 minutes. Flip and cook for another 3 minutes.\",\"5\":\"Add the white wine and lemon juice. Cook until the wine has reduced.\",\"6\":\"Add the cooked pasta to the skillet and serve.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":30,\"fat\":6,\"calories\":412,\"sugar\":3,\"carbohydrates\":52,\"fiber\":2}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/23dc482e025a44a6943765bdfee4c7f2/7_Pasta_Recipes_For_All_Pasta_Lovers.jpg\"','8 ounces linguine||1 tablespoon olive oil||1 large sweet onion||2 cloves garlic, minced||1 tablespoon rosemary||1 tablespoon thyme||1 teaspoon smoked paprika||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||1 pound large shrimp||1 cup white wine||1 tablespoon lemon juice||Parmesan cheese, for garnish||','mixing_bowl||wooden_spoon||strainer||tongs||dinner||special_occasion||stove_top||american||comfort_food||contains_alcohol||high_protein||low_sugar||pescatarian'),('eb-5d8af61cf4f5','\"Pork Red Na (Noodles And Gravy)\"','{\"0\":\"Combine marinade ingredients in a large bowl and once whisked together, add pork and marinate overnight.\",\"1\":\"Soak noodles in warm water before separating out. Drain noodles, then add dark soy sauce and mix around with your hands.\",\"2\":\"Heat wok or large non-stick pan to medium-high heat. Add 1 tbsp of rapeseed oil, once oil is shimmering, add half the noodles. Fry the noodles until they crisp up in places and char in places. Repeat this with the remaining noodles.\",\"3\":\"Wipe wok clean with paper towel, add sesame oil. Stir in garlic and soy bean paste. Cook until garlic begins to brown.\",\"4\":\"Add stock, soy sauce and palm sugar and bring to a boil.\",\"5\":\"Whisk cornstarch into a glass of water\",\"6\":\"Add the pork to the boiling sauce (must be boiling so the coating on the pork doesn’t come off)\",\"7\":\"And simmer for one minute before adding the broccoli.\",\"8\":\"Simmer for 3-4 more minutes.\",\"9\":\"Stir in corn starch mix, cook off until sauce thickens and glistens.\",\"10\":\"Serve over the rice noodles, adding chilli and shallots to garnish.\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":110,\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":27,\"fat\":29,\"calories\":815,\"sugar\":6}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/b050366ce4274e77babf9626cecf0b8a.jpeg\"','250g of thinly slice pork shoulder||450g of rice noodles||2 tsp of dark soy sauce||2-3 tbsp rapeseed oil||200g of broccoli||Pickled chili for garnish||Fried shallots for garnish||','fusion||stove_top||dinner||weeknight||dairy_free'),('eb-6fabfb0687ae','\"Zucchini Lasagna\"','{\"0\":\"Cut the ends off of the zucchini, and cut in half, lengthwise.\",\"1\":\"Using a vegetable peeler, peel long strips of zucchini (these will be your “noodles”) and set on a baking sheet lined with paper towels.\",\"2\":\"Dab zucchini strips with a paper towel to absorb the excess moisture.\",\"3\":\"In a large pot, add olive oil, onions, and garlic. Cook until translucent, about 4-5 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Add ground turkey, and cook for another 4-5 minutes, or until the turkey has browned slightly.\",\"5\":\"Pour in crushed tomatoes, basil, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper, tomato paste, and a bay leaf. Cover and let simmer for 30 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Preheat oven to 375˚F (190˚C).\",\"7\":\"In a bowl, combine ricotta cheese, egg, parsley, parmesan, salt, and pepper. Mix until well combined.\",\"8\":\"Using a baking dish, layer turkey sauce, zucchini strips, ricotta mixture, and parmesan. Repeat until there are 3 layers total, ending with the turkey sauce and topping that with parmesan cheese.\",\"9\":\"Bake for 50 minutes (times and temperatures may vary depending on the oven).\",\"10\":\"Let rest for at least 20 minutes.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":328,\"sugar\":6,\"carbohydrates\":13,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":25,\"fat\":19}','\"When it comes to comfort food, there are few meals as satisfying as warm, cheesy lasagna. This recipe is a lighter take on classic lasagna. It\\u2019s made with thinly sliced zucchini in place of noodles, and it calls for ground turkey for the meat sauce, but it still contains everything you love about the classic dish.\"','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/c37efd97131f4cd4bc48acc314ab7f34/zucchinilasagnafb.jpg\"','2 zucchinis||1 cup grated parmesan||','chefs_knife||baking_pan||cutting_board||mixing_bowl||oven_mitts||spat