ssing.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":44,\"fat\":41,\"calories\":662,\"sugar\":6,\"carbohydrates\":27,\"fiber\":0}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/6f3ef42468c94b2a9ed4fbba33176aa7/Thumb_A.jpg\"','- 4 oz cream cheese||- 1/4 cup hot sauce||- 2 1/2 cups cooked chicken||- 1 cup shredded Monterey Jack cheese||- 1 cup Mozzarella cheese||- 2 cans (8 oz each) refrigerated crescent dinner rolls.||','game_day||bake||american||comfort_food||casual_party||oven||mashup||baking_pan||mixing_bowl||chefs_knife||spatula||liquid_measuring_cup||oven_mitts||dinner||mccormick_game_day||franks_handheld_bites'),('ec-0c8ea3027a66','\"One-Pot Shrimp And Spinach Fettuccine Alfredo Pasta\"','{\"0\":\"In a large pot, heat the butter over medium-high heat until browned.\",\"1\":\"Toss in the shrimp and season with salt and black pepper. Sear just until pink on both sides. Remove the shrimp from the pot and set aside.\",\"2\":\"Sauté the garlic and bacon until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add in the spinach and stir until it begins to wilt.\",\"3\":\"Pour in the heavy cream and stir the pot to combine. Let the sauce come up to a simmer and reduce until thick and creamy, about 5 minutes.\",\"4\":\"Toss in the fettuccine, sprinkle over the parmesan cheese.\",\"5\":\"Sprinkle in the parsley and add the shrimp back to the pot. Toss until everything has warmed through.\",\"6\":\"Remove from heat and serve. Top with a sprinkle of fresh parsley.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":32,\"fat\":30,\"calories\":574,\"sugar\":2,\"carbohydrates\":46,\"fiber\":2}','','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/7e04ff3337eb4aa3883f3ca54798544d/BFV18034_One-PanShrimAndSpinachAlfredoThumb.jpg\"','2 tablespoon butter||1 pound shrimp, peeled and deveined||Salt, to taste||Black pepper, to taste||3 cloves garlic, minced||½ pound bacon, cooked, cut into small strips||7 ounces baby spinach||1½ cups heavy cream||1 pound fettuccine, cooked||¾ cup parmesan cheese, grated||⅓ cup parsley, chopped||','pan_fry||stove_top||weeknight||easy||comfort_food||one_pot_or_pan||american||dinner||seafood||date_night||sauce_pan||pyrex||measuring_spoons||wooden_spoon||tongs||chefs_knife||cutting_board||liquid_measuring_cup||colander||dry_measuring_cups||mccormick_ugc_one_pot_pasta'),('ec-392692f5788f','\"Lentil \\u0022Dirty Rice\\u0022\"','{\"0\":\"For the Sweet \\u0026 Sour Eggplant: Heat a large sauté pan over high heat. Add both oils and then the salted eggplant. Sauté until the eggplant begins to brown, adding more canola oil if needed. In a bowl or measuring\\u00A0cup, combine all remaining ingredients. Deglaze your hot browning eggplant pan with the vinegar mixture, allowing it to reduce by about half. Season with salt and pepper and set aside.\",\"1\":\"For the Crispy Garbanzo Beans: These are best (in my opinion) when deep fried until crispy in 325-degree vegetable oil... but they\\u0027re\\u00A0also very good when baked at 350 degrees in an oven.\",\"2\":\"If frying; toss the garbanzo\\u00A0beans with all spices and fry them for about 4 minutes, until golden brown and crunchy... then drain them on a paper\\u00A0towel while cooling.\",\"3\":\"If baking; toss the garbanzo beans with the oil, and then the spices, and bake. This will take approximately 45 minutes.\",\"4\":\"For the Sumac Yogurt Sauce: Combine all ingredients\\u00A0and keep cold until ready to use.\",\"5\":\"To assemble, place your grains in the base of a bowl. Top with warm eggplant, crispy garbanzo beans, a drizzle of sumac yogurt and fresh herbs.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":636,\"sugar\":58,\"carbohydrates\":120,\"fiber\":27,\"protein\":15,\"fat\":16}','\"During the COVID-19 pandemic, this dish became a\\u00A0regular hospital\\u00A0delivery staple because\\u00A0of its comforting heartiness, abundance of flavor, but also the fact that it\\u0027s meat free. We always offer a vegetarian option, but also try to make that option just as exciting as any meat-driven dish that we provide. We\\u0027ve also taken a version of this dish and added it to the current menu at Playa Provisions. That version is a bit more refined, but hits all the same notes.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/355fcbe6625f4a368ead24445800d209.jpeg\"','6 Japanese eggplants, sliced into 1-inch rounds and lightly salted for 15-20 minutes prior to cooking||2 cloves garlic, sliced||1 tablespoon sesame oil||1 tablespoon canola oil||1/2 red onion, diced||1/4 cup cider vinegar||1/8 cup sherry vinegar||1/4 cup mirin||2 tablespoons soy sauce||1/4 cup agave||1 tsp whole coriander seeds||pinch chili flake||salt and fresh black pepper to taste||','healthy||lunch||dinner||weeknight||high_fiber||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||vegetarian'),('ec-3ac23e63719d','\"One-Pot Butternut Squash Pilaf\"','{\"0\":\"To prep cut off both ends of the butternut squash and poke 10-15 air vents with a fork. Microwave on high for 3-4 minutes.\",\"1\":\"Peel the skin off of the squash. The skin should peel right off! Once peeled, cut into 1x1-inch (2x2-cm) cubes.\",\"2\":\"Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).\",\"3\":\"In a large dutch oven or oven-safe pot, sauté onion in olive oil for 3-4 minutes or until semi-translucent. Add garlic and sauté for 2 more minutes.\",\"4\":\"Add the thyme and cook for 2 minutes, until fragrant.\",\"5\":\"Add arborio rice and sauté until lightly toasted, then stir in salt, pepper and white wine.\",\"6\":\"Stir in butternut squash and and vegetable broth and bring to a boil.\",\"7\":\"Cover pot and transfer to oven. Bake for 15-20 minutes, until liquid is absorbed.\",\"8\":\"Garnish with parsley and serve immediately\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"calories\":1143,\"sugar\":21,\"carbohydrates\":116,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":5,\"fat\":68}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/1ffeadeed97b450b9092f65c72da511f/OnePotButternutSquashPilafFBMOSTFINAL.jpg\"','2 tablespoons olive oil||1 small yellow onion, diced||2 cloves garlic, 