\":\"Add soaked lentils, water, turmeric powder, cumin-coriander powder and salt to an InstantPot or a Pressure Cooker. Pressure cook in an Instant Pot on high setting for 15 minutes with natural steam release.\",\"2\":\"For pressure cooker cooking, cook on high heat until 2 whistles. Turn the heat down to low and cook for 8-10 minutes. Natural Pressure Release.\",\"3\":\"Whisk dal with a whisk or use a hand blender(if needed) until smooth.\",\"4\":\"Heat oil in a wok or a saucepan on medium heat. Add cumin seeds. Once the oil starts to become cloudy around cumin seeds, add minced onions. Cook onions until slightly golden.\",\"5\":\"Now add minced ginger and garlic, sauté for a few seconds. Add diced tomatoes, whole chilis, dried fenugreek, Kashmiri chili powder and curry leaves. Cook on low -medium while stirring for about a minute or until tomatoes start to break apart.\",\"6\":\"Add tadka to cooked Dal. If Dal is too thick add ½ cup to a cup of hot water to thin it down. Boil the Dal to reduce the liquid if needed. Garnish it with chopped cilantro and Garam Masala.\",\"7\":\"Serve warm with plain rice or roti.\"}','{\"sugar\":1,\"carbohydrates\":23,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":7,\"fat\":11,\"calories\":207}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/b97a62701f254d4c8b1f09f409dbfba1.jpeg\"','½ cup Split Pigeon Peas , Arhar or Toor Dal||¼ cup Mung Lentils , Mung(Moong) Dal||¼ cup Red Lentils , Masoor ki Dal||3 cups water , more to wash and soak the lentils||1 tsp turmeric Powder||1 tsp cumin-coriander powder||1 tsp salt||','stove_top||dinner||special_occasion||low_sugar||high_fiber||vegetarian'),('ec-d6b2b1a72b1f','\"Crackling Crust Roast Pork With Mojo\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C) .\",\"1\":\"Using a sharp knife, score the pork skin and fat in a diamond pattern, spacing the cuts ½ inch apart and taking care not to cut into the meat.\",\"2\":\"Combine the garlic and salt in a food processor and pulse until the garlic is finely chopped. Add the olive oil, whole oregano leaves, cumin, and orange and lime zests and process into a smooth paste.\",\"3\":\"Rub the paste all over the pork shoulder, making sure it gets into the scores. Transfer the pork shoulder to a baking dish or a roasting pan and pour the lime and orange juices around the pork.  Cover the baking dish with foil.\",\"4\":\"Bake until an instant-read thermometer inserted into the center of the pork registers between 180°F (82°C) and 190°F (88°C), 6–7 hours. Remove the pork from the oven and turn on the broiler.\",\"5\":\"Uncover the pork and turn the oven to broil. Return the pork to the oven and broil until the skin puffs and is golden brown and crisp, 10–15 minutes. Transfer the pork to a cutting board and let rest for 20 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Meanwhile, pour the pan juices into a small saucepan and bring to a boil over high heat. Cook until reduced slightly, about 10 minutes. Remove the sauce from the heat and pour through a fine-mesh strainer into a small bowl. Skim off the fat, if desired. Stir the finely chopped oregano into the sauce.\",\"7\":\"Serve the pork shoulder with the sauce and your favorite side dishes.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":6,\"fat\":16,\"calories\":236,\"sugar\":9,\"carbohydrates\":21}','\"This crispy, citrusy roast pork will be the star of your dinner table. The pork shoulder is marinated in a Cuban-inspired mojo sauce, baked for hours until tender, then broiled for that crispy, crackly skin. Pro tip: use a sharp knife to score the pork skin. This will help any excess fat render out during cooking, as well as allow those mojo flavors to really penetrate the meat!\"','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/350793.jpg\"','1 8-pound bone-in, skin-on pork shoulder||24 garlic cloves||2 tablespoons kosher salt||½ cup olive oil||¼ cup fresh oregano leaves, plus 1 tablespoon, finely chopped, divided||1 tablespoon ground cumin||Zest of 2 oranges||Zest of 2 limes||2 cups fresh lime juice (from about 16 limes)||1½ cups fresh orange juice (from 6–8 oranges)||','oven||food_processor||liquid_measuring_cup||baking_pan||mixing_bowl||dry_measuring_cups||chefs_knife||wooden_spoon||spatula||measuring_spoons||cutting_board||sieve||sauce_pan||comfort_food||pyrex||bake||dinner||cuban||special_occasion||lunch||dairy_free||cuba_african_cuisine'),('ec-d88b457e040c','\"Hidden Veggie Burgers\"','{\"0\":\"In a large bowl, season the beef with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder.\",\"1\":\"Shred the carrots and broccoli using a box grater and add to the bowl with the beef.\",\"2\":\"Mix well with a spoon or your hands and form into patties.\",\"3\":\"Either pan-fry or grill until cooked. Top with cheese and let it melt.\",\"4\":\"Assemble burger with your favorite toppings.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":44,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":31,\"fat\":19,\"calories\":487,\"sugar\":6}','','12','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/bd6f2217c1294d4897772b5d189ef976/BFV17853_HiddenVeggieBurgers_ThumbFB.jpg\"','2 pounds ground beef||1 tablespoon salt||1 teaspoon black pepper||1 teaspoon garlic powder||1 teaspoon onion powder||2 carrots, shredded||2 heads broccoli, shredded||12 slices cheddar cheese||12 burger buns||','easy||american||weeknight||spring||dinner||comfort_food||bbq||summer||kid_friendly||stove_top||pan_fry||grill||pyrex||mixing_bowl||cheese_grater||spatula||cast_iron_pan||dry_measuring_cups||measuring_spoons||saute_pan'),('ec-e4f74acfbfbe','\"Vegan Crab Cakes\"','{\"0\":\"Add chickpeas, hearts of palm, and artichoke hearts to food processor. Pulse until mixture is chopped, yet still slightly chunky.\",\"1\":\"Transfer mixture to large mixing bowl and add 1 cup (50 g) of bread crumbs, ¼ cup (55 g) vegan mayonnaise, Dijon mustard, 1 teaspoon lemon juice, salt, pepper, and Old Bay seasoning. Mix well.\",\"2\":\"Form the mixture into 6 1-inch (2 cm) thick patties.\",\"3\":\"Dip each patty in remaining bread crumbs.\",\"4\":\"Heat a pan of oil to 350˚F (180˚C). Fry each patty for 3-6 minutes per side, until golden brown.\",\"5\":\"Transfer to paper towel-lined plate to absorb excess oil.\",\"6\":\"For tartar sauce, combine remaining vegan mayo, relish, and 1 teaspoon lemon juice in mixing bowl.\",\"7\":\"Top the patties with tartar sauce, dill, and lemon juice.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":31,\"calories\":504,\"sugar\":5,\"carbohydrates\":43,\"fiber\":11,\"protein\":12}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/101282.jpg\"','1 15-ounce can chickpeas, drained and rinsed||1 15-ounce can hearts of palm, drained, rinsed and cut into large chunks||1 15-ounce can artichoke hearts, drained and rinsed||1½ cups panko bread crumbs, divided||¾ cup vegan mayonnaise, divided||1 teaspoon Dijon mustard||2 teaspoons lemon juice, divided||¼ teaspoon salt||¼ teaspoon pepper||1 tablespoon Old Bay seasoning||Oil, for frying||1 tablespoon sweet pickle relish||Dill, to serve||','stove_top||seafood||food_processor||cast_iron_pan||dinner||easy||deep_fry||date_night||casual_party||american||spatula||colander||pyrex||mixing_bowl||dry_measuring_cups||measuring_spoons||low_sugar||high_fiber||dairy_free||vegetarian'),('ed-1f74769428be','\"Make-Ahead Chicken \\u0026 Rice Bake\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).\",\"1\":\"In a skillet, melt butter, and cook onion, garlic, carrots, and celery until tender.\",\"2\":\"Transfer to a 9\\u0022 x 13\\u0022 (23 cm x 33 cm) disposable casserole dish, or split among 2 smaller dishes.\",\"3\":\"Add chicken, rice, soup, stock, salt, and pepper. Mix thoroughly, and cover with foil.\",\"4\":\"Bake for 30 minutes. Remove foil, top with bread crumbs if desired, and bake an additional 10 minutes. Or, bake for 30 minutes, let cool completely, cover, and freeze up to 2 months.\",\"5\":\"To reheat, let thaw in the refrigerator during the day. Bake as directed above.\",\"6\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":13,\"fat\":19,\"calories\":428,\"sugar\":5,\"carbohydrates\":47,\"fiber\":2}','','12','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/82130d826cf3423eb39ebc5c021c2b8b/chickenthumb.jpg\"','1 tablespoon butter||1 medium onion, diced||1 clove garlic, minced||4 carrots, finely diced||4 stalks celery, sliced||1 rotisserie chicken, shredded||1 cup uncooked, long grain white rice||1 can cream of chicken soup||3 cups chicken stock||Salt, to taste||Pepper, to taste||Bread crumbs, optional||','oven||american||freezer||meal_prep||big_batch||dinner||weeknight||bake||comfort_food'),('ed-63edb6b2e88d','\"Korean Pork Neck Soup\"','{\"0\":\"Add the pork neck bones to a large bowl and cover with cold water. Soak for 2 hours.\",\"1\":\"Bring a large pot of water to a boil.\",\"2\":\"Drain and rinse the pork bones, then blanch in the boiling water for about 7 minutes to remove any impurities. Drain and rinse the blanched pork bones until the water runs clear.\",\"3\":\"Return the pork bones to the pot and cover with clean water. Add the onion, green onions, garlic, and ginger. Cover and simmer over medium-low heat for 90 minutes.\",\"4\":\"While the broth is simmering, make the seasoning paste: Add the Korean chile flakes, soybean paste, Korean hot pepper paste, rice wine, fish sauce, perilla seed powder, garlic, black pepper, and ¼ cup of the pork broth and mix until well combined.\",\"5\":\"Once the broth has simmered for 90 minutes, uncover the pot and add the seasoning paste and stir to incorporate. Add the potatoes and cook for 10 minutes, until tender.\",\"6\":\"Add the Napa cabbage leaves, bean sprouts, crown daisy leaves, and perilla leaves. Boil for another 5 minutes, until the leaves are wilted.\",\"7\":\"Serve the soup hot with steamed rice, if desired.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fat\":2,\"calories\":228,\"sugar\":12,\"carbohydrates\":48,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":7}','\"BlackPink\\u2019s Lisa raves about Korean pork neck soup being one of her favorite dishes. It\\u2019s deliciously comfo