2\":\"Once all ingredients have been mixed, knead the dough by pulling, stretching, and folding for about 3-5 minutes, or until it turns elastic and semi-easy to mold.\",\"3\":\"Mold the dough into a sphere, and wrap it in plastic wrap and rest for 30 minutes, or until the dough becomes more relaxed, elastic, and much easier to mold.\",\"4\":\"Cut the dough in four pieces. Grab the first one, and keep the other wrapped, or cover them with a slightly wet towel to keep them fresh.\",\"5\":\"Flatten the first piece, and run it through the widest setting of your pasta maker. Increase the thinness number by one level each time you run the pasta through the machine.\",\"6\":\"Once you can see your fingers through the dough, proceed to cut the fettuccine, or any shape you wish.\",\"7\":\"In a pot with boiling water and salt, cook the pasta for 2 minutes or until it feels tender to the bite.\",\"8\":\"Serve with your favorite pasta sauce.\",\"9\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":18,\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":6,\"fat\":3,\"calories\":132,\"sugar\":0}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/15629d022b244f9fbbb45d821d8f9278/Homemapasta.jpg\"','1 ½ cups flour||3 eggs, beaten||¼ cup salt||','easy||dry_measuring_cups||kid_friendly||stove_top||chefs_knife||comfort_food||italian||strainer||cutting_board||tongs||lunch||dinner||date_night||weeknight||low_calorie||low_fat||5_ingredients_or_less||dairy_free||vegetarian'),('ef-37d80433f9c0','\"Italian-Style Bolognese (Rag\\u00F9)\"','{\"0\":\"Heat olive oil and butter in a large pan over medium heat. Add onion, carrot, celery, and pancetta. Cook for around 10 minutes until the onions start to look translucent.\",\"1\":\"Add the minced meats and brown all over, ensuring the meat is fully broken up and no large chunks remain.\",\"2\":\"Add salt and pepper to taste. Increase the heat, add the wine, and allow to evaporate for around 2-3 minutes.\",\"3\":\"In a large jug, dilute the tomato puree into the chicken stock and add to the pan, stir well.\",\"4\":\"Reduce to a low heat, then cover and simmer for 2 hours. Check from time to time to ensure the sauce is not drying out. If this occurs, add a small amount of stock.\",\"5\":\"Cook desired pasta and toss in the bolognese.\",\"6\":\"Top with parmesan cheese and serve.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":9,\"carbohydrates\":98,\"fiber\":4,\"protein\":40,\"fat\":37,\"calories\":887}','','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/video-api-prod/assets/38904e451e6d4841b3cc3e63d364ff02/Italian-Style_Bolognese_Ragu_Facebook_thumb_nail_.jpg\"','1 tablespoon olive oil||50 grams butter||1 medium onion, finely diced||1 large carrot, finely diced||1 celery stalk, finely diced||100 grams pancetta, diced||200 grams lean beef, minced||150 grams lean pork, minced||200 milliliters red wine||2 tablespoons double-concentrated tomato puree||500 milliliters chicken stock||','stove_top||fusion||easy||dinner||comfort_food||italian||kid_friendly||american||pan_fry||weeknight||valentines_day||spring||fall||winter||contains_alcohol'),('ef-993e45dda2de','\"Roast Chicken\"','{\"0\":\"Remove the giblets from the chicken cavity. Pat the chicken dry all over with paper towels, including the cavity.\",\"1\":\"Generously season the entire chicken with salt and pepper. With the tip of a toothpick, poke the skin of the chicken all over, creating at least 20 tiny holes.\",\"2\":\"Transfer the chicken to a rimmed baking dish and let sit in the refrigerator, uncovered, for 8-12 hours.\",\"3\":\"Preheat the oven to 450˚F (230˚C).\",\"4\":\"Remove the chicken from the refrigerator and let it warm to room temperature for 1 hour.\",\"5\":\"Truss the chicken legs. Using butcher’s twine, tie the legs together, then slip the twine under each leg, pull up to the top of the chicken, and flip the bird over. Pull the twine under the wings, loop around the neck, and then tie to secure and cut off any excess twine. Flip the bird over again and tuck the wings under the breasts.\",\"6\":\"Set the chicken, breast-side up, on a roasting rack set over a roasting pan.\",\"7\":\"Roast for 1 hour, or until a meat thermometer inserted in the thickest part of the chicken reaches 165˚F (75˚C).\",\"8\":\"Let the chicken rest at room temperature for 20 minutes.\",\"9\":\"To carve, remove the twine. Using a sharp knife, cut between the leg and the breast. When you reach the joint, bend it back and cut right through. Twist off the wings. To remove the breasts, cut straight down along the keel bone. Then, angling your knife outward, remove the breast. Break the legs down into thighs and drumsticks, if desired. Pull off the oysters from the underside of the chicken.\",\"10\":\"If you’d like, make chicken stock from the carcass. Add the carcass to a large pot with onions, celery, carrots, garlic, and other aromatics of your choice. Cover with water and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat to low and simmer for about 8 hours, skimming off the fat as needed. Store in the fridge for a few days or freeze for a few months.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":76,\"fat\":67,\"calories\":958,\"sugar\":0,\"carbohydrates\":0,\"fiber\":0}','\"\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/197456.jpg\"','1 4-5 pound whole chicken||Kosher salt, to taste||Freshly ground black pepper, to taste||','easy||oven||special_occasion||baking_pan||cutting_board||tongs||oven_mitts||dinner||weeknight||bake||chefs_knife||measuring_spoons||sauce_pan||liquid_measuring_cup||thanksgiving||christmas||high_protein||5_ingredients_or_less||dairy_free'),('f0-26e3a83ce4fc','\"Sunflower Veggie Burgers\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat oven to 375˚F (190˚C).\",\"1\":\"In the bowl of a food processor, add sunflower seeds. Process until finely ground.\",\"2\":\"Add onion, brown rice, thyme, salt, and water and process until combined.\",\"3\":\"Add carrot and celery and pulse several times to combine.\",\"4\":\"Using a ½ cup (120 ml) measuring cup, portion 5 patties from the mixture