le batch to keep on hand for easy protein to add to any meal!\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/321844.jpg\"','1 pound ground turkey||⅓ cup panko bread crumbs||1 tablespoon mayonnaise||2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce||1 teaspoon kosher salt||½ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper||1 tablespoon canola oil||','stove_top||pan_fry||mixing_bowl||dinner||comfort_food||dry_measuring_cups||one_pot_or_pan||lunch||american||measuring_spoons||game_day||weeknight||saute_pan||spatula||fourth_eat||summer_eat||low_carb||under_30_minutes||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour||dairy_free'),('f2-297546680fea','\"Grilled Cheeseburger Bombs\"','{\"0\":\"Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the ground beef, hamburger seasoning, and salt. Cook, breaking up the meat with a wooden spoon, until browned, 5–7 minutes. Drain off some of the excess fat, then return the skillet to the heat.\",\"1\":\"Add the mustard, Worcestershire sauce, and water. Bring to boil and cook until the liquid is reduced by half. Remove the pan from the heat.\",\"2\":\"On a lightly floured surface, roll out a biscuit into a 5-inch round. Add 2 American cheese quarters to the center and top with 3 tablespoons of the beef mixture. Wrap the biscuit dough around the filling and pinch the edges together to seal tightly. Set seam-side down on a parchment-lined baking sheet and repeat with the remaining ingredients.\",\"3\":\"Heat the grill to 375°F (190°F) and spray the grates with nonstick spray.\",\"4\":\"Brush the burger bombs with the egg wash and sprinkle sesame seeds on top.\",\"5\":\"Add the burger bombs to the hot grill over indirect heat and cook for 20–25 minutes, until the biscuits are golden brown and cooked through.\",\"6\":\"Serve with ketchup.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":14,\"fat\":12,\"calories\":629,\"sugar\":9,\"carbohydrates\":16,\"fiber\":1}','\"Stuff your favorite cheeseburger ingredients into canned biscuit dough and grill for 