n'),('f7-3e29ca944191','\"Pineapple Sweet Chili Salmon\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\",\"1\":\"Cut pineapple in half lengthwise, cutting from root through the leaves.\",\"2\":\"Hollow out the pineapple by slicing around the perimeter, leaving a ½ inch (1 ¼ cm) border.\",\"3\":\"Slice the pineapple inside the cut border, and scoop out with a spoon. Repeat with the other half and set aside, as this will be the serving bowl for the salmon.\",\"4\":\"Add pineapple and water to a blender and blend until smooth.\",\"5\":\"Pour the pineapple purée into a saucepan over medium heat.\",\"6\":\"Add the sugar, rice wine vinegar, chile flakes, salt, and garlic to the pan and bring to a simmer. Stir frequently until sauce becomes lighter in color and slightly thickens.\",\"7\":\"In a small bowl, combine the cornstarch with the water to make a slurry. Add the slurry to the sauce and until sauce has thickened, 4-7 minutes. Remove the pan from the heat.\",\"8\":\"Place the salmon on a parchment paper-lined baking sheet and cover each fillet with the sauce.\",\"9\":\"Bake for 12-15 minutes, depending on your desired doneness.\",\"10\":\"Serve the salmon the pineapple bowls over rice with more pineapple sweet chile sauce on the side.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":61,\"carbohydrates\":66,\"fiber\":0,\"protein\":25,\"fat\":16,\"calories\":505}','','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/e9cb7f2a1832454e867c74c93bd3899c/BFV224979_SummerSalmonDinnerForTwo_FB_Final.jpg\"','1 whole pineapple||½ cup water||½ cup sugar||n/a||2 tablespoons chile flakes||2 teaspoon salt||2 cloves garlic garlic, minced||2 salmon fillets||','oven||seafood||american||comfort_food||valentines_day||dinner||special_occasion||date_night||bake||pan_fry||weeknight||cutting_board||chefs_knife||sauce_pan||wooden_spoon||mixing_bowl||baking_pan||parchment_paper||summer||high_protein||high_fiber||dairy_free'),('f7-5308c7aa7ca8','\"Instant-Pot Short Ribs\"','{\"0\":\"In a liquid measuring cup or medium bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, rice vinegar, sesame oil, gochujang (adjust the quantity based on your preferred spice level), and honey.\",\"1\":\"Place the short ribs in a deep baking dish or large bowl and season generously on both sides with salt and pepper. Pour the soy sauce mixture over the ribs. Cover with plastic wrap and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour, up to overnight.\",\"2\":\"Preheat a 6-quart (6 Liter) Instant Pot on the high sauté setting. Once hot, add the coconut oil.\",\"3\":\"Remove the short ribs from the marinade and let any excess marinade drip off. Reserve the marinade for later.\",\"4\":\"Working in batches, add the short ribs to the Instant Pot and sear for 3-4 minutes on each side, until deeply caramelized. Transfer the short ribs to a baking sheet as they finish cooking and repeat with the remaining ribs.\",\"5\":\"After the short ribs are seared, add the pear, shallot, ginger, and garlic to the Instant Pot. Season with salt and pepper, and sauté for 4-5 minutes, or until the mixture is golden brown.\",\"6\":\"Return the short ribs to the Instant Pot, then pour in the reserved marinade. Place the lid on the Instant Pot, make sure the lid is set to “Sealing,” and change the setting to high pressure cooker. Set the timer for 20 minutes.\",\"7\":\"At the end of 20 minutes, carefully release the pressure from the Instant Pot by turning the knob from “Sealing” to “Venting,” making sure your hand is not over the release switch as the hot steam will come out of the top. Wait for the pressure to release and the Instant Pot to unlock before taking off the lid.\",\"8\":\"Remove the short ribs from the pot and change the setting to high sauté. Bring the sauce to a simmer and cook for about 5 minutes, or until reduced to about 2 cups (480 ml)\",\"9\":\"Add the cornstarch to the water and mix until completely dissolved. Add the slurry to the sauce and whisk continuously for another 3 minutes, or until the sauce thickens. Remove from the heat and let cool slightly. Skim off any excess oil from the top of the sauce, if desired.\",\"10\":\"Serve the short ribs over white rice. Pour about ½ cup (120 ml) of the sauce over the ribs and serve the rest on the side. Garnish with toasted sesame seeds, cilantro, and scallions, and serve with kimchi, if desired.\",\"11\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":32,\"fat\":26,\"calories\":471,\"sugar\":20,\"carbohydrates\":26,\"fiber\":1}','\"\"','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/200632.jpg\"','1 cup soy sauce||½ cup rice vinegar||¼ cup toasted sesame oil||¼ cup gochujang, or to taste||2 tablespoons honey||2 pounds flanken beef short ribs, ½-inch thick, each rib cut in half||Kosher salt, to taste||Ground black pepper, to taste||1 tablespoon coconut oil||1 Bosc or D’Anjou pear, finely chopped (about 1 cup)||¼ cup finely chopped shallot||3 tablespoons minced fresh ginger||1 tablespoon minced garlic||2 tablespoons water||1 tablespoon cornstarch||Cooked white rice, for serving||Toasted sesame seeds, for garnish||Fresh cilantro leaves, for garnish||Thinly sliced scallions, for garnish||Kimchi, for serving||','comfort_food||korean||tongs||whisk||healthy||easy||dry_measuring_cups||weeknight||baking_pan||dinner||steam||special_occasion||measuring_spoons||pan_fry||liquid_measuring_cup||oven_mitts||pyrex||mixing_bowl||cutting_board||chefs_knife||spatula||high_protein||dairy_free'),('f8-83e71e01de3f','\"Copycat Costco Bulgogi Bake\"','{\"0\":\"Marinate the bulgogi: add the ribeye, brown sugar, sesame oil, scallions, soy sauce, garlic, onion, ginger, Asian pear, and gochujang to a large bowl and mix until well-combined and the meat is fully coated. Marinate at room temperature for 30 minutes, or cover the bowl with plastic wrap and marinate in the refrigerator overnight.\",\"1\":\"Heat the avocado oil in a medium nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add the marinated bulgogi and cook for about 4 minutes, or until browned. Flip and cook for another 1–2 minutes, or until browned on the other side. Transfer bulgogi to a plate and let cool.\",\"2\":\"Assemble the bulgogi bakes: Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\",\"3\":\"Lightly dust a clean surface with flour, then use a rolling pin to roll out one portion of dough to a roughly 7 x 10-inch rectangle. Layer ¼ cup of shredded mozzarella cheese, a quarter the bulgogi, and another ¼ cup of cheese on the center of the dough, leaving a 2-inch border all the way around the edges. Fold a long side of dough up and over the fillings to the center, then repeat with the remaining long side, then the two short sides. Pinch and press the edges of the dough together to seal. Carefully transfer the bulgogi bake to the prepared baking sheet and repeat with the remaining ingredients to make 4 total.\",\"4\":\"In a small bowl, stir together the avocado oil and garlic.\",\"5\":\"Use a pastry brush to brush garlic oil on the tops of the bulgogi bakes, then sprinkle each with ¼ cup of mozzarella cheese.\",\"6\":\"Bake for15–17 minutes, or until the cheese and dough are golden brown. Let cool for 5 minutes before serving.\",\"7\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":36,\"fat\":41,\"calories\":749,\"sugar\":6,\"carbohydrates\":57}','\"If you love Costco\\u2019s chicken bake, then you have to try Costco Korea\\u2019s food court special, a bulgogi bake made with tender marinated ribeye steak and lots of mozzarella cheese.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/398387.jpg\"','1¼ pound boneless ribeye steak, thinly sliced||1½ tablespoons brown sugar||1½ tablespoons sesame oil||2 tablespoons chopped scallions||3 tablespoons soy sauce, preferably Sempio brand||2 tablespoons finely grated garlic||¼ medium white onion, grated||1½ teaspoons finely grated fresh ginger||½ medium Asian pear, grated||1 tablespoon gochujang||2 tablespoons avocado oil||','dinner||oven||korean||under_1_h