cuisine'),('fd-6d994f5870a4','\"Blueberry Almond Instant Oatmeal\"','{\"0\":\"Add the instant oatmeal, freeze-dried blueberries, almonds, vanilla bean, chia seeds, and sugar into a mason jar.\",\"1\":\"Store in a cool, dry place for up to a month.\",\"2\":\"To prepare, pour boiling water or milk over oats. Stir to combine and let sit for 3 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Serve with slivered almonds and fresh blueberries.\",\"4\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":9,\"carbohydrates\":62,\"fiber\":11,\"protein\":12,\"fat\":11,\"calories\":398}','','1','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/09eedd8bef98484aa07149605d651eef/BFV29387_InstantOatmeal4Ways_FB.jpg\"','½ cup instant oatmeal||2 tablespoons freeze-dried blueberries||1 tablespoon slivered almonds||1 tablespoon chia seeds||⅛ teaspoon vanilla bean||2 teaspoons sugar of choice||¾ cup boiling water or milk||','american||healthy||kid_friendly||easy||breakfast||meal_prep||dry_measuring_cups||pyrex||wooden_spoon||liquid_measuring_cup||measuring_spoons||high_fiber||dairy_free||vegan||vegetarian'),('fd-cc424ac0b42f','\"Loaded Baked Potato Soup\"','{\"0\":\"Preheat your oven to 425˚F (220˚C).\",\"1\":\"On a parchment paper-lined baking sheet, rub potatoes with salt, pepper, and olive oil.\",\"2\":\"Bake in preheated oven for 40-50 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Once cooled, peel and mash potatoes, and set aside.\",\"4\":\"Heat oil in large pot over a medium-high heat.\",\"5\":\"Add onion and garlic. Cook until translucent and garlic is fragant, about 5 minutes.\",\"6\":\"Add butter and melt.\",\"7\":\"Bring in flour and stir until mixture is lightly browned.\",\"8\":\"Add in the chicken broth and cream cheese. Stir until fully incorporated\",\"9\":\"Add in the mashed potatoes and combine.\",\"10\":\"Season with salt and pepper.\",\"11\":\"Garnish bowl with shredded cheese, bacon, and chives.\",\"12\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"sugar\":7,\"carbohydrates\":73,\"fiber\":6,\"protein\":11,\"fat\":20,\"calories\":503}','','6','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/84a5b4aa71b1476481fec65141e8e687/BFV330965SoupsToWarmYourSoulFBV2.jpg\"','4-5 pounds russet potatoes, washed||1 tablespoon olive oil||1 teaspoon salt||½ teaspoon pepper||1 onion, diced||3 cloves garlic||3 tablespoons butter||¼ cup flour||2½ cups chicken broth||8 ounces cream cheese||','stove_top||peeler||big_batch||liquid_measuring_cup||dutch_oven||comfort_food||winter||dinner||lunch||american||fall||easy||date_night||wooden_spoon||weeknight||one_pot_or_pan||meal_prep||dry_measuring_cups||tasty_ewd_fall||high_fiber'),('fe-761089609fe3','\"Classic Caesar Salad\"','{\"0\":\"Make the classic caesar dressing: On a cutting board, chop the garlic and anchovies together to combine. Sprinkle with the salt. Use the side of a knife to chop and mash the mixture into a smooth, homogeneous paste. Transfer the paste to a medium bowl.\",\"1\":\"Add the egg yolks and mustard to the bowl with the garlic anchovy paste. Whisk until the egg yolks lighten in color and become airy, about 2 minutes. While whisking continuously, drizzle in the vegetable and olive oils until the dressing is thick and emulsified. Whisk in the lemon juice; the dressing should loosen a bit but will still be thick enough to liberally coat the back of a spoon and should fall in ribbons when drizzled. Stir in the Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese, black pepper, and salt to taste. The dressing will keep in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.\",\"2\":\"Make the croutons: Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\",\"3\":\"In a medium bowl, toss the torn bread with the olive oil, salt, and pepper. Scatter across a baking sheet and bake for 8–10 minutes, turning the pan halfway through, until the croutons are golden brown and crispy on the outside but still tender on the inside.\",\"4\":\"Assemble the salad: On a serving platter or in a large bowl, arrange half of the little gem leaves and season with a pinch of salt. Drizzle with ⅓ cup of the dressing and top with half of the Parmesan the croutons. Repeat with the remaining ingredients to make another layer, adding more dressing to taste. Season with pepper. If desired, top with the protein of your choice, such as chicken, salmon, or shrimp. Serve immediately.\",\"5\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"carbohydrates\":27,\"fiber\":3,\"protein\":62,\"fat\":54,\"calories\":843,\"sugar\":3}','\"Caesar salad is a classic, and we think our recipe embodies everything you love about the dish\\u2013it\\u2019s tangy, creamy, crunchy, and garlicky. Drizzle little gem lettuce with homemade and hand-whisked Caesar dressing and top with torn-bread croutons and shaved Parmesan cheese. Serve with your choice of protein, if desired, but we think it\\u2019s pretty perfect as is.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/c65ee763a76545929a514d08507d49a3/BFV76633_ClassicvsVeganCaesarSalad_SO_032221_V8_1x1_OO_V2.jpg\"','2 garlic cloves, crushed and roughly chopped||6 oil-packed anchovy fillets, drained and roughly chopped||¼ teaspoon kosher salt, plus more to taste||2 large pastured egg yolks||2 teaspoons Dijon mustard||6 tablespoons vegetable oil||¼ cup extra-virgin olive oil||2 tablespoons lemon juice||¼ cup freshly grated Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese||¼–½ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper||','oven||american||baking_pan||dry_measuring_cups||liquid_measuring_cup||mixing_bowl||whisk||measuring_spoons||dinner||lunch||weeknight||high_protein||low_sugar||under_45_minutes||under_1_hour'),('fe-a6f23e728633','\"Citrus Peel Tofu\"','{\"0\":\"Add 1½ ounces (½ cup) of the orange peels to a small saucepan and cover with the water. Bring to a simmer over medium heat and cook for 5–8 minutes, or until the peels have softened and are fragrant. Drain to remove the orange peels and reserve 1 cup of steeping liquid.\",\"1\":\"Very thinly slice the remaining 1½ ounces (½ cup) of orange peels. Add to a medium bowl with the brown and granulated sugars and toss to coat. Let sit for 5–10 minutes to infuse the sugar with the orange flavor.\",\"2\":\"Pour the reserved warm orange-infused water over the sugared peels and stir until the sugar is mostly dissolved. Add the rice vinegar, soy sauce, ginger, chile garlic paste, and sesame oil and stir to incorporate. Add the tofu and gently toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 20–30 minutes.\",\"3\":\"Remove the tofu from the marinade (it’s okay if some of the orange peels stick to the tofu). Transfer to a large bowl and gently toss with 2 tablespoons of cornstarch until lightly coated. Reserve the marinade.\",\"4\":\"Heat 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium heat until shimmering. Working in batches, fry the tofu on all sides until golden brown and puffed, 5–7 minutes. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate and repeat with the remaining tofu.\",\"5\":\"In a small bowl, whisk together 2 tablespoons of the marinade with the remaining tablespoon of cornstarch until smooth.\",\"6\":\"Pour the remaining marinade into the pan and bring to a simmer over medium-low heat. Once simmering, whisk in the cornstarch slurry and return the tofu to the pan. Cook, stirring often to prevent burning, until the sauce is thickened and the tofu is well-coated, 3–4 minutes.\",\"7\":\"Serve the tofu over rice and garnish with scallions and toasted sesame seeds.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"fiber\":2,\"protein\":11,\"fat\":16,\"calories\":325,\"sugar\":28,\"carbohydrates\":37}','\"A saucy tofu dish with citrus peels.\"','4','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/f97c830f1f4741128e621a3e36254010.png\"','3 ounces (1 cup) orange peels (from about 4 oranges), pith removed, divided||1¼ cups water||⅓ cup brown sugar||2 tablespoons granulated sugar||⅓ cup rice vinegar||¼ cup soy sauce||1 teaspoon minced fresh ginger||1 tablespoon chile garlic paste||1 tablespoon toasted sesame oil||1 14-ounce block of extra-firm tofu, pressed and cut into ½-inch cubes||3 tablespoons cornstarch, divided||2–4 tablespoons vegetable oil||Cooked long-grain white rice||Thinly sliced scallions||Toasted sesame seeds||','dinner||date_night||vegetarian||stove_top||measuring_spoons||sauce_pan||under_1_hour||dairy_free||vegan'),('ff-8239b964b706','\"Penne Alla Vodka\"','{\"0\":\"Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large skillet.\",\"1\":\"Add onion and 1 clove of garlic, and cook until onions are translucent.\",\"2\":\"Add tomato sauce and mix to combine with onion and garlic.\",\"3\":\"Add vodka, dried basil, red pepper flakes, and salt. Let this to simmer for 2 minutes to allow most of the alcohol to burn off.\",\"4\":\"Add heavy cream and stir until fully combined. The sauce will turn into a beautiful light orange creamy mixture.\",\"5\":\"Add cooked pasta to vodka sauce and mix until noodles are fully coated in sauce.\",\"6\":\"Cover with a lid and let simmer for 5 minutes or until the sauce has reduced by half.\",\"7\":\"Garnish with basil.\",\"8\":\"Enjoy!\"}','{\"protein\":9,\"fat\":33,\"calories\":583,\"sugar\":6,\"carbohydrates\":42,\"fiber\":1}','','2','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/32abf05cc75341e8a460d00c2ad13f5f/BFV16692_3-Course_Italian_Dinner_FB.jpg\"','8 ounces cooked penne pasta||1 tablespoon olive oil||½ white onion, diced||1 garlic clove, minced||½ teaspoon red pepper flakes||1 teaspoon dried basil||1 teaspoon salt||½ cup vodka||1½ cup tomato sauce||½ cup heavy cream||','stove_top||italian||easy||dinner||weeknight||date_night||comfort_food||saute_pan||measuring_spoons||chefs_knife||cutting_board||spatula||liquid_measuring_cup||strainer||pyrex||sauce_pan||contains_alcohol||high_fiber||vegetarian'),('ff-bcbd282dc054','\"Garlic \\u0026 Honey Glazed Sesame Chicken\"','{\"0\":\"Cut chicken breasts into bite-sized pieces. Put chicken, coconut aminos, rice vinegar, sesame oil and Stevia in a plastic bag and marinate in the fridge for 1 to 2 hours; drain.\",\"1\":\"Add vegetables to a shallow pan or skillet over medium heat.\",\"2\":\"Mix cornstarch, flour, salt and pepper in a large, sealed plastic bag.\",\"3\":\"In small batches, add chicken to flour mixture, shake gently to coat and toss into pan until golden brown. Drain on a paper towel.\",\"4\":\"Mix honey, hoisin sauce, chili sauce, ketchup, coconut aminos and water. Add to pan and bring to a boil then simmer until sauce begins to thicken.\",\"5\":\"Mix sauce and chicken together. Sprinkle it with sesame seeds and green onion and serve.\"}','{\"protein\":25,\"fat\":14,\"calories\":298,\"sugar\":10,\"carbohydrates\":15,\"fiber\":1}','\"\"','8','\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/tasty-app-user-assets-prod-us-east-1/recipes/2d1ec70454e14256a610bbb5559c6920.png\"','4 chicken breasts, cubed||n/a||2 tbsp rice vinegar||1 tbsp sesame seed oil||2 tsp Sweetleaf Stevia||3 tbsp cornstarch||6 tbsp almond flour||1 teaspoon salt||½ teaspoon ground black pepper||Vegetable oil for cooking||','stove_top||comfort_food||dinner||weeknight||low_carb||high_protein||dairy_free');
